INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Powerhouse Gym & Ideometry: Weekly Sync',
  '## **Marketing Campaign Transition and Management**

The marketing ads team has been let go, and **Nina Belina''s team will take over all marketing ads, including meta ads and SMS campaigns** starting immediately (05:33).

- **The SMS campaign is currently in approval with HubSpot, expected to complete in 5 to 8 business days** (05:51)  
    - The developer will finalize the trial campaign today, including non-indexed pages for meta ads forms.  
    - Milan Wagner emphasized the need to track SMS automation approval closely since it impacts campaign launch timing.  
    - Nina confirmed the developer has access to all required systems, ensuring no blockers remain.  
    - The handover marks a shift from the previous ads team, requiring close coordination for a smooth transition.

- **Trial campaign must launch as soon as possible and run continuously without offers, focusing on driving trial club visits** (13:24)  
    - Milan specified the campaign will not include promotions but will target general trial awareness.  
    - Separate campaigns with different offers, including group fitness content, will follow this baseline trial campaign.  
    - Nina''s team will review and improve existing video and photo assets from prior marketing efforts to optimize ad performance.  
    - Milan will provide all existing campaign materials and Dropbox access to support asset availability.

- **On January 19th, the current zero enrollment promo campaign will be paused and replaced with a “dollar down + two weeks free” offer campaign focused on lead generation** (11:54)  
    - Milan will send detailed promo information and campaign recommendations to Nina’s team.  
    - Nina will consult with their paid media expert to decide whether to pause or update visuals for the transition.  
    - The new campaign aims to maximize online leads for sales representatives to close.  
    - This date allows a weekend buffer for preparation and ensures seamless promotion switching.

## **Audience Targeting Strategy for Meta Ads**

The team agreed to delegate audience targeting decisions to Nina’s marketing team with only high-level guidance from Milan (07:01).

- **Milan outlined basic location and age targeting: exclude under 18, target 18-50 tightly in Miami with a 2-3 mile radius, and extend up to age 65 with a 4-mile radius in Fort Lauderdale** (07:22)  
    - This refined geographic approach aims to improve ad relevance and cost efficiency.  
    - Milan deferred to the marketing team for selecting interests and detailed segments, emphasizing their expertise over his sales background.  
    - Nina suggested conducting a short market research to identify optimal audience segments before locking targeting parameters.  
    - Milan agreed with the approach to keep campaigns stable after launch to allow algorithms to optimize.

- **Interest targeting will focus on gym, health, and fitness-related themes, but final criteria will be decided by Nina’s team with iterative optimization** (09:10)  
    - Past campaigns by Ideometry provide a benchmark for targeting and creative strategy.  
    - Milan requested regular updates on any targeting changes to monitor performance.  
    - This flexible approach balances initial strategy with ongoing data-driven adjustments.

## **System Integrations and Data Tracking**

HubSpot and Meta integration is confirmed active, enabling accurate lead tracking, which is critical for measuring campaign ROI (08:26).

- **HubSpot now communicates directly with Meta, allowing lead conversion tracking without additional connection setup** (08:44)  
    - Milan wants a walkthrough of how data flows between platforms to monitor cost per lead and conversion rates.  
    - Nina will request technical details from their developer to clarify the integration’s capabilities.  
    - This integration reduces manual tracking work and improves attribution accuracy.  
    - The ability to see which Meta leads close in HubSpot supports data-driven marketing decisions.

- **The SMS automation remains in approval, causing slight delays, but should be resolved within the next week** (05:51)  
    - Milan emphasized the importance of completing this to enable automated outreach for campaigns.  
    - Nina confirmed the developer is ready to implement as soon as approval arrives.  
    - Timely completion of the SMS setup directly impacts campaign effectiveness.

## **Content and Asset Management**

Access and quality of marketing content are key for campaign success, with a focus on improving previous materials (14:02).

- **Milan will provide Nina’s team with Dropbox access containing old and new photos and videos to maximize creative options** (15:20)  
    - The previous marketing team’s videos and ad sets did not perform well, so Nina’s team will review and optimize them.  
    - Nina’s team can make changes and will share updates with Milan for approval to ensure quality and alignment.  
    - This content refresh aims to increase ad engagement and conversion rates.  
    - Having a broad content library enables faster iteration and testing of different creative approaches.

- **Nina’s developers will handle invisible pages setup for trial campaign forms on the website using existing Squarespace access** (17:47)  
    - No additional support from Milan’s side is needed for website changes.  
    - This setup ensures the forms remain unindexed to avoid SEO penalties while supporting ad tracking.  
    - Efficient handling of form pages avoids delays in campaign launches.

## **Campaign Workflow and Communication**

Clear processes and communication channels will support the transition and ongoing campaign management (16:44).

- **Nina will coordinate with her paid media expert on campaign transitions and share recommendations on pausing or updating ads** (12:59)  
    - Milan expects to receive all promo details and campaign materials promptly to meet the January 19th launch.  
    - Nina will ask questions and provide updates via chat to maintain smooth communication.  
    - This workflow supports quick decision-making and reduces turnaround time.  
    - Milan remains available to provide clarifications or additional content as needed.

- **The focus is on running only two active campaigns initially: the trial campaign and the new dollar down offer campaign** (18:23)  
    - The older zero enrollment campaign will be paused without further review to streamline efforts.  
    - This focus allows the team to allocate resources efficiently and measure campaign impact clearly.  
    - Milan emphasized the importance of a “win” to build momentum.  
    - Clear priorities improve team alignment and execution speed.',
  '2026-01-14 16:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Send all trial campaign and dollar down offer videos and photos to Marketing team for review and optimization (14:02)","completed":false},{"text":"Provide Dropbox access with old and new content to Marketing team (15:16)","completed":false},{"text":"Share detailed promo information and campaign launch instructions for January 19th new offer (12:36)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm with paid media expert about campaign switch strategy (pause/re-upload) and relay info to Marketing (12:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor SMS campaign approval status on HubSpot and report updates (05:43)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with developer to complete trial campaign setup and website form configurations (06:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Conduct market research and propose initial targeting criteria for Meta ads; run campaigns with iterative testing and adjustments (09:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Request detailed info from developer about HubSpot-Meta integration and how lead data is tracked/reviewed (08:26)","completed":false},{"text":"Consult paid media person regarding best practices for pausing or updating running campaigns, then communicate guidance (12:59)","completed":false},{"text":"Manage launching the trial campaign immediately and prepare the new campaign for January 19 launch (13:24)","completed":false},{"text":"Ensure developer handles invisible pages/forms for trial campaign on the website (17:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Take responsibility for running and managing the two approved active campaigns; no need to review the campaign being shut down (18:05)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
