    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85224401147?pwd=QUXrZwP0exehyaIxA52wYI5PNynjNm.1',
    '{"id":"01KEVVT7APBJRPKJQT7F0EB8HJ","title":"New North <> ThreatMark: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Budget Allocation**\n\nThe team refined budget splits and targeted new audiences to boost lead generation efficiency.\n\n- **Kate ThreatMark approved allocating around $500 per month** for LinkedIn campaigns targeting a new Central European audience, split from the existing **$1,500 monthly UK EMEA budget** to improve top-of-funnel lead gen (09:32)  \n    - The new audience showed a **90% match rate**, indicating high data quality and potential for strong engagement  \n    - Kate emphasized reusing existing creative assets to streamline setup and maintain consistency across UK, Nordics, and CE campaigns  \n    - This budget adjustment aims to diversify reach while keeping overall costs controlled and leveraging proven content  \n    - The move supports broader regional segmentation for more precise targeting and improved ROI  \n\n- **Nina Belina reported LinkedIn spend at $704 generated 8 leads** with a focus on high-value C-suite targets, including CEOs and CFOs, mainly from the US/Canada (5 leads) and EMEA (3 leads) regions (11:09)  \n    - Despite a higher cost per lead in Europe, the emphasis on senior roles justifies the expense by improving lead quality  \n    - Top-performing creative was the \"AI versus fraud\" ad, aligning content with audience interests to boost engagement  \n    - The Q2 mobile white paper ad had zero leads last week, suggesting a need to rethink targeting or creative for fraud specialists and cybersecurity VPs  \n    - Google Ads spend and performance declined due to budget pacing changes, with expectations for stabilization as allocation settles  \n\n- **Kate highlighted the importance of switching Google Ads and LinkedIn accounts to USD** to simplify billing and campaign management, with Colin tasked to update Google Ads currency soon (13:56)  \n    - LinkedIn business manager account setup requires review to enable currency change and smooth campaign transfers  \n    - This currency change is a medium-term priority to reduce complexity and improve financial tracking  \n\n## **Targeting and Geolocation Strategy**\n\nNew geographic and contact data requirements surfaced to support expanded campaign targeting.\n\n- **Nina clarified that adding the Bank Verlag in Germany to targeting requires contact emails linked to zip codes** to enable accurate geolocation-based campaigns (06:02)  \n    - Current US campaigns rely on zip codes connected to headquarters, but the bank''s Europe-based zip codes need verified contact data for effective targeting  \n    - The paid media specialist is investigating which specific contact info is necessary to support this new geofence targeting  \n    - This detail is critical to avoid wasted spend and ensure ads reach the intended financial decision-makers  \n    - Kate confirmed the bank is located in Germany and agreed that supplementary contact data is essential to extend targeting beyond US zip codes (07:37)  \n\n- **The team is monitoring competitor activity bidding on brand terms**, but Nina noted competitors’ budgets are too low to pose current risk, keeping brand visibility intact (11:09)  \n    - Campaign ad strength is average, but adding more site links and visual assets like logos is planned to improve quality scores and CTR  \n    - These optimizations are expected to maintain brand presence and fend off low-level competitor bids  \n\n## **Content Production and Asset Preparation**\n\nFinalizing creative assets and translations supports upcoming campaign launches and regulatory content releases.\n\n- **Nicola Harding podcast episode was finalized and pending Kate’s approval by end of day** for publication, ensuring timely content delivery (05:23)  \n    - Analytics team is working to enhance podcast insights, including time frames and episode data, to better understand audience engagement (08:44)  \n    - This data will help refine future podcast topics and distribution strategies for higher impact  \n\n- **The FDA white paper received approval and was sent to the PR agency for release under embargo**, with creative and web assets being prepared in HubSpot to support the launch (09:58)  \n    - Kate requested tidy-up of journey pages and website setups, aiming for smooth rollout once embargo lifts  \n    - This coordination ensures marketing channels are aligned for a cohesive campaign launch  \n\n- **For the German Bank Verlag campaign, translation of a regulatory PDF into German is underway**, but both Kate and Nina lack internal German language resources (15:07)  \n    - They plan to rely on ChatGPT for bulk translation with a freelancer or Fiverr proofreader to handle regional nuances and accuracy (16:21)  \n    - This approach balances cost and quality for timely content delivery in the German market  \n\n## **Website Migration and Technical Updates**\n\nProgress continues on site migrations and ongoing fixes to improve user experience and campaign readiness.\n\n- **The Bank Fraud Summit website migration is in progress with tickets submitted to IT and developers provided additional assets** to complete the transition (07:52)  \n    - Nina is testing minor website fixes and newsletter components aligned with recent creative briefs to enhance user engagement  \n    - These updates are critical to support upcoming campaigns and maintain seamless visitor experience during the migration  \n    - Kate will communicate any changes or delays from IT to keep the team aligned (16:57)  \n\n- **Mobile banner optimization for the homepage slider has been implemented**, resolving prior UX issues highlighted by Kate (05:28)  \n    - This improves mobile visitor engagement and supports campaign visibility for key promotions  \n    - The optimization reflects a focus on mobile-first experiences given rising mobile traffic  \n\n## **Process and Operational Improvements**\n\nOngoing adjustments to campaign tracking, reporting, and team coordination aim to increase efficiency and clarity.\n\n- **Nina''s team updated HubSpot lead source fields to better align with ABM campaigns**, enabling more accurate tracking and data-driven decision-making (05:28)  \n    - This change ensures all relevant lead information feeds into campaign performance analysis without gaps  \n    - It supports more granular attribution and optimization efforts across channels  \n\n- **Nina will coordinate with paid media specialists to identify exact data needs and campaign setup requirements for the new Bank Verlag ads**, ensuring readiness before launch (16:39)  \n    - This proactive communication reduces risks of delays or misalignment on targeting and creative  \n    - It also clarifies ownership and timelines for campaign activation  \n\n- **Kate suggested a potential ad opportunity in Germany linked to a regulatory PDF translation**, indicating exploration of localized content marketing to support lead generation in a new market (15:03)  \n    - Nina will investigate translation resource availability and cost-effective proofing options to expedite this initiative  \n    - This shows strategic intent to expand regional market penetration through tailored content  \n\n- **The team plans to keep the optional Friday catch-up meeting open**, allowing flexibility to address any last-minute issues before the weekend (17:07)  \n    - This approach balances efficient use of time with readiness for urgent needs, reflecting adaptive workflow management","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast","HubSpot","LinkedIn Campaign","Bank Verlag","Google Ads","Website Migration"],"overview":"- **Budget Adjustment:** $500 allocated for LinkedIn campaigns targeting Central Europe, enhancing top-of-funnel lead generation.  \n- **Lead Generation Results:** $704 spent on LinkedIn yielded 8 leads from C-suite targets, improving lead quality despite higher costs in Europe.  \n- **Campaign Targeting Needs:** Bank Verlag''s targeting requires zip code-linked contact emails for effective geolocation-based campaigns in Germany.  \n- **Content Production Updates:** Podcast episode finalized for release; FDA white paper sent for embargoed PR launch with aligned assets.  \n- **Website Migration Status:** Bank Fraud Summit website migration is ongoing, with minor fixes being tested to enhance user experience.  \n- **Operational Improvements:** HubSpot updates enhance ABM campaign tracking; coordination ensures readiness for upcoming Bank Verlag ad launch.","action_items":"\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nReview and provide feedback on “Behind Enemies Lines” podcast episode with Nicola Harding by end of day (05:23)\nProvide feedback on Central European LinkedIn account list and assist with running lead gen campaigns with £500 separate budget allocation (09:05)\nPrepare and tidy up FDA white paper creative assets, HubSpot journeys, and web pages for embargoed release (10:23)\nInform Nina of any changes regarding Bank Fraud Summit website migration; track support ticket progress (16:57)\nCoordinate with Colin on switching Google Ads account currency from pounds to dollars and LinkedIn Business Manager currency setup (14:04)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nConfirm and ensure podcast episode review and publication readiness (05:23)\nContinue optimizing HubSpot lead sources and mobile homepage banner (05:28)\nClarify geolocation targeting requirements including postal codes and contact data for Bank Verlag German campaign (06:40)\nFollow up with paid media specialists on needed info to start the Central Europe LinkedIn lead gen campaign (16:39)\nCheck availability of internal German translation/proofing resource or arrange external proofreader to support Bank Verlag campaign materials (15:51)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nContinue work on migrating Google Ads account currency from pounds to dollars; provide status update (14:23)\nSupport inquiries regarding LinkedIn campaign manager and currency setup (14:30)\n"},"duration":17.649999618530273,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"id":1,"name":"Nina Belina"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Sa.","index":0,"end_time":128.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":127.89,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Sat sam.","index":1,"end_time":229.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.95,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hello.","index":2,"end_time":246.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":245.93,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hi, Kate.","index":3,"end_time":247.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Oh, I''m sorry, this one.","index":4,"end_time":249.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.01,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Hi, Nina, how are you?","index":5,"end_time":252.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.29,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m good, how are you?","index":6,"end_time":254.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":252.97,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, not bad, thank you.","index":7,"end_time":255.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.49,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Not bad.","index":8,"end_time":256.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":255.73,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Good start of the week.","index":9,"end_time":258.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":257.28,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''ve got our SKO this week so we''re all kind of like pretending to do stuff.","index":10,"end_time":266.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.52,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That''s nice.","index":11,"end_time":269.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":12,"end_time":270.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.92,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":270.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.32,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Colin is not going to be able to join us because he has an off day and he.","index":14,"end_time":275.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":271.04,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"He didn''t even realize it until his wife mentioned it last week.","index":15,"end_time":279.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So yeah, it was a little bit of like last minute, but we''ll manage.","index":16,"end_time":284.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.68,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll manage.","index":17,"end_time":285.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.94,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And I did put in a call for later in the week, but I thought it''d be good for us to catch up on just a few things.","index":18,"end_time":292.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":285.78,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So it''ll just be me from our side today as well.","index":19,"end_time":295.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":292.9,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":20,"end_time":295.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.18,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":21,"end_time":296.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.66,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Second, So for the weekly meeting, the three things that we have finished is the Behind Enemies Lines podcast episode with Nicola, which I don''t know if you had time to review.","index":22,"end_time":316.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.26,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We can publish it, but I just wanted to be sure that everything is okay from your side.","index":23,"end_time":322.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317.71,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I still need to go through it, but I''m planning to do that by the end of the day.","index":24,"end_time":326.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.39,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So I will get you any feedback by then.","index":25,"end_time":328.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.59,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":26,"end_time":329.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":328.51,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And for HubSpot, we managed to update the lead sources and the lead source specific.","index":27,"end_time":337.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.47,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So now they''re, now they''re optimized for all information that are relevant for the ABM campaigns so they can follow through data for each of the properties and that should be.","index":28,"end_time":351.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":337.31,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Oh well from now on when it comes to the campaigns.","index":29,"end_time":354.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.17,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For the user experience, we optimized the mobile banner for the homepage slider, the one that you mentioned on the week previous.","index":30,"end_time":363.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And for the items we are working on, one of the questions that I had about the bank Verloc, I don''t know how you pronounce it, but the bank that you mentioned, that needs to be added to the targeting.","index":31,"end_time":377.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":364.09,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We don''t mind.","index":32,"end_time":378.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":377.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We don''t have an issue with adding it as a geographical point because usually we have zip codes that are then connected to headquarters, but since it''s connecting to finance banking emails, we do need contact data or an email to support the geolocation targeting.","index":33,"end_time":398.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":378.66,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":34,"end_time":401.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":400.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So just some additional information.","index":35,"end_time":407.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.44,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So that bank is in Germany.","index":36,"end_time":415.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":412.96,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''m actually sorry, I didn''t realize.","index":37,"end_time":417.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":416.24,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Is that confirmed?","index":38,"end_time":418.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.56,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Right, because I think this says targets us zip codes.","index":39,"end_time":421.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":418.76,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, these are, these are the ones that I asked our paid media specialist to check.","index":40,"end_time":426.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But I can also check, I mean for the eu we have other headquarters, but these are just Some of the few zip codes that we have.","index":41,"end_time":435.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.36,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So just for to have like an, an idea of what we need for the geofencing to work.","index":42,"end_time":441.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for usually we have a zip code and then we work with the contact data or email to connect it.","index":43,"end_time":447.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.9,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So the targeting notes that we are targeting users within within those headquarters.","index":44,"end_time":456.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.14,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So the list here is the ones that we are currently targeting with the US campaign for this additional bank.","index":45,"end_time":465.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":457.43,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We need some extra info for the contact data to support it.","index":46,"end_time":470.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":466.15,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":47,"end_time":471.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.51,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And for the website migration we are migrating the Bank Fraud Summit site and I think I already sent you the additional assets that the developers need for this.","index":48,"end_time":485.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.79,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And I also started working on tests for the small website fixes and for the newsletter that you sent a creative brief for.","index":49,"end_time":494.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":486.23,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For the podcast Analytics Calling is also working on checking if we can get more information when it comes to analytics.","index":50,"end_time":502.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":495.49,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So time frames, episode data, anything that could give us a little bit more of an insight of what works best when it comes to the podcasts.","index":51,"end_time":512.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":502.69,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And also to see how the Apple and Spotify accounts were set up and to see what''s the what which was the main point of contact there from the beginning for the items.","index":52,"end_time":528.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":513.09,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So only the feedback for the Nicola Harding episode, the sync on the Central European account list and I also wanted to ask if you have any additional feedback for the FDA white paper.","index":53,"end_time":543.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.38,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So yeah, I just said about the Nick episode.","index":54,"end_time":548.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.36,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''ll give you the feedback today on the Central European account list.","index":55,"end_time":552.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":548.64,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"This was actually uploaded to LinkedIn over the weekend.","index":56,"end_time":556,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.16,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We would like to run our kind of top of funnel lead gen. LinkedIn campaigns to this new audience.","index":57,"end_time":568.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":557.44,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Please if we could get your help with that in terms of our budget step.","index":58,"end_time":572.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.4,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think at the moment for our top of Funnel for the UK EMEA campaign it''s roughly like 1500amonth.","index":59,"end_time":583.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.12,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"If we could dedicate around 500 to this new audience as a separate campaign in LinkedIn that would be great.","index":60,"end_time":593.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.24,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Please.","index":61,"end_time":594.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.96,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"So basically a three way split between the UKI Nordics and then this new audience CE I think just reusing the existing creative that we really have just duplicating setup.","index":62,"end_time":612.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.72,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think our match rate was really high of 90% so hopefully this would be a pretty good audience for us.","index":63,"end_time":620.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.48,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay.","index":64,"end_time":622.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":621.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"On the FCE white paper, no more feedback or approved.","index":65,"end_time":627,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"It''s going to the PR agency today.","index":66,"end_time":629.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":628.06,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think they''re, they''re on, on leave today as well for the U.S. but we''re going to go ahead and get that released under embargo.","index":67,"end_time":638.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.9,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I don''t know what date.","index":68,"end_time":639.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.58,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think I said this in the message as well.","index":69,"end_time":641.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":639.94,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But I don''t know what date we''re targeting yet.","index":70,"end_time":642.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.26,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But if we could get like the creative assets of pages in HubSpot, you know, sorry, the journeys in HubSpot, the pages on the website set up, that''d be good.","index":71,"end_time":653.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.02,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''ve done some of them already, but just tidying up and getting that ready to publish would be great.","index":72,"end_time":659.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":653.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":73,"end_time":667.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.76,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And for the data analytics, our spend did go a little bit lower than last week, which is also together with the clicks and the impressions, which is kind of expected because we''ve been pacing the budget.","index":74,"end_time":682.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":669.32,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So we just because it''s allocated in a new way, we''re always going to see changes.","index":75,"end_time":688.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.68,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But what''s interesting that we see some additional competitors bidding for the brand name.","index":76,"end_time":694.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":689.34,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So which means that, you know, it''s.","index":77,"end_time":696.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":694.7,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The brand name is interesting but they''re also not causing any kind of damage with the bidding because it''s not that relevant.","index":78,"end_time":704.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":696.54,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"When it comes to the budgets that they are using.","index":79,"end_time":708.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":705.02,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For the ad strength, it''s still average.","index":80,"end_time":711.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":709.18,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We are adding four new site links.","index":81,"end_time":714.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.82,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But what would also be good is to add like additional, maybe logo images or things like that, which is something that I can talk with our paid media specialists and see like what else could be added to the campaign to increase the strength.","index":82,"end_time":729.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":714.62,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For LinkedIn, the spend is $704 and we had eight leads when it comes to the regional breakdown, five leads were from US and Canada and three were from the EMEA from the European and Middle Eastern region.","index":83,"end_time":748.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For one of the good sides of the a little bit higher cost per lead for especially for Europe is that we are showing interest towards like CEOs, Chief Finance, Financial officers, people are in the C suite.","index":84,"end_time":770.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.83,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So it means that even though the cost per lease is higher, we''re targeting people who are our target audience.","index":85,"end_time":776.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":770.11,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So people who are a little bit more higher up in the seniority chain.","index":86,"end_time":782.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.45,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And our top creative was AI versus fraud.","index":87,"end_time":786.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":782.97,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The mobile white paper ad, the Q2 campaign had zero leads this week and we are targeting mostly fraud specialists and VPs that handle any kind of cybersecurity topic.","index":88,"end_time":801.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":786.73,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"For the ad roll we had, we.","index":89,"end_time":804.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.83,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"We have the same campaign as usual, so maintaining brand visibility to with three creative variants and we had five clicks in the last week.","index":90,"end_time":817.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.43,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So and all the also on data box you can see the information for the last 30 days or you know, any range that you want to see when it comes to the beginning of the year, um, the campaigns are working well.","index":91,"end_time":831.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":818.15,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"The only thing that was changed was with the Google Ads that we''ve allocated the budget to pacing.","index":92,"end_time":838.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.93,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So now it''s looking a little bit different.","index":93,"end_time":840.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.85,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I''m not against doing anything different in Google Ads, but I do think we should move that over to, to a dollar''s account rather than pounds at some point.","index":94,"end_time":857.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":844.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We think we spoke a few weeks ago, but we should probably do that sooner rather than later.","index":95,"end_time":862.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.59,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, I will ask Colin because he did say that he was working on it, but I don''t know where he''s at.","index":96,"end_time":868.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":863.35,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, and the same with, with LinkedIn as well.","index":97,"end_time":872.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.55,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I think we, we''ve set up a business manager account ourselves so just need to look at how we get that transferred across and what that means with LinkedIn.","index":98,"end_time":884.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.75,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I know that you usually need to set up a new campaign manager for a different currency, but I''ll ask calling like what''s the process with Google Ads?","index":99,"end_time":895.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.32,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, but we can come back to that one.","index":100,"end_time":900.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.4,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"That''s not super urgent.","index":101,"end_time":901.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.12,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And that''s all for this week.","index":102,"end_time":905.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":903.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Just see another adroll point.","index":103,"end_time":911.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.61,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Actually we and potentially LinkedIn we have an opportunity in Germany that''s we''re looking to.","index":104,"end_time":919.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.17,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"No, that''s the, that''s the AD R1 that I''ve already mentioned.","index":105,"end_time":924.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.45,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The Bank Verlag.","index":106,"end_time":925.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.77,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"To support that German one.","index":107,"end_time":932.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":929.69,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We had a regulation PDF coming out that we''re going to get translated into German.","index":108,"end_time":938.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.09,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We can probably add to that campaign.","index":109,"end_time":941.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.54,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"The question was around like translation services.","index":110,"end_time":944.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":942.18,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I don''t suppose you have any translation people on hand, do you?","index":111,"end_time":950.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.42,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I would have to ask because I''ve never had to translate anything but I can ask if we have somebody on hand who can translate to German because I know that somebody asked me from my colleagues, colleagues if I can translate to German.","index":112,"end_time":967.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":951.22,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I was like no, no, no, we.","index":113,"end_time":969.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":967.35,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Haven''T got anyone here either that can, that can speak German I think.","index":114,"end_time":972.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":969.83,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I mean ChatGPT does like the bulk of the actual translation work.","index":115,"end_time":977.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":972.91,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"We just need proofing.","index":116,"end_time":978.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.15,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":117,"end_time":980.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":978.79,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"And it''s also German is very specific.","index":118,"end_time":983.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.35,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean like it can also be like regional differences but yeah, it''s good to find somebody to check it.","index":119,"end_time":990.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.47,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, otherwise I''ll just use like a Fiverr person.","index":120,"end_time":994.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":991.08,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"But yeah, that was all for me as well actually.","index":121,"end_time":997.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":995.88,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Nothing else.","index":122,"end_time":998.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":997.68,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I will ask additional information for the, the bank for the, the new set of ads for 500amonth and also I''ll ask the paid media specialists like what exact information does she need from.","index":123,"end_time":1015.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":999.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"To start the campaign?","index":124,"end_time":1016.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1015.16,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, sounds good.","index":125,"end_time":1018.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1017.57,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''ll let you know if there''s any changes with the Banking Fraud Summit website.","index":126,"end_time":1023.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.05,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I''ve got the ticket submitted so just waiting to hear from it.","index":127,"end_time":1026.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1023.29,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Okay, thank you.","index":128,"end_time":1028.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1027.65,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Cool.","index":129,"end_time":1029.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1029.33,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"All right.","index":130,"end_time":1030.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.29,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"I don''t know if we''ll need the catch up on Friday or just play it by ear, but it''s in there if we need it, okay?","index":131,"end_time":1038.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1032.69,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"If not, I''ll see you on Friday or on Monday.","index":132,"end_time":1041.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1038.45,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":133,"end_time":1042.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.05,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":134,"end_time":1043.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1042.77,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"text":"Bye.","index":135,"end_time":1044.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1043.89,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bye.","index":136,"end_time":1045.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.61,"speaker_name":"Kate ThreatMark"}],"dateString":"2026-01-19T15:00:00.000Z","host_email":"nina.belina@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85224401147?pwd=QUXrZwP0exehyaIxA52wYI5PNynjNm.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,kate.burwood@threatmark.com,gregory.smith@threatmark.com,nina.belina@marketersindemand.com,iulia.lungu@threatmark.com","colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","kate.burwood@threatmark.com","gregory.smith@threatmark.com","iulia.lungu@threatmark.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEVVT7APBJRPKJQT7F0EB8HJ","organizer_email":"nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Confirmed FDA white paper is approved and being released to PR agency under embargo.","Allocated $500 to new CE audience as separate LinkedIn campaign using existing creative.","Flagged need for additional contact data to enable geotargeting for German bank campaign.","Migrating Bank Fraud Summit website and preparing creative assets and HubSpot journeys.","Detected competitor bidding on brand name; ad strength remains average, more assets planned."],"highlights":[{"quote":"The list here is the ones that we are currently targeting with the US campaign.","speaker":"Kate ThreatMark"},{"quote":"We are showing interest towards like CEOs, Chief Finance, Financial officers.","speaker":"Nina Belina"},{"quote":"The FCE white paper, no more feedback or approved. It''s going to the PR agency today.","speaker":"Kate ThreatMark"}],"topics":["campaign","targeting","analytics","content","localization"],"model":"openai/gpt-4","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-21T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Campaign Performance and Budget Allocation**\n\nThe team refined budget splits and targeted new audiences to boost lead generation efficiency.\n\n- **Kate ThreatMark approved allocating around $500 per month** for LinkedIn campaigns targeting a new Central European audience, split from the existing **$1,500 monthly UK EMEA budget** to improve top-of-funnel lead gen (09:32)  \n    - The new audience showed a **90% match rate**, indicating high data quality and potential for strong engagement  \n    - Kate emphasized reusing existing creative assets to streamline setup and maintain consistency across UK, Nordics, and CE campaigns  \n    - This budget adjustment aims to diversify reach while keeping overall costs controlled and leveraging proven content  \n    - The move supports broader regional segmentation for more precise targeting and improved ROI  \n\n- **Nina Belina reported LinkedIn spend at $704 generated 8 leads** with a focus on high-value C-suite targets, including CEOs and CFOs, mainly from the US/Canada (5 leads) and EMEA (3 leads) regions (11:09)  \n    - Despite a higher cost per lead in Europe, the emphasis on senior roles justifies the expense by improving lead quality  \n    - Top-performing creative was the \"AI versus fraud\" ad, aligning content with audience interests to boost engagement  \n    - The Q2 mobile white paper ad had zero leads last week, suggesting a need to rethink targeting or creative for fraud specialists and cybersecurity VPs  \n    - Google Ads spend and performance declined due to budget pacing changes, with expectations for stabilization as allocation settles  \n\n- **Kate highlighted the importance of switching Google Ads and LinkedIn accounts to USD** to simplify billing and campaign management, with Colin tasked to update Google Ads currency soon (13:56)  \n    - LinkedIn business manager account setup requires review to enable currency change and smooth campaign transfers  \n    - This currency change is a medium-term priority to reduce complexity and improve financial tracking  \n\n## **Targeting and Geolocation Strategy**\n\nNew geographic and contact data requirements surfaced to support expanded campaign targeting.\n\n- **Nina clarified that adding the Bank Verlag in Germany to targeting requires contact emails linked to zip codes** to enable accurate geolocation-based campaigns (06:02)  \n    - Current US campaigns rely on zip codes connected to headquarters, but the bank''s Europe-based zip codes need verified contact data for effective targeting  \n    - The paid media specialist is investigating which specific contact info is necessary to support this new geofence targeting  \n    - This detail is critical to avoid wasted spend and ensure ads reach the intended financial decision-makers  \n    - Kate confirmed the bank is located in Germany and agreed that supplementary contact data is essential to extend targeting beyond US zip codes (07:37)  \n\n- **The team is monitoring competitor activity bidding on brand terms**, but Nina noted competitors’ budgets are too low to pose current risk, keeping brand visibility intact (11:09)  \n    - Campaign ad strength is average, but adding more site links and visual assets like logos is planned to improve quality scores and CTR  \n    - These optimizations are expected to maintain brand presence and fend off low-level competitor bids  \n\n## **Content Production and Asset Preparation**\n\nFinalizing creative assets and translations supports upcoming campaign launches and regulatory content releases.\n\n- **Nicola Harding podcast episode was finalized and pending Kate’s approval by end of day** for publication, ensuring timely content delivery (05:23)  \n    - Analytics team is working to enhance podcast insights, including time frames and episode data, to better understand audience engagement (08:44)  \n    - This data will help refine future podcast topics and distribution strategies for higher impact  \n\n- **The FDA white paper received approval and was sent to the PR agency for release under embargo**, with creative and web assets being prepared in HubSpot to support the launch (09:58)  \n    - Kate requested tidy-up of journey pages and website setups, aiming for smooth rollout once embargo lifts  \n    - This coordination ensures marketing channels are aligned for a cohesive campaign launch  \n\n- **For the German Bank Verlag campaign, translation of a regulatory PDF into German is underway**, but both Kate and Nina lack internal German language resources (15:07)  \n    - They plan to rely on ChatGPT for bulk translation with a freelancer or Fiverr proofreader to handle regional nuances and accuracy (16:21)  \n    - This approach balances cost and quality for timely content delivery in the German market  \n\n## **Website Migration and Technical Updates**\n\nProgress continues on site migrations and ongoing fixes to improve user experience and campaign readiness.\n\n- **The Bank Fraud Summit website migration is in progress with tickets submitted to IT and developers provided additional assets** to complete the transition (07:52)  \n    - Nina is testing minor website fixes and newsletter components aligned with recent creative briefs to enhance user engagement  \n    - These updates are critical to support upcoming campaigns and maintain seamless visitor experience during the migration  \n    - Kate will communicate any changes or delays from IT to keep the team aligned (16:57)  \n\n- **Mobile banner optimization for the homepage slider has been implemented**, resolving prior UX issues highlighted by Kate (05:28)  \n    - This improves mobile visitor engagement and supports campaign visibility for key promotions  \n    - The optimization reflects a focus on mobile-first experiences given rising mobile traffic  \n\n## **Process and Operational Improvements**\n\nOngoing adjustments to campaign tracking, reporting, and team coordination aim to increase efficiency and clarity.\n\n- **Nina''s team updated HubSpot lead source fields to better align with ABM campaigns**, enabling more accurate tracking and data-driven decision-making (05:28)  \n    - This change ensures all relevant lead information feeds into campaign performance analysis without gaps  \n    - It supports more granular attribution and optimization efforts across channels  \n\n- **Nina will coordinate with paid media specialists to identify exact data needs and campaign setup requirements for the new Bank Verlag ads**, ensuring readiness before launch (16:39)  \n    - This proactive communication reduces risks of delays or misalignment on targeting and creative  \n    - It also clarifies ownership and timelines for campaign activation  \n\n- **Kate suggested a potential ad opportunity in Germany linked to a regulatory PDF translation**, indicating exploration of localized content marketing to support lead generation in a new market (15:03)  \n    - Nina will investigate translation resource availability and cost-effective proofing options to expedite this initiative  \n    - This shows strategic intent to expand regional market penetration through tailored content  \n\n- **The team plans to keep the optional Friday catch-up meeting open**, allowing flexibility to address any last-minute issues before the weekend (17:07)  \n    - This approach balances efficient use of time with readiness for urgent needs, reflecting adaptive workflow management","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast","HubSpot","LinkedIn Campaign","Bank Verlag","Google Ads","Website Migration"],"overview":"- **Budget Adjustment:** $500 allocated for LinkedIn campaigns targeting Central Europe, enhancing top-of-funnel lead generation.  \n- **Lead Generation Results:** $704 spent on LinkedIn yielded 8 leads from C-suite targets, improving lead quality despite higher costs in Europe.  \n- **Campaign Targeting Needs:** Bank Verlag''s targeting requires zip code-linked contact emails for effective geolocation-based campaigns in Germany.  \n- **Content Production Updates:** Podcast episode finalized for release; FDA white paper sent for embargoed PR launch with aligned assets.  \n- **Website Migration Status:** Bank Fraud Summit website migration is ongoing, with minor fixes being tested to enhance user experience.  \n- **Operational Improvements:** HubSpot updates enhance ABM campaign tracking; coordination ensures readiness for upcoming Bank Verlag ad launch.","action_items":"\n**Kate ThreatMark**\nReview and provide feedback on “Behind Enemies Lines” podcast episode with Nicola Harding by end of day (05:23)\nProvide feedback on Central European LinkedIn account list and assist with running lead gen campaigns with £500 separate budget allocation (09:05)\nPrepare and tidy up FDA white paper creative assets, HubSpot journeys, and web pages for embargoed release (10:23)\nInform Nina of any changes regarding Bank Fraud Summit website migration; track support ticket progress (16:57)\nCoordinate with Colin on switching Google Ads account currency from pounds to dollars and LinkedIn Business Manager currency setup (14:04)\n\n**Nina Belina**\nConfirm and ensure podcast episode review and publication readiness (05:23)\nContinue optimizing HubSpot lead sources and mobile homepage banner (05:28)\nClarify geolocation targeting requirements including postal codes and contact data for Bank Verlag German campaign (06:40)\nFollow up with paid media specialists on needed info to start the Central Europe LinkedIn lead gen campaign (16:39)\nCheck availability of internal German translation/proofing resource or arrange external proofreader to support Bank Verlag campaign materials (15:51)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nContinue work on migrating Google Ads account currency from pounds to dollars; provide status update (14:23)\nSupport inquiries regarding LinkedIn campaign manager and currency setup (14:30)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"0035d607-4f86-482c-a2c6-85893d377589","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
