    '{"id":"01KF18YYJQDFXTMPXR0034RKPP","title":"Encamp // Website Feedback: Nina Belina and Kyley Crews (Jenny B.)","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Design and User Experience Improvements**\n\nThe team decided to remove background animations and standardize visual elements to improve readability and page load times.\n\n- **The animation in the background will be eliminated and replaced with a static orange accent line and desaturated background colors** to enhance text readability and reduce page load time concerns raised by the demand generation leader (05:44)  \n    - Developers initially liked the animation, but the team prioritized clarity and performance  \n    - The static design improves accessibility and user focus on content  \n    - Implementation will involve developers adjusting the existing design within the next development cycle  \n    - Expected impact includes faster page loads and better user engagement metrics due to clearer text visibility\n\n- **Uniform tile sizes and consistent styling will be enforced across all featured resource sections, including pluralizing resource categories like “case studies,” “ebooks,” and “webinars”** (07:32)  \n    - Tiles currently vary in size due to differing text lengths, complicating management  \n    - The team plans to set maximum text length or use ellipses to maintain uniformity  \n    - Consistent tile size supports a cleaner, more professional look, improving user experience  \n    - This will standardize the visual hierarchy and reduce cognitive load on visitors\n\n- **The orange border stroke around images will be removed from all product images following UX designer Brianna’s preference, while accent lines in orange or green may remain on page edges** (15:18)  \n    - Borders created by designers do not scale with images and complicate resolution issues  \n    - Accent lines that touch product images will be solid, not dotted, to align with brand feedback  \n    - Removing borders reduces visual clutter and highlights product imagery more naturally  \n    - This change balances design aesthetics with practical image quality concerns\n\n- **Background lines behind text will be desaturated gray rather than orange, with orange accents placed behind images or along page edges only** to maintain text clarity (19:09)  \n    - Orange behind text reduces readability, so desaturated gray backgrounds will be used consistently  \n    - Accent lines will frame images or page sections without interfering with copy  \n    - Gradient masks may be applied to static backgrounds to enhance focus on text areas  \n    - The dev team will assess impact on page speed before finalizing implementation\n\n## **Image Quality and Resource Asset Management**\n\nAddressing image resolution problems and establishing guidelines for consistent, high-quality visuals is critical for brand presentation.\n\n- **Many images used on the site suffer from low resolution and graininess, partly due to layered effects, prompting a directive to replace or improve image assets** (11:40)  \n    - Higher resolution images were uploaded but effects like heat maps degraded quality  \n    - Developers will experiment with different layering techniques to preserve image clarity  \n    - Improved images will boost professionalism and user trust on key pages  \n    - This effort aligns with maintaining brand standards and visual consistency\n\n- **Adobe Stock links have been provided for replacing industry page images, allowing easy access to high-quality photos while ensuring consistent theming across pages** (25:46)  \n    - The energy and utilities pages already use updated images featuring solar panels and infrastructure  \n    - This approach enables scalable image updates across all industry pages  \n    - Using licensed stock photos reduces risk and speeds up content refresh cycles  \n    - It also supports a unified look and feel, which enhances brand recognition\n\n## **Content and Typography Standardization**\n\nThe team prioritized text clarity and consistency, instituting global styling updates across CTAs, headings, and resource labels.\n\n- **All CTAs across headers and footers have been bolded to achieve a modern and unified appearance, improving visibility and clickability** (23:19)  \n    - Previously, CTA text was inconsistent, appearing as regular font in some areas  \n    - Bold CTAs create stronger visual calls to action, supporting conversion goals  \n    - The team agreed to keep current CTA sizes as they are effective  \n    - This change reflects a broader push to modernize site typography for better engagement\n\n- **Typography lines and accent colors will vary globally, using orange, green, or gray depending on context, with solid lines preferred over dotted ones for better visual flow** (17:15)  \n    - Colored accents may run the full page height and touch product images to align with designer feedback  \n    - This flexible approach balances visual interest with legibility  \n    - The team will prioritize implementing what is feasible within current development constraints  \n    - These decisions follow Jenny Vance’s UX perspective, ensuring design and function align\n\n- **Spacing around headers, particularly H2s, will be reduced according to updated brand guidelines to tighten layout and improve page flow** (19:09)  \n    - Excessive space above and below headers currently breaks visual continuity  \n    - The updated spacing will better group related content for easier scanning  \n    - Developers will follow the layout specifications from brand guidelines page 20  \n    - Improved spacing supports a cleaner, more engaging user experience\n\n## **Process Alignment and Team Coordination**\n\nFeedback and process changes were implemented early to avoid costly rework post-launch and ensure cross-team alignment.\n\n- **Christine, the new marketing leader, identified critical design issues during early dev reviews, prompting pre-launch fixes that improve site quality** (27:35)  \n    - Her fresh perspective caught problems that previous team members missed  \n    - Early detection avoids expensive post-launch corrections and preserves brand reputation  \n    - This highlights the value of cross-functional review and fresh eyes on projects  \n    - The team remains open to continuous feedback as development progresses\n\n- **The development team will assess feasibility and impact of design changes such as static lines and gradient masks, balancing aesthetics with performance** (21:18)  \n    - Technical considerations like page speed influence final design decisions  \n    - Developers will provide guidance to ensure changes are practical and maintain user experience  \n    - This collaborative approach aligns design goals with system capabilities  \n    - It ensures the site remains fast and accessible while looking polished\n\n- **A global approach to styling, image treatment, and typography will be maintained through centralized brand guidelines and developer communication** (27:35)  \n    - Brand guideline updates have been shared to maintain consistency across pages  \n    - Developers and designers will coordinate to keep visual elements uniform  \n    - This reduces confusion and streamlines future updates  \n    - Clear documentation supports smoother workflows and faster turnarounds","outline":null,"keywords":["website redesign","animation removal","image quality","typography","brand guidelines","UX design"],"overview":"- **Website Design Changes:** Background animations will be removed for static designs to enhance readability and page loading time.\n\n- **Uniform Resource Tiles:** Tile size and styling will be standardized for improved management and user experience across resource sections.\n\n- **Image Quality Improvements:** Low-resolution images will be replaced, ensuring high-quality visuals for better brand representation on the site.\n\n- **Updated CTAs and Typography:** CTAs will be bolded for visibility; typography will adjust spacing and color based on context to enhance clarity.\n\n- **Early Feedback Implementation:** New marketing leader''s insights led to pre-launch design fixes, reducing costly post-launch corrections and improving site quality.\n\n- **Centralized Brand Guidelines:** Consistent styling and images maintained through clear documentation, ensuring smooth updates across all site pages.","action_items":"\n**Nina Belina**\nRemove all animated background lines and replace with static solid orange accent lines and desaturated backgrounds as a priority (05:44)\nCoordinate with developers to standardize rectangle sizes and apply truncation with dots for long text blocks on Camp Personas (07:10)\nEnsure all featured resource labels are pluralized consistently and that the tile styles match the preferred uniform style with varied accent colors (07:32)\nWork with developers to improve image quality by removing any heatmap effects and upload high-resolution images uniformly across pages (11:40)\nRemove orange strokes on all images and screenshots globally except on icons/text tiles, as per UX designers’ preference; confirm if drop shadows are necessary (15:18)\nImplement solid colored accent lines that align with product images but avoid placing color accents behind text for improved readability (18:30)\nAdjust header spacing to align with updated brand guidelines ensuring less spacing above and below headers as shown on page 20 of brand doc (19:09)\nApply desaturation and possible gradient masks on full backgrounds to improve text readability without compromising page load times (20:58)\nReplace or update blog page image styles with bigger images for single blog posts; discontinue busy tile styles (21:40)\nRemove four blocks on Camp Personas and confirm correct text removals; ensure all CTAs use 700 Bold font weight including headers and footers (23:19)\nReview and apply Adobe stock photos for industry pages, particularly energy and utilities, using provided links for consistency (25:46)\nCollaborate with devs to finalize implementation of all these changes and ensure they align with the expectations of the marketing team and new leader (27:35)\n"},"duration":30.639999389648438,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Nina Belina"},{"id":1,"name":"Kyley"},{"id":2,"name":"Jenny B."}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi.","index":0,"end_time":238.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":238.41,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Hi, Nina.","index":1,"end_time":240.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":239.45,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"How are you?","index":2,"end_time":241.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":241.05,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Cold.","index":3,"end_time":244.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":243.53,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"How are you?","index":4,"end_time":245.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.41,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It''s so cold in Indiana right now.","index":5,"end_time":248.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.09,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Oh, I can imagine.","index":6,"end_time":250.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":249.05,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But it''s so cold.","index":7,"end_time":251.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.33,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I feel like it''s cold everywhere, you know.","index":8,"end_time":253.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":251.17,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Where are you located?","index":9,"end_time":255.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":254.25,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I''m in Zagreb, in Croatia.","index":10,"end_time":257.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And I mean, here it''s.","index":11,"end_time":260.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":258.36,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It wasn''t as cold as it is now, but like, the last couple of weeks, it''s been really, really like.","index":12,"end_time":266.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I see you.","index":13,"end_time":267.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":266.76,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"You have to be very careful when you''re on the street.","index":14,"end_time":269.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":267.48,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think it''s been mild here.","index":15,"end_time":272.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.76,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So now it''s, you know, 7 degrees Fahrenheit again.","index":16,"end_time":275.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.52,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And it''s.","index":17,"end_time":277.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.56,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I''m like, no, bring back the, like, 40s.","index":18,"end_time":281.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.96,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I. I liked that.","index":19,"end_time":282.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":281.76,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"That was good.","index":20,"end_time":283.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.72,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"We had a designer who''s in Argentina and he had power outage because of the heat wave.","index":21,"end_time":290.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And I was like, oh, I wish I had a heat wave.","index":22,"end_time":292.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":23,"end_time":294.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.32,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"But.","index":24,"end_time":297.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.52,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":25,"end_time":298.399,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":26,"end_time":299.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":299.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Hi.","index":27,"end_time":300.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":300.32,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I went through the comments on Buckheart, but wanted to ask if you wanted to go into a little bit more detail or, you know.","index":28,"end_time":308.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":301.44,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, I wanted to talk about, like, some of the global things that I like that we identified just to make sure that you''re aware of them.","index":29,"end_time":316.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.75,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Because for some of them, for example, the four blocks on the Camp Personas, I did remove some text, but it could be that I removed the wrong one.","index":30,"end_time":326.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":316.95,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So that could be also something to check.","index":31,"end_time":328.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":326.59,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, so the first.","index":32,"end_time":332.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.71,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Here, I''ll share my screen.","index":33,"end_time":333.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.07,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Here it is the first and what I would argue is the largest is eliminating this animation in the background.","index":34,"end_time":344.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.04,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I told the developers that we were moving them.","index":35,"end_time":346.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.04,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"They said that it''s a cool thing to have on the website, but I was like, sorry, it has to go.","index":36,"end_time":354.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.76,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It is cool, but our demand gen leader is a little worried about the readability behind, like, the text and we just can''t quite settle on it.","index":37,"end_time":367.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":355.08,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And then there''s also worries about page load time.","index":38,"end_time":370.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":367.18,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So, yeah, it seemed like the right call for now at least is to just.","index":39,"end_time":376.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.9,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Instead of having them moving just a solid orange accent line, just static, and then desaturating everything a little bit more so that when it''s got text behind it, it''s easy to read.","index":40,"end_time":391.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":376.9,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":392.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.35,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":42,"end_time":400.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.71,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"This was one thing, making sure that these are globally always the same size.","index":43,"end_time":404.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.15,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"We get some where, like one of the rectangles is bigger.","index":44,"end_time":411.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":407.87,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So we just want to make sure that that''s like a setting where that is static.","index":45,"end_time":417.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.87,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, I think this was due to the text sites.","index":46,"end_time":420.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":417.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":47,"end_time":421.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.96,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"The long texts.","index":48,"end_time":422.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":421.28,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":49,"end_time":422.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":422.32,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So I think we just have to determine what the longest one is and kind of Go from there.","index":50,"end_time":427.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":423.12,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Or we can have the titles off.","index":51,"end_time":431.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.48,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":52,"end_time":432.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.24,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I will tell the developers to put the dots until we see, you know, if we want to shorten them or not.","index":53,"end_time":439.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":432.72,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because it''s very difficult to make.","index":54,"end_time":440.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Manage all of them if they''re different sizes.","index":55,"end_time":442.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":440.89,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, okay.","index":56,"end_time":446.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":443.37,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":57,"end_time":448.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.25,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"These.","index":58,"end_time":449.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.69,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I put a note somewhere.","index":59,"end_time":450.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":449.29,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I know these all need to be plural.","index":60,"end_time":452.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":450.77,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It should be case studies, ebooks, blog posts, webinars.","index":61,"end_time":456.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.57,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So that seems like a global update.","index":62,"end_time":458.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":456.89,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"On any of the, like, featured resources.","index":63,"end_time":467.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":462.97,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"We want this treatment, but I would like to vary the colors.","index":64,"end_time":472.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.72,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So sometimes the topography would be the green or the orange instead of always teal.","index":65,"end_time":477.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":472.6,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"But there are a few pages that have just an entirely different featured resources.","index":66,"end_time":486.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":477.96,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And I''m not sure why some of them are different.","index":67,"end_time":492.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":487.4,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Let me see if I can find one.","index":68,"end_time":493.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.08,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I think that for the ones that showed before, they probably put green because of the image that''s behind it.","index":69,"end_time":503.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.37,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So you know that it''s not too colorful.","index":70,"end_time":505.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":503.53,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":71,"end_time":520.699,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":520.379,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"No, no worries.","index":72,"end_time":522.459,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":521.339,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, so like here, this is a different treatment.","index":73,"end_time":528.379,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.699,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So I just want them to be uniform and I don''t know, Jenny, do you think this or the other one.","index":74,"end_time":537.099,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.819,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Because the other one is a lot.","index":75,"end_time":538.779,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":537.419,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It could get busy.","index":76,"end_time":539.899,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":538.779,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I like this treatment more, but I. I think this is the treatment that''s using the stock photography.","index":77,"end_time":548.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.219,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"The other one is pulling in the, like the tile image that we uploaded.","index":78,"end_time":554.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":548.97,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"So I think this treatment.","index":79,"end_time":558.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.45,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"But pulling in the featured.","index":80,"end_time":561.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.17,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Whatever the second images.","index":81,"end_time":563.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":561.85,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah, would be great.","index":82,"end_time":564.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":563.77,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And make sure that the outline goes the whole way.","index":83,"end_time":567.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":564.73,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"This sort of cuts off, which is odd.","index":84,"end_time":569.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.37,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Something that we''ll have to take a look at, Kylie, then is for the blog articles, the featured image is like, has text on it.","index":85,"end_time":578.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":569.85,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah, that''s okay.","index":86,"end_time":580.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":579.17,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":87,"end_time":581.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":580.77,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Eventually I would kind of like to move away from that, but it''s fine for now.","index":88,"end_time":587.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":582.37,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It''s fine for now.","index":89,"end_time":587.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.09,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah.","index":90,"end_time":588.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":587.93,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"But yeah, I mean, even that example you just showed, you can see that the tiles are different sizes.","index":91,"end_time":595.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.85,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah.","index":92,"end_time":596.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":595.81,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":93,"end_time":596.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.29,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So we would want, you know, uniform tile size with the image area that fits our.","index":94,"end_time":602.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":597.17,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"The dimensions of our current resource images.","index":95,"end_time":606.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":602.85,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, that seems like a big global change.","index":96,"end_time":610.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":608.45,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So I apologize.","index":97,"end_time":612.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.73,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"All of my notes about the other ones can be disregarded.","index":98,"end_time":616.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":612.77,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So for the other resources, is it okay that they''re in colors or do you also want them white?","index":99,"end_time":623.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":619.17,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think we want them all like that.","index":100,"end_time":627.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":625.57,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Um, so I think we want to not do this, which actually makes sense because this is.","index":101,"end_time":634.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":627.78,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It makes it really hard to read our.","index":102,"end_time":635.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":634.26,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, this is a bit busy.","index":103,"end_time":637.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":636.1,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":104,"end_time":638.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So I think we should get rid of this as and then for like the global featured resource.","index":105,"end_time":645.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":638.58,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Do like we do on the thank you page, but just make sure that the outline goes the full way and that they are uniform in size.","index":106,"end_time":655.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.06,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":663.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.25,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So these then too.","index":108,"end_time":664.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.61,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"This should all be that other.","index":109,"end_time":668.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.77,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"The other style.","index":110,"end_time":673.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":672.61,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And then I noticed across the board.","index":111,"end_time":681.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":677.17,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Oh, wait, I do want to say this.","index":112,"end_time":684.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Anywhere where we do this.","index":113,"end_time":686.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":685.42,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"This should be wider.","index":114,"end_time":687.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":686.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"This seems really, really narrow to me, so I would like that widened.","index":115,"end_time":692.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":688.14,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"But this is a great page to show there are a lot of images that are not high enough quality.","index":116,"end_time":699.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.78,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":117,"end_time":700.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.06,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I was talking with the developer and I think that they used a layer that was supposed to make the images a little bit more to, you know, give them like a heat map effect and it didn''t really work out.","index":118,"end_time":714.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.42,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So I will tell them to try something, use something different because we tried uploading higher resolution images and I think it''s just due to the effect that they''re using.","index":119,"end_time":723.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":714.5,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":120,"end_time":725.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":724.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Because.","index":121,"end_time":725.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.26,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, like, even this one, it''s.","index":122,"end_time":727.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":725.54,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It''s quite grainy.","index":123,"end_time":728.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":727.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":729.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.78,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I. Yeah, it was just becoming an issue where a lot of them.","index":125,"end_time":737.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":731.35,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"That one was okay, but a lot of them are lower quality than I think we want.","index":126,"end_time":745.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.75,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And there was one issue.","index":127,"end_time":748.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.67,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I''m almost wondering if they''ve fixed it because it was like when there were four of these, the fourth one had really tight text and now I can''t find that.","index":128,"end_time":765.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":748.71,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So maybe they''ve addressed that already.","index":129,"end_time":768.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.84,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Oh, no.","index":130,"end_time":772.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.76,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Oh, this one.","index":131,"end_time":773.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.12,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So, yeah.","index":132,"end_time":775.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.92,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And that.","index":133,"end_time":776.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":775.6,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I saw that in several places.","index":134,"end_time":778.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":776.08,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It''s like the line facing just is off on that fourth tile.","index":135,"end_time":783.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":778.28,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And when it comes to the line.","index":136,"end_time":787.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":785.93,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Spacing, because the stroke is off on this too.","index":137,"end_time":790.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.21,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I think it''s usually a wider.","index":138,"end_time":794.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":792.65,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Let me find.","index":139,"end_time":796.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":795.69,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":140,"end_time":796.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.37,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Oh, and that one doesn''t have the orange stroke around it.","index":141,"end_time":802.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":799.53,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":142,"end_time":809.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.54,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"See how these are?","index":143,"end_time":810.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":809.78,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It''s a wider, a thicker stroke than here.","index":144,"end_time":813.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":145,"end_time":815.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.98,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I''ll ask them to make it a global change so it''s the same.","index":146,"end_time":819.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":816.82,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, that would be good.","index":147,"end_time":822.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":820.26,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And then so is adding the orange stroke around the image, is that a global thing or do we need to do that to the images every time?","index":148,"end_time":838.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Like, will we need.","index":149,"end_time":839.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":838.4,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"No, actually, when you see the border stroke on the tiles, it''s actually something that''s within the website.","index":150,"end_time":848.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.52,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So we have to put it on.","index":151,"end_time":850.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":848.96,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think it''s number two to be the correct size as the images, but the stroke on the images has been done by this designer.","index":152,"end_time":858.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":850.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So this is like.","index":153,"end_time":859.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.36,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"That''s the image.","index":154,"end_time":860.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.28,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay.","index":155,"end_time":861.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":860.96,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So every time we would want to do one of these, we will need to add a stroke to it.","index":156,"end_time":865.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":861.6,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":157,"end_time":866.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":865.96,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because it.","index":158,"end_time":866.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.2,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because the stroke wouldn''t Follow the outline.","index":159,"end_time":870.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":866.88,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"If it was.","index":160,"end_time":871.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.4,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, within the.","index":161,"end_time":872.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"That was my thought.","index":162,"end_time":873.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":872.96,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So, Jenny, that kind of.","index":163,"end_time":876.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":875.2,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"That''s something I think you need to think on, I guess is whether we want to always be doing a stroke on these.","index":164,"end_time":884.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.76,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I know that Jenny V. Liked like the line going into the images, but.","index":165,"end_time":896.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.16,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I think it also depends because we talked about the resolution.","index":166,"end_time":901.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And for example, when they''re like this, when you have like a smaller image within the image, you can not notice that some of the images have a little bit of a lower resolution.","index":167,"end_time":911.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":902.11,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But for example, if we would do the carousel, they would have to be, you know, high resolution because they wouldn''t be smaller.","index":168,"end_time":918.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.95,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So for example, if you.","index":169,"end_time":919.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.72,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So like some of the, like this image that''s on the page here for the compliance calendar, this is not like there''s.","index":170,"end_time":931.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":920.24,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"This is one image that like our designer made and like what she has popped out is all within that, like the background view.","index":171,"end_time":940.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":931.88,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"She''s just pulled out the data sets that we want that like align to the copy.","index":172,"end_time":945.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":940.8,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"But as you know, Nina, when we are going to take the carousel approach, those are two distinct product screens, like sometimes even from different sections of our app.","index":173,"end_time":957.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":946.54,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Because as like we''ve chatted with your team about.","index":174,"end_time":960.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":958.22,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah, like this, for example, these are two separate sections of our app that speak to this capability of having a total waste overview of your waste data.","index":175,"end_time":971.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":961.74,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"So, yeah, I, I mean, Kylie, Brianna has said that she does not like the orange outline.","index":176,"end_time":980.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":972.69,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"So maybe we just make the call right now.","index":177,"end_time":987.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.93,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"I didn''t know we were getting.","index":178,"end_time":991.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":989.57,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Instead of, sorry, you''re fine, Nina.","index":179,"end_time":996.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":992.13,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I mean, she was a little bummed about that.","index":180,"end_time":999.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":997.33,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So it''s really just managing that expectation more than anything.","index":181,"end_time":1004.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":999.25,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"That''s fine.","index":182,"end_time":1004.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1004.11,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"I mean, at the end of the, like, this is.","index":183,"end_time":1006.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1004.59,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah, let''s.","index":184,"end_time":1007.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1006.55,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"I don''t.","index":185,"end_time":1008.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1007.59,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"I would prioritize designers a UX designers pov, to be honest.","index":186,"end_time":1015.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1008.87,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah.","index":187,"end_time":1017.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.03,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":188,"end_time":1018.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1018.23,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"So then I think, Nina, for your team and I apologize for this, it would be removing all of the orange borders around the images and screenshots.","index":189,"end_time":1035.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.79,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Not like the tiles where we have, you know, an icon and text, but all of the images.","index":190,"end_time":1040.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.46,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And do you want them to add like a drop shadow, A global drop.","index":191,"end_time":1046.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1040.7,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Shadow Now, Sorry, Kylie, you also posed a thought around like for some of these typography lines, will we do a fully colored in orange or another brand color or is the topography all going to be in gray?","index":192,"end_time":1068.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1046.46,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"I think doing some accents on the edges could be nice.","index":193,"end_time":1074.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1069.66,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yes, I agree.","index":194,"end_time":1075.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1074.86,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Especially if it could go down the whole page.","index":195,"end_time":1077.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1075.82,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yes.","index":196,"end_time":1078.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1078.22,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"And yeah, we could do the orange.","index":197,"end_time":1082.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.78,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"We could do Some green.","index":198,"end_time":1083.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.33,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Sometimes I think there''s options.","index":199,"end_time":1085.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1083.41,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It''s really whatever we can get done.","index":200,"end_time":1088.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.13,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I fully agree and I did just remember, and this is another.","index":201,"end_time":1093.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.45,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"If we do want to take into account Jenny Vance''s feedback, those colored accents could touch the product images.","index":202,"end_time":1105.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1094.17,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"So rather like this example we have here, rather than have it be the dotted line, it could be a solid line that touches, goes behind.","index":203,"end_time":1114.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1106.27,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yep.","index":204,"end_time":1115.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1114.83,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yes.","index":205,"end_time":1116.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1115.63,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":206,"end_time":1118.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1117.23,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And I think that would appease her reference.","index":207,"end_time":1124.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1120.03,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah.","index":208,"end_time":1126.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1125.95,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Then it''s this spacing around our headers is really large.","index":209,"end_time":1132.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.47,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I think we need to get.","index":210,"end_time":1134.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.02,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s around the H2S or around the.","index":211,"end_time":1138.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.34,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"These headers.","index":212,"end_time":1139.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139.02,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Like if there''s a set space above and below, that''s really high, but it seems really, really large.","index":213,"end_time":1145.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139.82,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"But only above and below, not the one in between.","index":214,"end_time":1148.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.66,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Or do you want that we have this.","index":215,"end_time":1151.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1149.9,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"There''s a lot above it and there''s a lot below it and I would like all of it.","index":216,"end_time":1155.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1151.82,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":217,"end_time":1156.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1156.3,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It should be like true eyebrow copy.","index":218,"end_time":1160.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1157.59,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Like, that''s what.","index":219,"end_time":1162.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1161.43,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"So like it should be much closer to the header copy.","index":220,"end_time":1168.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1163.51,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah.","index":221,"end_time":1170.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1170.15,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And I wanted to ask when it comes to the background lines, just to be sure.","index":222,"end_time":1176.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1171.43,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So you want them to be solid lines and for them to be gray, not orange.","index":223,"end_time":1181.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.15,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So let''s.","index":224,"end_time":1186,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1184.64,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"If we look at this page, this one here, I would make be gray.","index":225,"end_time":1190.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1186,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I think everything that''s like primarily behind our text should be a desaturated gray.","index":226,"end_time":1199.359,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1190.64,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Where we could bring in a solid accent is like over here.","index":227,"end_time":1203.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1199.44,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Can I mark up some now?","index":228,"end_time":1206.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1204.4,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Is that an option?","index":229,"end_time":1207.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1206.64,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I can.","index":230,"end_time":1208.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1207.76,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Brilliant.","index":231,"end_time":1209.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1208.65,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So like we could do.","index":232,"end_time":1213.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1210.25,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Of course this is going to be right on my spot.","index":233,"end_time":1217.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.65,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Like this line could be orange and you know, something that is just down the side, like could have some orange just to frame it out.","index":234,"end_time":1233.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1220.33,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And if the orange is going to go behind anything, it should go behind an image, not behind the copy.","index":235,"end_time":1242.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1235.07,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And then.","index":236,"end_time":1245.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.83,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yes, not behind copy because that''s.","index":237,"end_time":1247.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1245.47,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"We''ve seen that that makes it very hard to read.","index":238,"end_time":1251.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1248.35,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Nina.","index":239,"end_time":1251.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1251.43,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Okay.","index":240,"end_time":1253.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1252.59,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then the full background, I think should be desaturated just a touch more to make sure that.","index":241,"end_time":1260.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1254.51,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"That this is easily readable.","index":242,"end_time":1262.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1260.19,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And if this is a static image, it might even be a matter of, you know, putting a gradient mask on so that things out here are darker and as you get towards the text, it''s less so.","index":243,"end_time":1278.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1266.28,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"But I don''t know enough about website development to know what that will do to page speed and everything.","index":244,"end_time":1284.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1278.6,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So I trust their judgment on what will make it work.","index":245,"end_time":1289.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1285.08,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Any other local things I had noticed, like I said, the Images.","index":246,"end_time":1307.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.93,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I made a lot of comments about images not being high enough quality.","index":247,"end_time":1313.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1307.49,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"We haven''t seen a blog page mockup.","index":248,"end_time":1318.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"But I will say when I clicked into here and saw this.","index":249,"end_time":1322.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1318.58,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Okay, this looks so much better.","index":250,"end_time":1324.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1322.94,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Okay, it''s gotten a lot better.","index":251,"end_time":1326.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1325.18,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"It was very, very boring when I looked the first time.","index":252,"end_time":1329.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1326.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And then I realized that you had to.","index":253,"end_time":1332.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1329.94,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And I was like, oh, they must.","index":254,"end_time":1335.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1334.62,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Not have done it yet.","index":255,"end_time":1336.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1335.62,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, because I said.","index":256,"end_time":1337.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1336.62,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because the blog, you know the one with the thumbnails, that one was done, but the single blog page wasn''t.","index":257,"end_time":1344.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1338.06,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"So it was probably that period in between.","index":258,"end_time":1347.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1345.09,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"This is great though.","index":259,"end_time":1349.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1348.29,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And so Jenny, for your reference, this is where I would love to start doing bigger images up here.","index":260,"end_time":1355.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1349.17,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And those would be like a smaller version of.","index":261,"end_time":1357.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1355.25,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"That will be our thumbnail.","index":262,"end_time":1358.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1357.53,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And so like, as we go, it''ll look a little better.","index":263,"end_time":1364.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1360.29,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":264,"end_time":1365.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1364.85,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, this looks much better.","index":265,"end_time":1369.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1368.5,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Cool.","index":266,"end_time":1374.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1374.02,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And.","index":267,"end_time":1376.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1376.1,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"But again, we''re going to get rid of this and switch to just the basic tiles.","index":268,"end_time":1380.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1376.46,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, I think.","index":269,"end_time":1384.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1381.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I think that''s all I wanted to point out.","index":270,"end_time":1387.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1385.62,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Also, you mentioned the text.","index":271,"end_time":1392.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1388.26,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Let me just check the four blocks and the encamps.","index":272,"end_time":1399.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1394.27,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Personas that need to be removed.","index":273,"end_time":1401.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1399.63,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Oh yeah, where.","index":274,"end_time":1403.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1402.03,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"What page is that on?","index":275,"end_time":1404.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1403.23,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Because I thought.","index":276,"end_time":1407.269,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.35,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because I was removing them myself from like the previous comments and now I''m not sure if I removed the right thing.","index":277,"end_time":1413.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1407.269,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, I think it was on one of the industry pages.","index":278,"end_time":1418.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1415.15,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Okay.","index":279,"end_time":1419.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1419.39,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Is it the waste page?","index":280,"end_time":1427.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1426.03,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Maybe.","index":281,"end_time":1427.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1427.39,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Okay, they''re not here.","index":282,"end_time":1442.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1441.23,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Chemicals page.","index":283,"end_time":1445.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.52,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"There they are.","index":284,"end_time":1452.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.32,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"This one''s okay.","index":285,"end_time":1453.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1452.6,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":286,"end_time":1464.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1464.12,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Otherwise, I think once we get those.","index":287,"end_time":1469.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1466.92,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Changes made and I made all the CTA''s 700 Bold, so.","index":288,"end_time":1477.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.76,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Because previously we didn''t have like for the footer and the header of the pages, it was like just a regular text.","index":289,"end_time":1486.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1477.18,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"It wasn''t a bold one in the CTAs.","index":290,"end_time":1488.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1486.42,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean, for me it did give a little bit more of like a modern feel that is not all unified, but now they''re all bold.","index":291,"end_time":1494.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1488.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And if that works, we can keep it that way.","index":292,"end_time":1497.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1494.94,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think the CTAs look good.","index":293,"end_time":1502.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1501.56,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, they were just very.","index":294,"end_time":1508.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1505.08,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And also for the images for.","index":295,"end_time":1511.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1509.08,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Do you want the CTA is bigger or not?","index":296,"end_time":1513.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.56,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think they''re fine the way they are.","index":297,"end_time":1515.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1514.36,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":298,"end_time":1516.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1516.2,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And for the industry images, the only page that I''ve changed images in are the ones that was.","index":299,"end_time":1526.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1518.52,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I think it was the energy and utilities.","index":300,"end_time":1528.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1526.26,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"But if you can see if that approach works, we can make it in the same theme for the other pages if it''s too much, because I did use like a lot of solar panels.","index":301,"end_time":1538.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1529.74,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And infrastructure Actually left comments that I hope will be helpful to replace with.","index":302,"end_time":1546.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1538.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And I put a link to an Adobe stock photo because I know you guys had used those before.","index":303,"end_time":1551.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1546.7,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So, like on all the industry pages, there are links out to different photography to use because that seemed easier because.","index":304,"end_time":1563.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1552.59,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"There''S a lot of, like, different ways you can change it.","index":305,"end_time":1567.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1563.59,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then I wasn''t sure.","index":306,"end_time":1568.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.23,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yep.","index":307,"end_time":1569.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1569.31,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":308,"end_time":1572.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1572.03,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"So when you go into them, like, they always.","index":309,"end_time":1576.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1573.31,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"They''ll say, like, replace with this image and it has a link to an Adobe stock.","index":310,"end_time":1580.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1576.35,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Because I thought, okay, they must have an Adobe stock account too, and so that''s easiest.","index":311,"end_time":1588.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.62,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Do you have anything else for the web pages?","index":312,"end_time":1595.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1592.14,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I don''t think so.","index":313,"end_time":1598.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1596.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I think the biggest change is going to be the animated lines, which I''ll tell our developers, you know, your train of, train of thoughts, and then they will also tell me how it can be managed and what can be achieved.","index":314,"end_time":1611.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1599.18,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Just so you know, how the lines can move and react to the blocks within the web page.","index":315,"end_time":1617.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1611.84,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"And then, you know, so we all know we are on the same side with that because, you know, it''s a huge change and then if they do it, then it''s not ideal.","index":316,"end_time":1629.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1617.96,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Then they would have to do everything again.","index":317,"end_time":1631.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1629.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":318,"end_time":1633.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1632.85,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":319,"end_time":1638.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1638.45,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Nina, we have a new marketing leader on the team.","index":320,"end_time":1641.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1638.85,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"So it was Christine who identified this.","index":321,"end_time":1644.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1642.13,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"You know, I mean, I feel pretty confident, Kylie, that the dev version of the pages is her first exposure to the website.","index":322,"end_time":1655.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1646.29,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Yeah.","index":323,"end_time":1655.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1655.33,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Because she truly did not start Nina until before the holiday break.","index":324,"end_time":1660.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1656.45,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"So, yeah, we recognize that this is a big shift, but we''re just glad to have caught it now, you know, while we''re in this stage of giving feedback and making changes rather than like.","index":325,"end_time":1674.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1660.8,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"You know, after the launch.","index":326,"end_time":1675.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1674.52,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":327,"end_time":1677.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1676.72,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And I think it''s one of the features that''s really.","index":328,"end_time":1679.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1677.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"I mean, it''s interesting to see, but it''s also easier to maybe manage once you see how Elementor works and you''ve worked within, you know, like a couple of months and then you know all the functionalities and you know that, like, what can go wrong, what cannot and.","index":329,"end_time":1694,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.92,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, totally great.","index":330,"end_time":1697.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1694,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"I think that''s all.","index":331,"end_time":1704.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1703.24,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"And for the headings, for the spaces, for the headings, I will tell them to just look at the one that you said in the brand guidelines.","index":332,"end_time":1718.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1711.96,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"That''s the correct one.","index":333,"end_time":1720.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1718.8,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Oh, let me send you, because I did make some edits to the brand guidelines.","index":334,"end_time":1731.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1722.85,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"There it is.","index":335,"end_time":1739.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1738.45,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Sorry, have to find them.","index":336,"end_time":1753.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1752.65,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Just sent.","index":337,"end_time":1778.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.5,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Just so you guys have that.","index":338,"end_time":1782.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1780.9,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"But yeah, like how it''s laid out in.","index":339,"end_time":1800.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1797.71,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"On page 20.","index":340,"end_time":1801.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1800.19,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"That''s kind of what we''re looking for is just not quite so much space in between them.","index":341,"end_time":1805.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1801.39,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Good.","index":342,"end_time":1822.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1822.46,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"I think we''re good.","index":343,"end_time":1823.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1822.62,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Wonderful.","index":344,"end_time":1827.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1827.18,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Okay.","index":345,"end_time":1831.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1830.86,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Thank you, Nina.","index":346,"end_time":1832.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1831.38,"speaker_name":"Kyley"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":347,"end_time":1833.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1832.7,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Thank you so much.","index":348,"end_time":1834.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1833.74,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"Have a good day.","index":349,"end_time":1835.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1834.58,"speaker_name":"Jenny B."},{"text":"You as well.","index":350,"end_time":1836.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1835.58,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Bye.","index":351,"end_time":1836.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1836.38,"speaker_name":"Nina Belina"},{"text":"Stay warm.","index":352,"end_time":1837.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1836.94,"speaker_name":"Kyley"}],"dateString":"2026-01-15T16:49:01.000Z","host_email":null,"meeting_link":null,"participants":[],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF18YYJQDFXTMPXR0034RKPP","organizer_email":"nina.belina@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Removed animation to improve readability and reduce page load concerns flagged by demand gen lead.","Standardized tile sizes and line spacing globally to ensure uniform visual presentation across pages.","Decided to eliminate orange image borders per design feedback; stroke must be added manually if reused.","Established color accent guidelines: orange, green, or gray applied based on content proximity and context.","Confirmed brand guideline updates will inform heading spacing adjustments to improve layout consistency."],"highlights":[{"quote":"It is cool, but our demand gen leader is a little worried about the readability.","speaker":"Kyley"},{"quote":"I would prioritize designers a UX designers pov, to be honest.","speaker":"Jenny B."},{"quote":"I will tell the developers to put the dots until we see, you know, if we want to shorten them or not.","speaker":"Nina Belina"}],"topics":["design","delivery","visuals"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-21T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website Design and User Experience Improvements**\n\nThe team decided to remove background animations and standardize visual elements to improve readability and page load times.\n\n- **The animation in the background will be eliminated and replaced with a static orange accent line and desaturated background colors** to enhance text readability and reduce page load time concerns raised by the demand generation leader (05:44)  \n    - Developers initially liked the animation, but the team prioritized clarity and performance  \n    - The static design improves accessibility and user focus on content  \n    - Implementation will involve developers adjusting the existing design within the next development cycle  \n    - Expected impact includes faster page loads and better user engagement metrics due to clearer text visibility\n\n- **Uniform tile sizes and consistent styling will be enforced across all featured resource sections, including pluralizing resource categories like “case studies,” “ebooks,” and “webinars”** (07:32)  \n    - Tiles currently vary in size due to differing text lengths, complicating management  \n    - The team plans to set maximum text length or use ellipses to maintain uniformity  \n    - Consistent tile size supports a cleaner, more professional look, improving user experience  \n    - This will standardize the visual hierarchy and reduce cognitive load on visitors\n\n- **The orange border stroke around images will be removed from all product images following UX designer Brianna’s preference, while accent lines in orange or green may remain on page edges** (15:18)  \n    - Borders created by designers do not scale with images and complicate resolution issues  \n    - Accent lines that touch product images will be solid, not dotted, to align with brand feedback  \n    - Removing borders reduces visual clutter and highlights product imagery more naturally  \n    - This change balances design aesthetics with practical image quality concerns\n\n- **Background lines behind text will be desaturated gray rather than orange, with orange accents placed behind images or along page edges only** to maintain text clarity (19:09)  \n    - Orange behind text reduces readability, so desaturated gray backgrounds will be used consistently  \n    - Accent lines will frame images or page sections without interfering with copy  \n    - Gradient masks may be applied to static backgrounds to enhance focus on text areas  \n    - The dev team will assess impact on page speed before finalizing implementation\n\n## **Image Quality and Resource Asset Management**\n\nAddressing image resolution problems and establishing guidelines for consistent, high-quality visuals is critical for brand presentation.\n\n- **Many images used on the site suffer from low resolution and graininess, partly due to layered effects, prompting a directive to replace or improve image assets** (11:40)  \n    - Higher resolution images were uploaded but effects like heat maps degraded quality  \n    - Developers will experiment with different layering techniques to preserve image clarity  \n    - Improved images will boost professionalism and user trust on key pages  \n    - This effort aligns with maintaining brand standards and visual consistency\n\n- **Adobe Stock links have been provided for replacing industry page images, allowing easy access to high-quality photos while ensuring consistent theming across pages** (25:46)  \n    - The energy and utilities pages already use updated images featuring solar panels and infrastructure  \n    - This approach enables scalable image updates across all industry pages  \n    - Using licensed stock photos reduces risk and speeds up content refresh cycles  \n    - It also supports a unified look and feel, which enhances brand recognition\n\n## **Content and Typography Standardization**\n\nThe team prioritized text clarity and consistency, instituting global styling updates across CTAs, headings, and resource labels.\n\n- **All CTAs across headers and footers have been bolded to achieve a modern and unified appearance, improving visibility and clickability** (23:19)  \n    - Previously, CTA text was inconsistent, appearing as regular font in some areas  \n    - Bold CTAs create stronger visual calls to action, supporting conversion goals  \n    - The team agreed to keep current CTA sizes as they are effective  \n    - This change reflects a broader push to modernize site typography for better engagement\n\n- **Typography lines and accent colors will vary globally, using orange, green, or gray depending on context, with solid lines preferred over dotted ones for better visual flow** (17:15)  \n    - Colored accents may run the full page height and touch product images to align with designer feedback  \n    - This flexible approach balances visual interest with legibility  \n    - The team will prioritize implementing what is feasible within current development constraints  \n    - These decisions follow Jenny Vance’s UX perspective, ensuring design and function align\n\n- **Spacing around headers, particularly H2s, will be reduced according to updated brand guidelines to tighten layout and improve page flow** (19:09)  \n    - Excessive space above and below headers currently breaks visual continuity  \n    - The updated spacing will better group related content for easier scanning  \n    - Developers will follow the layout specifications from brand guidelines page 20  \n    - Improved spacing supports a cleaner, more engaging user experience\n\n## **Process Alignment and Team Coordination**\n\nFeedback and process changes were implemented early to avoid costly rework post-launch and ensure cross-team alignment.\n\n- **Christine, the new marketing leader, identified critical design issues during early dev reviews, prompting pre-launch fixes that improve site quality** (27:35)  \n    - Her fresh perspective caught problems that previous team members missed  \n    - Early detection avoids expensive post-launch corrections and preserves brand reputation  \n    - This highlights the value of cross-functional review and fresh eyes on projects  \n    - The team remains open to continuous feedback as development progresses\n\n- **The development team will assess feasibility and impact of design changes such as static lines and gradient masks, balancing aesthetics with performance** (21:18)  \n    - Technical considerations like page speed influence final design decisions  \n    - Developers will provide guidance to ensure changes are practical and maintain user experience  \n    - This collaborative approach aligns design goals with system capabilities  \n    - It ensures the site remains fast and accessible while looking polished\n\n- **A global approach to styling, image treatment, and typography will be maintained through centralized brand guidelines and developer communication** (27:35)  \n    - Brand guideline updates have been shared to maintain consistency across pages  \n    - Developers and designers will coordinate to keep visual elements uniform  \n    - This reduces confusion and streamlines future updates  \n    - Clear documentation supports smoother workflows and faster turnarounds","outline":null,"keywords":["website redesign","animation removal","image quality","typography","brand guidelines","UX design"],"overview":"- **Website Design Changes:** Background animations will be removed for static designs to enhance readability and page loading time.\n\n- **Uniform Resource Tiles:** Tile size and styling will be standardized for improved management and user experience across resource sections.\n\n- **Image Quality Improvements:** Low-resolution images will be replaced, ensuring high-quality visuals for better brand representation on the site.\n\n- **Updated CTAs and Typography:** CTAs will be bolded for visibility; typography will adjust spacing and color based on context to enhance clarity.\n\n- **Early Feedback Implementation:** New marketing leader''s insights led to pre-launch design fixes, reducing costly post-launch corrections and improving site quality.\n\n- **Centralized Brand Guidelines:** Consistent styling and images maintained through clear documentation, ensuring smooth updates across all site pages.","action_items":"\n**Nina Belina**\nRemove all animated background lines and replace with static solid orange accent lines and desaturated backgrounds as a priority (05:44)\nCoordinate with developers to standardize rectangle sizes and apply truncation with dots for long text blocks on Camp Personas (07:10)\nEnsure all featured resource labels are pluralized consistently and that the tile styles match the preferred uniform style with varied accent colors (07:32)\nWork with developers to improve image quality by removing any heatmap effects and upload high-resolution images uniformly across pages (11:40)\nRemove orange strokes on all images and screenshots globally except on icons/text tiles, as per UX designers’ preference; confirm if drop shadows are necessary (15:18)\nImplement solid colored accent lines that align with product images but avoid placing color accents behind text for improved readability (18:30)\nAdjust header spacing to align with updated brand guidelines ensuring less spacing above and below headers as shown on page 20 of brand doc (19:09)\nApply desaturation and possible gradient masks on full backgrounds to improve text readability without compromising page load times (20:58)\nReplace or update blog page image styles with bigger images for single blog posts; discontinue busy tile styles (21:40)\nRemove four blocks on Camp Personas and confirm correct text removals; ensure all CTAs use 700 Bold font weight including headers and footers (23:19)\nReview and apply Adobe stock photos for industry pages, particularly energy and utilities, using provided links for consistency (25:46)\nCollaborate with devs to finalize implementation of all these changes and ensure they align with the expectations of the marketing team and new leader (27:35)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"98dbb348-b861-47ad-a928-b9a31926c113","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
    '2026-01-21 12:56:30.706111+00',
    '2026-01-21 12:56:30.706111+00'
  )
  RETURNING meeting_id, contract_id
)
INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Encamp // Website Feedback: Nina Belina and Kyley Crews (Jenny B.)',
  '## **Website Design and User Experience Improvements**

The team decided to remove background animations and standardize visual elements to improve readability and page load times.

- **The animation in the background will be eliminated and replaced with a static orange accent line and desaturated background colors** to enhance text readability and reduce page load time concerns raised by the demand generation leader (05:44)  
    - Developers initially liked the animation, but the team prioritized clarity and performance  
    - The static design improves accessibility and user focus on content  
    - Implementation will involve developers adjusting the existing design within the next development cycle  
    - Expected impact includes faster page loads and better user engagement metrics due to clearer text visibility

- **Uniform tile sizes and consistent styling will be enforced across all featured resource sections, including pluralizing resource categories like “case studies,” “ebooks,” and “webinars”** (07:32)  
    - Tiles currently vary in size due to differing text lengths, complicating management  
    - The team plans to set maximum text length or use ellipses to maintain uniformity  
    - Consistent tile size supports a cleaner, more professional look, improving user experience  
    - This will standardize the visual hierarchy and reduce cognitive load on visitors

- **The orange border stroke around images will be removed from all product images following UX designer Brianna’s preference, while accent lines in orange or green may remain on page edges** (15:18)  
    - Borders created by designers do not scale with images and complicate resolution issues  
    - Accent lines that touch product images will be solid, not dotted, to align with brand feedback  
    - Removing borders reduces visual clutter and highlights product imagery more naturally  
    - This change balances design aesthetics with practical image quality concerns

- **Background lines behind text will be desaturated gray rather than orange, with orange accents placed behind images or along page edges only** to maintain text clarity (19:09)  
    - Orange behind text reduces readability, so desaturated gray backgrounds will be used consistently  
    - Accent lines will frame images or page sections without interfering with copy  
    - Gradient masks may be applied to static backgrounds to enhance focus on text areas  
    - The dev team will assess impact on page speed before finalizing implementation

## **Image Quality and Resource Asset Management**

Addressing image resolution problems and establishing guidelines for consistent, high-quality visuals is critical for brand presentation.

- **Many images used on the site suffer from low resolution and graininess, partly due to layered effects, prompting a directive to replace or improve image assets** (11:40)  
    - Higher resolution images were uploaded but effects like heat maps degraded quality  
    - Developers will experiment with different layering techniques to preserve image clarity  
    - Improved images will boost professionalism and user trust on key pages  
    - This effort aligns with maintaining brand standards and visual consistency

- **Adobe Stock links have been provided for replacing industry page images, allowing easy access to high-quality photos while ensuring consistent theming across pages** (25:46)  
    - The energy and utilities pages already use updated images featuring solar panels and infrastructure  
    - This approach enables scalable image updates across all industry pages  
    - Using licensed stock photos reduces risk and speeds up content refresh cycles  
    - It also supports a unified look and feel, which enhances brand recognition

## **Content and Typography Standardization**

The team prioritized text clarity and consistency, instituting global styling updates across CTAs, headings, and resource labels.

- **All CTAs across headers and footers have been bolded to achieve a modern and unified appearance, improving visibility and clickability** (23:19)  
    - Previously, CTA text was inconsistent, appearing as regular font in some areas  
    - Bold CTAs create stronger visual calls to action, supporting conversion goals  
    - The team agreed to keep current CTA sizes as they are effective  
    - This change reflects a broader push to modernize site typography for better engagement

- **Typography lines and accent colors will vary globally, using orange, green, or gray depending on context, with solid lines preferred over dotted ones for better visual flow** (17:15)  
    - Colored accents may run the full page height and touch product images to align with designer feedback  
    - This flexible approach balances visual interest with legibility  
    - The team will prioritize implementing what is feasible within current development constraints  
    - These decisions follow Jenny Vance’s UX perspective, ensuring design and function align

- **Spacing around headers, particularly H2s, will be reduced according to updated brand guidelines to tighten layout and improve page flow** (19:09)  
    - Excessive space above and below headers currently breaks visual continuity  
    - The updated spacing will better group related content for easier scanning  
    - Developers will follow the layout specifications from brand guidelines page 20  
    - Improved spacing supports a cleaner, more engaging user experience

## **Process Alignment and Team Coordination**

Feedback and process changes were implemented early to avoid costly rework post-launch and ensure cross-team alignment.

- **Christine, the new marketing leader, identified critical design issues during early dev reviews, prompting pre-launch fixes that improve site quality** (27:35)  
    - Her fresh perspective caught problems that previous team members missed  
    - Early detection avoids expensive post-launch corrections and preserves brand reputation  
    - This highlights the value of cross-functional review and fresh eyes on projects  
    - The team remains open to continuous feedback as development progresses

- **The development team will assess feasibility and impact of design changes such as static lines and gradient masks, balancing aesthetics with performance** (21:18)  
    - Technical considerations like page speed influence final design decisions  
    - Developers will provide guidance to ensure changes are practical and maintain user experience  
    - This collaborative approach aligns design goals with system capabilities  
    - It ensures the site remains fast and accessible while looking polished

- **A global approach to styling, image treatment, and typography will be maintained through centralized brand guidelines and developer communication** (27:35)  
    - Brand guideline updates have been shared to maintain consistency across pages  
    - Developers and designers will coordinate to keep visual elements uniform  
    - This reduces confusion and streamlines future updates  
    - Clear documentation supports smoother workflows and faster turnarounds',
  '2026-01-15 16:49:01+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Remove all animated background lines and replace with static solid orange accent lines and desaturated backgrounds as a priority (05:44)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with developers to standardize rectangle sizes and apply truncation with dots for long text blocks on Camp Personas (07:10)","completed":false},{"text":"Ensure all featured resource labels are pluralized consistently and that the tile styles match the preferred uniform style with varied accent colors (07:32)","completed":false},{"text":"Work with developers to improve image quality by removing any heatmap effects and upload high-resolution images uniformly across pages (11:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Remove orange strokes on all images and screenshots globally except on icons/text tiles, as per UX designers’ preference; confirm if drop shadows are necessary (15:18)","completed":false},{"text":"Implement solid colored accent lines that align with product images but avoid placing color accents behind text for improved readability (18:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Adjust header spacing to align with updated brand guidelines ensuring less spacing above and below headers as shown on page 20 of brand doc (19:09)","completed":false},{"text":"Apply desaturation and possible gradient masks on full backgrounds to improve text readability without compromising page load times (20:58)","completed":false},{"text":"Replace or update blog page image styles with bigger images for single blog posts; discontinue busy tile styles (21:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Remove four blocks on Camp Personas and confirm correct text removals; ensure all CTAs use 700 Bold font weight including headers and footers (23:19)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and apply Adobe stock photos for industry pages, particularly energy and utilities, using provided links for consistency (25:46)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate with devs to finalize implementation of all these changes and ensure they align with the expectations of the marketing team and new leader (27:35)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: Techmode+New North (2026-01-20 20:00:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'b1f3ae44-0316-492e-aef1-bb260b814482',
    '2026-01-20 20:00:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KF9M61EM3G63FDFH1NSYAFM5',
    'Techmode+New North',
    '{"Christopher Quigley","Matthew Look","Lindsay Hall","Colin Costigan","Ryan Fisher"}'::text[],
    1970,
    'https://teams.microsoft.com/l/meetup-join/19:meeting_ODBmZWFjMWYtMWIxYi00NmZmLTgyMDEtOWFiZWJhYWEwYzVh@thread.v2/0?context={"Tid":"3801011d-e732-48ee-be2a-e499b1a29ba4","Oid":"e804fbe9-a623-4d26-a887-992e62fb92d1"}',
    '{"id":"01KF9M61EM3G63FDFH1NSYAFM5","title":"Techmode+New North","summary":{"notes":"## **SMB Landing Page and Campaign Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to create a dedicated **SMB landing page** emphasizing personalized, enterprise-level support for small to mid-sized businesses, avoiding terms like \"Enterprise\" to prevent misinterpretation (05:18).\n\n- **Matthew Look confirmed** the close rate is strong but drops significantly after **70+ seats**, highlighting the need to focus on SMBs with fewer users (05:45).\n    - They adjusted user ranges to **5 to 100 seats** to better target SMBs.\n    - The landing page will emphasize \"one call for all your needs\" with **live answer support**, appealing to SMBs seeking hassle-free service post-sale.\n    - Testimonials will be integrated from the homepage to build trust.\n    - This approach aims to differentiate from competitors who treat SMBs impersonally.\n\n- The **MSP search campaign and Microsoft campaign** are live with daily budgets of **$20 and $25**, respectively, but the **price offer PMAX campaign underperformed**, having generated only one low-quality lead, leading to plans for phasing it out (08:02).\n    - **Christopher Quigley noted** that the sole lead was unresponsive, reinforcing the decision to discontinue that campaign.\n    - Budget adjustments for ongoing campaigns will continue based on performance data.\n\n## **RingCentral and Competitor Landing Pages with Lead Capture**\n\nThe team is building a **RingCentral-specific landing page** with a quiz-style cost calculator designed to identify qualified leads by asking about contract dates, user counts, and pricing (12:33).\n\n- They acknowledged **Google search volume for \"RingCentral replacement\" and related terms is very low**, limiting paid campaign opportunities (10:17).\n    - **Matthew Look and Colin Costigan agreed** organic channels like email outreach, blogs, and SEO will be the primary traffic drivers.\n    - Colin will research **Microsoft Advertising’s search volume and restrictions** for RingCentral terms to explore alternatives.\n    - Early exploration of **ChatGPT-enabled ads** was mentioned as a future channel once available.\n\n- The quiz form is connected to **Gravity Forms via REST API** and successfully captures submissions, but **email notifications are not triggering**, blocking timely lead follow-up (14:12).\n    - Colin is tasked with diagnosing and fixing this notification issue, despite all settings appearing correct (18:08).\n    - The team plans to integrate form submissions with **HubSpot** for contact creation and notification once stable.\n    - They aim to create a **dynamic form template** to quickly replicate for multiple providers (e.g., Comcast), saving development time by using placeholders for page-specific data.\n\n- The landing pages will be linked with **blogs and email campaigns** to funnel visitors through multiple engagement steps, accommodating prospects at different sales funnel stages (21:42).\n\n## **Website AI Readiness and Blog Content Enhancements**\n\nThe team discussed improving the website’s **AI readiness and blog presentation**, focusing on varied post templates and image generation to enhance visual appeal and engagement (22:43).\n\n- Colin recommended **MidJourney for image generation**, citing its superior quality, quick generation of four options in under a minute, and ease of use despite billing through Discord (23:49).\n    - Lindsay will evaluate MidJourney versus alternatives like Banana Nano to decide on the best fit.\n    - The goal is to provide at least **three different blog post templates** to avoid uniformity and improve user experience.\n\n- Colin is exploring technical feasibility to support **multiple blog post templates or resource-type-specific layouts** in WordPress, enabling richer content variation (25:04).\n    - This change is intended to improve content differentiation and reader engagement without major platform overhaul.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Technical Issues**\n\nThe team encountered technical hurdles with **form notification emails** despite correct configuration, motivating a deeper dive by Colin to resolve the issue urgently (14:12).\n\n- The form submissions are visible in Gravity Forms but fail to send alerts to marketing, causing a bottleneck in lead response.\n- Integration with HubSpot for automatic contact creation and notifications is planned post-fix to streamline lead management.\n- They discussed using **dynamic placeholders in the form code** to avoid duplicating forms for each provider, improving maintainability and reducing development time.\n\n## **Campaign Performance and Market Insights**\n\nCurrent campaigns show mixed results, prompting strategic shifts.\n\n- The **MSP and Microsoft ads** have modest daily budgets and mostly stable performance, but the **PMAX price offer campaign is ineffective**, prompting plans to discontinue it (08:19).\n- Bing ads for Microsoft currently have **only one click and no form submissions**, with a cost of just **5 cents**, indicating low engagement but minimal expense (30:24).\n- The team recognizes the **lower competition in Bing ads**, offering a less crowded space for outreach despite low volume.\n- They acknowledge challenges with **search term volume and ad approval on Google and Microsoft**, particularly for replacement keywords of competitors like RingCentral.\n\n## **Strategic Vision and Next Steps**\n\nThe team is aligning on a multi-pronged approach combining **targeted landing pages, organic content, and email campaigns** to capture SMB leads and compete effectively in a constrained paid search environment.\n\n- Matthew’s vision is to build out **multiple provider-specific pages with integrated cost calculators**, linked to blogs and email outreach, to guide prospects progressively through the funnel (20:23).\n- Colin and Lindsay will focus on fixing form notifications, exploring HubSpot integration, and enabling dynamic form replication to accelerate page rollouts.\n- Keyword research and platform-specific ad term viability checks for Google and Microsoft will inform ongoing ad spend and targeting adjustments.\n- Content strategy includes enhancing blog templates and visuals with AI-generated images to boost engagement and SEO performance.","outline":null,"keywords":["SMB landing page","RingCentral","Gravity Forms","digital marketing campaigns","blog templates","AI image generation"],"overview":"- **SMB Landing Page Focus:** New page emphasizes personalized support for SMBs of 5-100 seats, with trust-building testimonials.\n- **Campaign Results:** MSP ($20) and Microsoft ($25) campaigns are ongoing, while PMAX campaign will be discontinued due to poor performance.\n- **RingCentral Page Development:** A RingCentral landing page with a lead-capturing quiz is underway, pivoting to organic channels for traffic.\n- **Technical Fixes Needed:** Form notifications are failing; integration with HubSpot is planned post-resolution for lead management efficiency.\n- **Content Strategy Enhancement:** Team aims to develop multiple blog templates and visuals using AI tools for improved engagement and SEO.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nInvestigate and resolve Gravity Forms email notification issues on WordPress (14:40)\nConduct keyword research to confirm search volume and advertising viability for RingCentral replacement terms on Microsoft platform (10:55)\nCheck feasibility of dynamic, single form usage with placeholder titles to reduce duplicated coding for provider-specific landing pages (20:55)\nExplore new WordPress post types or templates to allow multiple blog post templates for varied layouts (24:45)\n\n**Matthew Look**\nDevelop multiple landing pages similar to RingCentral cost savings calculator for other providers such as Comcast (20:25)\nIncorporate new landing pages into blogs and email campaigns to drive traffic (21:40)\n\n**Lindsay Hall**\nCheck out Banana Nano for AI image generation as a potential tool for blog images (23:44)\nCoordinate blog post template needs and communicate requirements to Colin for development (24:00)\n\n**Unassigned**\nMaintain focus on messaging emphasizing comprehensive customer support and ''one-call'' solution post-sale for SMB clients to enhance value proposition (06:38)\n"},"duration":32.84000015258789,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"id":1,"name":"Matthew Look"},{"id":2,"name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"id":3,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":4,"name":"Ryan Fisher"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Well, she''s got a big lipoma, big tumor too, that gets in her way, mobility and everything like that.","index":0,"end_time":9.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.08,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So that makes it extra challenging.","index":1,"end_time":11.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":9.68,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"So.","index":2,"end_time":11.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":11.4,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Yeah, that sounds.","index":3,"end_time":12.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":11.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, that sucks.","index":4,"end_time":13.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":12.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Nobody likes this cold weather, especially the elderly.","index":5,"end_time":16.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":14.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Even elderly animals.","index":6,"end_time":18.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":16.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":7,"end_time":19.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":19.2,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"I don''t know if I count as elderly yet, but I don''t like this weather anyways.","index":8,"end_time":24.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":20.24,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Depends on how I get out.","index":9,"end_time":25.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":24.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Some days I feel elderly.","index":10,"end_time":26.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":25.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Definitely have those.","index":11,"end_time":30.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":28.08,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":12,"end_time":31.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":30.96,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''ll do a sleep wrong and I''m a wreck the next day.","index":13,"end_time":34.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":32.56,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like, oh, my God, my freaking shoulder kills me.","index":14,"end_time":37.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":34.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m glad that happened.","index":15,"end_time":41.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":39.6,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Are we talking about body aches?","index":16,"end_time":45.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":43.68,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I have those.","index":17,"end_time":45.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":45.04,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, I can.","index":18,"end_time":46.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":45.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can speak on this topic.","index":19,"end_time":47.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":46.28,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yep.","index":20,"end_time":48.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":48.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s my shoulder.","index":21,"end_time":50.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":49.12,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s my shoulder.","index":22,"end_time":51.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":50.56,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yep.","index":23,"end_time":52.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":51.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I strained my neck a few months ago in my neck and back here.","index":24,"end_time":60.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":53.99,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And ever since then, if I lay the wrong way or hold my arm in the wrong position for too long, the whole thing either gets itchy or goes tingling because I have pinched nerves going on up here and I just cannot get it.","index":25,"end_time":72.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":60.55,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"So if you ever see me stick my arm out like this and do weird motions, it''s because I''m trying to get my arm to come back to life.","index":26,"end_time":77.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":72.59,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You''re not flexing.","index":27,"end_time":78.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.95,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No, I''m just trying to get the blood moving again.","index":28,"end_time":82.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":79.32,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":29,"end_time":83.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Your arms going numb with.","index":30,"end_time":86.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":83.24,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"With some of your other issues is not a.","index":31,"end_time":89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":87.08,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You''re like, oh, if I did it just go to sleep or am I dying?","index":32,"end_time":91.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.08,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Don''t know.","index":33,"end_time":94.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":93.64,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Every day is a fun adventure, right?","index":34,"end_time":96.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.36,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Don''t know.","index":35,"end_time":99.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":98.76,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Let me see if Ryan''s joining.","index":36,"end_time":104.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I know he''s got a lot going on.","index":37,"end_time":105.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":104.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Busy, busy.","index":38,"end_time":108.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":107.21,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Where are you, Colin?","index":39,"end_time":127.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What''s going on, buddy?","index":40,"end_time":128.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.97,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You know, trying to understand how accurate the Euro system is versus everything else that gets used for measuring weather.","index":41,"end_time":139.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":131.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m sure you guys are following this crazy storm.","index":42,"end_time":142.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":139.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, no, there''s a.","index":43,"end_time":145.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":143.54,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"No, we just got like a storm.","index":44,"end_time":148.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":146.5,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, we got like a polar vortex sitting on top of us, man.","index":45,"end_time":151.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":148.14,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s like 9 degrees blowing snow.","index":46,"end_time":155.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.46,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s a frigging mess here.","index":47,"end_time":156.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":155.62,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You probably saw it on the news.","index":48,"end_time":158.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.3,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You see our 100, our 100 car pile up.","index":49,"end_time":160.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":158.34,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin, I did not made national news.","index":50,"end_time":163.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":160.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"West Michigan.","index":51,"end_time":164.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":163.97,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, 100 over 100 cars just, you know, people don''t slow down and they''re like, hey, I can''t see what''s going on in front of me.","index":52,"end_time":171.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":164.77,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I''m going to continue it full speed ahead.","index":53,"end_time":173.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":171.29,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"And then they all just crash into each other.","index":54,"end_time":176.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":174.13,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, Yeah.","index":55,"end_time":178.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":177.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I see some that say we''re going to get like 4 or 5 inches and then others that say 16 to 22 inches.","index":56,"end_time":184.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":178.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like that''s quite a difference.","index":57,"end_time":186.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":184.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And also luck would have it that it''s my daughter''s first birthday party this weekend, so probably gonna have to cancel that.","index":58,"end_time":195.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":187.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That sucks.","index":59,"end_time":196.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.1,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":197.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.14,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You''re in Maryland.","index":61,"end_time":198.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":197.78,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We are, yeah.","index":62,"end_time":200.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":199.14,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You guys aren''t so good at driving in the snow and like we''re supposed to be good at driving in the snow, but we''re just up here talking about our 100 car pileup, so.","index":63,"end_time":209.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":201.7,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, better safe than sorry.","index":64,"end_time":212.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.78,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Ryan''s on it''s.","index":65,"end_time":213.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"What''s kind of funny is I''m on here with Colin and I get a new north past due invoice.","index":66,"end_time":217.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.94,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I just came through right when I''m talking to Colin.","index":67,"end_time":219.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":217.22,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Wolves.","index":68,"end_time":221.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":220.46,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It''s the first.","index":69,"end_time":222.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.74,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Just so you know, I did send it to the person to pay it.","index":70,"end_time":226.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":223.18,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"They did not do it.","index":71,"end_time":227.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":226.82,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Oh no.","index":72,"end_time":228.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":227.98,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I sent over a nasty email asking.","index":73,"end_time":231.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":229.02,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"You know that man, I''ll always vouch for you.","index":74,"end_time":235.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":234.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we pay on time.","index":75,"end_time":236.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":235.78,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We pay.","index":76,"end_time":237.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.98,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I know that''s important to me.","index":77,"end_time":242.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.27,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I try to live up to the expectation of what I expect from my clients.","index":78,"end_time":246.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.43,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Well, I appreciate that.","index":79,"end_time":247.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":246.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s something else that I was going to say, but I can''t remember.","index":80,"end_time":250.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":247.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, that it''s also.","index":81,"end_time":253.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":252.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s supposed to be like frozen after it snows for like 10 days.","index":82,"end_time":256.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":253.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s like between 1 and 10 degrees, man.","index":83,"end_time":259.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":256.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Don''t die.","index":84,"end_time":260.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":260.15,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"You guys aren''t.","index":85,"end_time":262.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":261.59,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Everything I''m seeing is like hypothermia warnings like don''t be outside for extended periods of time.","index":86,"end_time":267.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":262.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh no.","index":87,"end_time":269.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":268.7,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Might have to just let the dog do her business in that indoors and clean it up.","index":88,"end_time":274.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.94,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Yeah, you know he does that ever since we had a baby anyways because he no longer sleeps in our room, so.","index":89,"end_time":281.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":274.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So he''s angry with you.","index":90,"end_time":282.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":281.5,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah, his, his, his pushback is to go to the bathroom in the house at like 1 in the morning.","index":91,"end_time":290.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":282.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What a day.","index":92,"end_time":291.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":291.18,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"Oh man, I love that.","index":93,"end_time":293.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":292.38,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"All right, well, let''s get into it.","index":94,"end_time":296.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":295.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you asked us to build an SMB page.","index":95,"end_time":299.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":296.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I didn''t ask.","index":96,"end_time":300.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":299.88,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"No, just kidding, Lindsey.","index":97,"end_time":301.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.6,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I did.","index":98,"end_time":302.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I remember now that you.","index":99,"end_time":303.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"After you and I talked about it.","index":100,"end_time":304.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.44,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I remember that.","index":101,"end_time":305.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":304.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m glad I have that.","index":102,"end_time":306.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":305.08,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"It was not to change our landing page.","index":103,"end_time":310.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.68,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It was build an SMB landing page.","index":104,"end_time":311.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.2,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, new one.","index":105,"end_time":313.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":311.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I have that here.","index":106,"end_time":315.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":315,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I have a few line like enterprise experience.","index":107,"end_time":318.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":315.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":108,"end_time":318.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Size for growing teams so that it feels like enterprise level support, but not only dedicated for enterprise level level companies.","index":109,"end_time":325.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I thought you would really like this one.","index":110,"end_time":327.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":325.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"A business phone system.","index":111,"end_time":328.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":327.29,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That doesn''t treat you like a number.","index":112,"end_time":329.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":328.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I like that.","index":113,"end_time":331.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":330.13,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t like Enterprise.","index":114,"end_time":332.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":331.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I want Enterprise not on the page.","index":115,"end_time":333.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":332.25,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay, so let''s just.","index":116,"end_time":336.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.21,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t want people to scan it, misinterpret it.","index":117,"end_time":338.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.13,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re going to go with SMB pride.","index":118,"end_time":341.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":339.41,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We''re pride.","index":119,"end_time":342.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":341.73,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"We''re proud to be small.","index":120,"end_time":343.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":342.33,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":121,"end_time":344.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":343.89,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"I did reduce some of those numbers a little.","index":122,"end_time":347.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.17,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"There were some duplicates.","index":123,"end_time":348.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.97,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"There were some other bullshit in those numbers we first looked at.","index":124,"end_time":351.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":348.93,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Lindsey.","index":125,"end_time":351.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.01,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":126,"end_time":352.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":351.84,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I got all revised numbers and our close rate is actually pretty freaking good.","index":127,"end_time":357.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":352.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Our close rate is very good.","index":128,"end_time":358.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":357.12,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"But we do fall off at 70 plus.","index":129,"end_time":360.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.48,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":130,"end_time":361.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":360.72,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Still.","index":131,"end_time":362.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s still a thing.","index":132,"end_time":363.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":362.32,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So I had five to 100 users.","index":133,"end_time":367.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":364.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we going to replace that with seats?","index":134,"end_time":368.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you''d prefer seats?","index":135,"end_time":369.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":368.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that the right.","index":136,"end_time":371.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":370.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s fine.","index":137,"end_time":373.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":372.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":138,"end_time":375.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":373.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we got this stuff in here, and then I have a comment here where we''ll just load in the testimonials that are on the homepage, but I''ll send this over to you guys to review.","index":139,"end_time":384.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":375.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":140,"end_time":385,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":384.56,"speaker_name":"Lindsay Hall"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":141,"end_time":385.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385,"speaker_name":"Christopher Quigley"},{"text":"All right.","index":142,"end_time":388.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":387.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":143,"end_time":388.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":388.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t.","index":144,"end_time":389.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.8,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I don''t see it, but.","index":145,"end_time":390.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":389.64,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Colin, take a look at it.","index":146,"end_time":391.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":390.28,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We want to be like, we.","index":147,"end_time":392.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We want something in there about like, we''re like one call for all your needs.","index":148,"end_time":398.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":392.64,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like after the sale, you call us, we take care of everything.","index":149,"end_time":401.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":398.44,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":150,"end_time":401.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":401.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Live answer.","index":151,"end_time":402.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":401.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Somebody will take care of you.","index":152,"end_time":404.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":403.04,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"That''s.","index":153,"end_time":404.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.12,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We want to.","index":154,"end_time":404.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.36,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"We really want to push that home to those SMB teams.","index":155,"end_time":406.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":404.76,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Like, this isn''t.","index":156,"end_time":408.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":406.92,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"This goes off of your plate.","index":157,"end_time":409.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.16,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":158,"end_time":410.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":410.09,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":159,"end_time":410.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":410.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":160,"end_time":411.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":410.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just paid you guys.","index":161,"end_time":416.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":415.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"It''s paid.","index":162,"end_time":416.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.05,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"So perfect.","index":163,"end_time":417.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":416.73,"speaker_name":"Matthew Look"},{"text":"I''ll dive further into, like where I started with the business phone system that doesn''t treat you like a number.","index":164,"end_time":421.85,"sp