    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86093865913?pwd=ajXSuerDGmcROjfezSWYYGsa7iPOWd.1',
    '{"id":"01KEVVT7AQX3SKV91VJ207F0TY","title":"PTO Exchange Weekly","summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot Audit and Workflow Optimization**\n\nThe team is finalizing a detailed **HubSpot audit** to streamline workflows and improve lead nurturing by Thursday, aiming for better automation and reduced manual work (06:38).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** is completing the audit and will propose removing redundant fields and adding new options to improve data flow and automation logic.\n- The audit will clarify how sequences handle different lead statuses, especially for healthcare cold leads, ensuring automated sequences align with realistic outreach tactics.\n- A key focus is automating unenrollment from nurture sequences when a lead owner logs activity, reducing manual task loads for sales reps like **Stephanie Lucchesi**.\n- The audit will address confusing overlaps in workflows, such as leads enrolled in nurture emails after demo requests without proper unenroll triggers, exemplified by the **Valerie Cawthron** case.\n\n## **LinkedIn Outreach and Messaging Strategy**\n\nCurrent manual LinkedIn outreach shows low engagement, prompting plans to automate and overhaul messaging to boost efficiency and responses (17:35).\n\n- **Stephanie Lucchesi** noted that **15–20%** of LinkedIn connection updates are outdated, but updating contacts without response is inefficient.\n- The team agreed to develop industry-specific, automated LinkedIn messages with fallback general messaging focused on the **PTO benchmark report** to increase outreach effectiveness.\n- **Josh Reinhard** highlighted the low conversion rate from manual LinkedIn outreach, with few meaningful interactions despite high connection volumes.\n- Automating LinkedIn outreach will free up sales resources and reduce redundant manual effort while maintaining personalized messaging through predefined templates.\n\n## **Meeting Cadence and Internal Collaboration**\n\nThe team is restructuring meetings to integrate the new fractional CMO and improve communication efficiency by consolidating existing calls (08:04).\n\n- The new **fractional CMO, Carmen**, started and will join Monday marketing meetings, replacing a smaller internal sync.\n- The plan is to hold a combined **Monday meeting from 12:30 to 1:00 PM Pacific Time**, where Colin and Carmen both participate, streamlining updates and reducing redundant calls.\n- Colin is adjusting his schedule to accommodate this while ensuring no conflicts with existing standing meetings.\n- This consolidation aims to enhance strategic alignment across marketing, PR, and sales teams by including key stakeholders in one forum.\n\n## **Demo Request and Lead Follow-up Process**\n\nThe current demo request process has gaps causing leads to remain in automated sequences despite manual scheduling, requiring process refinement to avoid mixed messaging (20:14).\n\n- Leads who manually schedule demos outside the automated **Calendly** system, like **Valerie Cawthron**, are not properly unenrolled from nurture workflows, creating confusion.\n- The team agreed to build logic into workflows that automatically unenroll leads upon logged contact activity from the assigned sales rep, reducing manual unenrollment needs.\n- The existing timing of a **2-hour delay** before sending nurture emails after page views is confirmed as appropriate to allow reps to reach out first.\n- The audit will include recommendations to better sync demo request workflows with manual scheduling habits to improve lead experience and internal efficiency.\n\n## **Marketing Automation Overlap and AI-Powered Outreach**\n\nThere is overlap between the in-house automation and the third-party **11X AI tool**, which sends personalized emails to website visitors, requiring alignment to avoid prospect confusion (28:09).\n\n- The **11X tool** researches visitors and sends customized emails based on LinkedIn and company info, paused currently to evaluate effectiveness.\n- Colin identified duplication between 11X sequences and the internal HubSpot workflows that enroll prospects shortly after site visits.\n- **Josh Reinhard** explained the AI tool’s value lies in personalized, short emails tailored to prospects, but running both campaigns risks overwhelming contacts.\n- The new CMO will review and coordinate these tools to optimize messaging, reduce redundancy, and improve conversion rates across outreach channels.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Audit","LinkedIn Outreach","Marketing Automation","Workflow Enrollment","11X AI Platform","Fractional CMO Integration"],"overview":"- **HubSpot Audit Completion:** Finalizing audit by Thursday to streamline workflows and enhance lead nurturing and automation.\n- **LinkedIn Outreach Plan:** Automating outreach to improve engagement; updating contacts inefficiently affects 15-20% of connection updates.\n- **Meeting Restructure:** Consolidating meetings with new fractional CMO to enhance communication and align marketing and sales strategies.\n- **Demo Request Gaps:** Addressing issues with manual demo scheduling to enhance workflow and reduce confusion in nurture sequences.\n- **AI Tool Overlap:** Reviewing duplication between HubSpot workflows and 11X AI tool for smarter, less overwhelming prospect outreach.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nComplete and share HubSpot audit results and proposed workflow improvements by end of day Wednesday; present on Thursday (06:19)\nInvestigate LinkedIn message disappearance issue with Valerie Cawthron and liaise with LinkedIn support if needed; share findings pre-Thursday meeting (15:11)\nDevelop automated messaging framework for LinkedIn cadences and email outreach sequences; present updates on Thursday (18:59)\nModify workflows to add automatic unenrollment triggers based on logged sales activity to reduce manual unenrollment (26:10)\nCoordinate with team and fractional CMO Carmen on meeting scheduling and integration into marketing meetings (08:04)\nIncorporate analysis of overlapping automation between 11X and HubSpot sequences into audit report with recommendations (28:09)\n\n**Stephanie Lucchesi**\nContinue LinkedIn outreach activities with current cadences; update only contacts that respond; monitor engagement and provide feedback for revamping messaging (11:50)\nFollow up with Valerie Cawthron via voicemail and email to confirm receipt of demo invites and clarify communication issues (16:07)\nMonitor potential further LinkedIn message issues affecting other contacts and report to Colin (17:04)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nFacilitate meeting scheduling coordination between Colin, Carmen, and internal marketing team; approve meeting consolidation plan after Carmen’s onboarding (08:04)\nOversee and ensure proper unenrollment from sequences for manually scheduled demos booked outside of Calendly; communicate with sales team about process (21:01)\nContinue evaluating integration and use of 11X platform; coordinate strategic decisions with fractional CMO and Colin (29:45)\n\n**Dan Igo**\nParticipate in marketing meetings and provide feedback on automation and outreach impacts (25:05)\n"},"duration":34.13999938964844,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"id":2,"name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"id":3,"name":"Dan Igo"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Josh.","index":0,"end_time":221.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":220.479,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":221.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":221.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s up, Colin?","index":2,"end_time":222.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":221.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":3,"end_time":223.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, how you doing?","index":4,"end_time":225.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Doing well.","index":5,"end_time":226.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":225.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Recovering from a long weekend.","index":6,"end_time":230.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And recovering.","index":7,"end_time":231.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":230.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, cramming five days into four.","index":8,"end_time":234.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":231.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yes, I know how that feels.","index":9,"end_time":238.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":234.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Were you guys closed yesterday?","index":10,"end_time":242.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":240.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I assume not.","index":11,"end_time":243.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":242.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We were not.","index":12,"end_time":244.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":244.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I got sick this weekend, so I was also kind of took some meetings yesterday and didn''t take others.","index":13,"end_time":256.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":247.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I''m probably cramming five days into four and a half.","index":14,"end_time":259.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":256.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":15,"end_time":260.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":259.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, everyone''s getting sick.","index":16,"end_time":262.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":260.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if you have, like, the flu or whatever''s been going around, but it took my ass.","index":17,"end_time":267.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":262.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I just.","index":18,"end_time":269.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":267.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We.","index":19,"end_time":270.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We had this.","index":20,"end_time":270.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":270.15,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Every year.","index":21,"end_time":273.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We do this long weekend for MLK day in, like, the mountains up here outside seattle.","index":22,"end_time":280.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":273.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It''s like 90 miles inland, and we go to this.","index":23,"end_time":286,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":280.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We get these, like, really big houses and do it with a bunch of families.","index":24,"end_time":290.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":286,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We had like six families under the same roof and 12 kids.","index":25,"end_time":294.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was like, what are the odds that I''m not going to get sick?","index":26,"end_time":297.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t know if you''re escaping that one.","index":27,"end_time":299.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":297.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"My and my youngest son always sleeps in our room.","index":28,"end_time":304.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This year he decided he wanted to sleep with the big kids in the bunk room.","index":29,"end_time":308.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''re like, he''s probably not going to make it.","index":30,"end_time":310.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":308.56,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"He''ll start there, get freaked out.","index":31,"end_time":313.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":311.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we took the room that was closest to the kids room, and of course he ended up sleeping like a champ.","index":32,"end_time":318.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":313.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And we got, you know, three or four hours of sleep each night because the kids were crazy or they wake up at, like, you know, one kid wakes up at 5:45, their whole room is up at 5:45.","index":33,"end_time":331.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":319.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yes.","index":34,"end_time":331.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":331.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not.","index":35,"end_time":334.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Not the best recipe for health.","index":36,"end_time":337.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"No, I don''t think that''s how kids are advertised.","index":37,"end_time":341.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know.","index":38,"end_time":341.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was a fun weekend, though.","index":39,"end_time":343.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":341.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Good.","index":40,"end_time":343.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, Steph.","index":41,"end_time":345.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":344.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey.","index":42,"end_time":345.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.31,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"How''s it going?","index":43,"end_time":346.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.67,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Good.","index":44,"end_time":346.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you?","index":45,"end_time":347.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":346.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":46,"end_time":348.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":347.79,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I gotta ask, do you prefer Steph or Stephanie?","index":47,"end_time":351.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":348.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I''ve seen both.","index":48,"end_time":351.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Steph is good.","index":49,"end_time":352.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":352.03,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Okay.","index":50,"end_time":353.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":353.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Stephanie is my professional name.","index":51,"end_time":355.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":353.79,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"But I feel like we''re.","index":52,"end_time":356.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":355.39,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"We''re friends.","index":53,"end_time":357.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":356.47,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"We are.","index":54,"end_time":357.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":357.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re best friends.","index":55,"end_time":359.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":56,"end_time":360.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":359.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I really only have a few questions, Josh.","index":57,"end_time":363.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":361.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We met Thursday, and so I had Friday, and then yesterday was.","index":58,"end_time":367.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":363.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was close.","index":59,"end_time":367.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I''ll.","index":60,"end_time":369.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll give you some updates on progress that we''ve made and kind of where we''re at.","index":61,"end_time":372.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then when I open it up to some questions from you guys, unless there was anything pressing that you wanted to start the call with.","index":62,"end_time":378.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":372.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, just a couple of things just to touch before we drop.","index":63,"end_time":382.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":379.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we start with.","index":64,"end_time":384.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":382.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":65,"end_time":385.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":384.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one hope Sounds like the bullet list that I got you this morning was sufficient.","index":66,"end_time":390.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":385.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and sorry for the short notice.","index":67,"end_time":393.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":391.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I just wasn''t realizing Rob was going to want that.","index":68,"end_time":397.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, no worries.","index":69,"end_time":398.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and if it was like any other than a holiday week craving five days into four, then I would have been able to get it to you faster.","index":70,"end_time":407.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":399.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"New problem.","index":71,"end_time":407.589,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So cool.","index":72,"end_time":409.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then for the HubSpot audit, I''m knee deep in that right now, so that should be wrapped up by end of day tomorrow.","index":73,"end_time":420.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":409.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So sharing updates with you guys on Thursday as well as like what the game plan is of how we attack it, making sure that you guys are on board with, hey, we think we should deprecate this field or add a new field here or a new option here, these workflows, etc.","index":74,"end_time":432.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":420.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''ll be in tandem with.","index":75,"end_time":434.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":433.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s not going to be the full message of what the email copy is.","index":76,"end_time":438.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":436.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to just make sure that the flow that I''m, that I''m thinking for like, okay, if they''re in healthcare and they went cold, this is the automatic sequence that they go into.","index":77,"end_time":447.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":439.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just want to clarify those with all of you guys.","index":78,"end_time":450.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":447.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll be sharing updates on those on Thursday.","index":79,"end_time":452.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":450.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are there.","index":80,"end_time":455.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":454.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have you had a chance to look at the web pages that we sent over?","index":81,"end_time":457.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":455.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not yet.","index":82,"end_time":458.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":458.16,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":83,"end_time":459.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":458.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, just keep me updated on that.","index":84,"end_time":462.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":461.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":85,"end_time":463.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":463.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Cool.","index":86,"end_time":464.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know one other thing that you mentioned also Josh was getting me involved in more internal meetings on your guys side.","index":87,"end_time":471.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to talk through how we can streamline.","index":88,"end_time":473.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We already have our two meetings a week.","index":89,"end_time":475.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":473.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not sure if maybe we remove this one earlier and substitute it with an internal meeting that you need me to join or what you''re kind of expecting there.","index":90,"end_time":483.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":475.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we hired our fractional CMO on Friday.","index":91,"end_time":488.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":484.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":92,"end_time":489.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":488.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And she''s starting today.","index":93,"end_time":492.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.73,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So we''re going to kind of give her like a week to like figure out what her plan is going to be and then start incorporating her into these meetings as well.","index":94,"end_time":503.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":492.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So since Sam left we like usually me, it would be like me, Rob, Sam and Kristen, who''s our PR person would meet for a half an hour every Monday, what Rob and I were just talking about, but we want to let Carmen like kind of get settled in and figure out was maybe we.","index":95,"end_time":525.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.25,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If you.","index":96,"end_time":525.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know if you have like what your schedule looks like on Mondays, but we have a 1230.","index":97,"end_time":533.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":525.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We were thinking either have our meeting go from 12 until 1245 and have you and Carmen both on that call together to replace that meeting and then have like steph And Dan and Dave, if he wants to join the Thursday meeting.","index":98,"end_time":549.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":533.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But Carmen will be on both now going forward all the time.","index":99,"end_time":551.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":549.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or do we want to do something else?","index":100,"end_time":555.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":552.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But that was, like, one of the things where I think is we kind of combine our Monday meeting into the bigger marketing.","index":101,"end_time":562.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":555.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":102,"end_time":563.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m all for consolidating.","index":103,"end_time":564.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I will say on Mondays, I have a standing call.","index":104,"end_time":568.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you were saying 12:45 Pacific time, I imagine, right?","index":105,"end_time":571.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":568.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m saying Pacific time.","index":106,"end_time":572.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":571.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":107,"end_time":572.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":572.38,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":108,"end_time":573.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":572.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So if that were to.","index":109,"end_time":575.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If that were to run for like, 30 minutes or even my section for 30 minutes.","index":110,"end_time":580.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":575.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So 12:30 Pacific to 1 Pacific.","index":111,"end_time":584.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":581.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can make that work on a weekly basis.","index":112,"end_time":586.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But after that, I am pretty much in meetings until the end of the day.","index":113,"end_time":589.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":586.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But could you start it at 3 Eastern Time?","index":114,"end_time":594.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":590.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"12 Pacific.","index":115,"end_time":594.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":116,"end_time":596.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"To replace this meeting.","index":117,"end_time":597.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Replay.","index":118,"end_time":599.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Basically replace this meeting.","index":119,"end_time":600.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":599.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, I know we''re meeting Tuesday, but, like, normally when we meet Monday.","index":120,"end_time":603.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":600.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":121,"end_time":604.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Meet from 12 until 1245 and incorporate the New north stuff into the larger team meeting.","index":122,"end_time":610.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":123,"end_time":610.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Marketing meeting.","index":124,"end_time":612.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":611.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I do have a call that''s standing right before this every week.","index":125,"end_time":617.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":613.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I could start at the same time as this every week.","index":126,"end_time":619.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or I could see if.","index":127,"end_time":621.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":620.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because that is an internal one every week.","index":128,"end_time":623.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":621.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I could see if that could move.","index":129,"end_time":624.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If it has to start at 12 Pacific instead of 12:30.","index":130,"end_time":630.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":625.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":131,"end_time":631.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Or we could meet from 12:15 until 12:30 to talk about anything non New north related.","index":132,"end_time":640.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":631.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s marketing.","index":133,"end_time":641.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":640.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then you just join at 12:30.","index":134,"end_time":643.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":641.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We could do that.","index":135,"end_time":644.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s what we''ll do.","index":136,"end_time":646.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If you''re available to join at 12:15 because your other meeting ends early or whatever.","index":137,"end_time":650.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":646.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Join whenever you want.","index":138,"end_time":651.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":650.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But then each week you just join at 12:30.","index":139,"end_time":654,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":140,"end_time":654.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds like a plan.","index":141,"end_time":655.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":654.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s like.","index":142,"end_time":656.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":655.92,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But again, we want to give Carmen the ability to tell us if that works for her also because, like, yeah.","index":143,"end_time":662.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":656.52,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So that''s potentially subject to change.","index":144,"end_time":665.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":663.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But I think that sounds like a good, good plan.","index":145,"end_time":668,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":146,"end_time":668.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":147,"end_time":669.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At some point, like, we''ll need to.","index":148,"end_time":673.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":670.96,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Once she kind of, like, gets her bearings, probably.","index":149,"end_time":676.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":673.17,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Probably schedule like an hour or two or so, you know?","index":150,"end_time":679.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":676.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":151,"end_time":680.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":679.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Nice.","index":152,"end_time":680.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Formal introduction.","index":153,"end_time":681.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":680.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Dive through everything we''ve done so far, what we''re setting up for the future, everything like that.","index":154,"end_time":685.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":681.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, definitely.","index":155,"end_time":686.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":685.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, like, we''ve spoken about your capabilities, but obviously you guys do a better job of explaining how you guys would work together than we have, so.","index":156,"end_time":695.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":157,"end_time":696.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":695.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":158,"end_time":697.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":696.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No problem at all.","index":159,"end_time":698.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":697.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":160,"end_time":700,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then the last thing I want to check is, and Steph, thank you for joining.","index":161,"end_time":703.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Any issues you''ve been running into with any of the automations or tasks assigned or anything like that.","index":162,"end_time":708.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":703.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I was just saying I had like a boatload of LinkedIn requests come through.","index":163,"end_time":718.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.64,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I was saying to Josh, I mean some of them probably like, I don''t know, 50, 15, 20% of them are their old organization and HubSpot.","index":164,"end_time":730.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":720.32,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"That''s been.","index":165,"end_time":731.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":730.49,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I was like updating all of them and I was saying, Josh, like I''m not gonna do that unless they respond.","index":166,"end_time":737.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":731.53,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I''m kind of keeping.","index":167,"end_time":739.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":737.93,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Unless you want me to like reach out to you guys.","index":168,"end_time":742.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":740.01,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"But I''m just.","index":169,"end_time":742.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":742.29,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"That''s not like a good use of my time to be like updating those unless we see like, you know, some sort of response from them.","index":170,"end_time":749.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":742.77,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"But I am going into LinkedIn, I am like doing the cadences.","index":171,"end_time":752.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":749.53,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I know we talked about kind of updating those, so hopeful we can maybe revamp those.","index":172,"end_time":758.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.85,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Because I was also mentioning to Josh that I''m doing some shorter.","index":173,"end_time":761.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.03,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":174,"end_time":762.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Outreach because I haven''t gotten any responses and you saw the number of connection requests that came in.","index":175,"end_time":768.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":762.31,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I would expect even just like.","index":176,"end_time":770.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.39,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Some little bit of jump through.","index":177,"end_time":772.949,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":771.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":178,"end_time":773.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":772.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":179,"end_time":773.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.35,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"But nothing yet.","index":180,"end_time":774.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":773.83,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So.","index":181,"end_time":775.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.87,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Okay.","index":182,"end_time":775.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":183,"end_time":775.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we can definitely talk about that on Thursday as well then.","index":184,"end_time":778.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":185,"end_time":779.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":779.11,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":186,"end_time":779.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":779.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that was.","index":187,"end_time":781.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":779.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Well, we did.","index":188,"end_time":784.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"She step.","index":189,"end_time":785.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.8,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Did have a specific issue.","index":190,"end_time":788.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":785.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that was weird that.","index":191,"end_time":791.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":789.36,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I don''t know.","index":192,"end_time":791.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That doesn''t make that much sense to me and I. I don''t know, might as well while we''re here.","index":193,"end_time":796,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":791.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But yeah.","index":194,"end_time":796.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was a demo request.","index":195,"end_time":801.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":799.92,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"It was a demo request initially.","index":196,"end_time":803.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yep.","index":197,"end_time":804.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":803.68,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"And I just called her.","index":198,"end_time":807.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":804.96,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I spoke to her on the phone, we had a conversation, she asked me to set up a call.","index":199,"end_time":813.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":807.64,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I like sent her an invite.","index":200,"end_time":815.69,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.77,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"She apparently didn''t receive my invite.","index":201,"end_time":819.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":817.21,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"And then she also screenshot like some messages she sent me on LinkedIn that when I opened my LinkedIn message with her, I have literally nothing in there.","index":202,"end_time":832.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":819.69,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":203,"end_time":833.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s this contact''s name?","index":204,"end_time":835.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Valerie.","index":205,"end_time":837.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":836.55,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"What''s her last name?","index":206,"end_time":838.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":837.67,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"It''s like.","index":207,"end_time":839.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":838.71,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah, C A W T H R O n. It''s actually Val B a L actually in LinkedIn it might be Valerie.","index":208,"end_time":852.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":840.87,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"In LinkedIn it''s Valerie.","index":209,"end_time":854.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It is Valerie.","index":210,"end_time":854.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":854.03,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":211,"end_time":855.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":854.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cawthron.","index":212,"end_time":856.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":855.19,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, I see her here.","index":213,"end_time":858.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":857.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"See a meeting that Gong recorded.","index":214,"end_time":861.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":859.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Interesting.","index":215,"end_time":874.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I know it''s not fun to look at the side of my head while I look at my other monitoring to figure this out, but.","index":216,"end_time":886.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":882.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh good.","index":217,"end_time":887.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":887.39,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m not seeing any Messages either on LinkedIn but I see her screenshot.","index":218,"end_time":916.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":911.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unfortunately this might be something to.","index":219,"end_time":919.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":917.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That we have to take up with LinkedIn support.","index":220,"end_time":920.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":919.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This looks to be more of an issue on their side.","index":221,"end_time":925.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just makes me wonder if there''s been other replies that.","index":222,"end_time":930.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":926.51,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":223,"end_time":932.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That have.","index":224,"end_time":933.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Obviously concerning.","index":225,"end_time":936.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":935.23,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah, because they''re not.","index":226,"end_time":937.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, they''re not showing in our system.","index":227,"end_time":939.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":937.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This issue seems to be on the LinkedIn side.","index":228,"end_time":948.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll.","index":229,"end_time":957.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":956.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''ll continue to dig in to this.","index":230,"end_time":962.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":957.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a strange issue for sure.","index":231,"end_time":963.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And she wasn''t getting your emails, you said?","index":232,"end_time":966.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":964.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Apparently not.","index":233,"end_time":968.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":967.43,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I just left her a voicemail just to be like, hey, call me so that I can resend it to you, like with you on the phone.","index":234,"end_time":974.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":968.11,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"But she''s obviously getting emails are automated emails, so it is interesting.","index":235,"end_time":981.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":976.79,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"But yeah, she''s like, I never received, you know, the invite for.","index":236,"end_time":985.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":982.79,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"And it was like, I imagine you asked her like the basic, like, is it in your spam?","index":237,"end_time":989.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I haven''t spoken to her after this.","index":238,"end_time":993.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":990.63,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I just left her a voicemail and just told her to call me back because she had a couple questions too.","index":239,"end_time":1000.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":993.63,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So if I don''t hear from her in the next hour, I''ll just then shoot her an email and be like, are you receiving this?","index":240,"end_time":1006.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.07,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":241,"end_time":1008.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s interesting because we''re not seeing any issues on like any of the automation side or even in Hay Reach.","index":242,"end_time":1012.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1008.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s definitely on the LinkedIn side.","index":243,"end_time":1016.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1012.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":244,"end_time":1017.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1016.67,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Super weird.","index":245,"end_time":1019.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1019.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":246,"end_time":1021.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1020.59,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Because I can see all of your messages for that.","index":247,"end_time":1024.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1021.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s just like, is there other issues that''s, you know, happening with the 40 other people I reached out to?","index":248,"end_time":1030.44,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1024.44,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I can see your messages going out.","index":249,"end_time":1032.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1030.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":250,"end_time":1034.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1034.12,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I mean, everything seems to work from the, like, product, like from Heyreach being connected to LinkedIn.","index":251,"end_time":1041.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1035.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so it seems like, yeah, there''s something wrong with the LinkedIn profile.","index":252,"end_time":1044.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1041.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, I''ll dig into that and see if LinkedIn has anything in their support forms that maybe can fix that.","index":253,"end_time":1051.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":254,"end_time":1052.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1052.15,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"The other thing that Steph and I were talking about this morning, talking to is like, for the amount of outreach they''re doing on these LinkedIn connections and the small amount of interaction that we''re getting that maybe we''re going to change this process because it seems like a lot of work for them to do.","index":255,"end_time":1073.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"You know, in my mind, it was like these people are connecting with us on LinkedIn and want to make sure that we''re doing customized outreach.","index":256,"end_time":1081.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1073.99,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Being that it''s not, has not been effective.","index":257,"end_time":1085.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1081.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I don''t know if there''s a different process we want to use or if we want to just automate it so that they don''t have to do these manual steps.","index":258,"end_time":1093.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it''s still doing outreach because like I''ve had like when I was doing it before Steph started, I had like one or two people that I was able to actually like talk to over LinkedIn.","index":259,"end_time":1105.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.18,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Out of the.","index":260,"end_time":1106.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1105.46,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"However many that I sent out, I don''t know that Dan''s had any.","index":261,"end_time":1110.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.02,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So.","index":262,"end_time":1112.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1112.05,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, I mean, I would like to automate it more with messages.","index":263,"end_time":1116.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1112.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what we can even do is like have like a industry specific messages and then there''s always like you need a fallback in case something breaks in the enrichment.","index":264,"end_time":1125.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we would just have a more generalized message probably about the PTO benchmark report.","index":265,"end_time":1129.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, we can build that really quickly.","index":266,"end_time":1132.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1129.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can even present that on Thursday as well.","index":267,"end_time":1134.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1132.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":268,"end_time":1139.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1138.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s, that''s, that is easy to fix.","index":269,"end_time":1142.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1139.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":270,"end_time":1143.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1143.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you guys are reviewing the web pages.","index":271,"end_time":1145.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1143.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Keep me updated on the internal meetings and what you want to do there.","index":272,"end_time":1148.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1145.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Thursday we''ll go through HubSpot audit.","index":273,"end_time":1151,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1148.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The.","index":274,"end_time":1152.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1152.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anything that I dig up I''ll share with you guys between now and then on LinkedIn forums that could be wrong with the account.","index":275,"end_time":1158.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1153.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then also put together the new messaging as well as the framework for the automated email outreach sequences in HubSpot.","index":276,"end_time":1165.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1158.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now do you know, I have another question for you.","index":277,"end_time":1171.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1168.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So part of the way this whole thing with Valerie Cawthron got surfaced was that an email went up from Sam today, right?","index":278,"end_time":1187.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.87,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Today.","index":279,"end_time":1187.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1187.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, today about.","index":280,"end_time":1189.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1187.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that was the other thing I was going to ask.","index":281,"end_time":1190.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1189.07,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"There was no way for me to remove her from.","index":282,"end_time":1193.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1190.79,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I looked because I, weirdly enough, before this came to me, I was like, should I be removing her from this cadence?","index":283,"end_time":1200.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1194.83,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Because I did have like another, you know, task created.","index":284,"end_time":1205.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1200.99,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"And then I went into her profile and there was no way like usually it says like unenroll and there was nothing there.","index":285,"end_time":1212.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1205.95,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So like this email came, came from Sam today.","index":286,"end_time":1217.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1214.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Boost your total reward strategy with PTO exchange.","index":287,"end_time":1223,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1219.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then I don''t know.","index":288,"end_time":1229.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1225.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks like Sam had that set up just as an automation.","index":289,"end_time":1239.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1236.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they submit the demo request.","index":290,"end_time":1242.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1239.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what, what''s the setup?","index":291,"end_time":1247.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1244.6,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It looks like as soon as they submit a demo request, they get those emails.","index":292,"end_time":1253.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1247.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But like in my case, I called her and then scheduled a demo and that wasn''t like triggered.","index":293,"end_time":1270.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1261.18,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"But Steph, you''re saying.","index":294,"end_time":1274.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1273.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Like when I go into her.","index":295,"end_time":1278.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1277.03,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"When you''re in HubSpot, do you have tasks and she''s enrolled in a sequence right now?","index":296,"end_time":1286.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, that might have been me enrolling her.","index":297,"end_time":1292.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1288.79,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I can''t remember.","index":298,"end_time":1293.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1292.39,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I think I might have enrolled her in, like, a demo request.","index":299,"end_time":1296.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1293.99,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So sequence.","index":300,"end_time":1298.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1297.11,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"But then you should be able to unenroll them.","index":301,"end_time":1302.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1298.88,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Right, that''s what I thought.","index":302,"end_time":1303,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1302.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It was like, yeah, this probably will shake out in the audit that you guys are doing.","index":303,"end_time":1310.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There was like a thing that when people were submitting a demo request.","index":304,"end_time":1314.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.04,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It.","index":305,"end_time":1318.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1318.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was like if they filled out the popup add because they hit request the demo, we were still going to put them in a sequence in case they didn''t complete the.","index":306,"end_time":1333.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1318.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The actual scheduling, like the.","index":307,"end_time":1335.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1333.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The thing that would go on calendly.","index":308,"end_time":1337.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1335.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If they didn''t actually schedule it there.","index":309,"end_time":1340.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1338.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We were going to enroll them in a sequence to make sure that we''re converting on as many of these people that are hitting request a demo.","index":310,"end_time":1346.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1340.81,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So they hit.","index":311,"end_time":1347.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1346.57,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"They hit the button, request a demo.","index":312,"end_time":1349.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1347.37,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"There''s an option to just book with you directly on calendly.","index":313,"end_time":1352.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1349.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"If they don''t actually schedule with you on calendly, then they get put into some kind of a sequence so that we can schedule it.","index":314,"end_time":1361.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1353.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So if someone does book with you on calendly, you''re supposed to just then unenroll them in the sequence because something is already scheduled.","index":315,"end_time":1371.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1361.83,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But in this case, it doesn''t sound like she scheduled something with you through calendly.","index":316,"end_time":1377.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1371.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"She did not.","index":317,"end_time":1379.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1378.48,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I called her and then I manually booked it through in Outlook.","index":318,"end_time":1383.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1379.28,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Right.","index":319,"end_time":1384.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1384,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So.","index":320,"end_time":1385.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1385.36,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Which we just have to consider, like, that''s usually how I do things.","index":321,"end_time":1397.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1390.56,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Like if I. I send an email out and if they don''t respond that day, I''m gonna call the next day because it''s a demo request.","index":322,"end_time":1404.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1397.36,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So they''re expecting your call.","index":323,"end_time":1405.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1404.32,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":324,"end_time":1406.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here''s exactly what happened.","index":325,"end_time":1409.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1406.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Share my screen.","index":326,"end_time":1411.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so I''m looking at Val.","index":327,"end_time":1413.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1412.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So she came in, and then when I go over on the right side here can see workflow memberships.","index":328,"end_time":1423.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1414.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everything that she''s enrolled in.","index":329,"end_time":1425.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1423.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so she''s currently enrolled in this automated nurture.","index":330,"end_time":1429.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1426.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the unenroll is here.","index":331,"end_time":1430.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1429.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that what you were clicking?","index":332,"end_time":1431.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1430.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Stephan was giving you an error.","index":333,"end_time":1432.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1431.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Normally, can you go back to her contact?","index":334,"end_time":1437.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1434.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":335,"end_time":1438.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1437.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Normally it says, like, if someone''s.","index":336,"end_time":1442.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Enrolled, it says it like over her name on the left side.","index":337,"end_time":1446.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1442.13,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"On the left side.","index":338,"end_time":1446.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.21,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And then you can just hit unenroll.","index":339,"end_time":1448.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.89,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":340,"end_time":1449.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1449.33,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"See how I went to that drop down and there was no unenroll.","index":341,"end_time":1454.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1449.97,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So maybe I didn''t.","index":342,"end_time":1455.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.13,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So how would I know?","index":343,"end_time":1456.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1455.89,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"I''m pretty sure I put her in, like, cadence.","index":344,"end_time":1460.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1457.49,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Right.","index":345,"end_time":1461.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.2,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Like, that''s why she''s getting tasks.","index":346,"end_time":1463.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.4,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Obviously that automated one is something on top of what I did, which I. Yeah.","index":347,"end_time":1468.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1463.2,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So she Went through workflows to get like state drop down updated based on the company then assigned to you.","index":348,"end_time":1476.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1468.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then I don''t know what these are.","index":349,"end_time":1478.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1477.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m gonna have to figure that out in our audit HR division assignment.","index":350,"end_time":1481.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then this is duplicative, so.","index":351,"end_time":1488.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1484.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":352,"end_time":1488.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1488.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then it just looks like they were enrolled in this nurture sequence which we open this up, has at least one page view of PTF Solutions and.","index":353,"end_time":1499.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1488.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry, I was on a call with Mercer joining late.","index":354,"end_time":1508.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1505.3,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Hey, Dan, how are you?","index":355,"end_time":1511.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1509.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Good.","index":356,"end_time":1511.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you?","index":357,"end_time":1512.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1511.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":358,"end_time":1513.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1512.91,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Sorry about your Texans.","index":359,"end_time":1515.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1514.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it was brutal.","index":360,"end_time":1518.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1516.99,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":361,"end_time":1521.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, Josh, for this flow, just looks like anyone that views the PTO Solutions page and is not a current customer gets enrolled in this.","index":362,"end_time":1531.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1521.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":363,"end_time":1532.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1532.35,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":364,"end_time":1537.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1536.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"These are the emails that she was getting, which.","index":365,"end_time":1540.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1537.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which I. I don''t mind.","index":366,"end_time":1544.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1540.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, you know this.","index":367,"end_time":1546.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1544.75,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So she wasn''t actually enrolled in a sequence stuff.","index":368,"end_time":1551.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1548.51,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s why you couldn''t unenroll her.","index":369,"end_time":1552.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1551.07,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Because she wasn''t enrolled in anything.","index":370,"end_time":1553.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1552.55,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, she was in a workflow, not a. Yeah.","index":371,"end_time":1556.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1553.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So then if we get in touch with somebody, should we go into the side like you just showed and unenroll them from the automated stuff?","index":372,"end_time":1569.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1559.23,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":373,"end_time":1570.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1570.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we could just build into this.","index":374,"end_time":1572.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1570.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I can just add a update to this to basically change the goal of this to say as soon as, you know, we could just have a field or we can say activity.","index":375,"end_time":1586.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1572.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We can even just have activity from the contact owner to say like, if X has happened, don''t like take them out of the sequence to save you guys on the manual side.","index":376,"end_time":1598.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1586.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t see any need for you to do that manually.","index":377,"end_time":1600.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1598.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, agreed.","index":378,"end_time":1602.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1601.04,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"So I think if, like, if an email is logged, we''ll probably go with something like that from the contact owner, then, you know, take them out of this.","index":379,"end_time":1611.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1602.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Which brings me to a question of, is two hours enough?","index":380,"end_time":1616.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1614.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, someone fills out or someone views the page, we have their information.","index":381,"end_time":1620.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1616.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is only currently waiting two hours before sending them the email.","index":382,"end_time":1624.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1621.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think two hours is like a nice time.","index":383,"end_time":1628.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1626.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like it''s pretty quick for someone to get an email after they''ve been browsing.","index":384,"end_time":1631.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1628.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if I want to make sure that your process, Steph and Dan is not interrupted by that.","index":385,"end_time":1635.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1631.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I like the two hours.","index":386,"end_time":1639.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1637.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Depends on when it comes in.","index":387,"end_time":1646.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1644,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Right?","index":388,"end_time":1647.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1646.96,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Yeah, but I mean, I. I''d like to think if a demo request comes in during work hours, like I''m gonna reach out immediately.","index":389,"end_time":1660.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1647.81,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"And then if that email is logged, they''re taken out of the sequence anyway.","index":390,"end_time":1667.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1664.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":391,"end_time":1668.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1668.13,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Okay.","index":392,"end_time":1675.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1674.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":393,"end_time":1676.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1675.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Josh, to your point, this is all going to be in the audit and recommendations that we put together.","index":394,"end_time":1679.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll just have to.","index":395,"end_time":1680.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Where we''ll leave the meeting on Thursday is like, here''s everything that we recommend doing.","index":396,"end_time":1684.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just need your sign off and then we build it.","index":397,"end_time":1686.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this will be part of that.","index":398,"end_time":1688.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1687.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":399,"end_time":1689.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1689.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The other thing, which I got to kind of untangle here a little bit, but we also work with that company, 11X, and they have a automation that''s set up that I have them paused right now because really kind of want to figure out where we''re at.","index":400,"end_time":1713.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1690.06,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But if somebody comes to our website and stays there for like, more than five seconds, they get put into a sequence using their tool.","index":401,"end_time":1724.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1713.43,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And I don''t know if that''s, you know, duplicative of what we''re doing or if it''s additive or if it''s like, you know, should we not be.","index":402,"end_time":1742.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1726.26,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, we''re kind of running two of the same campaigns, which could lead to confusion for the customer or prospect.","index":403,"end_time":1751.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1744.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I showed you guys, like, the automation we built of RB2B to DE.","index":404,"end_time":1755.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1752.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Anonymize traffic, check if they''re in HubSpot as a customer.","index":405,"end_time":1759.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1755.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If they are not, then they move forward as an enrollment into the email sequence, which seems like exactly what they''re doing.","index":406,"end_time":1767.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1759.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":407,"end_time":1768.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.03,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Which I''m not sure why Sam was setting it up so that it was hitting.","index":408,"end_time":1774.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.39,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"From getting hit from both sides.","index":409,"end_time":1776.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1774.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That seems like that could be annoying, you know.","index":410,"end_time":1783.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.2,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That could be annoying.","index":411,"end_time":1784.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1783.84,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":412,"end_time":1785.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1785,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Prospect of getting it.","index":413,"end_time":1787.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1785.72,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"I mean, one of the benefits of this 11x, like when it works and the way that it''s supposed to work is like, you know, it''s an AI tool that''s doing research on the company and it''s.","index":414,"end_time":1801.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1787.4,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"And it.","index":415,"end_time":1802.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1801.64,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"The messaging that it sends is like, you know, pulling in relevant information.","index":416,"end_time":1807.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1802.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It looks at the person''s LinkedIn and their background and it''s like really building, like very customized email.","index":417,"end_time":1816.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1808.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Short.","index":418,"end_time":1816.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1816.33,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Short and sweet.","index":419,"end_time":1817.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1817.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But like, you know, feels like it.","index":420,"end_time":1820.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1817.97,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Was written by someone who looked at their profile.","index":421,"end_time":1821.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1820.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":422,"end_time":1822.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1822.41,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So, like, I''ll give you an example.","index":423,"end_time":1825.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1823.61,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So I just pulled this up.","index":424,"end_time":1825.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1825.13,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is the website visitors thing again.","index":425,"end_time":1831.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1825.93,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is a pause thing.","index":426,"end_time":1832.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1831.62,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But.","index":427,"end_time":1832.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.7,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But this guy, Dean Millsap, who would come in so that their tool does all this research on Ruby Tuesdays.","index":428,"end_time":1841.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1832.9,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"He''s a restaurant manager.","index":429,"end_time":1843.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1841.62,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"He''s a.","index":430,"end_time":1845.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1844.82,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"That''s his job title.","index":431,"end_time":1846.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1845.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":432,"end_time":1846.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1846.54,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":433,"end_time":1847.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1846.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But it.","index":434,"end_time":1849.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1849.3,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But it would pull in.","index":435,"end_time":1851.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1850.66,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This is what Ruby Tuesday''s benefit package is.","index":436,"end_time":1854.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1851.74,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"It shows that you really invest in your team.","index":437,"end_time":1856.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1854.42,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"We do this.","index":438,"end_time":1857.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1856.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Is that something worth exploring?","index":439,"end_time":1860.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1857.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Then wait two days again using like, short.","index":440,"end_time":1867.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1861.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Whatever prompts we''ve given The AI tool.","index":441,"end_time":1871.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1868.71,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":442,"end_time":1871.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1871.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, now it''s talking about turnover reduction, Industry stuff.","index":443,"end_time":1883.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1872.63,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So it like generates this as.","index":444,"end_time":1885.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1884.08,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"As it goes.","index":445,"end_time":1886.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1885.76,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"But again, I have all of this on pause, but at some point we need to figure out what''s doing what.","index":446,"end_time":1894.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1886.88,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I, you know, to be honest, I had.","index":447,"end_time":1898.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1894.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I knew you guys were working with 11x.","index":448,"end_time":1901.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1899.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I wasn''t sure exactly how you''re working with them.","index":449,"end_time":1904.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1901.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean that this is like what their tool does, or you build a list and you give it the ICP of what you''re looking for and it does the same kind of thing where it''s doing research on the person sending out customized emails to them.","index":450,"end_time":1917.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1904.48,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Not this is.","index":451,"end_time":1919.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1918.11,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"This one is website visitors, but like, you know, we also have like health care.","index":452,"end_time":1923.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1919.27,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Right.","index":453,"end_time":1925.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1924.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":454,"end_time":1925.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1925.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"List that you provide, financial services, whatever.","index":455,"end_time":1928.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1925.47,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Are the sequences.","index":456,"end_time":1929.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1928.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Column that, that you just covered for website visitors.","index":457,"end_time":1931.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1929.15,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Are those emails coming from our inboxes?","index":458,"end_time":1934.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1931.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"From my inbox.","index":459,"end_time":1935.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1934.47,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Like, not your PTO exchange inbox, but the ones that we''ve set up to send on your behalf.","index":460,"end_time":1940.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1936.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":461,"end_time":1941.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1940.19,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"I was just curious.","index":462,"end_time":1942.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1941.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":463,"end_time":1945.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1945.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":464,"end_time":1946.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1945.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This is good to know.","index":465,"end_time":1947.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1946.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Definitely ties into the report then of what everyone''s doing.","index":466,"end_time":1949.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1947.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":467,"end_time":1951.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1950.59,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Okay.","index":468,"end_time":1952.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1951.469,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And part of this, again, like, why we hired a cmo so she can work through all of this stuff and then work with you on the execution of it.","index":469,"end_time":1963.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1952.67,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"So.","index":470,"end_time":1963.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1963.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":471,"end_time":1965.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1964.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":472,"end_time":1969.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1968.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, yeah, still good to know.","index":473,"end_time":1970.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1969.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":474,"end_time":1972.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1971.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so I know I have.","index":475,"end_time":1973.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1972.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I laid out my laundry list of things that I''m going to have ready to present to you guys on Thursday.","index":476,"end_time":1977.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1973.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was there anything else you guys wanted to go through?","index":477,"end_time":1978.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1977.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, so.","index":478,"end_time":1982.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1981.58,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":479,"end_time":1984.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1982.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, thank you for your time, Dan, again, sorry that you had to watch C.J.","index":480,"end_time":1988.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1984.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"stroud.","index":481,"end_time":1988.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1988.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There are four interceptions.","index":482,"end_time":1989.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1988.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I''m, I''m a.","index":483,"end_time":1992.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1990.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"First and foremost, I''m a Vikings fan.","index":484,"end_time":1993.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1992.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"But I jumped on.","index":485,"end_time":1994.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1993.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":486,"end_time":1994.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Texans were your backup.","index":487,"end_time":1995.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1994.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":488,"end_time":1996.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1995.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, I''m just kind of used to it, the gut punch every season.","index":489,"end_time":2001.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1996.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"So, yeah, I gotcha now.","index":490,"end_time":2005.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2001.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Now I''m like, I''m hearing all these rumors about CJ Stroud getting traded to the Vikings, and I''m like, oh, my gosh.","index":491,"end_time":2010.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2005.07,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"},{"text":"Well, good luck with that.","index":492,"end_time":2014.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2012.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, following you.","index":493,"end_time":2015.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2014.87,"speaker_name":"Stephanie Lucchesi"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":494,"end_time":2017.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2016.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you guys so much for your time.","index":495,"end_time":2019.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2017.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, thanks, Colin.","index":496,"end_time":2020.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2019.45,"speaker_name":"Josh Reinhard"},{"text":"Thanks, Colin.","index":497,"end_time":2021.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2020.37,"speaker_name":"Dan Igo"}],"dateString":"2026-01-20T19:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/86093865913?pwd=ajXSuerDGmcROjfezSWYYGsa7iPOWd.1","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,josh@ptoexchange.com,dan@ptoexchange.com,davids@ptoexchange.com,stephanie@ptoexchange.com","josh@ptoexchange.com","dan@ptoexchange.com","davids@ptoexchange.com","stephanie@ptoexchange.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEVVT7AQX3SKV91VJ207F0TY","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.83,"bullets":["Colin confirmed HubSpot audit will wrap by tomorrow with updates and recommendations shared Thursday.","Team discussed replacing Monday check-in with a consolidated marketing meeting including new CMO Carmen.","Josh flagged possible overlap and confusion with parallel automations from internal workflows and 11X.","Stephanie raised visibility issues with LinkedIn messaging and low response rate from manual outreach.","Colin will revise automated sequences to auto-unenroll contacts once manual engagement is detected."],"highlights":[{"quote":"It seems like a lot of work for them to do... has not been effective.","speaker":"Josh Reinhard"},{"quote":"We''ll just have to... need your sign off and then we build it.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"},{"quote":"There was no way for me to remove her from... I looked.","speaker":"Stephanie Lucchesi"}],"topics":["workflow","automation","delivery","meetings","outreach"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-20T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **HubSpot Audit and Workflow Optimization**\n\nThe team is finalizing a detailed **HubSpot audit** to streamline workflows and improve lead nurturing by Thursday, aiming for better automation and reduced manual work (06:38).\n\n- **Colin Costigan** is completing the audit and will propose removing redundant fields and adding new options to improve data flow and automation logic.\n- The audit will clarify how sequences handle different lead statuses, especially for healthcare cold leads, ensuring automated sequences align with realistic outreach tactics.\n- A key focus is automating unenrollment from nurture sequences when a lead owner logs activity, reducing manual task loads for sales reps like **Stephanie Lucchesi**.\n- The audit will address confusing overlaps in workflows, such as leads enrolled in nurture emails after demo requests without proper unenroll triggers, exemplified by the **Valerie Cawthron** case.\n\n## **LinkedIn Outreach and Messaging Strategy**\n\nCurrent manual LinkedIn outreach shows low engagement, prompting plans to automate and overhaul messaging to boost efficiency and responses (17:35).\n\n- **Stephanie Lucchesi** noted that **15–20%** of LinkedIn connection updates are outdated, but updating contacts without response is inefficient.\n- The team agreed to develop industry-specific, automated LinkedIn messages with fallback general messaging focused on the **PTO benchmark report** to increase outreach effectiveness.\n- **Josh Reinhard** highlighted the low conversion rate from manual LinkedIn outreach, with few meaningful interactions despite high connection volumes.\n- Automating LinkedIn outreach will free up sales resources and reduce redundant manual effort while maintaining personalized messaging through predefined templates.\n\n## **Meeting Cadence and Internal Collaboration**\n\nThe team is restructuring meetings to integrate the new fractional CMO and improve communication efficiency by consolidating existing calls (08:04).\n\n- The new **fractional CMO, Carmen**, started and will join Monday marketing meetings, replacing a smaller internal sync.\n- The plan is to hold a combined **Monday meeting from 12:30 to 1:00 PM Pacific Time**, where Colin and Carmen both participate, streamlining updates and reducing redundant calls.\n- Colin is adjusting his schedule to accommodate this while ensuring no conflicts with existing standing meetings.\n- This consolidation aims to enhance strategic alignment across marketing, PR, and sales teams by including key stakeholders in one forum.\n\n## **Demo Request and Lead Follow-up Process**\n\nThe current demo request process has gaps causing leads to remain in automated sequences despite manual scheduling, requiring process refinement to avoid mixed messaging (20:14).\n\n- Leads who manually schedule demos outside the automated **Calendly** system, like **Valerie Cawthron**, are not properly unenrolled from nurture workflows, creating confusion.\n- The team agreed to build logic into workflows that automatically unenroll leads upon logged contact activity from the assigned sales rep, reducing manual unenrollment needs.\n- The existing timing of a **2-hour delay** before sending nurture emails after page views is confirmed as appropriate to allow reps to reach out first.\n- The audit will include recommendations to better sync demo request workflows with manual scheduling habits to improve lead experience and internal efficiency.\n\n## **Marketing Automation Overlap and AI-Powered Outreach**\n\nThere is overlap between the in-house automation and the third-party **11X AI tool**, which sends personalized emails to website visitors, requiring alignment to avoid prospect confusion (28:09).\n\n- The **11X tool** researches visitors and sends customized emails based on LinkedIn and company info, paused currently to evaluate effectiveness.\n- Colin identified duplication between 11X sequences and the internal HubSpot workflows that enroll prospects shortly after site visits.\n- **Josh Reinhard** explained the AI tool’s value lies in personalized, short emails tailored to prospects, but running both campaigns risks overwhelming contacts.\n- The new CMO will review and coordinate these tools to optimize messaging, reduce redundancy, and improve conversion rates across outreach channels.","outline":null,"keywords":["HubSpot Audit","LinkedIn Outreach","Marketing Automation","Workflow Enrollment","11X AI Platform","Fractional CMO Integration"],"overview":"- **HubSpot Audit Completion:** Finalizing audit by Thursday to streamline workflows and enhance lead nurturing and automation.\n- **LinkedIn Outreach Plan:** Automating outreach to improve engagement; updating contacts inefficiently affects 15-20% of connection updates.\n- **Meeting Restructure:** Consolidating meetings with new fractional CMO to enhance communication and align marketing and sales strategies.\n- **Demo Request Gaps:** Addressing issues with manual demo scheduling to enhance workflow and reduce confusion in nurture sequences.\n- **AI Tool Overlap:** Reviewing duplication between HubSpot workflows and 11X AI tool for smarter, less overwhelming prospect outreach.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nComplete and share HubSpot audit results and proposed workflow improvements by end of day Wednesday; present on Thursday (06:19)\nInvestigate LinkedIn message disappearance issue with Valerie Cawthron and liaise with LinkedIn support if needed; share findings pre-Thursday meeting (15:11)\nDevelop automated messaging framework for LinkedIn cadences and email outreach sequences; present updates on Thursday (18:59)\nModify workflows to add automatic unenrollment triggers based on logged sales activity to reduce manual unenrollment (26:10)\nCoordinate with team and fractional CMO Carmen on meeting scheduling and integration into marketing meetings (08:04)\nIncorporate analysis of overlapping automation between 11X and HubSpot sequences into audit report with recommendations (28:09)\n\n**Stephanie Lucchesi**\nContinue LinkedIn outreach activities with current cadences; update only contacts that respond; monitor engagement and provide feedback for revamping messaging (11:50)\nFollow up with Valerie Cawthron via voicemail and email to confirm receipt of demo invites and clarify communication issues (16:07)\nMonitor potential further LinkedIn message issues affecting other contacts and report to Colin (17:04)\n\n**Josh Reinhard**\nFacilitate meeting scheduling coordination between Colin, Carmen, and internal marketing team; approve meeting consolidation plan after Carmen’s onboarding (08:04)\nOversee and ensure proper unenrollment from sequences for manually scheduled demos booked outside of Calendly; communicate with sales team about process (21:01)\nContinue evaluating integration and use of 11X platform; coordinate strategic decisions with fractional CMO and Colin (29:45)\n\n**Dan Igo**\nParticipate in marketing meetings and provide feedback on automation and outreach impacts (25:05)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"fa472773-e29c-4b27-aa69-1ecec05bfb29","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
