    '{"id":"01KF9DC7GFAXFVPB2T3SXPCDFJ","title":"KTC // MiD: Weekly Marketing Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Account-Based Marketing (ABM) Campaign Setup**\n\nThe ABM campaign setup is complete and poised to launch immediately after the website goes live.\n\n- **The ABM campaign setup is finished and awaiting the website launch scheduled for the 30th, with ongoing daily page builds until then** (15:12)  \n    - The team created a targeted contact list of about **6,000 prospects** segmented by company, job title, location, and LinkedIn profile to enable tailored messaging.  \n    - Kristen requested removing “hi” from initial messages, which has been implemented to improve outreach tone and engagement.  \n    - Colin emphasized coordinating final approvals and DNS updates with Ryan after the website completion to ensure smooth campaign activation.  \n    - Segment customization reflects intent to personalize content by business type, increasing relevance and response rates.  \n\n- **A negative list will exclude current clients such as Oak Tree from outreach to avoid confusion and maintain client relationships** (11:00)  \n    - Michael confirmed some current client data exists in HubSpot, with plans to expand as ATS integration completes by month-end.  \n    - Colin explained that once integrated, HubSpot will automatically cross-check contacts to prevent overlap and duplicate outreach.  \n    - This integration reduces manual effort and minimizes risk of alienating existing clients through accidental contact.  \n    - Michael’s cautious approach to data entry reflects desire to wait for this automation before fully populating HubSpot.  \n\n## **Website and Digital Asset Development**\n\nThe website and supporting digital assets are advancing on a tight schedule to support marketing and hiring efforts.\n\n- **Website pages are being developed daily and expected to be finalized by the 30th for campaign launch** (12:00)  \n    - The team created a testimonials page designed for video and text testimonials to boost credibility and engagement.  \n    - Background music and voiceover options for promotional content are ready, with samples to be sent for selection.  \n    - Colin highlighted seamless integration with HubSpot to host landing pages, improving user experience and lead capture.  \n    - The website will include a branded subpage for job postings, supporting recruitment efforts with a consistent Richie May brand.  \n\n- **LinkedIn company page and social assets will be updated post-ID.me payroll clarity to avoid conflicts** (14:41)  \n    - Michael offered to grant admin access once ID.me updates finalize, allowing the team to manage LinkedIn business manager setups and campaigns.  \n    - Colin recommended setting up a LinkedIn business manager for shared access and smoother support interactions.  \n    - LinkedIn remains the primary social channel due to audience alignment, with no plans to expand to other platforms currently.  \n    - This phased approach balances timely updates with Michael’s payroll situation to avoid risks.  \n\n## **Recruitment and ATS Integration**\n\nRecruitment processes will benefit from improved ATS integration and branded job posting capabilities.\n\n- **Michael plans to introduce Lauren, his Koolaid CSM, to collaborate on job posting workflows and landing page branding** (08:40)  \n    - Koolaid’s ATS will be leveraged to post jobs and track hiring activities, integrated with Richie May branding for a unified experience.  \n    - The goal is to create a branded landing page link that can be shared to give candidates a clear, professional application path.  \n    - This reduces candidate confusion and enhances employer branding consistency amid growing hiring needs.  \n    - The introduction aims to establish direct communication between Koolaid and the marketing team for faster execution.  \n\n- **End-of-month ATS to HubSpot integration will automate job and candidate data syncing, improving efficiency** (11:30)  \n    - Once live, this integration will automatically feed HubSpot with recruiting data, enabling real-time updates and targeted outreach.  \n    - Michael’s current manual data input is limited pending this automation to ensure accuracy and reduce effort.  \n    - Colin confirmed the integration will include logic to exclude existing clients from outreach lists, preserving client relations.  \n    - This technical upgrade is critical to scaling recruitment marketing without increasing administrative overhead.  \n\n## **Social Media and LinkedIn Strategy**\n\nLinkedIn will remain the central social platform with controlled access for campaign management and profile updates.\n\n- **Focus remains on LinkedIn as the primary social channel aligned with target audience and campaign goals** (13:30)  \n    - Michael confirmed no current plans to expand to Facebook or other platforms, keeping efforts concentrated and efficient.  \n    - Colin plans to manage company page and ad account access through a LinkedIn business manager for better control and collaboration.  \n    - This setup mitigates risks associated with personal account access and supports campaign execution.  \n    - The strategy leverages LinkedIn’s professional network to maximize recruitment and brand awareness impact.  \n\n- **Campaign-related LinkedIn updates will wait until ID.me’s internal changes stabilize to avoid conflicts with Michael’s personal profile** (14:41)  \n    - Michael offered to provide access after payroll changes are finalized, ensuring no disruptions to his compensation.  \n    - The team is prepared to handle both company page and personal LinkedIn updates to maintain consistent messaging and presence.  \n    - This cautious timing reflects sensitivity to employee concerns and prioritizes operational stability.  \n    - It shows a pragmatic approach to social media management tied closely to business realities.","outline":null,"keywords":["LinkedIn Updates","ATS Integration","ABM Campaign","HubSpot Management","Website Development","Client Outreach Exclusion"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Launch:** Campaign ready to launch post-website, aimed for January 30 with 6,000 tailored prospects list.  \n- **Client Exclusion Strategy:** Current clients like Oak Tree excluded to avoid confusion and manage relationships effectively.  \n- **Website Development Progress:** Website finalization by January 30, includes testimonials and job postings to enhance credibility and recruitment.  \n- **ATS Integration Benefits:** End-of-month integration will automate data syncing, improving recruitment efficiency and targeting in HubSpot.  \n- **LinkedIn as Primary Channel:** Focus on LinkedIn for campaigns, with access controlled until post-ID.me payroll clarity to avoid conflicts.  \n- **Phase Management Approach:** Updates and access are timed with payroll stability considerations, ensuring smooth social media strategy execution.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend updated contact list and campaign materials to Michael and Kristen for review (10:05)\nProvide instructions and assist Michael in setting up LinkedIn Business Manager and sharing admin access for company page and ads (12:50)\nDeliver background music and voiceover options for campaign assets to Michael for feedback (14:05)\nCoordinate final website page approvals and update DNS settings with Ryan after completion (12:23)\nRun negative list of current clients in HubSpot to exclude from outreach (15:30)\n\n**Michael Kersten**\nComplete introduction email for Lauren (Koolaid CSM) to marketing team to enable ATS integration (15:16)\nReview and approve ABM campaign contact list and segmentation, ensuring current clients are excluded (10:30)\nProvide any additional testimonials or permission to use existing ones for website testimonial page (13:40)\nDecide timing for LinkedIn profile updates post-ID.me payroll resolution and grant access to marketing team when ready (14:40)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nDocument LinkedIn Business Manager setup instructions and share with Michael (12:50)\n"},"duration":16,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Guille Santana"},{"id":2,"name":"Michael Kersten"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey, Colleen, how''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":188.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, how are you doing?","index":1,"end_time":190.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.27,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Well, Having some papas fritas.","index":2,"end_time":269.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":190.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s sliced apples with Tajin.","index":3,"end_time":275.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":272.74,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Nice.","index":4,"end_time":277.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":276.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I wish they were papas fritas.","index":5,"end_time":281.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.7,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be good.","index":6,"end_time":285.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":284.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I haven''t moved from this chair in like four, four and a half hours.","index":7,"end_time":290.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":286.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh, no.","index":8,"end_time":291.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":290.61,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I don''t know if my legs are gonna work when I stand up.","index":9,"end_time":296.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sometimes I see tasks from you at like midnight and like we''re calling.","index":10,"end_time":303.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.01,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"It''s all good.","index":11,"end_time":305.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":304.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I. I like take a break at.","index":12,"end_time":307.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"At 5 o'' clock my time to do a couple hours with my daughter and give my wife a break.","index":13,"end_time":316.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":309.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":317.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":317,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"A few more minutes.","index":15,"end_time":390.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then sent an email.","index":16,"end_time":392.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":390.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It.","index":17,"end_time":411.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":410.8,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":18,"end_time":452.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.09,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":19,"end_time":453.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":452.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Hey, Michael.","index":20,"end_time":454.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just over to a new laptop and of course Zoom is not on there and it''s wants to try to load it, so I had to hurry up and pull up my Mac.","index":21,"end_time":462.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":454.89,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I apologize.","index":22,"end_time":463.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":462.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"No, no worries.","index":23,"end_time":464.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":464.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":24,"end_time":466.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":465.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":25,"end_time":466.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"How about you?","index":26,"end_time":467.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":466.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Doing all right.","index":27,"end_time":468.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":467.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No complaints.","index":28,"end_time":471.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Long weekend?","index":29,"end_time":472.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":471.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":30,"end_time":472.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":31,"end_time":473.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I got the.","index":32,"end_time":475.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I forget who sent it to me, but I got the updates from my LinkedIn site.","index":33,"end_time":479.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":475.15,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"There''s a couple updates that are coming down with ID me.","index":34,"end_time":483.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":480.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I just need to let that transpire here in the next.","index":35,"end_time":485.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"This week.","index":36,"end_time":486.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":485.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I should be able to start making some of those updates next week.","index":37,"end_time":489.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":487.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They''re kind of doing a push, a mass amass, you know, return to office.","index":38,"end_time":494.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And, you know, a lot of positions, including mine, are more remote.","index":39,"end_time":497.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":494.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So they''re going to kind of say, hey, here''s what your options.","index":40,"end_time":499.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":497.42,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Once that''s, you know, been released, then I don''t, I don''t feel bad about updating, but they''re writing out checks, so I don''t want to update anything until I see what my check is, if you know what I mean.","index":41,"end_time":509.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":499.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I totally get that and agree with it.","index":42,"end_time":513.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":509.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, sounds good.","index":43,"end_time":518.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you for letting us know.","index":44,"end_time":519.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":518.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s no problem at all.","index":45,"end_time":520.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":519.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":46,"end_time":520.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.18,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then the other thing I''m going to do too is, and you guys can brainstorm about this, but I''m going to make an introduction to you, to Lauren.","index":47,"end_time":530.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":520.46,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Lauren is my CSM over at Koolaid, and right now Kulate''s the ATS system that I use, obviously, to track our jobs.","index":48,"end_time":537.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":530.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And everything else is in there with the Richie Mae stuff.","index":49,"end_time":540.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":537.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I have all my stuff in there, but I''m getting to the point where with certain stuff, I need to probably post something.","index":50,"end_time":546.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":540.83,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So what we.","index":51,"end_time":547.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They have a way of posting the jobs.","index":52,"end_time":549.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":548.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I told her what I was envisioning is, you know, maybe you Guys, she can talk to you and tell you, hey, this is what out of the box.","index":53,"end_time":556.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":549.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Maybe we can do something on a.","index":54,"end_time":558.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":556.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Maybe you can.","index":55,"end_time":558.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.17,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"On a landing page, brand it all Richie May type stuff.","index":56,"end_time":561.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":558.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I can.","index":57,"end_time":562.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You can give me a link and then I can give it to the Richie May folks.","index":58,"end_time":565.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":562.77,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So somebody hits on open Positions, it''ll click it, but it''ll reroute it to that sub page that you guys have.","index":59,"end_time":571.849,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":565.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Brown it all Richie May just so we can collect it with us hiring all these different roles.","index":60,"end_time":578.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":571.849,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t traditionally post, but, you know, occasionally I get these, you know, freaking candidates that think I''m pin.","index":61,"end_time":584.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":578.33,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I''m trying to, you know, scam them.","index":62,"end_time":586.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So then they go to the website and there''s nothing there and blah, blah, blah.","index":63,"end_time":590.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":586.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So I told her that, you know, I''m assuming that''s something we can set.","index":64,"end_time":594.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.08,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Up and you guys can help do that.","index":65,"end_time":596.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":594.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But I told her I would just do an introduction, let the two of you guys schedule something and figure it out, and then you can kind of add that into the overall plan.","index":66,"end_time":602.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":596.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":67,"end_time":603,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":602.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds good to me.","index":68,"end_time":604.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":69,"end_time":604.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":604.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":70,"end_time":605.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":605.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, let''s dive into this.","index":71,"end_time":609,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":607.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so for the ABM plan, so our setup is actually finished.","index":72,"end_time":617.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":612.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re now just waiting on the go live of the website to get this campaign in place.","index":73,"end_time":622.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":617.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That being said, we made the update that Kristen asked for, which was removing hi from the messages to start.","index":74,"end_time":628.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":623.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s all been done.","index":75,"end_time":629.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there''s any other feedback, just let us know.","index":76,"end_time":631.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":629.92,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And if you need this link again, let me know.","index":77,"end_time":633.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":631.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ve also created the contact list.","index":78,"end_time":637.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":634.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so here we have about 6,000 people that fit into the criteria that we discussed.","index":79,"end_time":645.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":638.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We haven''t broken out with what company they work at, full name, job title, location, their LinkedIn profile.","index":80,"end_time":652.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also broke them out into further segments because we''re going to have that customized content based on their business.","index":81,"end_time":658.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":652.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can see that breaking broken down here as well.","index":82,"end_time":660.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":658.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":83,"end_time":661.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Honestly, when you guys are hitting that, just make sure we don''t hit like Oak Tree or some of my current clients just so they''re.","index":84,"end_time":669.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":662.7,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"They don''t.","index":85,"end_time":669.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":669.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We don''t include them in a outreach.","index":86,"end_time":672.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":670.28,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":87,"end_time":672.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":88,"end_time":673.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And is all of that already loaded into HubSpot, Right?","index":89,"end_time":676.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":673.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Current customers?","index":90,"end_time":676.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":676.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":91,"end_time":677.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":676.68,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Some of that stuff is there.","index":92,"end_time":677.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":677.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I don''t have everything in there.","index":93,"end_time":678.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":677.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I was waiting for you guys to kind of get control of some stuff.","index":94,"end_time":682.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":678.88,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I was going to start pushing some stuff in there.","index":95,"end_time":683.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":682.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I need to get in there.","index":96,"end_time":684.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":683.92,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, I was, full disclosure, being somewhat lazy because I Was hoping that.","index":97,"end_time":689.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":685.56,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m hoping that the integration from the ATS to there will be done at the end of the month.","index":98,"end_time":693.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":689.24,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So that way I can.","index":99,"end_time":694.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":693.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''ll automatically send it and then you guys can go in there and refresh it like we had talked about and don''t have.","index":100,"end_time":699.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":694.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we''ll just be able to.","index":101,"end_time":700.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":699.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"In clay, we can actually set of direct integration where it checks if anyone from that company exists.","index":102,"end_time":705.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":103,"end_time":705.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":705.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":104,"end_time":706.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":705.78,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":105,"end_time":707.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":706.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But we''ll send this over in the meantime so that you and Kristen can go through it.","index":106,"end_time":710.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":707.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":107,"end_time":710.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":710.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"We''ve also already built out a few of the pages in HubSpot, so I can just show you some of these.","index":108,"end_time":718.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":711.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So everything is coming together.","index":109,"end_time":719.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looks nice.","index":110,"end_time":721.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Pop up here.","index":111,"end_time":723.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":722.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you''ll see these obviously being built in in your HubSpot account.","index":112,"end_time":727.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And the final page is being built on the 30th, so we have pages being developed every day from here to the 30th.","index":113,"end_time":734.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we are done.","index":114,"end_time":735.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":734.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You guys do final pass and approval and then we''ll just coordinate the updates with Ryan on the DNS side of things.","index":115,"end_time":742.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":735.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":116,"end_time":743.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":743.3,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then, hey, speaking of updates too, as I told you and maybe on your plan, but I know what you wanted me to Update my personal LinkedIn stuff.","index":117,"end_time":751.86,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":743.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Do you guys want to go in there and I can give you access to.","index":118,"end_time":755.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.66,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But I''m assuming you also want to update my LinkedIn social site.","index":119,"end_time":758.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":755.54,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Company site, KTF.","index":120,"end_time":760.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You know, Kirsten Talent.","index":121,"end_time":761.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":760.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"I''m assuming you guys, you know, I can give you access and you can.","index":122,"end_time":764.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":761.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Have at it or whatever.","index":123,"end_time":765.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":764.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just tell me who I need to invite and I think I can give you admin rights or whatever.","index":124,"end_time":768.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":765.48,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then you guys can go in there and do whatever you want.","index":125,"end_time":770.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":768.52,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":126,"end_time":770.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, so what we like to do is we actually have you set up a business manager on LinkedIn.","index":127,"end_time":775.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":770.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"This that way like, we are not like the only ones on your account or someone needs to talk to support or anything like that.","index":128,"end_time":783.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":775.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll send over Da and Paula, if you can just write down, um, we''ll send over the instructions for setting up that business manager and then how to share access with us.","index":129,"end_time":790.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":783.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":130,"end_time":791.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":790.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":131,"end_time":791.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":791.35,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"But yeah, that was change.","index":132,"end_time":793.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":792.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"You guys can change everything from that standpoint then too?","index":133,"end_time":796.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":793.71,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, so if you give us company page and like ad account access, which we''ll need anyway for these campaigns, then we can make that change.","index":134,"end_time":802.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":796.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":135,"end_time":803.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":802.79,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"And then on the social side, Obviously we have LinkedIn.","index":136,"end_time":806.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":803.43,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Do.","index":137,"end_time":806.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":806.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are we going to do any other social.","index":138,"end_time":807.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":806.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Do I need any other social sites?","index":139,"end_time":808.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":807.55,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Are we just going to mainly just keep with LinkedIn.","index":140,"end_time":810.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":808.95,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Right.","index":141,"end_time":810.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":810.51,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"LinkedIn, I think, is really your audience.","index":142,"end_time":812.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":810.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, it''s.","index":143,"end_time":813.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":812.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s your whole audience.","index":144,"end_time":814.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":813.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I don''t know if you''re doing much on Facebook, you know, I think over there.","index":145,"end_time":817.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":814.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, not unless you guys tell me we are.","index":146,"end_time":819.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":817.93,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, I got you.","index":147,"end_time":821.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":820.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have this testimonials page built out as well.","index":148,"end_time":824.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":821.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I really like this.","index":149,"end_time":825.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":824.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Got spots for video testimonials, text testimonials, everything like that.","index":150,"end_time":829.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":825.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we can load these in as a post type once we have the.","index":151,"end_time":832.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":829.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The list of everything.","index":152,"end_time":833.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":832.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless.","index":153,"end_time":834.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":833.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Unless you say, like, hey, Colin, everything''s on the website and I don''t have anything else.","index":154,"end_time":837.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":834.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool, we''ll just take from that.","index":155,"end_time":839.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":837.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But if you have anything else, I know you''ve had some conversations recently, so if you could just send us those, that''d be great.","index":156,"end_time":843.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":839.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":157,"end_time":844.4,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":843.6,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":158,"end_time":846,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":845.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, next we will send these over again because I hate playing them over Zoom, but we have the background music and voiceover options, so we''ll give you a few options there of what we can move forward with.","index":159,"end_time":857.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":847.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we also have the document with the LinkedIn updates.","index":160,"end_time":863.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":858.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, when you, whatever schedule you''re on with ID me and the changes and everything going on over there, I do not want to impact you getting a paycheck by any means.","index":161,"end_time":871.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":863.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, we can.","index":162,"end_time":873.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If you want to make these updates after then, or if you want to give us access.","index":163,"end_time":876.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":873.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you mentioned that at some point too, for us to make the changes, whatever you want to do there, just let us know.","index":164,"end_time":881.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":876.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I can give you guys access to my personal one, too.","index":165,"end_time":883.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":881.34,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Once again, you just have to tell me how to do it.","index":166,"end_time":885.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":883.9,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"So.","index":167,"end_time":885.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":168,"end_time":886.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":885.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":169,"end_time":886.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":886.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Cool.","index":170,"end_time":887.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":886.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":171,"end_time":889.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":888.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then that was actually pretty much everything because from there it''s just the content calendar, which I know we''re working with Kristen on.","index":172,"end_time":895.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":889.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the big things, we''ll send over the contact list and then the background music and voiceover options, and then everything else, we''re full steam ahead on the website.","index":173,"end_time":905.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":895.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s going to be done in 10 days.","index":174,"end_time":906.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we have your LinkedIn profile that will handle when your ID me situation moves through.","index":175,"end_time":912.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":907.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":176,"end_time":912.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Plan.","index":177,"end_time":913.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":912.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, good deal.","index":178,"end_time":914.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":913.31,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":179,"end_time":914.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":914.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":180,"end_time":915.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":915.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I''ll send you that invite or I''m sending that intro to Lauren and then you guys.","index":181,"end_time":921.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":916.75,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Yeah, Lauren from.","index":182,"end_time":922.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":921.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, your ats.","index":183,"end_time":923.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":922.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep, yep.","index":184,"end_time":923.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":923.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":185,"end_time":924.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then.","index":186,"end_time":925.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":924.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yep.","index":187,"end_time":925.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Once that''s done, we''ll run the.","index":188,"end_time":926.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":925.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The negative list of the HubSpot clients as well.","index":189,"end_time":929.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":926.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cool.","index":190,"end_time":930.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.03,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":191,"end_time":931.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":930.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, awesome.","index":192,"end_time":931.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":931.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, well, that''s everything from our end.","index":193,"end_time":933.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll give you guys some time back.","index":194,"end_time":935.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":933.64,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"Talk to you soon.","index":195,"end_time":935.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":935.12,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"},{"text":"All right, See you.","index":196,"end_time":936.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":935.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a great day, Michael.","index":197,"end_time":937.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":936.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You too, boy.","index":198,"end_time":938.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":937.44,"speaker_name":"Michael Kersten"}],"dateString":"2026-01-20T18:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/83519004309?pwd=JvKSZR6BzSlyNxK5WTgZHYayMsLSKi.1&jst=2","participants":["colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,michael@kerstentalentcapital.com,kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co,paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com,kristen.baller@richeymay.com","guille.santana@marketersindemand.com","michael@kerstentalentcapital.com","kristen@kerstentalentcapitals.co","paula.ocampo@marketersindemand.com","kristen.baller@richeymay.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF9DC7GFAXFVPB2T3SXPCDFJ","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
