    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82863851108?pwd=5bIrn9T1fg2TPcRKxcy9zf3WYHjFWf.1',
    '{"id":"01KF3KCYHKR6MV67GVMENKDAZN","title":"Aligned Growth Engine | Alignment Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Qualification Metrics**\n\nThe team established a clear baseline of **approximately 96 leads per month** with a **historical cost per lead near $400**, noting recent dips in both cost and lead quality that affect conversion (03:18).\n\n- **Georgi explained** that lead cost varies significantly by channel, with Google charging for all leads regardless of quality, inflating average costs, while third-party partners like Rise only charge for qualified leads, offering more controlled spend.\n- The qualification rate is **around 40-45%**, with leads needing to be legitimate restaurant owners seeking point-of-sale (POS) systems, and lifecycle stages are updated manually by sales members after initial contact.\n- The typical sales cycle is about **4 weeks**, with **roughly one-third of qualified leads closing**, translating to a **close rate of about 1 in 3 qualified leads**.\n- The lifetime value (LTV) per customer is estimated at **$11,400 over 28 months**, with a **customer acquisition cost (CAC) payback period under 4 months**, reflecting a healthy investment return despite inherent assumptions and industry volatility.\n\n## **Customer Retention and Industry Challenges**\n\nThe restaurant POS market faces high churn due to external factors, making retention a critical challenge that is largely uncontrollable (12:36).\n\n- **Georgi highlighted** that about **3 out of 10 signed customers never go live** due to restaurant failures, permit issues, or financial problems, emphasizing industry-wide instability.\n- Competitors experience **20-25% quarterly churn**, while their churn is reportedly lower but still significant enough to require constant new customer acquisition.\n- Smaller accounts generating **less than $30,000 monthly revenue** are more prone to churn and payment issues, often requiring collections, whereas larger accounts over $100,000 show more stability.\n- The onboarding team actively follows up weekly for up to 4-6 months to reduce drop-offs, showing a focus on aggressive customer activation.\n\n## **Marketing Spend and Channel Performance**\n\nCurrent marketing spend shows diminishing returns, especially on Google Ads and third-party platforms, prompting a need for diversification and optimization (17:25).\n\n- Georgi reported a recent **budget increase from $20,000-$30,000 to about $78,000 over 3-4 months**, mainly through the Rise platform, which doubled lead volume but failed to increase paying customers due to poor lead quality.\n- Google Ads budget typically caps around **$12,000 monthly** because spend beyond that yields little return; quality remains low despite budget increases.\n- The team prioritizes Google Ads for optimization due to their ability to control ad levers, unlike third-party partners who control traffic sources and pricing models.\n- Georgi expressed openness to exploring **new channels, including podcasts, PR articles, Reddit, and Facebook ads**, reflecting a strategic push toward a more holistic marketing approach beyond paid leads.\n\n## **Lead Quality and Sales Process Optimization**\n\nLead quality is a major concern, with a target to reduce junk leads to **under 30%**, aiming for about **70% qualified leads** to improve conversion and reduce wasted spend (19:33).\n\n- Automated CRM systems integrate incoming leads instantly, notifying sales reps, and apply a **structured 11-12 touchpoint outreach sequence** within the first 5 days to maximize engagement.\n- Junk leads are identified clearly during qualification and moved into a dedicated ''junk'' category within the CRM instead of being deleted, allowing ongoing tracking and analysis.\n- Pre-qualification questions on landing pages help filter leads by concept type and average revenue, yet junk leads still persist, mainly from sources like Google.\n- The sales team reports highest lead quality from the company website (**70-80% qualification**) and a niche YouTube influencer channel whose leads close about **70% of the time**, though volume from this channel is low.\n- Referral programs exist but yield minimal new leads, indicating untapped potential in leveraging word-of-mouth.\n\n## **Strategic Priorities and Next Steps**\n\nThe group agreed on focusing efforts on improving lead quality, optimizing Google Ads, and expanding marketing channels, with a roadmap presentation planned for the following week to align on goals and resource allocation (46:29).\n\n- Georgi emphasized the desire for the marketing partner to act as a strategic advisor, not just executors, trusting their expertise to guide decisions across channels including email, podcasts, and content marketing.\n- The internal team has invested in in-house resources such as a videographer, graphic designer, and developer to support marketing output based on external strategy recommendations.\n- The next meeting is scheduled for **Monday at 9:00 AM Pacific Time**, where the marketing roadmap and campaign goals will be presented.\n- Georgi will share anonymized CRM data showing lead sources and lifecycle stages during the week to enable detailed channel analysis and targeted strategy development.","outline":null,"keywords":["lead qualification","cost per lead","marketing channels","customer acquisition cost","restaurant POS","churn rate"],"overview":"- **Lead Generation Metrics:** Establish baseline of 96 leads/month; lead cost averages $400, with a 40-45% qualification rate.  \n- **Sales Cycle Insights:** Typical sales cycle is 4 weeks; close rate is 1 in 3 qualified leads, lifetime value is $11,400.  \n- **Customer Retention Challenges:** 30% of signed customers never go live; high churn in POS market requires continual new acquisition efforts.  \n- **Marketing Spend Trends:** Budget increased from $20,000 to $78,000; need to optimize Google Ads for better returns and explore new channels.  \n- **Lead Quality Focus:** Aim to reduce junk leads to under 30%; optimize sales outreach with 11-12 touchpoints within 5 days.  \n- **Strategic Next Steps:** Improve lead quality, align on marketing goals; next meeting set for Monday at 9:00 AM Pacific Time.","action_items":"\n**Georgifuntarov**\nShare anonymized CRM lead source and lifecycle stage data to support analysis of lead quality and channel performance by end of the week (37:45)\nCoordinate availability and confirm next meeting for marketing roadmap presentation (Monday 9 AM Pacific) (47:20)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend meeting recording, transcript, and booking link for next session to Georgifuntarov (47:50)\nPrepare marketing strategy and roadmap presentation focused on lead metrics, channels, and optimization for the upcoming meeting (46:50)\n\n**Marketers in Demand Team**\nAnalyze shared lead and channel data to identify cost-effective marketing mix and opportunities for volume/quality improvement (42:15)\nDevelop recommendations to diversify marketing channels beyond Google Ads, including content and PR strategies (29:45)\n"},"duration":49.310001373291016,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":1,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":2,"name":"Dan Rényi"},{"id":3,"name":"georgifuntarov"},{"id":4,"name":"Justin Brown"}],"sentences":[{"text":"What''s going on?","index":0,"end_time":1.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hey.","index":1,"end_time":5.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":4.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":2,"end_time":6.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":5.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Colin.","index":3,"end_time":29.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":29.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"You froze for me.","index":4,"end_time":30.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":29.45,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Oh, really?","index":5,"end_time":32.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":31.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":6,"end_time":33.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":32.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Now you''re back.","index":7,"end_time":36.01,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":35.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Okay, maybe I was just really, really looking at something.","index":8,"end_time":40.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":36.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey there.","index":9,"end_time":43.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":43.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Hey, Georgie.","index":10,"end_time":45.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":44.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How are you guys doing?","index":11,"end_time":46.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":45.53,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Good, how are you?","index":12,"end_time":47.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good.","index":13,"end_time":48.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":48.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Brett is out with food poisoning today, so it''s going to be just me for today.","index":14,"end_time":53.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":49.61,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Sorry to hear that.","index":15,"end_time":55.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":54.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"For.","index":16,"end_time":55.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":55.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For Brett.","index":17,"end_time":56.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":55.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not a fun.","index":18,"end_time":57.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s okay.","index":19,"end_time":58.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":57.76,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"No worries.","index":20,"end_time":59.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":58.52,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But we should be able to.","index":21,"end_time":60.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":59.12,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You know, I can help you guys out with anything.","index":22,"end_time":62.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":60.32,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We can go over anything together today, so not an issue at all.","index":23,"end_time":64.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":62.2,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":24,"end_time":65.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.64,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And before we get started, how was.","index":25,"end_time":67.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were you on vacation last week or just some time off?","index":26,"end_time":70,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":67.68,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, I. I''m.","index":27,"end_time":71.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":70.32,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I''m getting my MBA right now.","index":28,"end_time":73.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":71.96,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I had two classes that I had to take last week that were actually very helpful for our company too.","index":29,"end_time":77.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":73.28,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I was out in the Bay Area just taking classes, networking and things like that.","index":30,"end_time":83.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":78.48,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So, yeah, a little bit busy last week.","index":31,"end_time":86.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":83.95,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Nice.","index":32,"end_time":87.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":86.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":33,"end_time":89.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":88.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"All right, well, yeah, so we''ll dive into our alignment meeting.","index":34,"end_time":93.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":89.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, I know we went through this a bit in our last meeting, Georgie, but I kind of would just start with the frame of what this meeting is.","index":35,"end_time":99.589,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":94.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So it''s not like this is your strategy presentation or this is exactly what needs to be done.","index":36,"end_time":105.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":100.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is my connection breaking up for anyone else or is it just Dan?","index":37,"end_time":108.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":105.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You''re clear for me.","index":38,"end_time":109.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":108.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":39,"end_time":110.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":110.09,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Hear from me too.","index":40,"end_time":111.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":110.37,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":41,"end_time":111.45,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":111.01,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":42,"end_time":112.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":111.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just want to get in alignment.","index":43,"end_time":115.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":114.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you for sending over those high level data points that we had asked for.","index":44,"end_time":118.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just want to, you know, dig into those a little bit further.","index":45,"end_time":121.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":119.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then what this all leads into is us having an understanding of historical context and what Rescue is looking to accomplish with marketing help.","index":46,"end_time":129.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":121.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That then leads into our strategy, which is our roadmap presentation.","index":47,"end_time":133.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":129.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Colin, let me jump in for one second.","index":48,"end_time":136.93,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":134.57,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"I just want to introduce Tristan.","index":49,"end_time":138.09,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":136.93,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So I forgot Tristan wasn''t on the first.","index":50,"end_time":140.41,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":138.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"No, all good.","index":51,"end_time":141.01,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":140.41,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"All good.","index":52,"end_time":141.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":141.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":53,"end_time":141.73,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":141.45,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"So.","index":54,"end_time":142.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":141.73,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So Georgie, Tristan is my business partner, the other co founder of Marketers in Demand.","index":55,"end_time":148.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":142.57,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"When it comes to alignment especially and just analyzing data, listening to Tristan and Colin go back and forth is quite interesting.","index":56,"end_time":159.05,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":149.05,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"And they''re both.","index":57,"end_time":160.81,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":159.77,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"They''re both very good at it, at analyzing CRMs and databases.","index":58,"end_time":164.49,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":160.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Tristan has a background working for Oracle IBM, so just wanted to introduce him real quick.","index":59,"end_time":170.57,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":164.81,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"He and Colin are gonna have probably the majority of the questions for today, but Tristan, I''ll stop talking once you.","index":60,"end_time":175.21,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":170.97,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Introduce yourself real quick, by the way.","index":61,"end_time":177.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":175.21,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I''m sure you guys probably are already.","index":62,"end_time":179.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":177.53,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Can we record a meeting so I can share with Brett?","index":63,"end_time":180.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":179.01,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"By the way, because we''ve got it going.","index":64,"end_time":182.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":180.85,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we have that.","index":65,"end_time":185.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":182.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Thanks, Georgie.","index":66,"end_time":186.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Nice to to meet you.","index":67,"end_time":187.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Colin just got off to a good start.","index":68,"end_time":189.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I was gonna let him just keep rolling, but.","index":69,"end_time":191.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":189.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But we''re excited to get into it and talk some more today, so.","index":70,"end_time":196.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.93,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Good to meet you, Tristan.","index":71,"end_time":197.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":196.96,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":72,"end_time":199.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":198.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, yeah, I want to start by grounding us in the numbers that you provided.","index":73,"end_time":202.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":199.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we always make sure that we''re talking from the same baseline.","index":74,"end_time":204.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":75,"end_time":205,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":204.88,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So you sent for 20, 25, roughly 96 leads per month, cost per lead.","index":76,"end_time":211.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":205,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Historically around the $400 mark.","index":77,"end_time":213.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":211.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It seems like maybe the cost per lead has dipped down a bit, but the quality has also dipped down with that.","index":78,"end_time":220.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that true?","index":79,"end_time":222.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":80,"end_time":223.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":222.97,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So it''s the.","index":81,"end_time":224.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":223.41,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s kind of hard to put exact number on a cost per lead.","index":82,"end_time":227.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":224.57,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s kind of like an average just because we have some places where, you know, pay like 100 bucks a lead.","index":83,"end_time":232.89,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":227.61,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Then you go to Google and, and here''s the other part, actually.","index":84,"end_time":237.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":232.89,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So for example, for Google, we pay for every single lead.","index":85,"end_time":240.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":237.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":86,"end_time":240.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":240.29,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Doesn''t matter if it''s like a junk lead or if it''s like a real person.","index":87,"end_time":243.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":240.61,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We pay for everything.","index":88,"end_time":244.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":244.01,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So the average is pretty high there.","index":89,"end_time":246.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":244.93,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Just because you''re paying for a lot of junk too.","index":90,"end_time":248.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":246.53,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Where with our third party partners like Rise, where we are listed like you know, number two, three, we pay only for the glue leads with them.","index":91,"end_time":256.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":249.06,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So therefore it''s a little bit more controlled.","index":92,"end_time":258.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":256.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So it''s kind of hard.","index":93,"end_time":259.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":258.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s no like a single way to measure it but.","index":94,"end_time":261.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":259.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":95,"end_time":262.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":261.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, you''d have to go buy channel.","index":96,"end_time":263.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":262.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":97,"end_time":263.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"For the most part, 4 or 500.","index":98,"end_time":265.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":263.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s just kind of like what we''ve seen across multiple places.","index":99,"end_time":268.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":265.54,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":100,"end_time":269.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":268.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And that''ll be a big piece, you know, if we do move forward with this engagement, diving into the actual accounts, seeing because.","index":101,"end_time":275.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":269.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we''re going to want to break it down by channel.","index":102,"end_time":277.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":275.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''ll give us the best picture of what''s coming through.","index":103,"end_time":279.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":277.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And your CRM, I''m sure it is based on the life cycle stages that you sent over.","index":104,"end_time":285.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":279.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like then we can see source attribution, things like that and really make a, a data backed decision on the channels to attack a few other ones.","index":105,"end_time":294.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":285.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So what I was able to get out of that is that it looks like your close rate is 1 out of every 3 qualified leads.","index":106,"end_time":300.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":294.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that correct?","index":107,"end_time":302,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":301.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so I think it was in the email already.","index":108,"end_time":304.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":302.56,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But roughly the percentages that we.","index":109,"end_time":306.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":304.72,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And this is like historical, not just this year, but over the last few years.","index":110,"end_time":309.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":306.56,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So leads obviously 100% from there usually qualify.","index":111,"end_time":313.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":309.4,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Around 40, 45% of the leads actually qualify.","index":112,"end_time":315.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":313.12,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We actually get to talk to them.","index":113,"end_time":317.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":315.88,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"The proposal stage, usually right around the 30 to 35% of the total leads of the 100%.","index":114,"end_time":323.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":318.44,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Again, we get them to some kind of proposal stage.","index":115,"end_time":326.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":323.64,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And once we reach to the proposal stage, where we''ve given them numbers and everything, usually we were about to.","index":116,"end_time":332.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":327.24,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We''re able to close about half of those people.","index":117,"end_time":334.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":332.88,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":118,"end_time":335.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":335.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Cashier has been lower for many different reasons.","index":119,"end_time":339.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":335.8,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So this past year was lower.","index":120,"end_time":340.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":339.29,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But historically, usually right around half of them, once they get to proposal stage, were able to close.","index":121,"end_time":345.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":340.61,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Usually.","index":122,"end_time":345.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":345.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":123,"end_time":346.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":124,"end_time":346.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I want to dive into those reasons in a minute.","index":125,"end_time":348.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":346.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You mentioned 40 to 45% of those leads coming in are qualified.","index":126,"end_time":353.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Can we go through the qualification criteria?","index":127,"end_time":355.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":353.73,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, honestly, not very hard to get somebody to be qualified.","index":128,"end_time":358.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":356.25,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You need to be a restaurant.","index":129,"end_time":359.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":358.93,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You need to be a real owner of the restaurant that actually is looking for a point of sale.","index":130,"end_time":363.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":359.93,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We do not do retail, so sometimes people will call for retail system.","index":131,"end_time":367.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":364.44,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We don''t do those.","index":132,"end_time":368.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":367.6,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So honestly, for the most part, if somebody answers, they are for the most part qualified, unless they ask for something outside of what we normally do.","index":133,"end_time":377.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":369.48,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So, yeah, it basically just needs to be a legitimate, rational owner looking for a point of sale.","index":134,"end_time":382.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":379,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"From there, even if it''s six months out, we still count as a qualified opportunity because we can follow up with them, et cetera.","index":135,"end_time":389.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":382.84,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Um, but yeah, just we just need to talk with actual legitimate restaurant owners essentially, that are looking for a point of sale.","index":136,"end_time":394.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":389.54,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":137,"end_time":395.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so was that that qualification and life cycle stage are then updated, I guess, when they have that first meeting with your team?","index":138,"end_time":401.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":395.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":139,"end_time":402.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":401.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yes.","index":140,"end_time":402.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":402.14,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And from there we actually get a feel for.","index":141,"end_time":404.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":402.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Is it six months out, is it a week out?","index":142,"end_time":406.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":404.26,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"For the most part.","index":143,"end_time":407.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":406.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Very rarely do they like reach out, like six months out.","index":144,"end_time":410.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":407.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Typically like same month next month, maybe three months out at the most.","index":145,"end_time":414.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":410.38,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s usually the time frame a typical sales cycle usually run around four weeks for a typical deal.","index":146,"end_time":419.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":414.74,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":147,"end_time":420.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I mean, with restaurant owner mindset, something that should be front of mind being a POS tends to fall towards.","index":148,"end_time":427.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":420.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Towards the bottom of the list of priorities.","index":149,"end_time":429.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":427.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, gotcha.","index":150,"end_time":431.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":429.98,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":151,"end_time":431.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so you said the estimated value of these customers.","index":152,"end_time":435.619,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":431.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m just going to use LTV as that metric.","index":153,"end_time":437.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.619,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s around $11,400 over 28 months.","index":154,"end_time":440.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":437.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"With which when we compare that to your CAC, that gets you guys CAC payback, basically just under four months, which is a pretty healthy metric.","index":155,"end_time":448.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":441.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I wanted to dive into that and see what you were actually like striving for.","index":156,"end_time":452.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":448.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, do you want to make money?","index":157,"end_time":453.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is it making that back faster?","index":158,"end_time":455.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":453.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does LTV need to increase?","index":159,"end_time":456.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, what does that look like?","index":160,"end_time":458.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":457.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":459.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":458.85,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So out of all the numbers that I''ve given you, those are the two, they''re the most, I would say, guesses.","index":162,"end_time":464.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":459.29,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"All the other ones, you know, there''s, we have data behind these two are very hard.","index":163,"end_time":468.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":464.21,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And I''ll give you the reasons why it''s very hard to actually calculate.","index":164,"end_time":470.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":468.49,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So these are just some assumptions that I''ve made.","index":165,"end_time":472.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":470.73,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So our contract is 28 months.","index":166,"end_time":475.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":473.56,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And basically how I got to this number is our 28 month agreement multiplied times the average amount that we make per customer.","index":167,"end_time":482.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":475.96,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Now with that being said, I would say three out of 10 customers, they sign up with us, never go live just because restaurants are just very high fail rate essentially.","index":168,"end_time":493.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":482.84,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Also a lot of our customers don''t stay with us for as long as they should throughout the 28 months.","index":169,"end_time":498.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":493.48,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"The whole industry as a whole is pretty high failure rate industry.","index":170,"end_time":501.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":498.53,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Obviously some of them stay way longer than 28 months.","index":171,"end_time":505.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":503.25,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Some of them stay only a few months and then we have to send them to collections because they don''t want to pay, you know, whatever.","index":172,"end_time":510.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":505.57,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So what I''m trying to say is very hard to put a number and I don''t think it''s even possible to calculate an exact number.","index":173,"end_time":515.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":511.25,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I''m just giving a very base level.","index":174,"end_time":517.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":515.65,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"If somebody signs up, put up and sticks through the initial term of 28 months, that''s kind of like our payoff.","index":175,"end_time":522.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":517.25,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Same thing with the customer acquisition cost, again like $500.","index":176,"end_time":528.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":523.33,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have a good idea of how much it costs us to acquire a customer.","index":177,"end_time":530.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":528.35,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"From there it''s a little bit of unknown, for example, how much the commission is going to be to the salespeople.","index":178,"end_time":536.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":531.07,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s a variable there.","index":179,"end_time":538.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":536.59,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s a variable as far as how long it''s going to take us to do the onboarding with them.","index":180,"end_time":541.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":538.75,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Typically we have a process, but sometimes it can take longer or shorter depending on how responsive they are.","index":181,"end_time":547.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":542.11,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So hard to put a true cost on that as well.","index":182,"end_time":550.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":547.87,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So that''s like a very rough number.","index":183,"end_time":552.59,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":550.75,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Um, but as a whole, to give you like an idea, all of our work is upfront.","index":184,"end_time":557.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":553.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Everything that we spend and help us cost is basically in those first two weeks commissions, paying for leads, training.","index":185,"end_time":563.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":557.21,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Once we pay that 1500 $2000.","index":186,"end_time":566.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":563.61,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Even if it''s $3000, whatever it is, it''s actually probably not 3000, but let''s call it $2000.","index":187,"end_time":570.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":566.05,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Our cost after is very, very minimal.","index":188,"end_time":573.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":570.57,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I would call it as passive as it gets.","index":189,"end_time":576.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":574.09,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And because of that, our margins are pretty high after that if they stick around and.","index":190,"end_time":581.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":577.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But yeah, so everything for us is like investing upfront and after that, essentially our only overhead.","index":191,"end_time":587.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":582.71,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Realistically, just wages.","index":192,"end_time":588.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":587.39,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":193,"end_time":589.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so, you know, if we''re looking to say, let''s just say this is one of our goals or okrs or what we operate on.","index":194,"end_time":596.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":589.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So objectives and key results.","index":195,"end_time":598.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for looking at this, you know, CAC payback that''s already at under four months, what are you looking to get that number to?","index":196,"end_time":604.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":598.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you trying to make that back in the first month?","index":197,"end_time":606.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":604.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or is it something like we actually need a better understanding of?","index":198,"end_time":610.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":606.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, if a restaurant has this many terminals, they tend to stay on longer, we tend to make more money a lot faster.","index":199,"end_time":615.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":610.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How does that breakdown work?","index":200,"end_time":616.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":615.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think the biggest part of it is the salespeople commission and the actual amount we pay to Google or whoever.","index":201,"end_time":623.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":617.53,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":202,"end_time":623.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":623.61,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Those are, I don''t want to say set in stone, but pretty hard to like dramatically decrease.","index":203,"end_time":629.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":625.05,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And because of that, all of them, actually I think that where we are right now are pretty hard to move just because, you know, we pay our people hourly for the onboarding.","index":204,"end_time":640.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":631.21,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So we can''t really change that.","index":205,"end_time":642.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":641.03,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":206,"end_time":642.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":642.23,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I guess like the cost per lead can drop down, but even if you drop it down but 100, $200, it doesn''t really move the needle that much, to be honest with you.","index":207,"end_time":650.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":643.51,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Same thing with the commissions.","index":208,"end_time":651.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":650.55,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We cannot really, you know, dramatically.","index":209,"end_time":653.069,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":651.71,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"All of a sudden I cut in half the commission.","index":210,"end_time":654.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":653.069,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So any kind of improvement there will be, you know, not as significant.","index":211,"end_time":658.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":654.55,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"The pricing on the other side, the, the, the lifetime value of the customer.","index":212,"end_time":664.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":660.71,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have played around with a lot of different price instruction, including a new one that we''re going to be making here in the next week or so.","index":213,"end_time":670.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":665.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You''ll probably see from your research in our industry has kind of become a little bit of a bottom to the race as far as pricing.","index":214,"end_time":676.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":671.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And it''s kind of hard to increase that very significantly unless you have something that nobody else has, which is very hard because you come up with it and everybody else copies it in the following month or two.","index":215,"end_time":689.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":677.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I guess what I''m trying to say is not necessarily improving that ratio deal to deal, but mostly maybe the volume of deals to kind of like improve that.","index":216,"end_time":698.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":689.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s just kind of like where my thoughts are.","index":217,"end_time":700.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":699.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But it doesn''t mean there''s no other way to improve it.","index":218,"end_time":702.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":700.74,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''re looking at, you know, increasing lead Quality, increasing lead, quantity, and really seeing how we can drive to marginally improve that 3.7 turnaround, which again, is very strong for the industry.","index":219,"end_time":713.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":702.86,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":714.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":714.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And I think, like, maybe that''s a good way to look at it as the deals that we do get.","index":221,"end_time":718.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":714.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I think that''s a pretty good ratio already.","index":222,"end_time":720.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":718.79,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"The problem is the deal that we do not get or the junk that we pay for.","index":223,"end_time":724.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":720.71,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I think that''s where we have to absorb a lot of those that maybe we''re not necessarily thinking about when you''re talking about this, you know, ratio.","index":224,"end_time":731.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":724.15,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And that''s where we can get ourselves caught a little bit of losing money.","index":225,"end_time":734.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":731.27,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I think like you said, like the quality of the leads, so we get to maximize that is probably where we can improve things rather than the actual deals we already close.","index":226,"end_time":742.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":734.79,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":227,"end_time":743.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":742.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because, you know, if you pay, let''s just toss out numbers, three grand on Google Ads, you get two leads.","index":228,"end_time":747.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know whether either of them move forward, one of them move forward, both of them move forward.","index":229,"end_time":750.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":747.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You still paid $3,000 for those leads.","index":230,"end_time":752.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":750.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So.","index":231,"end_time":752.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":752.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":232,"end_time":753.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":752.99,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, sorry guys, I had a question.","index":233,"end_time":756.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.67,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Going back to the metrics.","index":234,"end_time":758.03,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.47,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So you mentioned that, you know, restaurants are not always easy because many of them go out of business and whatnot.","index":235,"end_time":764.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":758.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Do you have an idea about your churn rate or maybe your net recurring revenue just so we know if, like, if we have a leaky bucket.","index":236,"end_time":773.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":764.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So how much.","index":237,"end_time":774.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":773.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How much of your customer base are you losing month to month?","index":238,"end_time":777.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":774.39,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah, I cannot share those exact numbers, but what I can tell you is that I can talk about other companies actually that publicly traded.","index":239,"end_time":784.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":777.98,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Very.","index":240,"end_time":785.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":785.42,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So if you look, ours is much better than other companies.","index":241,"end_time":789.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":785.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But it''s not abnormal to see our competitors, for example, to have 20, 25 churn rate every quarter.","index":242,"end_time":797.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":790.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s pretty significant.","index":243,"end_time":799.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":798.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Ours is not that high.","index":244,"end_time":801.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":800.14,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Um, but it''s definitely a concern in our industry that you have to replenish your customer base every quarter because you get, you know, you lose a significant chunk.","index":245,"end_time":810.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":802.31,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Again, just because the nature of the industry.","index":246,"end_time":811.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":810.43,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":247,"end_time":813.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":812.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think all that we need to know is whether we have a leaky bucket that needs to be addressed.","index":248,"end_time":818.469,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":813.43,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because if it''s very leaky, then it doesn''t make sense to go into growth.","index":249,"end_time":823.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":818.469,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"We need to fix that first.","index":250,"end_time":824.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":823.59,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"But then, you know, you make.","index":251,"end_time":826.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":824.83,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":252,"end_time":826.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":826.47,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So in honesty, we''ve looked at as well, and like I said, some of our customers that we sign up, you know, people have gone through a sales process.","index":253,"end_time":833.91,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":827.03,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We''ve agreed on everything, and then they actually are agreeing to do business with us.","index":254,"end_time":837.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":834.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Don''t even Go live.","index":255,"end_time":838.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":837.33,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And we''ve looked at those a lot as like, is this something that we are doing?","index":256,"end_time":841.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":838.45,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And no matter how many times we''ve looked at it, it''s just the way the industry is.","index":257,"end_time":845.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":841.65,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And a lot of times what happens is that somebody will sign up and they just can''t get their permit from the city.","index":258,"end_time":849.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":845.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"They won''t let them open up because they cannot pass fire inspection.","index":259,"end_time":852.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":849.65,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Their lease fell through.","index":260,"end_time":853.69,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":852.53,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":261,"end_time":854.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":853.69,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So what I''m trying to say is those situations are.","index":262,"end_time":856.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":854.21,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Have nothing to do with us in our product.","index":263,"end_time":858.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":856.85,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s just the industry permits going out of business.","index":264,"end_time":862.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":858.93,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s a very low margin for restaurants.","index":265,"end_time":865.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":863.14,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I think a good restaurant probably operates between 5 and maybe 10 operating margin.","index":266,"end_time":871.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":865.38,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"The most of them are 5 or below.","index":267,"end_time":874.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":872.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":268,"end_time":874.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":874.62,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So they have very small margins to make money.","index":269,"end_time":876.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":874.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And that shows in the way they operate.","index":270,"end_time":879.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":877.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And this is why they go out of business a lot.","index":271,"end_time":880.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":879.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So a lot of the reasons that we cannot control those reasons.","index":272,"end_time":883.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":880.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"What I''m trying to say.","index":273,"end_time":884.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":883.62,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So even there is a little bit of leaky bucket, but there''s nothing we can do about it.","index":274,"end_time":888.23,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":884.3,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s not just.","index":275,"end_time":888.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":888.23,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"This is the industry.","index":276,"end_time":889.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":888.63,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":277,"end_time":889.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":889.35,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"No company can do anything about that.","index":278,"end_time":891.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":889.71,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":279,"end_time":892.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":891.47,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":280,"end_time":892.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":892.11,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Okay, thanks with that.","index":281,"end_time":894.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Just to peel that.","index":282,"end_time":895.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That layer back a little bit further.","index":283,"end_time":897.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":895.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I talk to sales teams all the time and I see like, all right, yeah, we did qualify them.","index":284,"end_time":904.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":899.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We kind of had some, like, gut feeling maybe something wasn''t perfectly aligned.","index":285,"end_time":908.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":904.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you guys see that?","index":286,"end_time":909.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":908.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And maybe any correlation between the clients that do churn?","index":287,"end_time":912.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.75,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, you know, we had a feeling that this.","index":288,"end_time":914.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":913.02,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We signed over 28 months, six months later, we knew it was going to go bad.","index":289,"end_time":918.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":914.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"If there is any, I would say is accounts, they have very low sales.","index":290,"end_time":922.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":918.94,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And by low sales, to kind of give you guys an idea, and you even laugh at this because I have the same question sometimes how that''s even possible.","index":291,"end_time":929.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":922.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Businesses, they do under $30,000 a month, which I actually have a joke that I call them hobbies, not businesses, because, you know, at that point, right.","index":292,"end_time":938.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":929.98,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s like a few hundred dollars a day.","index":293,"end_time":939.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":938.14,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Like, what are you doing?","index":294,"end_time":940.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":939.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":295,"end_time":940.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":940.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Um, but unfortunately, there''s a lot of those businesses that exist, and it doesn''t mean that they''re always doing that much in sales, but whatever, something happened, Covid.","index":296,"end_time":947.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":940.83,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"They were not able to recover.","index":297,"end_time":948.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":947.19,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Whatever.","index":298,"end_time":949.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":948.59,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right?","index":299,"end_time":949.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":949.07,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Or they''re trying to get up and running.","index":300,"end_time":950.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":949.39,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Those businesses that do like, you know, around 30,000 or less even, you know, those customers, you know, they''re very price conscious, obviously.","index":301,"end_time":959.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":951.47,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And as soon as something is not right, we have a Lot of issues with them, retaining them, getting them up and running.","index":302,"end_time":965.51,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":959.15,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And it''s just very hard because anytime something kind of goes off the normal path and then they incur a cost or something doesn''t operate like they, they need to, it becomes a huge deal and it becomes kind of like, you know, almost like a deal breaker that they have to go to collections because they''re, they want to cancel, they don''t want to pay cancellation fees to cover our costs and then we have to send them to collections a lot of times.","index":303,"end_time":986.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":965.51,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So those small accounts is what I''m trying to say is usually the problematic ones.","index":304,"end_time":989.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":986.12,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Car accounts like hundred thousand and above, like more like a watercolor average restaurants are not as there''s not as many issues with those.","index":305,"end_time":996.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":990.12,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":306,"end_time":997.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":996.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I mean Georgie, looking at these numbers, things look relatively healthy in many ways from a metric standpoint.","index":307,"end_time":1005.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":998.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But having a conversation with you and Brett last or sorry the week before last, there''s definitely some anecdotal information that we need to pull out of these.","index":308,"end_time":1013.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1005.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one of those is, I know you said you''ve worked with a few marketing agencies in the past.","index":309,"end_time":1017.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The recommendation would largely be like well we just need to put more money into it.","index":310,"end_time":1020.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1017.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I know you guys have fluctuated your spend over the years of what you''re doing per channel and especially with a channel like goog ads, we are paying no matter what the quality that comes through is.","index":311,"end_time":1031.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when you did have those increases in monthly budget, let''s just say for Google Ads specifically, did you see junk.","index":312,"end_time":1038.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1032.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Climb a lot more?","index":313,"end_time":1039.28,"speaker_id":4,"start_time":1038.52,"speaker_name":"Justin Brown"},{"text":"Were you seeing quality climb as well or you know why?","index":314,"end_time":1042.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1039.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so it was yes, definitely.","index":315,"end_time":1046.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1043.52,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So there was a. I think with Google overall and again I just using our company as an example because I don''t have access to other companies data.","index":316,"end_time":1052.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1046.24,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t know if it''s strategy to be an AI is kind of contributing to Google.","index":317,"end_time":1056.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1052.96,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Google as a whole not being as effective or just we have not been able to be managed to manage our own account as well as it should be.","index":318,"end_time":1062.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1056.44,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But there''s definitely been more junk from Google.","index":319,"end_time":1065.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1063,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You know, overall just the quality has not been there.","index":320,"end_time":1068.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1066.04,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We did increase the budget there a little bit.","index":321,"end_time":1070.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1068.92,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Most of the increasing budget that we had these last four or five months when we really tried to kick things up was through this company called Rise that I mentioned to you that we do ranking on essentially.","index":322,"end_time":1080.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1070.76,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So normally we are listening there on number two.","index":323,"end_time":1082.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1080.76,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Number three.","index":324,"end_time":1083.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1082.64,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We actually did try to get listed number one because you get, you know, I think those months we got like 200 leads a month.","index":325,"end_time":1088.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1083.64,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So almost it deal with our leads.","index":326,"end_time":1090.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1088.84,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":327,"end_time":1090.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1090.64,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But they were, we were not able to convert them into paying business whether they were junk or they were just, you know, not as qualified as they should be.","index":328,"end_time":1099.32,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1091.72,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And yeah, we upped our budget.","index":329,"end_time":1101.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1099.559,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You know, I don''t remember what it was from 20, 30 grand overall for over market to 7 or 80 for three or four months.","index":330,"end_time":1106.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1101.64,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":331,"end_time":1107,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1106.64,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s a substantial increase.","index":332,"end_time":1108.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1107.08,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right?","index":333,"end_time":1108.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1108.44,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":334,"end_time":1109.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1108.76,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we just did not see more business being signed up.","index":335,"end_time":1111.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1109.12,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Could it be our salespeople maybe as well?","index":336,"end_time":1114.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1112.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But there is no way that there''s not at least a little bit of uptick.","index":337,"end_time":1117.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1114.94,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, that''s kind of just what we saw.","index":338,"end_time":1120.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1117.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There was definitely more junk overall and just less qualified deals.","index":339,"end_time":1123.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1120.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":340,"end_time":1124.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1123.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And you know we do see that and it takes a lot of work of being in the account every week and managing, you know, what you''re seeing or even on the PMAX side, you know, setting up reports back to Google Ads to tell them what a junk lead is.","index":341,"end_time":1134.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1124.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So there''s, there''s a few different things that we can look at there.","index":342,"end_time":1137.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1135.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Junk, unfortunately on a platform like Google is still going to come through because people are always finding out ways to get their competitors spend more money.","index":343,"end_time":1144.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1137.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, you might have toast tab out there just paying someone to click on your guys ads.","index":344,"end_time":1148.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1144.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You never know.","index":345,"end_time":1148.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1148.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It just needs to be a healthy ratio.","index":346,"end_time":1151.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1149.8,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Like we obviously aware that we''re not gonna, we''re never gonna work with somebody where there''s absolutely no junk.","index":347,"end_time":1156.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1151.6,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":348,"end_time":1156.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1156.16,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It just, it just cannot be like 50, 50, 40, 60, you know, we cannot be on those levels of junk where we''re getting like less like actual leads than junk.","index":349,"end_time":1165.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1156.52,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":350,"end_time":1165.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1165.16,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I mean 20, 30%, whatever.","index":351,"end_time":1167.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1165.88,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Like we understand that.","index":352,"end_time":1168.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1167.76,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":353,"end_time":1169.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1168.96,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Just needs to be LTE ratio between the two.","index":354,"end_time":1171.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1169.16,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":355,"end_time":1171.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so if you were to put a number to that, like that healthy range, what number is in your head?","index":356,"end_time":1175.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Under 30?","index":357,"end_time":1176.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1175.81,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I think I want to get it under 30.","index":358,"end_time":1178.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1176.41,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay, so 70% quality.","index":359,"end_time":1179.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1178.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think that, what if we get around a 7% quality?","index":360,"end_time":1182.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1179.77,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I think we''ll be in good shape.","index":361,"end_time":1183.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1182.21,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":362,"end_time":1183.61,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1183.29,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":363,"end_time":1184.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":364,"end_time":1184.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1184.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Georgia, can I ask one question?","index":365,"end_time":1186.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1184.61,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know from the, if, if it doesn''t get to that level, what, what is the, the issue there?","index":366,"end_time":1193.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1186.25,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is it the time spent from the sales team qualifying those or kind of like what''s the, the major issue there?","index":367,"end_time":1199.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1193.33,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If you''re not able to increase the, the percentage of quality?","index":368,"end_time":1203.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1199.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like what''s my, my theory behind why it would not be happening or what do you mean?","index":369,"end_time":1208.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1203.6,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, like because I''m just wondering, you Know, optimizing for more quality.","index":370,"end_time":1213.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1208.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like is it the manual effort that goes into that?","index":371,"end_time":1216.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1213.2,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is that the issue where it takes up time or like what?","index":372,"end_time":1218.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1216.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I, I don''t think so.","index":373,"end_time":1220.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1219.28,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I''ll kind of give you an idea of what we do once a league comes in.","index":374,"end_time":1223.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1220.72,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t think that''s the issue.","index":375,"end_time":1224.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1223.44,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So we have an automated system first or any lead from any source, it automatically gets plugged into our CRM and notifies the sales rep immediately as, as soon as it comes in.","index":376,"end_time":1233.88,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1225.6,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We don''t call leads on the weekends, so that, that could be contributing a little bit to it.","index":377,"end_time":1238.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1234.28,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":378,"end_time":1238.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1238.12,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So if something comes on Saturday or Sunday, we don''t call it until Monday.","index":379,"end_time":1241.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1238.28,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So that''s obviously not ideal, but that could be contributing.","index":380,"end_time":1244.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1241.28,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But the leads that come in while we are here, which is majority of them, we have a, so we, we do a week long cycle sequence of calling them twice the first day.","index":381,"end_time":1256.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1244.84,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"They get an automatic email, we text them and we have like you know, 11 or 12 touch points in those first five days.","index":382,"end_time":1263.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1256.2,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"If they''re truly interested in talking to us, there is no way that we didn''t reach out.","index":383,"end_time":1267.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1263.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s not our process, what I''m trying to say.","index":384,"end_time":1270.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1267.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s just legitimate.","index":385,"end_time":1272.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1271.22,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"They''re not interested or they''re just not even like a real lead.","index":386,"end_time":1274.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1272.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":387,"end_time":1274.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1274.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I don''t think it''s necessarily our process of why they''re not being qualified.","index":388,"end_time":1279.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1275.78,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And even when we, because some of them actually do answer and they just tell us, I have no idea why you''re calling.","index":389,"end_time":1284.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1280.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I never enter my information anywhere.","index":390,"end_time":1285.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1284.34,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It must be some scammer just putting my information over the Internet.","index":391,"end_time":1289.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1286.34,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We do get, not a lot, but we do get some of those.","index":392,"end_time":1291.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1289.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I think it''s just something within the optimization whether it''s Google, where you know, whatever we''re getting our leads from.","index":393,"end_time":1297.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1292.74,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I think that''s majority of where the issue is coming from.","index":394,"end_time":1300.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1297.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay, got that.","index":395,"end_time":1302.419,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1301.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And, and what happened?","index":396,"end_time":1303.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1302.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or well, I guess two, two questions here.","index":397,"end_time":1306.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1303.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, when you say some of the leads are just purely junk, it could they be filtered out earlier in the process?","index":398,"end_time":1314.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1307.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like even before you kick off that workflow?","index":399,"end_time":1316.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1314.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like I, I don''t know, I''m just wondering maybe where do you draw the line between like junk and not a good lead?","index":400,"end_time":1325.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1316.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or could you help us like maybe draw a line the same?","index":401,"end_time":1327.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1325.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like what, what do you all do internally?","index":402,"end_time":1329.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1327.94,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Usually it''s like very obvious there is no, it''s usually it''s not like close.","index":403,"end_time":1333.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1329.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s kind of, it''s usually like kind of what I said is basically like why even calling.","index":404,"end_time":1337.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1333.66,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I have no idea why you''re calling me.","index":405,"end_time":1338.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1337.06,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I''ve never entered my information anywhere.","index":406,"end_time":1339.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1338.22,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Or hey, like yes, thanks for calling me.","index":407,"end_time":1342.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1340.41,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I''m talking to five other companies.","index":408,"end_time":1343.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1342.21,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":409,"end_time":1343.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1343.33,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Like, I mean can you call me back tomorrow?","index":410,"end_time":1345.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1343.57,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s still qualified deal.","index":411,"end_time":1346.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1345.09,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":412,"end_time":1346.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1346.17,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So usually it''s pretty clear cut.","index":413,"end_time":1348.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1346.65,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s no real, you know, it''s not a close call usually.","index":414,"end_time":1352.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1348.57,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":415,"end_time":1352.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1352.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Some things and I don''t know if we''ve shared our landing page with you guys yet or not.","index":416,"end_time":1356.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1353.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So something we''ve done on our landing pages is that we actually ask a few questions to kind of, you know, pre qualify them at least a little bit.","index":417,"end_time":1363.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1356.73,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So we ask them for the concept type, we ask them for their average revenue.","index":418,"end_time":1367.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1363.61,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So that way we''re using at least a little bit of, you know, a filtering process on.","index":419,"end_time":1371.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1367.62,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"People don''t just submit information without even knowing what it is.","index":420,"end_time":1374.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1371.78,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And even then we''re still seeing some junk obviously.","index":421,"end_time":1377.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1374.66,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay, got that.","index":422,"end_time":1379.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1378.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then what happened?","index":423,"end_time":1382.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So what do you do with the junk lead at some point?","index":424,"end_time":1386.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1382.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Do you delete them from the CRM or like what is that process?","index":425,"end_time":1389.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1386.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, we don''t delete them.","index":426,"end_time":1390.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1389.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So we have, so we''ve actually expanded on the stages in a pipeline.","index":427,"end_time":1394.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1390.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Used to be a little bit more simple but now we have, we have a junk category essentially we don''t delete them, we just put them in our junk category.","index":428,"end_time":1401.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1394.98,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So there is a list of those leads that are just junk.","index":429,"end_time":1404.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1401.73,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So yeah, some of the categories that we have it goes from lead to I think we call it discovery not qualified but the same idea, discovery qualified.","index":430,"end_time":1412.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1405.17,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have demo booked, demo showed up, demo didn''t show up, proposal sent, closing stage, we have a deal, one deal lost.","index":431,"end_time":1421.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1413.249,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have also a marketing reactivation which means that we have talked to them, they''re just not ready to buy yet.","index":432,"end_time":1427.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1421.89,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So they kind of go through basically like a email sequence where they get emails every week or so and then the last category is junk.","index":433,"end_time":1436.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1427.71,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So we don''t delete them, they stay in the CRM.","index":434,"end_time":1438.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1436.15,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay, got that.","index":435,"end_time":1440.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1438.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And so I mean maybe back to one of Colin''s original questions.","index":436,"end_time":1445.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1440.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just like the, you''re looking for more volume, right?","index":437,"end_time":1449.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1445.47,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"More leads but higher quality.","index":438,"end_time":1450.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1449.07,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like what?","index":439,"end_time":1451.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1450.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How do you balance those two things?","index":440,"end_time":1453.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1451.82,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because there will always be, and we''ve mentioned that, you know, there will always be some filters that you need to put in place.","index":441,"end_time":1459.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1453.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, that''s just the nature of advertising.","index":442,"end_time":1461.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1459.66,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s going to be some waste there.","index":443,"end_time":1463.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1461.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I''m just trying to think from our perspective Are we really optimizing your existing ad spend as much as possible?","index":444,"end_time":1469.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1463.34,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is that the goal or is the goal to get more volume?","index":445,"end_time":1471.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1469.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Could you maybe like weigh those, those things for us?","index":446,"end_time":1475.1,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1472.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think it''s both.","index":447,"end_time":1476.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1475.66,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So the like where we at right now as far as quality and volume, actually the quantity is not, it''s still in a good place.","index":448,"end_time":1488.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1476.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I think the quality though is just not there at all.","index":449,"end_time":1491,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1488.16,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And I think that''s affected our total closed deals right now.","index":450,"end_time":1495.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1492.2,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And we''re starting to even think about like maybe we should start looking at, instead of spending those extra $50,000 in spend with these companies, maybe we should just hire outside salespeople and have them do more of a door to door because that, that money is better spent there with 10 people.","index":451,"end_time":1510.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1496.12,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":452,"end_time":1510.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1510.43,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So yeah, it''s, it''s.","index":453,"end_time":1513.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1512.39,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t know the best way to manage it.","index":454,"end_time":1515.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1513.91,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Obviously this is why like we''re talking to you guys but we historically has been better and has dropped off and we''re trying to figure out is Google.","index":455,"end_time":1523.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1515.71,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I think Google is the one place to me that we always have as much control as possible with these other companies.","index":456,"end_time":1529.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1523.75,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I cannot tell a third party company how to get their leads or where to get their leads.","index":457,"end_time":1533.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1530.07,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":458,"end_time":1534.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1533.99,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We get listed on their website with number 1, 2, 3, whatever position and the traffic is what it is.","index":459,"end_time":1539.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1534.11,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":460,"end_time":1539.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1539.36,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"They get to make those decisions, how they advertise, how they get their traffic.","index":461,"end_time":1543.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1539.56,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Whereas with Google we get to put the levers and make decisions and improve leads or not improve leads.","index":462,"end_time":1549.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1543.48,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":463,"end_time":1549.8,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1549.52,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So to me Google is kind of like a key account that we can use but unfortunately has not been able to provide for us either good quality or good quantity recently.","index":464,"end_time":1560.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1550.04,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And I know Colin, we don''t have the budget allocation across channels.","index":465,"end_time":1566.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1561.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Can you.","index":466,"end_time":1567.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1566.52,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know Colin, that was some of the questions you had.","index":467,"end_time":1569.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1567.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I don''t mean to jump ahead but like what, what does that look like Georgie, when you''re, you''re evaluating like where to allocate your budget?","index":468,"end_time":1576.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1569.39,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, because like you said you on the Google side you can optimize the landing page as much as possible, try to filter out as many, you know, qualify as many folks up front as you can.","index":469,"end_time":1585.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1576.63,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But then on the flip side when you''re advertising through third party sites, a lot of those are coming through.","index":470,"end_time":1590.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1585.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You can''t control how do you weigh the budget?","index":471,"end_time":1593.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1590.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"There''s there.","index":472,"end_time":1593.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1593.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Good question.","index":473,"end_time":1595.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1594.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s very platform specific because there''s definitely a limit to every platform that you can spend above which you do not get much of a return.","index":474,"end_time":1605.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1595.42,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":475,"end_time":1606.06,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1605.66,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And with time you Just gotta get have to get a feel for it.","index":476,"end_time":1609.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1606.94,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"With Google I think our our budget has been about $12,000 for the longest time.","index":477,"end_time":1613.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1609.42,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Just because above that you''re just not really getting much for what you''re paying for.","index":478,"end_time":1619.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1613.78,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Does it mean we don''t want to go above 12,000?","index":479,"end_time":1621.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1619.68,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Absolutely not.","index":480,"end_time":1622,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1621.36,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"If it''s working and we see kind of like those ratio we talked about like 70, 30 of leads, you know, they''re good versus junk.","index":481,"end_time":1629.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1622,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We''re more than happy to increase the budget.","index":482,"end_time":1631.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1629.28,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s just that we have not been able to get the traction we want to.","index":483,"end_time":1633.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1631.08,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"For example from Google, this other platform that I mentioned that we get ranked on majority of leads were coming from there.","index":484,"end_time":1640.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1633.64,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"When we get listed on there, I think our spend has been anywhere between 15 to maybe $30,000 and we had good success there.","index":485,"end_time":1648.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1640.48,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We did increase it to 60,000 for a few months and we got worse results.","index":486,"end_time":1653.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1649.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So that we have figured out that with them if you go above $30,000 you''re really not getting any much more, but you''re spending a lot more.","index":487,"end_time":1661.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1653.66,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So it''s very platform specific.","index":488,"end_time":1663.259,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1661.42,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And those are probably the two main places except our website obviously that quote unquote is organic even though it''s technically still paying for that from somewhere else.","index":489,"end_time":1672.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1663.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":490,"end_time":1672.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1672.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Those are the three main places we get our leads.","index":491,"end_time":1674.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1672.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Got it.","index":492,"end_time":1676.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And that''s something that we would want to look at.","index":493,"end_time":1678.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is there any way to get some of that information?","index":494,"end_time":1681.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1678.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because that is really the point of diminishing returns.","index":495,"end_time":1686.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1681.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Every company sees that right.","index":496,"end_time":1688.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1686.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"At some point and you have to figure out what channel, what allocation and mix of channels is going to allow us to grow at the rate we need to grow.","index":497,"end_time":1698.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1688.56,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And sometimes you push too much into a channel and you get diminishing returns.","index":498,"end_time":1701.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1698.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Some companies can still live with those diminishing return.","index":499,"end_time":1704.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1702.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Even though the leads are the cost per league costs more.","index":500,"end_time":1707.92,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1704.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"They still the CAC payback still works for them.","index":501,"end_time":1710.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1707.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And it''s okay.","index":502,"end_time":1711.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1710.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s like you''re paying a little bit more on the tail end of that but that you can live with it.","index":503,"end_time":1715.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1711.88,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is the goal for you all to find different channels in mix and get variety or is it to get volume of leads?","index":504,"end_time":1724.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1716.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like you know, if Colin, Dan and I are looking at this from a strategy standpoint, what do you feel like are the big goals that you''re looking for there?","index":505,"end_time":1732.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1724.12,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, and I get on your guys perspective.","index":506,"end_time":1734.44,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1732.48,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You guys are trying to figure out how to provide value to us.","index":507,"end_time":1736.68,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1734.44,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":508,"end_time":1736.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1736.68,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So it''s worth it for you guys and for us.","index":509,"end_time":1738.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1736.84,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I 100 get that and Us not being able to share a lot of those numbers, I. I know it''s frustrating and I''ll put it this way.","index":510,"end_time":1746.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1738.2,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I think out of the channels that we have right now, so Captera or, you know, Captera and or Gardner or gather the same company, there''s nothing we can optimize there.","index":511,"end_time":1756.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1746.2,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There.","index":512,"end_time":1756.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1756.52,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It just, it is what it is, right?","index":513,"end_time":1758.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1756.76,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We are just, you know, we get leads through them.","index":514,"end_time":1760,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1758.24,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s nothing that you guys can do there to help us.","index":515,"end_time":1762.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1760.26,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"At least that I''m aware of.","index":516,"end_time":1764.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1763.06,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Same thing with this company Rise.","index":517,"end_time":1766.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1765.22,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":518,"end_time":1766.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1766.74,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There is a little bit of a description on there that, you know, you put on your listing as far as, you know, your headline and three bullet points.","index":519,"end_time":1773.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1767.14,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We can take a look at that to optimize it based off a message that we might find that works across all of our channels.","index":520,"end_time":1778.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1773.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right, but that''s as far as we can do there.","index":521,"end_time":1780.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1778.42,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right?","index":522,"end_time":1780.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1780.3,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s nothing that you guys can do to groundbreakingly change what that''s them doing it.","index":523,"end_time":1784.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1780.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":524,"end_time":1784.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1784.38,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Google is the one that we can really, you know, use you guys as help.","index":525,"end_time":1788.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1784.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Beyond that, we are actually, you know, looking to see what else can we do.","index":526,"end_time":1792.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1788.57,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":527,"end_time":1792.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1792.49,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"What are the channels are we now using?","index":528,"end_time":1794.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1792.81,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Should we start posting more content like podcasts the way you guys have done in the past?","index":529,"end_time":1798.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1794.41,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So the way I look at is that I think you guys can help us with Google from the existing channels.","index":530,"end_time":1803.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1798.65,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have tried Reddit and Facebook.","index":531,"end_time":1806.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1804.57,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"If you guys think or see there is an opportunity there too, maybe we should revisit those as well.","index":532,"end_time":1811.21,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1806.73,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But I would consider those still new to us.","index":533,"end_time":1813.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1811.29,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I think most of the opportunity here is like, what, what.","index":534,"end_time":1816.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1813.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"What else is out there that we''re not doing that we can do to improve our marketing while also working on Google as well.","index":535,"end_time":1823.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1817.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Like for example, we just signed up and started doing.","index":536,"end_time":1827.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1824.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We''re going to do a lot more PR articles and blogs and try to get publications to just talk about us so we get our name out there.","index":537,"end_time":1833.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1827.66,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I think we''re really looking to look, how can we, you know, do new things out there that we have not done that can bring more value to us?","index":538,"end_time":1840.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1833.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Because there''s just no more.","index":539,"end_time":1841.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1840.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s no more juice to squeeze out of what we''re doing right now, at least from what we''re seeing, other than just putting more money in which we can do our own, right, other than Google again, that''s just kind of like the view that I have up until now.","index":540,"end_time":1852.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1842.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Unless there''s something else that you guys might be able to see that we don''t see.","index":541,"end_time":1855.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1852.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":542,"end_time":1857.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1855.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think, you know, diving into this, I think we also need to understand the foundation of, like, do we understand the ICP and every different, you know, breakdown of the ICP perfectly, or what they''re looking to see as a message or a call to action or something.","index":543,"end_time":1870.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1857.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you also mentioned.","index":544,"end_time":1872.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1871.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you have junk and you have qualified.","index":545,"end_time":1874.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1872.94,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, you know, at some portion, there''s.","index":546,"end_time":1876.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1874.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a breakdown of like 30 move here, 20 move there before that happens.","index":547,"end_time":1881.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1876.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know, when they are in qualified and let''s say they don''t come to a demo call or they don''t move forward to whatever next step.","index":548,"end_time":1887.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1881.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you doing any sort of outreach to those?","index":549,"end_time":1890.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1887.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like, we qualified them, but they''re just cold right now.","index":550,"end_time":1892.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1890.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we do have a marketing list that goes out, I don''t know, three times a week at this point.","index":551,"end_time":1898.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1894.26,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":552,"end_time":1899.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1898.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Get some of those people to reply back.","index":553,"end_time":1900.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1899.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Not at a. I would say maybe like 10 of them a month or so.","index":554,"end_time":1903.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1900.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So that''s our way to stay in touch with them.","index":555,"end_time":1906.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1904.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Marketing emails every week.","index":556,"end_time":1907.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1906.74,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":557,"end_time":1908.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1908.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":558,"end_time":1909.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1909.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But broadcast to a large list, probably with not too much personalization, I would imagine.","index":559,"end_time":1914.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1909.54,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Correct.","index":560,"end_time":1914.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1914.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Those will be just general emails that are, you know, here''s a new feature, here''s an update.","index":561,"end_time":1918.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1914.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Or did you think about, you know, whatever.","index":562,"end_time":1920.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1918.38,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yes.","index":563,"end_time":1920.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1920.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Staying top essentially, rather than.","index":564,"end_time":1922.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1920.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s not a salesperson reaching out to all of those.","index":565,"end_time":1925.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1922.62,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Sometimes they do.","index":566,"end_time":1927.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1926.14,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So they get to do their own, obviously outbound.","index":567,"end_time":1930.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1928.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And it''s up to them if they want to reach out to old deals or new deals.","index":568,"end_time":1934.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1931.22,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But, you know, that''s kind of, you know, it''s not something really required in Jesus necessarily.","index":569,"end_time":1938.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1934.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":570,"end_time":1938.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1938.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, that''s great.","index":571,"end_time":1939.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1938.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And, you know, I definitely want to dive into Google Ads and develop a strategy there that we can follow.","index":572,"end_time":1944.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1939.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, Georgie, to be completely honest, it would scare me to death if that was our only strategy and our only channel.","index":573,"end_time":1949.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1944.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We need some diversification.","index":574,"end_time":1951.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1950.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":575,"end_time":1952.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1952.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Honestly.","index":576,"end_time":1953.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1952.66,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And if that''s the only thing you guys do for us, will probably not be able to work together.","index":577,"end_time":1956.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1953.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":578,"end_time":1956.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1956.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t want Google Ads to be the only thing that we''re doing together.","index":579,"end_time":1959.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1957.26,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I''m looking at this as more like a holistic approach, guys, as more of a replacement of somebody that''s in house doing our marketing as a whole.","index":580,"end_time":1966.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1959.98,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That means emails, that means podcasts, that means whatever it is.","index":581,"end_time":1969.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1966.94,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":582,"end_time":1970.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1969.98,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t necessarily want.","index":583,"end_time":1972.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1971.099,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And here''s my view, too.","index":584,"end_time":1973.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1972.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t want to tell you guys what we should do because I don''t want to influence you.","index":585,"end_time":1976.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1973.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You guys have done this with other companies.","index":586,"end_time":1978.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1976.94,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"If we do that kind of two things happen.","index":587,"end_time":1980.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1978.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You guys basically just execute for us rather than think for us.","index":588,"end_time":1983.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1980.62,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And I want you guys to think for us.","index":589,"end_time":1985.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1983.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Otherwise the value of all of you is less than it can be essential.","index":590,"end_time":1989.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1985.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s how I do it.","index":591,"end_time":1990.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1989.47,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And we like to be accountable as well, you know, to the goals that we''re going to lay out and everything.","index":592,"end_time":1994.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1990.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we need to be able to drive strategy if we''re accountable to those numbers.","index":593,"end_time":1997.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1994.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, there''s things that we''re good at and things that we''re not good at, and we''re very aware of that.","index":594,"end_time":2001.19,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1997.35,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And we''re trusting you guys and your expertise to essentially think for us and advise us on that.","index":595,"end_time":2006.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2001.43,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And then we''ll obviously do our work if there''s anything.","index":596,"end_time":2008.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2006.15,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"For example, we just hired a videographer in house to film any kind of video professionally.","index":597,"end_time":2012.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2008.35,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You know, we have in house graphic designer in house developer that can build this specifically for us to build things for websites, marketing, landing pages.","index":598,"end_time":2021.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2013.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So we have invested in house to have the resource to putting the work to put the output that you guys tell us that we should do.","index":599,"end_time":2027.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2021.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":600,"end_time":2028.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2027.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":601,"end_time":2028.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2028.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to dive a little bit back into those numbers though.","index":602,"end_time":2031.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2029.179,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So, you know, 96 leads, let''s say, coming in in a typical month, it sounds like everyone is getting reached out to, you know, even if it comes on a weekend, on Monday, they get a couple phone calls and there''s a drip sequence.","index":603,"end_time":2041.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2031.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you have an idea of how many of those people never respond, like, are just cold immediately?","index":604,"end_time":2047.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2042.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll say this, you know, so let''s say we reach.","index":605,"end_time":2051.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2048.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We reach about 40, 45% of them.","index":606,"end_time":2053.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2051.3,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So the other 60 to 55%, chances are that we probably have not talked to them or at least good.","index":607,"end_time":2061.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2053.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"40% of them were just never able to speak to.","index":608,"end_time":2063.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2061.66,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":609,"end_time":2064.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2063.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":610,"end_time":2064.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2064.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then moving down to like discovery call.","index":611,"end_time":2066.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2064.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that 30%, I think you said.","index":612,"end_time":2068.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2066.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was the number about 40?","index":613,"end_time":2069.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2068.54,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"About 40%.","index":614,"end_time":2070.696,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2069.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"40S?","index":615,"end_time":2071.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2070.804,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":616,"end_time":2071.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2071.29,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Mid.","index":617,"end_time":2071.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2071.53,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Mid to low 40s?","index":618,"end_time":2072.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2072.05,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":619,"end_time":2073.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2072.97,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":620,"end_time":2073.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2073.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then from there to getting to a demo call.","index":621,"end_time":2075.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2073.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What does that look like?","index":622,"end_time":2076.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2075.65,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I used.","index":623,"end_time":2078.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2077.49,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I used to track these.","index":624,"end_time":2079.17,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2078.09,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So here''s what happened with that.","index":625,"end_time":2080.53,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2079.17,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So maybe two, three years ago, we switched to.","index":626,"end_time":2083.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2080.53,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I came up with this virtual demo where people can watch their own demo versus scheduling demos with us because of the skewed the data quite significantly because they don''t have to meet with us anymore.","index":627,"end_time":2092.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2083.93,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":628,"end_time":2093.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2092.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I actually know everybody that does a demo with us because they do it on now.","index":629,"end_time":2096.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2093.49,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Um, before that, I would say about, you know, 30% of the a hundred percent basically usually do about a demo.","index":630,"end_time":2103.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2097.32,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So almost everybody that we get to talk to and qualify does a demo.","index":631,"end_time":2106.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2103.76,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Almost kind of like is basically almost like a guarantee.","index":632,"end_time":2108.84,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2106.56,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":633,"end_time":2109.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2109,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":634,"end_time":2110.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2110.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we may even want to think about, you know, does online like self guided demo probably should count a little differently than actual sales call demo.","index":635,"end_time":2117.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2110.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":636,"end_time":2117.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2117.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":637,"end_time":2117.96,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2117.64,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But whether it''s with us or on their own, for the most part we''ve talked to them, they''ve interacted with our software in one way or another.","index":638,"end_time":2123.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2117.96,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":639,"end_time":2124.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2124.06,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And then you also said 3 out of 10 customers don''t go live.","index":640,"end_time":2127.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2124.26,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So is that after proposal, after like they sign and they don''t customers, this.","index":641,"end_time":2133.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2127.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is paid customers signed contracts.","index":642,"end_time":2134.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2133.06,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You''ve agreed.","index":643,"end_time":2135.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2134.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We''re doing business together, we''re starting to do the onboarding.","index":644,"end_time":2138.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2135.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And while we''re doing the onboarding with them, they either just completely disappear again because something''s going on and they even want to talk to us anymore or because there is delays.","index":645,"end_time":2146.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2138.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":646,"end_time":2147.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2146.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And like, you know, and then just they''re just being honest with us.","index":647,"end_time":2149.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2147.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":648,"end_time":2149.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2149.22,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I literally ran out of money.","index":649,"end_time":2151.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2149.73,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Hey, I cannot get my permit, my lease fell through, I have to look for a new building, whatever.","index":650,"end_time":2155.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2151.05,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I mean you''ll be surprised with the, you know, things that happen.","index":651,"end_time":2158.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2155.25,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But yeah, so I.","index":652,"end_time":2160.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2158.93,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There is definitely.","index":653,"end_time":2161.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2160.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And it fluctuates year to year, month to month.","index":654,"end_time":2163.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2161.09,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Some years has been 6 out of 10, some years been 7 out of 10, some have been 8 out of 10.","index":655,"end_time":2167.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2163.49,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So.","index":656,"end_time":2168.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2168.05,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But there is definitely a percentage of customers that just do not drop off, Just drop off.","index":657,"end_time":2174.29,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2168.33,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And, and we''ve looked at it so many times and we constantly ask ourselves what can we do?","index":658,"end_time":2179.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2174.29,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And it is not like we don''t actually, we just let it be right for those customers.","index":659,"end_time":2183.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2179.26,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have an onboarding team that reaches, calls them, emails them every single week to follow up with them.","index":660,"end_time":2188.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2183.74,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Leaves a voicemail, sends an email, are you guys ready?","index":661,"end_time":2191.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2188.78,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Are you guys ready?","index":662,"end_time":2192.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2191.78,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Every single week.","index":663,"end_time":2193.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2192.42,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And after like, I don''t know, four or five, six months, at some point we obviously stop doing that.","index":664,"end_time":2198.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2193.98,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But we are very proactive as far as getting an answer from them.","index":665,"end_time":2201.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2198.54,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We don''t just leave it be as well.","index":666,"end_time":2202.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2201.38,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So it''s not a strength.","index":667,"end_time":2204.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2202.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":668,"end_time":2205.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2204.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I want to shift a little bit then to the, the quality conversation.","index":669,"end_time":2209.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2205.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you know you''re getting feedback from your sales team.","index":670,"end_time":2212.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2209.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We just had an influx of leads that they love.","index":671,"end_time":2214.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2212.78,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Like let''s talk about the best 20 of leads flowing in.","index":672,"end_time":2217.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2214.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is there like it was this channel like, or is it a mix of channels and they''re all Kind of delivering some junk, some quality.","index":673,"end_time":2224.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2217.5,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"How does that look?","index":674,"end_time":2225.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2224.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, and, and by the way, so this is going to go into the data that we have and I can actually pull it up for the last month or so because I haven''t looked at it in some time here.","index":675,"end_time":2232.74,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2225.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Brett looks at it now.","index":676,"end_time":2234.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2233.14,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So we saw and this is something maybe I can share with you guys.","index":677,"end_time":2238.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2236.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I have for our CRM reporting for every deal that comes through, it shows the channel we came from and it shows the stage they''re at currently and does not show their contact information.","index":678,"end_time":2249.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2238.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It just shows like a randomly generated id.","index":679,"end_time":2252.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2250.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And that''s something actually we share with our partners for them to optimize, you know, their strategies with promoting us.","index":680,"end_time":2258.97,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2253.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So that''s something actually we can share with you guys to look at that because it shows you every leader we''ve got for the month, it shows you where it came from and the stage of it.","index":681,"end_time":2268.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2260.01,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So that''ll be great data for you guys.","index":682,"end_time":2269.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2268.25,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be awesome.","index":683,"end_time":2270.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2269.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I can, I can pull up and take a look at it.","index":684,"end_time":2273.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2271.29,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But I think it''s been a pretty healthy mix of everything.","index":685,"end_time":2276.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2273.81,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t think there''s one place that I at least recall that was, you know, just standing out as far as where we''re closing deal from.","index":686,"end_time":2282.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2276.73,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I would say that I think and this is probably pretty natural that our website provides much higher quality leads.","index":687,"end_time":2288.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2282.73,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And that''s normal though because if you go to our website you''re pretty high intent customers.","index":688,"end_time":2292.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2288.38,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You''ve heard from somewhere else about us.","index":689,"end_time":2294.38,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2292.54,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s not random, right?","index":690,"end_time":2295.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2294.38,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, those tend to be qualifying like at 70, 80%.","index":691,"end_time":2298.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2295.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":692,"end_time":2299.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2298.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Like almost like always qualified those.","index":693,"end_time":2301.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2299.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Are we able to close them much higher.","index":694,"end_time":2303.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2301.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So obviously that those are Harding them.","index":695,"end_time":2305.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2303.26,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There is one source actually that we have, I think I put in his name is Dave, the real barman on YouTube.","index":696,"end_time":2311.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2305.26,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":697,"end_time":2311.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2311.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So he''s.","index":698,"end_time":2313.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2312.8,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t want to call him.","index":699,"end_time":2314.04,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2313.24,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"He''s an influencer, quote unquote.","index":700,"end_time":2316,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2314.04,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"He did used to have his own inventory for bars that he sold.","index":701,"end_time":2320.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2316.4,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I think he sold a company but he has his own company.","index":702,"end_time":2322.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2320.16,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So he basically makes these videos about different point of sales and you get leads through his form that people click on YouTube essentially.","index":703,"end_time":2329.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2322.72,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Those are extremely high intent.","index":704,"end_time":2331.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2329.6,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Those are.","index":705,"end_time":2332.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2332,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"If we get one, you almost can guarantee yourself like it''s a done deal.","index":706,"end_time":2335.92,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2332.56,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":707,"end_time":2336.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2336,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not because they''re ready to buy but because they''re just.","index":708,"end_time":2338.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2336.72,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"He has.","index":709,"end_time":2339.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2339,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Well they''re doing the research right.","index":710,"end_time":2340.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2339.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And they have a lot of trust in him that whatever he''s recommending is actually good.","index":711,"end_time":2344.76,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2341.32,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So we don''t get as many from him anymore.","index":712,"end_time":2347.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2345.08,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I would say like maybe a couple of months.","index":713,"end_time":2349.24,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2347.4,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But those are guaranteed to be qualified.","index":714,"end_time":2352,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2350.04,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You''ll talk to them and like almost like a 70% chance you''re going to close the deal too, so.","index":715,"end_time":2356.6,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2352,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But the volume is very, very low.","index":716,"end_time":2358.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2356.84,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have done two videos with him recently in the last two months that just.","index":717,"end_time":2361.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2358.56,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s not been any volume there, which is kind of surprising as well for us.","index":718,"end_time":2364.2,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2361.56,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":719,"end_time":2364.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2364.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are you running any ads to promote his video or giving any shared budget?","index":720,"end_time":2368.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2364.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are not.","index":721,"end_time":2369.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2368.85,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I don''t know if he''s doing.","index":722,"end_time":2370.57,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2369.49,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t think he is.","index":723,"end_time":2371.41,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2370.57,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, he''s just kind of collecting a paycheck from every company which is actually very obviously profitable for him and profitable for us.","index":724,"end_time":2379.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2371.81,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Because if it''s a guaranteed deal.","index":725,"end_time":2380.769,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2379.37,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":726,"end_time":2381.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2380.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re happy to pay them a little bit more than somewhere else.","index":727,"end_time":2383.49,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2381.33,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Just because obviously like we''re not paying for one out of 10.","index":728,"end_time":2387.01,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2383.49,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We''re not paying for 10 to close one, we''re paying one to close one.","index":729,"end_time":2389.77,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2387.17,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So therefore it optimizes for us.","index":730,"end_time":2391.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2389.77,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It works out for everyone very well.","index":731,"end_time":2392.85,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2391.37,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":732,"end_time":2393.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2393.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So in your source dropdown, I imagine that Dave, you know, is one of those like Google Ads would be another.","index":733,"end_time":2398.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2393.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do you guys go into like referrals or even incentivizing current customers with referral options?","index":734,"end_time":2402.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2398.35,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because I mean, this is such a word of mouth industry.","index":735,"end_time":2404.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2402.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, we do, we do have a referral program, by the way, while we''re talking, I''m going to check to see the last month just to see if anything stands out.","index":736,"end_time":2410.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2404.79,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We do have, we do have a referral program where we pay them 500 if they refer somebody to us.","index":737,"end_time":2417.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2411.35,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have not got many.","index":738,"end_time":2418.79,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2417.51,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Again, we''ll probably get like, you know, a couple here and there every month or every other month.","index":739,"end_time":2424.16,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2419.27,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But so we do have one.","index":740,"end_time":2426.4,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2425.28,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It just has not been something people really want to do, apparently.","index":741,"end_time":2429.12,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2426.4,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":742,"end_time":2430.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2430.08,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":743,"end_time":2431.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2431.12,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I don''t know if it would be something that you could also add as a column, but I would like to understand like by restaurant type or even also by like role and title that you''re talking to.","index":744,"end_time":2439.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2431.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because there''s restaurant management groups that we probably want to get into and then there''s also like the direct owner operator, you know, doing everything at this location or multiple locations.","index":745,"end_time":2447.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2439.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":746,"end_time":2449.26,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2448.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And by.","index":747,"end_time":2450.14,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2449.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I''m looking at these, for example, for the last.","index":748,"end_time":2451.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2450.14,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Or this is January only.","index":749,"end_time":2453.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2451.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Sorry.","index":750,"end_time":2453.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2453.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So for January only, like I''m looking at the qualified leads essentially just because it''s not been long enough for us to close any of these Deals in January, but to kind of give you an idea where they''re coming from.","index":751,"end_time":2462.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2453.94,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I see, you know, we have about 20 qualified right now for this month so far.","index":752,"end_time":2467.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2462.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And then 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7.","index":753,"end_time":2470.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2467.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Eight of them are from this rice company, ICL.","index":754,"end_time":2474.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2470.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"2, 3, 3 from our website, a couple from this Dave guy.","index":755,"end_time":2479.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2474.774,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So, like, Rise is really like the main behind, like the, you know, behind the qualified ones.","index":756,"end_time":2485.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2480.23,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And then all the other ones are, you know, like three or four.","index":757,"end_time":2487.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2485.03,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s like three or four from Gardner or Captera.","index":758,"end_time":2489.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2487.27,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"There''s three or four from Natural Intelligence, which is very similar company to Rise.","index":759,"end_time":2493.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2489.99,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So there''s like, you know, just a splash of, you know, three or four from each source.","index":760,"end_time":2497.31,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2493.75,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And then Garden.","index":761,"end_time":2498.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2497.31,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":762,"end_time":2498.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2498.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or sorry, Rise beyond seems to be like the main one is like eight or nine.","index":763,"end_time":2501.75,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2498.23,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":764,"end_time":2502.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2502.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And none from Google Ads.","index":765,"end_time":2504.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2502.9,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And Google, let me see, what do we have from Google?","index":766,"end_time":2507.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2504.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, our Google Ads were not working right now, if you remember, I told you this for whatever.","index":767,"end_time":2513.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2509.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Oh, right, yeah, yeah.","index":768,"end_time":2515.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2513.82,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":769,"end_time":2516.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2515.34,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But typically they''ll be like, you know, there''ll be like maybe like five or six from Google.","index":770,"end_time":2519.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2516.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"A little bit more than the other ones.","index":771,"end_time":2520.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2519.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But again, the quality has been so important, they actually don''t really qualify.","index":772,"end_time":2524.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2520.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But there will be some there.","index":773,"end_time":2525.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2524.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":774,"end_time":2525.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2525.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":775,"end_time":2527.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2526.94,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":776,"end_time":2529.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2528.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, that would be awesome if you could send that over.","index":777,"end_time":2530.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2529.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s exactly what we''re looking for.","index":778,"end_time":2531.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2530.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I can send that over.","index":779,"end_time":2533.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2532.07,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"All right, perfect.","index":780,"end_time":2534.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2533.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because we jumped around a bit, but it was a great conversation.","index":781,"end_time":2538.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2536.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Shortest.","index":782,"end_time":2542.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2542.31,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We''ve kind of answered all of these.","index":783,"end_time":2544.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2543.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so, you know, when we''re making the qualification determination, you guys mentioned an automation that you have set up.","index":784,"end_time":2555.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2550.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Is that automatically changing, like the lifecycle stage of the contact that comes in to show that they''re qualified based on, you know, data or based on whatever metrics you''re looking at.","index":785,"end_time":2567.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2557.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or is that a sales member, like, manually saying, this isn''t qualified?","index":786,"end_time":2571.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2567.71,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s a sales member updating the stage of the deal.","index":787,"end_time":2574.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2572.51,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So if it''s whatever, it doesn''t matter.","index":788,"end_time":2577.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2575.07,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Whatever stage it is, is a sales member moving it across the stages as they figure out where they should be.","index":789,"end_time":2582.81,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2577.43,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":790,"end_time":2583.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2583.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":791,"end_time":2584.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2583.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":792,"end_time":2585.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2584.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Then we talked about.","index":793,"end_time":2585.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2585.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you mark leads as junk and then there''s qualified.","index":794,"end_time":2588.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2585.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a few sequences going out to them, but that''s probably something that we should tie into a little bit deeper.","index":795,"end_time":2594.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2588.96,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We could probably develop an entire funnel there.","index":796,"end_time":2597.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2595.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, great.","index":797,"end_time":2598.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2597.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So really getting into the alignment.","index":798,"end_time":2601.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2599.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I think we''ve kind of hammered down on these.","index":799,"end_time":2602.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2601.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s going to be looking at the most important metrics being cost per lead.","index":800,"end_time":2606.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2602.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then looking as, as these prospects move through the life cycle stages and what kind of conversion rates that we''re having.","index":801,"end_time":2613.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2607.04,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Are there any other metrics that are like, this is something we have to be super focused on?","index":802,"end_time":2618.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2613.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I think those two.","index":803,"end_time":2620.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2619.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And then again, I think just over a number of leads.","index":804,"end_time":2622.13,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2620.25,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":805,"end_time":2622.33,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2622.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Because if we do that and there''s like 30 of them.","index":806,"end_time":2624.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2622.33,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":807,"end_time":2624.329,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2624.09,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s not, I mean, that''s fine, but you know, it''s not accomplishing the scale they want to do.","index":808,"end_time":2628.37,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2624.329,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So.","index":809,"end_time":2628.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2628.37,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, I think number of leads ratio of, you know, again, like qualified whatever or versus a junk whatever you want to call that.","index":810,"end_time":2636.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2628.81,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And then I forgot what all the third ones you said, but what was.","index":811,"end_time":2640.28,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2636.48,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"The third one I was qualified cost per lead.","index":812,"end_time":2642.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2640.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I think those three metrics are probably realistically like where we need to be paying attention to.","index":813,"end_time":2648.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2642.88,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":814,"end_time":2649.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2648.8,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Can I have a question about that, Giorgio?","index":815,"end_time":2651.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2649.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So I think in the previous call, because I looked at your transcript, you guys mentioned that you''re considering moving up market, meaning you want to target restaurants with multiple locations, which has a bunch of advantages because they''re probably more stable.","index":816,"end_time":2665.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2651.76,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Adoption rate is going to be higher, Churn is going to be lower.","index":817,"end_time":2668.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2665.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"And have you perhaps segmented these numbers based on one location restaurant versus multiple location restaurant?","index":818,"end_time":2677.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2669.01,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Because what I''m getting at obviously is the math might be changing.","index":819,"end_time":2682.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2677.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So if we were to say, okay, let''s go after higher value customers, then I''m sure the lifetime value is going to be higher.","index":820,"end_time":2688.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2682.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"The cost of acquisition might be higher, but they might be worth more.","index":821,"end_time":2694.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2689.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"So.","index":822,"end_time":2694.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2694.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":823,"end_time":2696.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2694.96,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I, so right now where we at, I think basically all of them were the single location type of restaurants.","index":824,"end_time":2702.08,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2696.52,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Very rarely do we get like a multi location deal come through like maybe every few months or so.","index":825,"end_time":2706.72,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2702.08,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So because of that, we don''t have like necessary numbers behind them.","index":826,"end_time":2710.48,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2707.28,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But the way I think about it is that, you know, like, it''s almost kind of like you need both.","index":827,"end_time":2715.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2711.2,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":828,"end_time":2715.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2715.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t think we''re ever going to focus exclusively only to one.","index":829,"end_time":2718.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2715.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You need the little guys to kind of keep the wheel moving.","index":830,"end_time":2722.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2718.94,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":831,"end_time":2722.54,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2722.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And then the big one every now and then comes and makes and speeds things up very quickly for you.","index":832,"end_time":2727.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2722.78,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s harder to get those big deals just like obviously by nature because they take longer to make a decision.","index":833,"end_time":2732.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2728.3,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s a bigger account, takes longer to go through a process.","index":834,"end_time":2735.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2732.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":835,"end_time":2735.9,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2735.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I mean in ideal world we have a lot, a lot of smaller accounts is just kind of like you know, support the revenue and are a big part of the growth.","index":836,"end_time":2746.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2736.38,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But then every now and then, let''s say 70, 30, let''s say 30% of those big deals.","index":837,"end_time":2750.15,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2746.11,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":838,"end_time":2750.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2750.15,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Or 40% of the big deals where they really make significant difference just because the scale they do take a year, but when they sell or six months or whatever.","index":839,"end_time":2758.27,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2750.35,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But when they do sign, they make such a big impact that like it really pushes the revenue forward.","index":840,"end_time":2763.35,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2758.43,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"But they''re not as frequent.","index":841,"end_time":2764.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2763.35,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right.","index":842,"end_time":2764.83,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2764.55,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So I think there needs to be a balance of both.","index":843,"end_time":2766.95,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2765.07,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t think we ever going to just do only one.","index":844,"end_time":2768.67,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2766.95,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right?","index":845,"end_time":2768.99,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2768.67,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":846,"end_time":2769.55,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2769.07,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Your word is kind of like, you know, 70, 30.","index":847,"end_time":2771.63,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2769.79,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And then obviously the economics behind those big orders is completely different.","index":848,"end_time":2774.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2771.63,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"The pricing that we give them is different.","index":849,"end_time":2776.73,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2775.05,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"The cost to acquire is probably different.","index":850,"end_time":2779.05,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2777.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I don''t have that information to know what it looks like, but if it is different, it probably is different.","index":851,"end_time":2783.65,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2779.13,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s okay.","index":852,"end_time":2784.25,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2783.65,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And we can figure that out as we get there.","index":853,"end_time":2786.09,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2784.25,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, makes sense.","index":854,"end_time":2787.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2786.57,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"},{"text":"Makes sense.","index":855,"end_time":2788.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2787.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, well, Georgie, I think I have everything that I need.","index":856,"end_time":2791.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2788.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So one, I want to say thanks for being a trooper.","index":857,"end_time":2794.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2792.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know these first two meetings are us just peppering you with a bunch of questions, but it''s really useful for us to do this and do it quickly so that we can get on the same page.","index":858,"end_time":2800.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2794.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"As far as what the next meeting is, is us presenting our roadmap and goals for your marketing campaigns and how we can help rescue.","index":859,"end_time":2808.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2800.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I want to get that on the calendar and then I''ll also follow up with the.","index":860,"end_time":2813.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2808.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The Fireflies recording here.","index":861,"end_time":2814.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2813.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":862,"end_time":2815.39,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2814.91,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":863,"end_time":2816.03,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2815.39,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, let us know we are available.","index":864,"end_time":2817.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2816.11,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I''m assuming next week probably.","index":865,"end_time":2818.87,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2817.71,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"What I mean, for next meeting, right?","index":866,"end_time":2820.11,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2818.87,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, next week.","index":867,"end_time":2821.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2820.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I can send you a booking link like I did last time.","index":868,"end_time":2823.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2821.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or we can just look at calendars right now.","index":869,"end_time":2824.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2823.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Do it now.","index":870,"end_time":2826.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2826.34,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Okay.","index":871,"end_time":2827.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2826.9,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Again, this is a priority for us.","index":872,"end_time":2828.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2827.34,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So just tell me what day mornings are usually easier for us by.","index":873,"end_time":2832.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2828.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And I know you guys are on a different time zone, but before 10 o'' clock Pacific time, any day should be good for us.","index":874,"end_time":2840.78,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2832.82,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So just let me know what we guys have on the calendar.","index":875,"end_time":2842.3,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2840.78,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We''ll make a priority.","index":876,"end_time":2843.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2842.3,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, I think we could do.","index":877,"end_time":2844.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2843.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Or 10 o''.","index":878,"end_time":2850.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2849.14,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Clock.","index":879,"end_time":2850.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2850.06,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think we could do Monday at noon Eastern.","index":880,"end_time":2854.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2851.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''d be 9am Your time.","index":881,"end_time":2856.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2854.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":882,"end_time":2857.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2856.51,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s.","index":883,"end_time":2857.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2857.07,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"That''s perfect for us.","index":884,"end_time":2858.43,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2857.47,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":885,"end_time":2859.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2859.07,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, I''ll get that sent out and then I''ll also send this recording transcript and let me know if you have any questions.","index":886,"end_time":2865.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2859.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But yeah, if you could share that file that you had referenced between now and just sometime this week, that would be fantastic.","index":887,"end_time":2871.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2865.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then, yeah, we''ll show up to the next meeting with our roadmap, and it''ll be us doing a majority of the talking.","index":888,"end_time":2876.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2871.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can give your voice a little rest there.","index":889,"end_time":2879.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2876.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":890,"end_time":2879.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2879.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Thank you for bearing with us.","index":891,"end_time":2880.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2879.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"I know you guys wanting more data from us, but we just have to be conscious of, you know, we''re, you know, like, to be honest with you, we have never shared our numbers with anybody.","index":892,"end_time":2889.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2880.94,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Maybe it''s part of the reason why things have not worked out in the past, but we''ve.","index":893,"end_time":2893.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2889.94,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have no.","index":894,"end_time":2894.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2893.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We have no investors.","index":895,"end_time":2895.94,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2894.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"We.","index":896,"end_time":2896.5,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2896.18,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"You know, that''s like the most important part of our company.","index":897,"end_time":2899.7,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2896.5,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Right?","index":898,"end_time":2900.1,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2899.7,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Our value behind it.","index":899,"end_time":2901.86,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2900.58,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And if we start giving it out, I''m not saying that you guys are going to go out and.","index":900,"end_time":2904.82,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2901.86,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"And you can always shoot people and stuff like that.","index":901,"end_time":2906.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2905.1,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"It''s just not worth our time, though.","index":902,"end_time":2908.02,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2906.66,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"So we try to protect as much as we can.","index":903,"end_time":2909.66,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2908.02,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I totally hear you.","index":904,"end_time":2911.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2909.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, all.","index":905,"end_time":2911.98,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2911.34,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"All good.","index":906,"end_time":2912.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2911.98,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And we have our NDA and everything in place, too, so.","index":907,"end_time":2914.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2912.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":908,"end_time":2915.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2915.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":909,"end_time":2916.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2915.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Feel free to anonymize the data any way that you need to feel comfortable.","index":910,"end_time":2919.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2916.34,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And.","index":911,"end_time":2920.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2919.7,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, really looking forward to the next meeting.","index":912,"end_time":2921.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2920.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":913,"end_time":2922.62,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2922.14,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Thank you guys so much.","index":914,"end_time":2923.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2922.62,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Good to meet you guys.","index":915,"end_time":2924.22,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2923.46,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Tristan and Dan.","index":916,"end_time":2925.34,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2924.22,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":917,"end_time":2926.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2925.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Next week.","index":918,"end_time":2927.18,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2926.62,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":919,"end_time":2928.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2927.58,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, well, thank you very much.","index":920,"end_time":2929.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2928.46,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Have a good one.","index":921,"end_time":2930.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2929.66,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, bye.","index":922,"end_time":2931.46,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":2930.22,"speaker_name":"georgifuntarov"},{"text":"See you, George.","index":923,"end_time":2932.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2931.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Later.","index":924,"end_time":2932.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":2932.14,"speaker_name":"Dan Rényi"}],"dateString":"2026-01-20T17:30:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/82863851108?pwd=5bIrn9T1fg2TPcRKxcy9zf3WYHjFWf.1","participants":["tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com,justin.brown@marketersindemand.com,gfuntarov@rezku.com,brett.martin@rezku.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com","dan.renyi@marketersindemand.com","justin.brown@marketersindemand.com","gfuntarov@rezku.com","brett.martin@rezku.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KF3KCYHKR6MV67GVMENKDAZN","organizer_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Clarified CAC payback is under four months; Georgie open to optimizing for higher volume or quality.","Mapped lead funnel: 40–45% qualify, ~30% reach proposal, ~50% of proposals close.","Georgie flagged Google Ads performance has dropped; open to optimization and channel diversification.","Sales and marketing funnel stages are well-defined from lead to junk; CRM updated manually by reps.","Georgie encouraged strategic leadership, not just execution; seeks full-stack marketing support."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I don''t necessarily want... Google Ads to be the only thing that we''re doing together.","speaker":"georgifuntarov"},{"quote":"We''re trusting you guys and your expertise to essentially think for us and advise us.","speaker":"georgifuntarov"},{"quote":"It would scare me to death if that was our only strategy and our only channel.","speaker":"Colin Costigan"}],"topics":["lead quality","channels","CAC","CRM","churn"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-20T22:31:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Lead Generation and Qualification Metrics**\n\nThe team established a clear baseline of **approximately 96 leads per month** with a **historical cost per lead near $400**, noting recent dips in both cost and lead quality that affect conversion (03:18).\n\n- **Georgi explained** that lead cost varies significantly by channel, with Google charging for all leads regardless of quality, inflating average costs, while third-party partners like Rise only charge for qualified leads, offering more controlled spend.\n- The qualification rate is **around 40-45%**, with leads needing to be legitimate restaurant owners seeking point-of-sale (POS) systems, and lifecycle stages are updated manually by sales members after initial contact.\n- The typical sales cycle is about **4 weeks**, with **roughly one-third of qualified leads closing**, translating to a **close rate of about 1 in 3 qualified leads**.\n- The lifetime value (LTV) per customer is estimated at **$11,400 over 28 months**, with a **customer acquisition cost (CAC) payback period under 4 months**, reflecting a healthy investment return despite inherent assumptions and industry volatility.\n\n## **Customer Retention and Industry Challenges**\n\nThe restaurant POS market faces high churn due to external factors, making retention a critical challenge that is largely uncontrollable (12:36).\n\n- **Georgi highlighted** that about **3 out of 10 signed customers never go live** due to restaurant failures, permit issues, or financial problems, emphasizing industry-wide instability.\n- Competitors experience **20-25% quarterly churn**, while their churn is reportedly lower but still significant enough to require constant new customer acquisition.\n- Smaller accounts generating **less than $30,000 monthly revenue** are more prone to churn and payment issues, often requiring collections, whereas larger accounts over $100,000 show more stability.\n- The onboarding team actively follows up weekly for up to 4-6 months to reduce drop-offs, showing a focus on aggressive customer activation.\n\n## **Marketing Spend and Channel Performance**\n\nCurrent marketing spend shows diminishing returns, especially on Google Ads and third-party platforms, prompting a need for diversification and optimization (17:25).\n\n- Georgi reported a recent **budget increase from $20,000-$30,000 to about $78,000 over 3-4 months**, mainly through the Rise platform, which doubled lead volume but failed to increase paying customers due to poor lead quality.\n- Google Ads budget typically caps around **$12,000 monthly** because spend beyond that yields little return; quality remains low despite budget increases.\n- The team prioritizes Google Ads for optimization due to their ability to control ad levers, unlike third-party partners who control traffic sources and pricing models.\n- Georgi expressed openness to exploring **new channels, including podcasts, PR articles, Reddit, and Facebook ads**, reflecting a strategic push toward a more holistic marketing approach beyond paid leads.\n\n## **Lead Quality and Sales Process Optimization**\n\nLead quality is a major concern, with a target to reduce junk leads to **under 30%**, aiming for about **70% qualified leads** to improve conversion and reduce wasted spend (19:33).\n\n- Automated CRM systems integrate incoming leads instantly, notifying sales reps, and apply a **structured 11-12 touchpoint outreach sequence** within the first 5 days to maximize engagement.\n- Junk leads are identified clearly during qualification and moved into a dedicated ''junk'' category within the CRM instead of being deleted, allowing ongoing tracking and analysis.\n- Pre-qualification questions on landing pages help filter leads by concept type and average revenue, yet junk leads still persist, mainly from sources like Google.\n- The sales team reports highest lead quality from the company website (**70-80% qualification**) and a niche YouTube influencer channel whose leads close about **70% of the time**, though volume from this channel is low.\n- Referral programs exist but yield minimal new leads, indicating untapped potential in leveraging word-of-mouth.\n\n## **Strategic Priorities and Next Steps**\n\nThe group agreed on focusing efforts on improving lead quality, optimizing Google Ads, and expanding marketing channels, with a roadmap presentation planned for the following week to align on goals and resource allocation (46:29).\n\n- Georgi emphasized the desire for the marketing partner to act as a strategic advisor, not just executors, trusting their expertise to guide decisions across channels including email, podcasts, and content marketing.\n- The internal team has invested in in-house resources such as a videographer, graphic designer, and developer to support marketing output based on external strategy recommendations.\n- The next meeting is scheduled for **Monday at 9:00 AM Pacific Time**, where the marketing roadmap and campaign goals will be presented.\n- Georgi will share anonymized CRM data showing lead sources and lifecycle stages during the week to enable detailed channel analysis and targeted strategy development.","outline":null,"keywords":["lead qualification","cost per lead","marketing channels","customer acquisition cost","restaurant POS","churn rate"],"overview":"- **Lead Generation Metrics:** Establish baseline of 96 leads/month; lead cost averages $400, with a 40-45% qualification rate.  \n- **Sales Cycle Insights:** Typical sales cycle is 4 weeks; close rate is 1 in 3 qualified leads, lifetime value is $11,400.  \n- **Customer Retention Challenges:** 30% of signed customers never go live; high churn in POS market requires continual new acquisition efforts.  \n- **Marketing Spend Trends:** Budget increased from $20,000 to $78,000; need to optimize Google Ads for better returns and explore new channels.  \n- **Lead Quality Focus:** Aim to reduce junk leads to under 30%; optimize sales outreach with 11-12 touchpoints within 5 days.  \n- **Strategic Next Steps:** Improve lead quality, align on marketing goals; next meeting set for Monday at 9:00 AM Pacific Time.","action_items":"\n**Georgifuntarov**\nShare anonymized CRM lead source and lifecycle stage data to support analysis of lead quality and channel performance by end of the week (37:45)\nCoordinate availability and confirm next meeting for marketing roadmap presentation (Monday 9 AM Pacific) (47:20)\n\n**Colin Costigan**\nSend meeting recording, transcript, and booking link for next session to Georgifuntarov (47:50)\nPrepare marketing strategy and roadmap presentation focused on lead metrics, channels, and optimization for the upcoming meeting (46:50)\n\n**Marketers in Demand Team**\nAnalyze shared lead and channel data to identify cost-effective marketing mix and opportunities for volume/quality improvement (42:15)\nDevelop recommendations to diversify marketing channels beyond Google Ads, including content and PR strategies (29:45)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"bc3f286d-3997-4a03-9355-fbbd3a684344","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
