    '{"id":"01KEW5A0BT5BEZZ41K7PVC0TVZ","title":"New North x Planon Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Planning and Points Management**\n\nThe team agreed on a flexible ABM campaign structure with a **60-point monthly budget** fully covered by leadership to ensure campaign success (04:06).\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum** explained that the **60 points** cover all regular work, with any overage gifted by leadership, avoiding extra cost to the client.\n- Campaign components like targeted ads, outreach sequences, and image ad refreshes are bundled to optimize point use and efficiency.\n- The point usage will vary monthly, with heavier setup work in the early months (January-February) and lighter management tasks later.\n- A **contract amendment** for gifted points is pending legal approval, which is critical to proceed with the expanded campaign scope (29:54).\n\n## **Survey and Outreach Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to combine direct call invitations for priority accounts with a digital survey for broader outreach, aiming for **early campaign launch in February** (09:33).\n\n- Priority contacts from two key university segments will receive a call invitation first, followed by a digital survey if no response comes within 1-2 weeks.\n- The survey will be short, with **3 to 5 questions**, designed for quick completion (under 2 minutes) to maximize response rates.\n- Questions will focus on identifying key struggles, interest in purchasing solutions within a defined timeframe, and openness to new technologies.\n- Taylor suggested keeping questions generic but relevant to sales insights, enabling targeted follow-up campaigns based on responses.\n\n## **Audience List Enrichment and Targeting**\n\nThe plan includes enriching two university-related contact lists to reach at least **200 contacts each**, with potential to expand further, prioritizing new university titles (15:01).\n\n- Taylor will enrich the \"Real Estate\" and \"Director of Space\" tabs using Clay, focusing on titles that fit the campaign’s target profile.\n- Lauren identified approximately **420+ contacts** across these segments, with suppression of existing customers to avoid overlap.\n- Additional university contacts are prioritized to increase volume in key segments like CIO, finance, and facility management, aiming for lists of **200+ contacts** per tab.\n- This enriched audience allows segmented outreach: calls for priority segments and surveys for larger groups.\n\n## **Survey Content and Messaging Development**\n\nThe team will develop messaging focused on offering a **10-minute or less call with solution experts**, emphasizing industry challenges and delivering a branded report in return (24:38).\n\n- Lauren emphasized framing the call around current higher education issues like regulatory changes and funding cuts.\n- Taylor will draft outreach sequences for both call scheduling and survey participation, awaiting finalized survey questions from Lauren’s team.\n- Messaging will highlight the value of the report, showing participants how their peers are impacted and what solutions are available.\n- The goal is to make the offer appealing and clear to maximize engagement and conversions.\n\n## **Approval Process and Timeline Alignment**\n\nLauren will lead creating a detailed campaign plan document with timelines and deliverables to secure formal approval from management and design teams by mid-February (27:04).\n\n- This document will clarify monthly milestones, responsibilities, and review deadlines to avoid delays, particularly in creative approvals.\n- Taylor will prepare an outline of initiatives and goals to support Lauren’s discussions with leadership.\n- Approval of the legal addendum for gifted points is a key dependency before campaign work can fully proceed (29:54).\n- Lauren confirmed strong internal support from Jay and expects buy-in from her manager and GM once the plan is formalized.\n\n## **Video Project Status**\n\nLauren is coordinating final edits with Roderick’s team to complete the video project, aiming to finalize changes quickly to avoid further delays (30:48).\n\n- She will communicate clearly that no further edits will be accepted after this stage to keep the project on track.\n- This will allow the video to be delivered promptly to support campaign assets and messaging.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","survey development","audience enrichment","outreach sequence","gifted points","higher education challenges"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Structure:** Team agreed on a flexible ABM budget of 60 points monthly, covered by leadership for success.\n\n- **Survey Launch Strategy:** Direct calls followed by a digital survey for priority accounts, targeting February launch.\n\n- **Contact List Goals:** Enrich two university-related lists, aiming for at least 200 contacts each, focusing on new titles.\n\n- **Messaging Development:** Team to create outreach messaging for calls with solution experts, emphasizing industry challenges for engagement.\n\n- **Timeline Approval Process:** Detailed campaign plan document due by mid-February for management approval and clear responsibilities.\n\n- **Video Project Coordination:** Final edits being made to the video, no further revisions accepted to meet campaign timeline.","action_items":"\n**Lauren Poirier**\nProvide detailed survey questions in coordination with Jay within about a week (19:27)\nFinalize and send the contract amendment with legal’s one remaining redline to Taylor’s team (30:23)\nShare video edits with Roderick and his team to finalize and send to Taylor (30:38)\nReview and approve the forthcoming detailed campaign plan document to facilitate leadership buy-in (27:04)\nSupply the specific updates to audience data for removing suppressed contacts (customers) and prioritize new universities for Clay enrichment (14:57)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nDraft and send a clear, detailed written campaign plan outlining timelines, goals, and responsibilities for Lauren to share with her team and leadership (26:30)\nInitiate Clay enrichment for the “Real Estate” and “Director of Space” tabs aiming for approximately 200 contacts each (15:40)\nDevelop preliminary outreach sequences for both call invitations and digital survey campaigns, awaiting final survey questions before completing survey messaging (23:46)\nMonitor gifted points approval contingent on receiving signed contract amendment and coordinate with owner Justin for contract status updates (29:54)\nKeep Lauren updated through Teams on progress and confirm launch timelines and goals once contract and plans are finalized (27:50)\n"},"duration":31.600000381469727,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"id":1,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Hey there.","index":0,"end_time":183.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":183.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":1,"end_time":185.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":185.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":187.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.87,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"How are you?","index":3,"end_time":187.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":187.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Good.","index":4,"end_time":188.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you doing a paint project back there?","index":5,"end_time":190.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":188.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I am.","index":6,"end_time":193.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I just realized that you can see it''s my office, and unfortunately, I don''t really like any of them, so I''m starting from.","index":7,"end_time":201.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Really?","index":8,"end_time":202.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, that''s a bummer.","index":9,"end_time":203.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":10,"end_time":205.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":204.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m looking for a green, but not like a.","index":11,"end_time":208.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":205.51,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like a neutral green.","index":12,"end_time":210.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":209.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Nothing that''s, like, too froggy.","index":13,"end_time":213.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":210.56,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I guess I was gonna say.","index":14,"end_time":214.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":213.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I like the green one.","index":15,"end_time":215.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":214.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, it''s like a sage green.","index":16,"end_time":217.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":215.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s getting there.","index":17,"end_time":218.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":217.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s closer to what I want, for sure.","index":18,"end_time":220.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":218.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a fun project.","index":19,"end_time":222.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":220.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I was looking at paint this weekend at Lowe''s.","index":20,"end_time":224.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":222.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"My husband, too, for my office.","index":21,"end_time":225.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":224.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because we were there for something else, and I was like, it could be fun to do that.","index":22,"end_time":228.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":225.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I feel like my wall is all over the place right now.","index":23,"end_time":231.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":228.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I have no idea what to do with it.","index":24,"end_time":232.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":231.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":25,"end_time":233.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":232.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s hard.","index":26,"end_time":234.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":233.6,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s hard to pick a color.","index":27,"end_time":236,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":234.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It is.","index":28,"end_time":237.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s a big, like, commitment, I guess, because then you have to.","index":29,"end_time":241.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":237.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If you want to change it.","index":30,"end_time":242.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":241.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It takes a long time.","index":31,"end_time":243.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":242.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it feels like it for sure.","index":32,"end_time":245.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":243.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, so kind of a little bit more informal.","index":33,"end_time":249.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":246.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just wanted to walk through some things with you today.","index":34,"end_time":251.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":249.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Don''t have, like, exact slides we can follow, per se, but I wanted to share with you kind of what I''m thinking as far as the points plan.","index":35,"end_time":259.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":251.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then I did just put in here what you just shared with me over teams.","index":36,"end_time":263.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":259.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So based on what is included here in the campaign, ideas, depending on what you do, I went ahead and put it into a points plan to show potentially what this could look like.","index":37,"end_time":275.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":264.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Again, I want to preface that not all of these things may be needed depending on what you and your team decide to do.","index":38,"end_time":281.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":276.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Some of them may change a little bit because it depends on the size of the survey, how many questions we''re doing.","index":39,"end_time":288.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":282.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But as I said before, so your monthly points is 60amonth, and that''s all you''re going to be responsible for.","index":40,"end_time":295.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":289.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We really want this campaign to be successful for you guys.","index":41,"end_time":298.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":295.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We want you to get the results you''re looking for.","index":42,"end_time":300.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":298.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And so my leadership team is willing to gift you those points.","index":43,"end_time":304.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":300.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So anything outside of the 60 point scope, you don''t need to worry about or be responsible for.","index":44,"end_time":309.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":304.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s why I''m saying, like, I wouldn''t pay too close attention to a couple of these points because we may have to change a couple things.","index":45,"end_time":315.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":309.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And like I said in ClickUp, but we track points because our team spends hours working on things and that''s how we like track projects and things like that.","index":46,"end_time":323.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":315.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But ultimately in Pulse you''ll see the credited section if we go over and the credits will be returned back to you.","index":47,"end_time":329.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":323.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, so if you''re wondering about how like the whole points of that will work.","index":48,"end_time":333.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":329.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I just wanted to show you kind of how we''d set this up.","index":49,"end_time":336.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":334.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So ultimately either way, we''d be setting up a new ABM campaign.","index":50,"end_time":339.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":336.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if we did more than one initiative, we can layer that within one task because.","index":51,"end_time":345.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":340.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because a lot of them will go together.","index":52,"end_time":347,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":345.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we do like the targeted ads that would just kind of go together as a setup, that would be a little bit separate because we would just set up the paid media, which is only five points.","index":53,"end_time":357.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":347.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if we did like the offer and survey and the intent based approach that can all be compiled into like that setup ABM task.","index":54,"end_time":366.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":358.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we develop the new outreach sequence, I have that in here too.","index":55,"end_time":370.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":366.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Just picking out the kind of copy that we want to send out with a survey that we do or if we''re just retargeting people from ads, we would just create that new outreach sequence.","index":56,"end_time":380.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":370.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m not sure if we want to develop a new list.","index":57,"end_time":383.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":381.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know you have the edits back that we''re working on.","index":58,"end_time":386.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":383.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we wanted to add additional people like out of clay, that would be something that we could do through clay.","index":59,"end_time":393.139,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":387.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We could enrich the lists and just see if we can get some additional people depending on kind of those new guidelines you sent us.","index":60,"end_time":398.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":393.139,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So depending on how big we want to do the campaign, if we''re not doing the testing campaign, we can look into that.","index":61,"end_time":404.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Um, and then the image ad creative package.","index":62,"end_time":408.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":405.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Now that we are gonna not run with the old things.","index":63,"end_time":411.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":408.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Cause that campaign is over.","index":64,"end_time":412.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":411.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We would just wanna create refreshed image ads that we could use to run simultaneous ads while we have whatever campaign we''re doing running.","index":65,"end_time":419.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because like Dan said when we met last time, it''s super beneficial to have them running together.","index":66,"end_time":424.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":419.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we would wanna refresh those a little bit.","index":67,"end_time":426.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":424.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Depending on our ultimate messaging, there may be one or two we could throw in there as far as like for the just brand awareness.","index":68,"end_time":432.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":426.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But ultimately we would have to create some new ones.","index":69,"end_time":435.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":432.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s where that one would come in.","index":70,"end_time":437.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":435.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the other things you''re familiar with like managing abm, I only have two points assigned to that this month because we have.","index":71,"end_time":445.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":438.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We worked on a new strategy and we worked on redoing the customer audience.","index":72,"end_time":451.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":445.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I didn''t want to do the full 10 points obviously because we don''t have a one running right now.","index":73,"end_time":455.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":451.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So this title will be updated in Pulse as well, just based on what we did.","index":74,"end_time":460.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":455.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So you guys can see on your end, and then the other things are going to stay the same.","index":75,"end_time":465.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":460.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sometimes you''ll notice too, with the Tech Stack, these are just the things we have running, like factors.","index":76,"end_time":470.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":466.38,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"LEM list the Tech stack will most likely include if we enrich any audience lists.","index":77,"end_time":476.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":471.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So Clay will go into the Tech stack.","index":78,"end_time":479.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":476.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So the way it works is you''d have to spend a lot of points in Clay, which is kind of how that works, for it to be charged to you, because enriched lists and they can get like hundreds of ones without it charging anything.","index":79,"end_time":492.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":479.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it would take a lot to make that move.","index":80,"end_time":495.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":493.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like in a large amount, it may move to like 21 points, but again, anything over 60 you don''t have to worry about.","index":81,"end_time":501.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":495.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s kind of how I would see.","index":82,"end_time":503.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":501.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s kind of getting late in the month now.","index":83,"end_time":505.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":503.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m not sure if we''re getting approval back necessarily for January on all these things now, but that''s how I had it kind of just specked out in here.","index":84,"end_time":512.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":505.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if you move to February, once we have all of those heavier lift tasks for ABM complete things are running, then we move into just a management kind of time where we''re just managing everything.","index":85,"end_time":523.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":512.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And that would be definitely not as many points.","index":86,"end_time":528.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":524.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then in March, if we did the survey option, we would want to develop the survey like you, me and Dan had talked about last week, where we create some kind of PDF or something that we can send to the people that participated, make it look nice, and then also, you know, potentially have it on your website, maybe in like a gated form for viewers.","index":87,"end_time":547.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":528.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that would be about 30 points.","index":88,"end_time":550.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":548.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Again, give or take, we would see exactly the scope of work if it was a shorter survey, if it was a longer survey, but again, we would cover anything over the 60.","index":89,"end_time":558.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":550.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it will balance out like month to month too.","index":90,"end_time":561.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":558.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Obviously we have smaller months and larger months in here, but ultimately that''s how I see it.","index":91,"end_time":567.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":562.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As far as points working, do you have any questions on that before we get into the specifics of, like, goals.","index":92,"end_time":573.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":567.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And things like that as far as the survey goes, since we''re looking at an extension through the end of April, would it be possible to move that initiative up to February to give that like two to three months in order to run?","index":93,"end_time":590.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So when I say like the survey, that would be with the results.","index":94,"end_time":594.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":591.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sorry, I should reword that.","index":95,"end_time":596.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":594.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So, like, if we created a PDF with the results of the survey, the actual survey, I have here, like set it up.","index":96,"end_time":603.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":596.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because if we''re only setting up a survey to send out, Whether we use SurveyMonkey, whether we use Lemlist, that''s, that''s way more simple to like compile questions that developing the survey like results.","index":97,"end_time":615.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll just add that in here right now.","index":98,"end_time":617.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":615.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would be a heavier lift because we''d want it to look nice, have your branding and things like that.","index":99,"end_time":622.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":618.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we would develop the survey right away if we got the go ahead from you.","index":100,"end_time":626.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":623.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":101,"end_time":627.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":626.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Which is what this is and clarifying question there.","index":102,"end_time":630.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So for some reason I thought that the survey would be like we sit down and actually have a call, whether it''s, you know, me or Jay and his team, and then we share the recording with you.","index":103,"end_time":642.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":630.18,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I kind of thought that that would, that was the CTA that we would say like will you sit down with us and we discuss.","index":104,"end_time":647.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We can do it that way as well.","index":105,"end_time":649.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":647.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Which would eliminate any additional like sensitive set up.","index":106,"end_time":651.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":649.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ve done it both ways for clients.","index":107,"end_time":653.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":651.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I have one client that says call us today and we can sit down and talk about this.","index":108,"end_time":657.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":653.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I have another client that I''m working with right now that we just set up a whole survey with like five questions.","index":109,"end_time":662.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":657.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s super, super quick, two minute survey and they com.","index":110,"end_time":665.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":662.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We compile the data for them on the back end and then people get sent the results who participated early and then they use it for newsletter engagement like down the road for months.","index":111,"end_time":675.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":665.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if the whole ultimate goal is to just getting people on a call, then we would just create a dynamic outreach sequence to encourage to make that scheduled call so we wouldn''t have to set anything up per se.","index":112,"end_time":687.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":675.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the developing, like the results from it.","index":113,"end_time":692.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":687.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If, if there was a way that you, your team could compile some data, like what are people seeing in the industry?","index":114,"end_time":698.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"What are some struggles you guys are seeing?","index":115,"end_time":700.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":698.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then you can do something like Planon''s take on this, like Planon''s insights into this, what we could do to help kind of thing.","index":116,"end_time":707,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":700.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then we would develop that into the PDF, like as, as the giveaway after that.","index":117,"end_time":711.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":707,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Not the giveaway, but the product.","index":118,"end_time":713.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":711.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like what, what we''re gonna show for all of those calls.","index":119,"end_time":716.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":713.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I guess.","index":120,"end_time":717.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":716.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":121,"end_time":718.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":717.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s how that would work.","index":122,"end_time":719.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":718.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, that makes sense.","index":123,"end_time":721.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":720.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''m wondering maybe there''s, there''s a way to combine both approaches.","index":124,"end_time":725.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":721.61,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Both a digital survey and like a.","index":125,"end_time":727.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.17,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"In a call asking questions.","index":126,"end_time":728.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":727.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We can do a test audience too.","index":127,"end_time":730.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":729.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like we had mentioned, like if you have a Group of people.","index":128,"end_time":732.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You''re like, I feel like these people might schedule like an in person call.","index":129,"end_time":737.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":732.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s one thing.","index":130,"end_time":738.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":737.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then if you have a list that''s like, these are really busy people, they''re probably not going to want to jump on the call, but maybe they''ll answer three questions, five questions.","index":131,"end_time":744.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":738.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can do it like a test that way.","index":132,"end_time":746.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I was thinking maybe the priority account.","index":133,"end_time":749.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":746.97,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Start with those and send out the offer to sit down and have a call.","index":134,"end_time":753.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then after like a week or two weeks, depending on the amount of responses we get, extend that offer to more people.","index":135,"end_time":760.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":753.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then from there like we give it like a month and then we''re like, okay, we''re just going to send out the digital link and see what.","index":136,"end_time":767.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.57,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We can there, right?","index":137,"end_time":768.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we could do it either way like that.","index":138,"end_time":771.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And kind of, that''s kind of the good thing about ABM is if you have a lot of time, you can test and see what works.","index":139,"end_time":777.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":771.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because we have, you know, just until April will be.","index":140,"end_time":780.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":777.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We want to get things rolling as soon as possible so we can make those adjustments where needed.","index":141,"end_time":784.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":780.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, we can kind of see what''s working and if it''s not, we can pivot and, and switch it to just let''s answer these questions.","index":142,"end_time":791.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":784.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":143,"end_time":792.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":792,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, that sounds good.","index":144,"end_time":794.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":792.4,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that''s the point side of things.","index":145,"end_time":798.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":796.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know you had just mentioned the specific document to share with leadership.","index":146,"end_time":803.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":798.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''ll need your, you know, feedback on specific goals and what you''re looking for and what we''re looking to do.","index":147,"end_time":809.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":803.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So with the research report, it''s all kind of dependent on what we decide to do.","index":148,"end_time":815.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":810.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like you''re saying we may do this, we may do that when we launch.","index":149,"end_time":819.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":815.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It will determine exactly the number we can set.","index":150,"end_time":821.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":819.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like this is probably a probable goal that we can choose because if we don''t get approval back to like mid February, then we would have to change it kind of like the first time around where we had a number and then we had to shrink it just depending on when it was launched.","index":151,"end_time":833.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s my thoughts around that.","index":152,"end_time":835.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":834.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s hard.","index":153,"end_time":836.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":835.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I wouldn''t want to put like an exact number on it until we have them set up.","index":154,"end_time":839.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":836.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They''re about to be pushed live and we can say, okay, this is how much time they''re going to run.","index":155,"end_time":845.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":839.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This is kind of what we''re going to expect out of goals.","index":156,"end_time":847.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":845.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s what I would say right now about that.","index":157,"end_time":851.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":848.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If the only variable is when we launch, can we add an assumption like assuming that we''re able to Start this new phase of the campaign February 1st.","index":158,"end_time":861.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":851.44,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Our goal would be like five meetings booked per month or whatever the goal ended up being.","index":159,"end_time":866.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":861.279,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Can we add just an assumption there to cover that?","index":160,"end_time":869.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":867.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":161,"end_time":870.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like we could add that in there, especially just for our sake of knowing when it''s going to launch.","index":162,"end_time":874.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":870.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It will also determine or depend on audience size.","index":163,"end_time":877.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":874.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we''re sending it to a smaller group, obviously we''re not going to expect that they''re all going to answer.","index":164,"end_time":882.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":877.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we''re sending it to like a thousand people, our numbers would change.","index":165,"end_time":885.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just determine depending on what exactly the campaign is set up for and who it''s set up for will help us make those goal, like calls specifically number wise.","index":166,"end_time":897.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":886.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":167,"end_time":897.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So for the audience.","index":168,"end_time":898.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think I can answer that right now.","index":169,"end_time":900.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":898.7,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, that''d be great.","index":170,"end_time":901.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":900.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So just when we make the changes that I had sent over via team, so there was only like maybe 10 or 20 people that I think we should remove.","index":171,"end_time":909.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":901.66,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then if we can use clay to try to build out, I think the real estate and space tabs were a little bit more sparse.","index":172,"end_time":916.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":910.44,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So if we can build those out a little more and then add in anyone that we can get from those new universities, I know that''s probably a bigger lift in clay to get those built out, but I think once we do that, we can target all of those people.","index":173,"end_time":933.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":916.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good to know.","index":174,"end_time":935.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":934.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it would be the entire spreadsheet.","index":175,"end_time":938.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":936.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m just pulling it up right now.","index":176,"end_time":939.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":938.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Because we didn''t make those changes.","index":177,"end_time":940.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":178,"end_time":941.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":941.29,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yep.","index":179,"end_time":942.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":941.85,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"With pre.","index":180,"end_time":944.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":943.45,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I mean, if it''s a matter of prioritizing, preference goes to the new ones.","index":181,"end_time":949.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":944.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And there is some overlap with those new universities and universities we already have on the list.","index":182,"end_time":954.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":949.01,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They''re not completely new, but those are the priority ones.","index":183,"end_time":959.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":954.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"The both of these tabs.","index":184,"end_time":962.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":960.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":185,"end_time":962.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yep.","index":186,"end_time":963.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":962.97,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, let''s see how many there are.","index":187,"end_time":966.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":963.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"There''s 51 here.","index":188,"end_time":968.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":966.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"There should be like 420ish.","index":189,"end_time":971.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":968.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, so there''s more for the US side?","index":190,"end_time":974.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":972.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, way more.","index":191,"end_time":976.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":974.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I was just thinking if we break it down and maybe we could use those two tabs as like a test curve, but that''s a little bit bigger.","index":192,"end_time":984.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you thinking you''re going to be interested in doing the fill out the survey questions at all first?","index":193,"end_time":994.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":988.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or you want to just try the call aspect or approach first, see how it goes and then pivot.","index":194,"end_time":1000.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":994.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or would you be interested in doing the call aspect maybe on these two tabs and then the rest of them we have them actually fill out a survey.","index":195,"end_time":1010.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1000.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":196,"end_time":1010.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That''s kind of what I''m leaning towards.","index":197,"end_time":1012.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.98,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then with the two priority tabs, we send out the call offer, and then if we don''t get a response within a certain amount of time, then try again.","index":198,"end_time":1019.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1012.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Digital messaging.","index":199,"end_time":1021.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1020.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":200,"end_time":1022.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1021.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can.","index":201,"end_time":1023.25,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We can do that way.","index":202,"end_time":1024.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then this is.","index":203,"end_time":1027.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1026.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This must be the old version.","index":204,"end_time":1030.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1029.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I guess this is the old version is.","index":205,"end_time":1032.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1030.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So this tab.","index":206,"end_time":1034.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Sorry, you said real estate.","index":207,"end_time":1036.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1034.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"This is the one you would like.","index":208,"end_time":1037.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Enriched that one and the next one, the director of space tab too, since there''s, I think only like 20 or so on each.","index":209,"end_time":1044.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1037.73,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Those are really good titles for us.","index":210,"end_time":1047.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1045.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So that would be great to build out if we can.","index":211,"end_time":1049.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1047.22,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, as far as how many do you.","index":212,"end_time":1053.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1049.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is there a specific number you want to get this list to?","index":213,"end_time":1055.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"100 people?","index":214,"end_time":1057.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1056.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"50 people.","index":215,"end_time":1058.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1057.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Ideally.","index":216,"end_time":1061.18,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1060.46,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think some of the other tabs had like 5 to 600.","index":217,"end_time":1064.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1061.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think CIO and finance or maybe the two biggest.","index":218,"end_time":1067.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1064.54,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Facility management, I think was a big one too.","index":219,"end_time":1070.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":220,"end_time":1071.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1070.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we can get those two tabs to like 200.","index":221,"end_time":1076.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1071.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":222,"end_time":1078.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1078.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"At a minimum, that would be really great.","index":223,"end_time":1081.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1078.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Especially.","index":224,"end_time":1082.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Especially the real estate.","index":225,"end_time":1084.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1082.95,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Well, especially because we''re pulling some out too.","index":226,"end_time":1086.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1084.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":227,"end_time":1087.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1087.35,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I removed Pennsylvania and ut.","index":228,"end_time":1091.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1087.79,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Those are customers, so that''s why I pulled those.","index":229,"end_time":1093.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1091.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Gotcha.","index":230,"end_time":1094.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, those are on the suppression list.","index":231,"end_time":1097.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I didn''t mark every university that''s on the suppression list.","index":232,"end_time":1103.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1099.82,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I marked them when I saw them.","index":233,"end_time":1105.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1104.22,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But I provided that list of universities in teams.","index":234,"end_time":1109.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1105.78,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":235,"end_time":1111.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1110.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, so just to recap, so for these two groups, we''re going to enrich them and get them as well to 200 each, depending.","index":236,"end_time":1123.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or it''ll be higher because there''s so many different universities.","index":237,"end_time":1126.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1123.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think it will be higher since there''s like 400 something across the two labs.","index":238,"end_time":1131.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1127.09,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So as many as we can get for these that fit into the.","index":239,"end_time":1134.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1131.97,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":240,"end_time":1135.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1134.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Title categories that we have breakdowns for.","index":241,"end_time":1137.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1135.33,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, these will probably be a little bit bigger.","index":242,"end_time":1139.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1137.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So these two will enrich them for just the university title.","index":243,"end_time":1142.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1139.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"See what we can get.","index":244,"end_time":1142.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then these will be the call to action of getting on a call.","index":245,"end_time":1147.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1143.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the rest of these will be to fill out a survey.","index":246,"end_time":1150.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1147.17,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you have a particular approach you want to take to those questions?","index":247,"end_time":1157.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1150.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is there something that you and your team are like, we know exactly which questions we want to ask.","index":248,"end_time":1161.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1158.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or is that something we''ll just wait to hear back from you on what the questions are and then we can set it up from there?","index":249,"end_time":1167.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":250,"end_time":1167.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":251,"end_time":1168.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1167.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think I need to talk to Jay about some more specifics around what we want to ask, but we can get that to you pretty quickly.","index":252,"end_time":1174.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1168.22,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I''ll try to get that in the next week or so.","index":253,"end_time":1176.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.46,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I would just recommend keep it very short, like very short questions and maybe only five.","index":254,"end_time":1182.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1176.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, three to five.","index":255,"end_time":1183.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.39,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just because people''s attention spans, if they see that there''s a 10 question, they''re going to go, no, I''m not going to do that.","index":256,"end_time":1188.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1183.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if it''s like, like one of my other clients right now it''s a five question survey that we''re running and we literally say it''s a two minute, which is even generous, like five, five question survey.","index":257,"end_time":1198.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1188.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I, you could do it and if you are in the industry and you know the answer right away, it would take you 30 seconds.","index":258,"end_time":1203.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1198.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Right.","index":259,"end_time":1205.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1204.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So just, I would just say keep them very short questions and short answer options and only multiple choice if you''re having them fill out something that also makes people click out of the page.","index":260,"end_time":1216.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1205.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In your experience making these reports, is there any like hot type of question that you use as like the title or like something that really grabs attention that you''ve noticed?","index":261,"end_time":1228.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1217.2,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I wouldn''t say there''s like one just because I work through across different industries.","index":262,"end_time":1235.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1231.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But one of the biggest ones that people answer is first is what is the biggest struggle that you have right now?","index":263,"end_time":1242.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1236.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the additional questions like one of my clients right now works in the inventory space and so one of their questions is what is the biggest struggles you''re facing right now?","index":264,"end_time":1250.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1242.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then they kind of get into the like percentages of something and then what they''d be open to like kind of fixing.","index":265,"end_time":1257.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1250.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would you be open to like just for an example, integrating AI into your systems.","index":266,"end_time":1263.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1257.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you comfortable with where you''re at?","index":267,"end_time":1264.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1263.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Kind of give people the option and that ultimately gives us feedback for your thing.","index":268,"end_time":1269.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1264.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m, I''m just thinking plan on now if they''re interested because some people may be facing a problem and they''re not at that point quite yet where they''re like, oh, I''m not there yet.","index":269,"end_time":1279.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1269.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And it kind of gives us insight into if this is a problem that they''re facing.","index":270,"end_time":1282.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1279.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"How long has this been going on?","index":271,"end_time":1283.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1282.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t know the exact things that people for plan on would say, but if, if it kind of gives you.","index":272,"end_time":1291.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1283.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me back up.","index":273,"end_time":1292.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1291.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The best way to do this is what is going to be helpful for you and your sales team to see from these people.","index":274,"end_time":1297.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that''s how I would approach it.","index":275,"end_time":1299.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1297.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s not just for like research''s sake, but what questions can you ask these people that will ultimately benefit your sales team to contact some of these people down the road?","index":276,"end_time":1310.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1299.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It will be an anonymous survey because that''s how they work.","index":277,"end_time":1314.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1311.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But if we know what groups that we''re targeting and we''re asking questions that would apply across the board to people that you would reach out to, it will be beneficial either way.","index":278,"end_time":1323.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1314.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I would keep it generic in that sense.","index":279,"end_time":1325.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1323.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like if these are all people that you would reach out to to try to get business or plan on, what are questions that you want answered by the exact people you''re trying to get on the phone?","index":280,"end_time":1334.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1325.57,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":281,"end_time":1334.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1334.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I would just think of it that way.","index":282,"end_time":1336.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1334.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Not as much like the specifics and the nitty gritty of things, but one is helpful for you guys to know for approaching them in the future.","index":283,"end_time":1343.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1336.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":284,"end_time":1344.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1343.83,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And also in return, like, what can you advertise later on?","index":285,"end_time":1347.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1344.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if you see a ton of people are saying, my biggest struggle is space management or whatever, then you guys could potentially do a campaign.","index":286,"end_time":1355.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1347.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We, you know, run organic social around that big problem because, you know, so many people are clicking it.","index":287,"end_time":1360.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1355.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In the one survey I''m running now, we''re seeing a ton of people are clicking the exact same option and it''s being sent to 3,000 plus contacts, which is again, great data for my client because they''re like, wow, now we know that this is the biggest struggle.","index":288,"end_time":1372.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1360.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let''s talk about this more in our newsletter in our socials.","index":289,"end_time":1375.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1372.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So think through it that way, I would say, when you come up with the questions.","index":290,"end_time":1379.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1375.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, no, that''s good advice.","index":291,"end_time":1380.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1379.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I appreciate that.","index":292,"end_time":1381.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1380.68,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll definitely do that.","index":293,"end_time":1383.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1381.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"One question that I think I''d like to ask for our sake is like, are you interested?","index":294,"end_time":1389.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1384,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Are you pursuing purchasing the type of system that we sell within the next like X number of months?","index":295,"end_time":1394.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1389.76,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just.","index":296,"end_time":1395.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1394.96,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah, like, is there a real opportunity here?","index":297,"end_time":1397.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1395.24,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Exactly.","index":298,"end_time":1398.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, something like that.","index":299,"end_time":1399.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1398.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would.","index":300,"end_time":1399.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would kind of like give you insight into if they''re at that stage of buying yet.","index":301,"end_time":1403.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1399.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, that''s good to know.","index":302,"end_time":1405.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1403.84,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"One thing I wanted to mention, just talking about building up more titles in clay.","index":303,"end_time":1409.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1405.52,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Once we build out the titles for the two new university tabs, you might not even need to add more to the real estate and space tabs.","index":304,"end_time":1419.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1410.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like that might add enough titles just across those universities that you don''t have to add more.","index":305,"end_time":1425.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1419.48,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Right.","index":306,"end_time":1426.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Typically.","index":307,"end_time":1427.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1426.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But okay.","index":308,"end_time":1428.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1427.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","index":309,"end_time":1430.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1429.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we''ll enrich these two.","index":310,"end_time":1432.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1430.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I will start to come up with a sequence, just outline of what we could say when we''re trying to get them on a call and then what we can say if we''re trying to get them to fill out a survey.","index":311,"end_time":1444.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1432.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like I said, I''LL probably wait a little bit more on the survey just until we get questions from you to kind of see what it''s around to focus that copy.","index":312,"end_time":1451.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"However, for the call, is there anything you can tell me about what those calls kind of look like?","index":313,"end_time":1456.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are they 15 minutes, are they 20 minutes survey calls?","index":314,"end_time":1460.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1456.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":315,"end_time":1461.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like if we have them jump on a call, can we say we''d love to talk to you for 15 minutes, 30 minutes, kind of make it more appealing than just saying like open endedly hop on a call because you never know what that means and we can kind of explain what they''d walk through.","index":316,"end_time":1474.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1461.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is there anything, you know, off the top of your head that we could work into that copy?","index":317,"end_time":1477.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1474.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think that we could say 10 minutes or less.","index":318,"end_time":1481.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1478.13,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I can''t imagine that it has to be any longer than that.","index":319,"end_time":1484.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1481.28,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Beyond that, I mean, maybe have a call with our solution experts.","index":320,"end_time":1492.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1487.36,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think we could.","index":321,"end_time":1495.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1494.72,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If you think that that''s compelling, then maybe we could add that, like have a call with our solution expert and ask a few questions or answer a few questions around like the main struggles that your university is facing.","index":322,"end_time":1508.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1495.56,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Specifically right now there''s a lot that''s changing in higher ed with like different regulations and funding cuts from the government and stuff like that.","index":323,"end_time":1519.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1510.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So maybe we could tie in, like given how quickly the landscape of higher education is evolving, like sit down with us and answer a few questions and receive the report in return.","index":324,"end_time":1534.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1520.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"On like.","index":325,"end_time":1535.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1534.51,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":326,"end_time":1536.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1535.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Find out if your university has unique struggles or if it''s across the board, something.","index":327,"end_time":1541.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1536.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"That is what I''m thinking.","index":328,"end_time":1542.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1541.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We''ll definitely want to paint it around what they''re going to get out of it that you know, like this report will help you to see what other universities are going through, things like that.","index":329,"end_time":1551.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1542.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we, we would want to make that shiny at the end, right?","index":330,"end_time":1555.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1551.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, but yeah.","index":331,"end_time":1556.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1555.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, so let''s focus on this for now then once we have the exact specifics of all this and we can talk a little bit about an ad approach that we can work simultaneously across.","index":332,"end_time":1569.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1556.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me just make sure there''s nothing else.","index":333,"end_time":1572.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1570.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think that''s it for now.","index":334,"end_time":1577.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1575.88,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we can get started on that.","index":335,"end_time":1580.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1579.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll definitely start working on the list and like I said, just an outline of what those messages will look like and then we can go from there and I will keep you updated as far as anything that we have on our end.","index":336,"end_time":1593.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1580.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then once we kind of have everything confirmed, we can use one of our meeting times, whether it''s next week, to go through the specifics of maybe a potential launch time.","index":337,"end_time":1603.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1593.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then the goals that we''re thinking, depending on our audience sizes and lists.","index":338,"end_time":1606.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1603.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think it''d be good to separate in the beginning, at least, if we''re initiating a call, a goal for that, initiating a survey, and then if we have to pivot and, you know, make it.","index":339,"end_time":1616.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1606.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If these don''t get any traction, we''ll change the number to, like, a whole number for everybody across the board.","index":340,"end_time":1622.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1616.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":341,"end_time":1623.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1623.07,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":342,"end_time":1624.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1623.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And just to kind of clarify my message, too, in the chat, I would really.","index":343,"end_time":1629.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1624.51,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I really want to build out with you a written plan.","index":344,"end_time":1633.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1629.79,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s just.","index":345,"end_time":1636.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1635.39,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s an.","index":346,"end_time":1636.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.03,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s a weird place right now where we don''t have a team lead.","index":347,"end_time":1639.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1636.59,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"We actually have someone starting on the 20th.","index":348,"end_time":1641.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1639.23,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And so I just want to be able to provide this document to, like, my manager, who''s not necessarily involved, but seems to have opinions for some reason.","index":349,"end_time":1652.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1642.13,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I want to be able to share this with her and be like, okay, read this.","index":350,"end_time":1657.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1654.21,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Like, let me know what you think if you have any concerns and get that approval in writing.","index":351,"end_time":1663.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1657.89,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Because I. Yeah, I just.","index":352,"end_time":1665.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1663.57,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I don''t want to be in a place where a month after we launch, they''re like, why are you doing survey?","index":353,"end_time":1669.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1665.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And that''s.","index":354,"end_time":1669.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1669.53,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I understand.","index":355,"end_time":1671.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1670.94,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You got to have your bases covered, too.","index":356,"end_time":1672.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1671.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That makes sense.","index":357,"end_time":1673.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1672.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would it be better in a deck form or just a document form?","index":358,"end_time":1676.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1673.54,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think a document.","index":359,"end_time":1678.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1676.78,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"What makes sense for me.","index":360,"end_time":1679.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1678.3,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I mean, if it''s.","index":361,"end_time":1680.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1679.66,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If it''s a deck with, like, the charts and whatnot, if that''s easier, that''s fine.","index":362,"end_time":1684.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1680.34,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"But I just want to have timelines of what we expect to accomplish each month.","index":363,"end_time":1689.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1684.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"And then I can share that with, like, my design team, too, and say, can you commit to reviewing, you know, the graphics?","index":364,"end_time":1695.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1689.74,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"If we provide them to you on this date, can you review them within a week just to get everybody, like, aligned so that we don''t have.","index":365,"end_time":1702.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1695.58,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Because I know that''s been a big slowdown.","index":366,"end_time":1705.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1703.41,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yes.","index":367,"end_time":1706.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1706.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I will say with that.","index":368,"end_time":1708.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1706.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you think that this is definitely the route we''re going to go then is a survey?","index":369,"end_time":1711.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1708.37,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I guess I should have asked that before I start working on it.","index":370,"end_time":1714.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1711.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Specifically, do you think that this is something you''ll get approval on, that we can go ahead and launch, so we can go ahead and start, like, kind of the preliminary work on this?","index":371,"end_time":1722.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1714.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think that we will get approval.","index":372,"end_time":1724.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1722.93,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I talked to Jay.","index":373,"end_time":1726.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1725.79,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"He''s fully on board, and that holds a lot of weight since he''s the manager of, like, the Solutions Advisor team.","index":374,"end_time":1732.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1726.51,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":375,"end_time":1732.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1732.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The only other person is my manager and maybe our gm, but I think they''re going to think it''s a good idea too.","index":376,"end_time":1739.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1733.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Do you know when you''ll have like their say on it?","index":377,"end_time":1743.31,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1740.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, this document is to get their approval.","index":378,"end_time":1745.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1743.55,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I think in order to see.","index":379,"end_time":1747.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1745.67,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay.","index":380,"end_time":1748.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1747.55,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In order to get their like full buy in, I think you need to give them the details.","index":381,"end_time":1752.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1748.19,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Is there a specific number you''re looking for as far as like your goal for this?","index":382,"end_time":1757.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1752.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like, if I send you an outline, maybe I''ll outline exactly what our initiatives are into a document.","index":383,"end_time":1762.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1757.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll leave it open ended for now.","index":384,"end_time":1764.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1763,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can give you my suggestion and then we kind of talk about it that way.","index":385,"end_time":1768.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1764.36,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Would that be best?","index":386,"end_time":1769.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1768.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":387,"end_time":1769.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1769.4,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":388,"end_time":1770.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1769.8,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I can create a work on it together.","index":389,"end_time":1771.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1770.12,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1772.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1772.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I don''t want to hold you up in.","index":391,"end_time":1773.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1772.6,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"In talking to them.","index":392,"end_time":1774.96,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1774.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I can create that outline.","index":393,"end_time":1776.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1774.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Kind of just what we''re thinking here.","index":394,"end_time":1777.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1776.32,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Build out this a little bit better.","index":395,"end_time":1779.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1778.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":396,"end_time":1780.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1780.38,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Send that over to you.","index":397,"end_time":1782.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1781.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s perfect.","index":398,"end_time":1782.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.22,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":399,"end_time":1783.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1782.9,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I think it will also help us kind of feel out like who''s doing what, what are our dates look like, what''s the end?","index":400,"end_time":1788.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1783.26,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It''s easier for me sometimes to write it out than to talk about it.","index":401,"end_time":1792.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1788.86,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"It just feels so abstract.","index":402,"end_time":1794.299,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1792.94,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Easier when it''s on paper.","index":403,"end_time":1795.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1794.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":404,"end_time":1795.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, understandable.","index":405,"end_time":1797.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1795.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The only other thing I want to mention before we hop off is the owner, Justin, one of our owners, I was talking to him about these gifted points.","index":406,"end_time":1805.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1797.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Very much contingent on getting that contract amendment back.","index":407,"end_time":1808.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1805.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So that is the only other thing kind of holding it up is if we''re doing all this extra work.","index":408,"end_time":1812.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1809.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"He just wants to make sure we get that signed addendum back.","index":409,"end_time":1815.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1812.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just want.","index":410,"end_time":1816.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1815.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know it''s not in your hands right now, but just wanted to remind you there that he''s really waiting on that.","index":411,"end_time":1822.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1816.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":412,"end_time":1823.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1822.63,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Before I start putting in all these requests for the gifted points, he''s going to be asking me, you know, where''s this contract?","index":413,"end_time":1828.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1823.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I, I just.","index":414,"end_time":1829.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1828.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Understandable.","index":415,"end_time":1830.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1829.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Just got an email late last night from our legal team with.","index":416,"end_time":1835.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1831.99,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"They have like one red line.","index":417,"end_time":1837.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1835.91,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So I''ll get that over to you.","index":418,"end_time":1838.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1837.15,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":419,"end_time":1839.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1838.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds good.","index":420,"end_time":1840.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1839.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":421,"end_time":1841.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1841.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, I''m excited to work on this.","index":422,"end_time":1842.63,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1841.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll start working on those things.","index":423,"end_time":1843.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1842.63,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And oh, did you have any updates on the video at all?","index":424,"end_time":1846.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1843.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Are you still working through that?","index":425,"end_time":1848.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1846.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No.","index":426,"end_time":1848.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1848.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thank you for sharing that.","index":427,"end_time":1849.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1848.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"I need to send that over to Roderick and his team and let them know that we need to get all of our edits to you guys.","index":428,"end_time":1856.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1849.71,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"There''s no, there''s no going back, so I need to make that clear to them and then send that over to them.","index":429,"end_time":1863.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1856.47,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"So thank you for that.","index":430,"end_time":1864.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1863.53,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Of course.","index":431,"end_time":1865.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1864.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All right, Lauren, I will be in touch with you on teams.","index":432,"end_time":1867.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1865.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And, yeah, I hope you have a good rest of your day.","index":433,"end_time":1869.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1867.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You, too.","index":434,"end_time":1870.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1869.57,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":435,"end_time":1871.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1870.37,"speaker_name":"Lauren Poirier"},{"text":"Bye.","index":436,"end_time":1871.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1871.25,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"dateString":"2026-01-15T15:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85838482744?pwd=DfHCIIaG2yOwHknntqCcBJ0t7zVKZZ.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","lauren.poirier@planonsoftware.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEW5A0BT5BEZZ41K7PVC0TVZ","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Outlined phased ABM rollout with call-first and digital survey fallback by April deadline.","Agreed on preferred survey call length of 10 minutes or less for better engagement.","Taylor confirmed leadership approval to gift points beyond 60/month to support campaign scope.","Team committed to enriching priority university contact tabs to reach up to 200 titles each.","Lauren requested written plan to align cross-functional stakeholders ahead of new team lead start."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We really want this campaign to be successful for you guys.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"I really want to build out with you a written plan.","speaker":"Lauren Poirier"},{"quote":"We can do a test audience too... we can pivot and switch it.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"topics":["abm","survey","delivery","audience","approval"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-turbo","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-16T21:12:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **ABM Campaign Planning and Points Management**\n\nThe team agreed on a flexible ABM campaign structure with a **60-point monthly budget** fully covered by leadership to ensure campaign success (04:06).\n\n- **Taylor Doerbaum** explained that the **60 points** cover all regular work, with any overage gifted by leadership, avoiding extra cost to the client.\n- Campaign components like targeted ads, outreach sequences, and image ad refreshes are bundled to optimize point use and efficiency.\n- The point usage will vary monthly, with heavier setup work in the early months (January-February) and lighter management tasks later.\n- A **contract amendment** for gifted points is pending legal approval, which is critical to proceed with the expanded campaign scope (29:54).\n\n## **Survey and Outreach Strategy**\n\nThe team decided to combine direct call invitations for priority accounts with a digital survey for broader outreach, aiming for **early campaign launch in February** (09:33).\n\n- Priority contacts from two key university segments will receive a call invitation first, followed by a digital survey if no response comes within 1-2 weeks.\n- The survey will be short, with **3 to 5 questions**, designed for quick completion (under 2 minutes) to maximize response rates.\n- Questions will focus on identifying key struggles, interest in purchasing solutions within a defined timeframe, and openness to new technologies.\n- Taylor suggested keeping questions generic but relevant to sales insights, enabling targeted follow-up campaigns based on responses.\n\n## **Audience List Enrichment and Targeting**\n\nThe plan includes enriching two university-related contact lists to reach at least **200 contacts each**, with potential to expand further, prioritizing new university titles (15:01).\n\n- Taylor will enrich the \"Real Estate\" and \"Director of Space\" tabs using Clay, focusing on titles that fit the campaign’s target profile.\n- Lauren identified approximately **420+ contacts** across these segments, with suppression of existing customers to avoid overlap.\n- Additional university contacts are prioritized to increase volume in key segments like CIO, finance, and facility management, aiming for lists of **200+ contacts** per tab.\n- This enriched audience allows segmented outreach: calls for priority segments and surveys for larger groups.\n\n## **Survey Content and Messaging Development**\n\nThe team will develop messaging focused on offering a **10-minute or less call with solution experts**, emphasizing industry challenges and delivering a branded report in return (24:38).\n\n- Lauren emphasized framing the call around current higher education issues like regulatory changes and funding cuts.\n- Taylor will draft outreach sequences for both call scheduling and survey participation, awaiting finalized survey questions from Lauren’s team.\n- Messaging will highlight the value of the report, showing participants how their peers are impacted and what solutions are available.\n- The goal is to make the offer appealing and clear to maximize engagement and conversions.\n\n## **Approval Process and Timeline Alignment**\n\nLauren will lead creating a detailed campaign plan document with timelines and deliverables to secure formal approval from management and design teams by mid-February (27:04).\n\n- This document will clarify monthly milestones, responsibilities, and review deadlines to avoid delays, particularly in creative approvals.\n- Taylor will prepare an outline of initiatives and goals to support Lauren’s discussions with leadership.\n- Approval of the legal addendum for gifted points is a key dependency before campaign work can fully proceed (29:54).\n- Lauren confirmed strong internal support from Jay and expects buy-in from her manager and GM once the plan is formalized.\n\n## **Video Project Status**\n\nLauren is coordinating final edits with Roderick’s team to complete the video project, aiming to finalize changes quickly to avoid further delays (30:48).\n\n- She will communicate clearly that no further edits will be accepted after this stage to keep the project on track.\n- This will allow the video to be delivered promptly to support campaign assets and messaging.","outline":null,"keywords":["ABM campaign","survey development","audience enrichment","outreach sequence","gifted points","higher education challenges"],"overview":"- **ABM Campaign Structure:** Team agreed on a flexible ABM budget of 60 points monthly, covered by leadership for success.\n\n- **Survey Launch Strategy:** Direct calls followed by a digital survey for priority accounts, targeting February launch.\n\n- **Contact List Goals:** Enrich two university-related lists, aiming for at least 200 contacts each, focusing on new titles.\n\n- **Messaging Development:** Team to create outreach messaging for calls with solution experts, emphasizing industry challenges for engagement.\n\n- **Timeline Approval Process:** Detailed campaign plan document due by mid-February for management approval and clear responsibilities.\n\n- **Video Project Coordination:** Final edits being made to the video, no further revisions accepted to meet campaign timeline.","action_items":"\n**Lauren Poirier**\nProvide detailed survey questions in coordination with Jay within about a week (19:27)\nFinalize and send the contract amendment with legal’s one remaining redline to Taylor’s team (30:23)\nShare video edits with Roderick and his team to finalize and send to Taylor (30:38)\nReview and approve the forthcoming detailed campaign plan document to facilitate leadership buy-in (27:04)\nSupply the specific updates to audience data for removing suppressed contacts (customers) and prioritize new universities for Clay enrichment (14:57)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nDraft and send a clear, detailed written campaign plan outlining timelines, goals, and responsibilities for Lauren to share with her team and leadership (26:30)\nInitiate Clay enrichment for the “Real Estate” and “Director of Space” tabs aiming for approximately 200 contacts each (15:40)\nDevelop preliminary outreach sequences for both call invitations and digital survey campaigns, awaiting final survey questions before completing survey messaging (23:46)\nMonitor gifted points approval contingent on receiving signed contract amendment and coordinate with owner Justin for contract status updates (29:54)\nKeep Lauren updated through Teams on progress and confirm launch timelines and goals once contract and plans are finalized (27:50)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"da151509-5dd2-445a-95ac-ab25677c3681","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
