INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: New North x Planon Weekly Meeting',
  '## **ABM Campaign Planning and Points Management**

The team agreed on a flexible ABM campaign structure with a **60-point monthly budget** fully covered by leadership to ensure campaign success (04:06).

- **Taylor Doerbaum** explained that the **60 points** cover all regular work, with any overage gifted by leadership, avoiding extra cost to the client.
- Campaign components like targeted ads, outreach sequences, and image ad refreshes are bundled to optimize point use and efficiency.
- The point usage will vary monthly, with heavier setup work in the early months (January-February) and lighter management tasks later.
- A **contract amendment** for gifted points is pending legal approval, which is critical to proceed with the expanded campaign scope (29:54).

## **Survey and Outreach Strategy**

The team decided to combine direct call invitations for priority accounts with a digital survey for broader outreach, aiming for **early campaign launch in February** (09:33).

- Priority contacts from two key university segments will receive a call invitation first, followed by a digital survey if no response comes within 1-2 weeks.
- The survey will be short, with **3 to 5 questions**, designed for quick completion (under 2 minutes) to maximize response rates.
- Questions will focus on identifying key struggles, interest in purchasing solutions within a defined timeframe, and openness to new technologies.
- Taylor suggested keeping questions generic but relevant to sales insights, enabling targeted follow-up campaigns based on responses.

## **Audience List Enrichment and Targeting**

The plan includes enriching two university-related contact lists to reach at least **200 contacts each**, with potential to expand further, prioritizing new university titles (15:01).

- Taylor will enrich the "Real Estate" and "Director of Space" tabs using Clay, focusing on titles that fit the campaign’s target profile.
- Lauren identified approximately **420+ contacts** across these segments, with suppression of existing customers to avoid overlap.
- Additional university contacts are prioritized to increase volume in key segments like CIO, finance, and facility management, aiming for lists of **200+ contacts** per tab.
- This enriched audience allows segmented outreach: calls for priority segments and surveys for larger groups.

## **Survey Content and Messaging Development**

The team will develop messaging focused on offering a **10-minute or less call with solution experts**, emphasizing industry challenges and delivering a branded report in return (24:38).

- Lauren emphasized framing the call around current higher education issues like regulatory changes and funding cuts.
- Taylor will draft outreach sequences for both call scheduling and survey participation, awaiting finalized survey questions from Lauren’s team.
- Messaging will highlight the value of the report, showing participants how their peers are impacted and what solutions are available.
- The goal is to make the offer appealing and clear to maximize engagement and conversions.

## **Approval Process and Timeline Alignment**

Lauren will lead creating a detailed campaign plan document with timelines and deliverables to secure formal approval from management and design teams by mid-February (27:04).

- This document will clarify monthly milestones, responsibilities, and review deadlines to avoid delays, particularly in creative approvals.
- Taylor will prepare an outline of initiatives and goals to support Lauren’s discussions with leadership.
- Approval of the legal addendum for gifted points is a key dependency before campaign work can fully proceed (29:54).
- Lauren confirmed strong internal support from Jay and expects buy-in from her manager and GM once the plan is formalized.

## **Video Project Status**

Lauren is coordinating final edits with Roderick’s team to complete the video project, aiming to finalize changes quickly to avoid further delays (30:48).

- She will communicate clearly that no further edits will be accepted after this stage to keep the project on track.
- This will allow the video to be delivered promptly to support campaign assets and messaging.',
  '2026-01-15 15:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Provide detailed survey questions in coordination with Jay within about a week (19:27)","completed":false},{"text":"Finalize and send the contract amendment with legal’s one remaining redline to Taylor’s team (30:23)","completed":false},{"text":"Share video edits with Roderick and his team to finalize and send to Taylor (30:38)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and approve the forthcoming detailed campaign plan document to facilitate leadership buy-in (27:04)","completed":false},{"text":"Supply the specific updates to audience data for removing suppressed contacts (customers) and prioritize new universities for Clay enrichment (14:57)","completed":false},{"text":"Draft and send a clear, detailed written campaign plan outlining timelines, goals, and responsibilities for Lauren to share with her team and leadership (26:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Initiate Clay enrichment for the “Real Estate” and “Director of Space” tabs aiming for approximately 200 contacts each (15:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Develop preliminary outreach sequences for both call invitations and digital survey campaigns, awaiting final survey questions before completing survey messaging (23:46)","completed":false},{"text":"Monitor gifted points approval contingent on receiving signed contract amendment and coordinate with owner Justin for contract status updates (29:54)","completed":false},{"text":"Keep Lauren updated through Teams on progress and confirm launch timelines and goals once contract and plans are finalized (27:50)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
  true
FROM new_meeting;

-- Meeting: BioSAFE Weekly Meeting (2026-01-13 18:30:00+00)
WITH new_meeting AS (
  INSERT INTO compass_meetings (contract_id, meeting_date, source, external_id, title, participants, duration_seconds, recording_url, transcript, sentiment, raw_metadata, created_at, updated_at)
  VALUES (
    'ca141f89-32e5-42c5-8c4d-bb32dee9aef2',
    '2026-01-13 18:30:00+00',
    'fireflies',
    '01KEQBG5BC2T15DVQWAFZ9KWDD',
    'BioSAFE Weekly Meeting',
    '{"Dan Nelsen","Taylor Doerbaum"}'::text[],
    1182,
    'https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81421883896?pwd=9iHNOeWOt9gp3Uqm9ajWXxGhOvoFVO.1',
    '{"id":"01KEQBG5BC2T15DVQWAFZ9KWDD","title":"BioSAFE Weekly Meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Website Launch and Design Adjustments**\n\nThe team is finalizing website edits aiming for a launch early next week.\n\n- **Dan Nelsen confirmed the last round of website feedback is expected by midday tomorrow, with the goal of launching on Tuesday following the holiday** (19:10)  \n    - Dan’s team is reviewing final edits today and tomorrow to avoid delays.  \n    - Taylor Doerbaum suggested launching on a Monday or Tuesday to monitor performance early in the week.  \n    - They agreed to pivot launch timing if feedback or changes delay readiness.  \n    - The launch timing aligns with internal holiday schedules to ensure full team availability.  \n\n- **Design improvements will include three mockups for header layout and photo presentation to enhance visual separation and impact** (05:28)  \n    - Taylor’s team will create versions with a blue banner behind header text and options to add dimension behind images.  \n    - Dan requested swapping the far-left hero image with a sharper, less-used photo from their folder to improve page appeal.  \n    - Taylor will note this swap for Brandon or Roland to act on during their review.  \n    - These design options will be sent to Dan for selection prior to final swap without disturbing ongoing site review.\n\n- **Dan emphasized the need for clearer space delineation on the homepage, suggesting visual separation between header, photos, and text areas** (02:31)  \n    - He proposed dropping the \"Safe engineering as a world leader\" text lower to create breathing room near the contact section.  \n    - Taylor agreed to explore banner backgrounds or text highlights to distinguish segments from the navigation bar.  \n    - Dan deferred final preference to the design team’s judgment, trusting their ability to find the best layout.  \n    - These layout changes aim to enhance user focus and brand message clarity.\n\n## **Poster Design Refinements**\n\nMinor but important formatting corrections will finalize the poster’s presentation quality.\n\n- **Dan requested removal of white margin bubbles around text boxes, replacing them with gray boxes and a tighter white border to reduce visual clutter** (15:14)  \n    - Taylor confirmed they will reduce box thickness and align it better with the gray background.  \n    - This adjustment targets a cleaner, more consistent poster look that matches overall design language.  \n    - Dan sees this as a straightforward fix to improve aesthetic balance.\n\n- **Text formatting issues including compressed text, inconsistent font sizes, and typos will be corrected across the poster** (16:37)  \n    - Taylor will have their team run a full control check for alignment and font consistency after recovering editing permissions.  \n    - Dan stressed the importance of a fresh review to catch subtle formatting errors missed by prior reviews.  \n    - This quality check ensures professional presentation and avoids distracting imperfections.  \n    - The team acknowledged that some squishing occurred during file permission constraints, explaining current issues.\n\n- **Copy tightening will merge two lines into one on the poster’s lower section to match formatting standards** (15:55)  \n    - Dan emailed the revised copy to Taylor for implementation.  \n    - This change supports a more compact and visually uniform layout.  \n    - The adjustment will help the poster’s readability and overall coherence.\n\n## **Content and SEO Strategy Post-Launch**\n\nContent updates and SEO focus are planned immediately following the website launch.\n\n- **Dan approved the blog content, marking it ready for site publication to enhance ongoing content marketing efforts** (18:30)  \n    - Taylor confirmed they will upload the blog to the website to increase fresh content availability.  \n    - This addition supports SEO and engagement objectives post-launch.  \n    - The timely blog publication will complement the new site’s launch momentum.\n\n- **SEO optimization will become the priority once the site is live, aiming to improve organic traffic and search ranking** (18:52)  \n    - Taylor noted the team’s availability resumes Tuesday post-holiday, aligning with the launch timeline.  \n    - They plan to shift from design edits to SEO tactics immediately after launch.  \n    - This phased approach maximizes resource focus and business impact.\n\n## **Team Coordination and Communication**\n\nClear communication protocols and documentation support smooth project progress.\n\n- **Taylor will keep Dan updated on all design changes and provide the three header mockups for review before final decisions** (19:18)  \n    - This ensures Dan’s team can review and approve changes without disrupting ongoing feedback cycles.  \n    - Transparency in updates helps maintain alignment and avoid surprises.  \n    - The approach balances iterative feedback with efficient workflows.\n\n- **Dan requested notes be left on design files to guide Brandon and Roland during their review, ensuring clarity on requested changes** (06:42)  \n    - Taylor confirmed she will add comments to relevant assets for easy reference.  \n    - This reduces confusion and accelerates review turnaround.  \n    - The note-taking practice supports accountability and smooth handoffs.\n\n- **Dan shared challenges with accessing encrypted design storage but confirmed Taylor’s team replicated necessary files to avoid delays** (18:02)  \n    - The workaround prevented bottlenecks in editing and review cycles.  \n    - Taylor acknowledged the technical issue and ensured continuity of work.  \n    - This contingency maintained project momentum despite file access hurdles.","outline":null,"keywords":["Website launch","homepage design","poster edits","image replacement","visual hierarchy","quality control"],"overview":"- **Website Launch:** Final edits expected by midday tomorrow, aimed for a launch on Tuesday post-holiday.  \n- **Design Mockups:** Three new header layout versions will enhance visual impact, including a sharper hero image.  \n- **Poster Adjustments:** White margin bubbles will be replaced with gray boxes for a cleaner presentation.  \n- **SEO Focus Post-Launch:** SEO optimization efforts will begin immediately after site launch for improved traffic and ranking.  \n- **Team Coordination:** Regular updates on design changes will ensure alignment and timely feedback throughout the process.  \n- **Access Issues:** Encrypted design storage challenges resolved by replicating files, maintaining project momentum.","action_items":"\n**Dan Nelsen**\nProvide final feedback from team on website edits by end of day or midday next day and notify Taylor when complete (00:47)\nConfirm if any other sharper lead photo options exist in folder to best replace far-left homepage image and share suggestions via chat/folder (05:28)\nReview and confirm poster copy consolidation and font size/format consistency and coordinate any further required corrections (15:50)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend website developer three mockups of homepage top header variations with blue background banners and image dimension effects for selection (04:57)\nSwap the far-left homepage image with a sharper alternative as discussed and add a comment/note on backend for design team visibility (06:42)\nPerform a comprehensive quality control check on poster design for typos, font sizes, and formatting issues, particularly for compressed text areas (17:14)\nUpload approved blog content to website to increase fresh content post-launch (18:30)\nKeep Dan updated on all changes and send finalized design mockups for review (19:18)\n"},"duration":19.700000762939453,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"id":1,"name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"sentences":[{"text":"Extra fun.","index":0,"end_time":0.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":0.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Oh, wow.","index":1,"end_time":1.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":0.96,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s really tough.","index":2,"end_time":2.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":3,"end_time":2.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"A lot of people on our team too, internally cross time zones and I always think it''s crazy how, you know, everybody''s in a different part of the day.","index":4,"end_time":9.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Some people are on calls in the dark and it''s just funny.","index":5,"end_time":12.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":10.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s a tricky.","index":6,"end_time":15.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":13.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"For sure.","index":7,"end_time":15.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":15.48,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":8,"end_time":17.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":17.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So thank you for getting the poster over.","index":9,"end_time":22.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":18.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It looks good.","index":10,"end_time":23.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":22.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I. I think just two little comments on it and other than that, everything looked good.","index":11,"end_time":27.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":23.2,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Good.","index":12,"end_time":28.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":27.85,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":13,"end_time":29.21,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":28.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":14,"end_time":29.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":29.29,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then I have my team looking through the last round of website edits.","index":15,"end_time":39.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":32.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"If they have any comments, this should be the last round and then we should be ready to go.","index":16,"end_time":45.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":17,"end_time":46.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":46.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s exciting.","index":18,"end_time":47.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":47.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m hoping to have any feedback end of day today, kind of midday, tomorrowish.","index":19,"end_time":53.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":47.85,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then depending on what that looks like, we can either talk kind of launch and timeline there or see what implementing any edits would look like.","index":20,"end_time":64.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":54.18,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":21,"end_time":65.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":64.66,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If they just want to leave comments.","index":22,"end_time":66.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":65.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Whenever you''re ready, I''ll send it over to our developer to do that.","index":23,"end_time":70.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":66.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then as far as launching, we would just want to launch obviously on a Monday or Tuesday early in the week so we can keep an eye on it.","index":24,"end_time":76.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":70.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I did have one comment.","index":25,"end_time":78.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":77.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I reviewed it with Bailey yesterday.","index":26,"end_time":81.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":78.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I was just bringing her in on a couple.","index":27,"end_time":82.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":81.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Couple of our changes.","index":28,"end_time":83.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":82.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"She just recommended.","index":29,"end_time":84.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":83.7,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I know we had talked about this homepage and your vision for it a little bit.","index":30,"end_time":88.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":84.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"She had just recommended putting the header, like the text header above these three pictures and wanted to see what your input was on that.","index":31,"end_time":97.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":88.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And we could also move like the actual like copy down here below.","index":32,"end_time":101.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":97.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But she just thought that maybe having this header would be beneficial for the top at least.","index":33,"end_time":106.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And if you wanted to keep the additional like sub copy but below, we can do that.","index":34,"end_time":110.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":106.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"She just said it''s good.","index":35,"end_time":111.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":110.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s better for like visibility on the page.","index":36,"end_time":115.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":112.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That way it shows kind of like your brand tagline ahead of anything else.","index":37,"end_time":120.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":115.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I know you had mentioned that you did want the pictures like kind of front and center, so totally your call as far as like your preference.","index":38,"end_time":127.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":120.23,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But we can continue to keep these like at the center and just move the heading up.","index":39,"end_time":131.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But wanted to get your like, your feedback there and see what you thought.","index":40,"end_time":133.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Um, I think that would work fine.","index":41,"end_time":139.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":135.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"What I''d.","index":42,"end_time":140.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"What I''m thinking as I look at this though is so right right now.","index":43,"end_time":146.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":140.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I think we could use more space delineation.","index":44,"end_time":150.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":45,"end_time":151.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":151.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Kind of as this.","index":46,"end_time":154.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":152.96,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"As you see the screen, the different segments are kind of delineated by white space, which with, I think the all white background just doesn''t create kind of natural, natural kind of divisions for the eye to look at.","index":47,"end_time":171.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":48,"end_time":172.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And if this is all kind of one then kind of one graphic you''re looking at, then maybe we want to try to find a way of breaking up the kind of black on white future waste treatment for hospitals and biopharma.","index":49,"end_time":184.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"World leader below.","index":50,"end_time":186.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.47,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So, so maybe we drop that last file Safe engineering as a world leader in eco friendly text there.","index":51,"end_time":192.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":186.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Create a little bit more space with the contact us.","index":52,"end_time":195.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":192.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":53,"end_time":196.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then have a, and then blow out the photos a little bit more.","index":54,"end_time":200.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":197,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I think moving the names to the top is fine.","index":55,"end_time":203.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"If we do that though, I just want to be conscious of how so like picture if these are straight above.","index":56,"end_time":211.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":203.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yes.","index":57,"end_time":212.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":212.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"The tissue digester is going to look very similar to products like the way the text size and font is going to be very close to the products resources and about us.","index":58,"end_time":228.2,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":213.24,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So if we do move that up there, I''d maybe maybe like a blue element or something.","index":59,"end_time":236.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":229.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":60,"end_time":236.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like a banner behind it to kind of.","index":61,"end_time":238.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":236.68,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":62,"end_time":239.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":239.18,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Behind it or that holds that element or just something to create a little bit more visual separation, right?","index":63,"end_time":245.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we could do that.","index":64,"end_time":247.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":245.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We also wanted to see if, if you did want some kind of banner backing behind the pictures too, we could make them stand out more.","index":65,"end_time":255.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":248.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or if you would prefer just the text has that color behind it, we can do that.","index":66,"end_time":260.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":255.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think I get what you''re saying though, where you want these to be separated from the header.","index":67,"end_time":263.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":260.22,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So it would make more sense, I think to have that color like you''re saying at the top to separate from the navigation bar.","index":68,"end_time":269.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":263.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s, it''s, it''s tough for me to kind of have a preference on it without sitting and playing with it because it''s going to kind of come down to how it looks.","index":69,"end_time":277.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":269.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"You know, you''ve got a great design team.","index":70,"end_time":280.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":278.14,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I, you know, they''ve done really good work.","index":71,"end_time":283.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.42,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''m sure that they will have thoughts on how best to lay this out without sitting here and kind of mocking it up myself.","index":72,"end_time":290.62,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":283.34,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I don''t really have particularly strong preferences because it''s just hard to kind of imagine what it would look like.","index":73,"end_time":296.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":290.62,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"What we can do is instead of messing with what''s going on in bug Herd now so your team can finish reviewing.","index":74,"end_time":302.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":297.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We won''t change anything.","index":75,"end_time":303.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":302.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can have our team create like three mock ups of a design of what this just top header could look like if we did the blue background on the text.","index":76,"end_time":310.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":303.86,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And then we could also create some like dimension behind the pictures to kind of make them stand out a little bit more.","index":77,"end_time":316.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":310.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like you''re saying it''s just that plain white background.","index":78,"end_time":318.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":316.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So why don''t we create three versions and then I can send those over to you.","index":79,"end_time":321.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":318.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That way you can pick which one and then we can just swap it out without editing what''s actually been put on the site.","index":80,"end_time":327.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":321.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Does that.","index":81,"end_time":328.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":327.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That sounds great.","index":82,"end_time":329.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And can we.","index":83,"end_time":330.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.4,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Let''s swap out that picture on the far left.","index":84,"end_time":333.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.28,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That''s a good picture to have on the page, but it''s not the sexiest picture we have.","index":85,"end_time":337.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":333.48,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And.","index":86,"end_time":338.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":338.2,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And you know, the other two we have on here are great.","index":87,"end_time":341.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":339.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":88,"end_time":343.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":342.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I just rather have something that look a little bit sharper is going to the headline image there.","index":89,"end_time":348.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.64,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":90,"end_time":349.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do you have a specific one in mind or do you want to just go through the folder and maybe.","index":91,"end_time":352.72,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":349.52,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No, just go through.","index":92,"end_time":354.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":352.72,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Go through the folder.","index":93,"end_time":355.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":354.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I mean the one we have on the.","index":94,"end_time":357.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.12,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Is the, you know, the sharp photo.","index":95,"end_time":361.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":358.74,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So if so, I''d be just.","index":96,"end_time":367.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.98,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''d be happy using that.","index":97,"end_time":369.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":367.22,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Ideally, if there''s another one that pops like that, that would be better just because I know we''re getting a lot of mileage out of this picture already.","index":98,"end_time":376.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":369.3,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But if nothing else kind of jumps out, then this would be the right one to use there.","index":99,"end_time":381.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It''s just, it''s sharp, it looks good.","index":100,"end_time":383.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":381.54,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I prefer the angle it''s at and there''s less kind of clutter in the image.","index":101,"end_time":388.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":383.34,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":102,"end_time":389.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":388.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I think that that''s a really good photo.","index":103,"end_time":391.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.86,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It''s great for scale.","index":104,"end_time":392.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.66,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It shows the 150.","index":105,"end_time":393.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":392.66,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We definitely want to have it up there.","index":106,"end_time":395.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":393.94,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I don''t think it''s the lead photo we want on this page.","index":107,"end_time":399.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":395.46,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, yeah, that makes sense.","index":108,"end_time":400.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":399.46,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll swap that out.","index":109,"end_time":401.46,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":400.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Could you just.","index":110,"end_time":402.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.1,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"As long as you''re in there, can you just toss a note on that?","index":111,"end_time":406.98,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":402.82,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So if Brandon or Roland are looking at that today, they just kind of see a comment there.","index":112,"end_time":412.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":407.14,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yes, I can.","index":113,"end_time":413.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":412.98,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I mean the other one that comes to mind is the picture of the 2 600.","index":114,"end_time":435.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":431.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"There''s a few pictures of dual 6 hundreds sitting next to each other, both on a customer floor as well as in our shop.","index":115,"end_time":443.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":435.37,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I think they were in a folder in the Google Drive labeled like STI 600s or something.","index":116,"end_time":448.66,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":444.34,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Those are the other photos that kind of come to mind.","index":117,"end_time":451.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":448.66,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":118,"end_time":453.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":452.58,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Was it in one of these specific.","index":119,"end_time":469.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":467.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Folders or maybe a. Oh, try picture website.","index":120,"end_time":473.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":470.07,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"No, that''s.","index":121,"end_time":484.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":483.67,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"One.","index":122,"end_time":491.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":490.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No, that was a new one.","index":123,"end_time":493.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":491.99,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It.","index":124,"end_time":495.28,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":495.04,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Sure where that one is.","index":125,"end_time":530.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":529.29,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I''m trying to see if I''ve got a local copy.","index":126,"end_time":537.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":532.17,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This is.","index":127,"end_time":540.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":539.61,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This also wouldn''t be a bad one to use for that one second.","index":128,"end_time":545.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":540.21,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Let''s see if I can drop it in the chat.","index":129,"end_time":547.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.85,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"No, it doesn''t want to do that.","index":130,"end_time":551.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Let me go into the Drive.","index":131,"end_time":553.88,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":552.6,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"New north folder.","index":132,"end_time":565.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":564.2,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yes.","index":133,"end_time":566.52,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":566.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Cool.","index":134,"end_time":567.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":566.92,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Folder 1326.","index":135,"end_time":573.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":569.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That''s a good one.","index":136,"end_time":583.64,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":582.68,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Oh, I''m going to drop a second photo in here.","index":137,"end_time":588.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":585.16,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This isn''t to use, but it''s just to see the second one is what the dry wax block.","index":138,"end_time":593.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":588.08,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"The dry wax block looks like.","index":139,"end_time":596.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.84,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So unfortunately, I don''t think we can really use that for anything.","index":140,"end_time":603.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":599.56,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll delete that.","index":141,"end_time":631.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":603.64,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And are these to replace on a.","index":142,"end_time":637.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":635.49,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"On the STI page specifically or the.","index":143,"end_time":640.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":637.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"On that.","index":144,"end_time":642.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":641.41,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Oh, that was kind that.","index":145,"end_time":643.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.29,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Well, that''s the systems.","index":146,"end_time":644.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.61,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"There was another photo we had.","index":147,"end_time":646.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":644.85,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"No.","index":148,"end_time":646.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.13,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So it was for that hero image of the three on the.","index":149,"end_time":650.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":646.45,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, it was to replace the far left.","index":150,"end_time":652.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":650.45,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, gotcha.","index":151,"end_time":653.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":652.77,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":152,"end_time":654.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":653.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I also dropped.","index":153,"end_time":656.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.26,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"If you look back in the folder.","index":154,"end_time":659.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":656.78,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, the first or the third one.","index":155,"end_time":661.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":659.06,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":156,"end_time":664.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":664.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I just.","index":157,"end_time":666.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":665.9,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"The first one is better.","index":158,"end_time":668.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":666.7,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''m not sure where.","index":159,"end_time":670.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":668.62,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Where else we''re using that.","index":160,"end_time":672.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":670.78,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I just don''t.","index":161,"end_time":672.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.22,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Off the top and so if we have that somewhere else that we don''t want to move, we could use the other one.","index":162,"end_time":677.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":672.9,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I think that''s a good photo to use for this.","index":163,"end_time":681.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":677.9,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":164,"end_time":683.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":682.56,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":165,"end_time":683.68,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":683.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m gonna see if we can sharpen it a little bit too on our back end.","index":166,"end_time":688.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":684.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Is it too low res?","index":167,"end_time":690.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":688.8,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It just.","index":168,"end_time":691.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It.","index":169,"end_time":692.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":691.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s good.","index":170,"end_time":693.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":692.28,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Like it just looks like there might be a little bit blurriness.","index":171,"end_time":695.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":693.04,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m just wondering if they put it on the page if it would get any blurrier.","index":172,"end_time":697.76,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":695.2,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''d probably be fine as is because right now these aren''t super blown up.","index":173,"end_time":701.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":697.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"If we make them a little bigger, I would just see if maybe we could make it a little clearer.","index":174,"end_time":706.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":702.08,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But it''s not bad by any means.","index":175,"end_time":708.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":706.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, let''s.","index":176,"end_time":709.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.99,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It''s.","index":177,"end_time":710.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":709.67,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It''s holding decent resolution on my screen, so maybe that''s just because I''m sharing.","index":178,"end_time":716.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":179,"end_time":717.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":716.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But it''s.","index":180,"end_time":719.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":718.83,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Particularly if it''s that smaller thumbnail, then that''s a good use of it.","index":181,"end_time":723.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.43,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That''s also the same system in the same site as the live operational videos we have.","index":182,"end_time":730.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.87,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":183,"end_time":731.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":730.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":184,"end_time":734.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":733.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, so actually that''s.","index":185,"end_time":738.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.61,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So if we use this then as a.","index":186,"end_time":741.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":738.37,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"If we wanted to use this as like the thumbnail photo for those videos, that, that would work.","index":187,"end_time":747.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I don''t, I don''t remember what the.","index":188,"end_time":749.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":747.77,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"The thumbnail is on those or how those are holding.","index":189,"end_time":751.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":749.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But if it''s a less good cover image, we could always use this.","index":190,"end_time":755.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":751.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a good, good point.","index":191,"end_time":757.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":755.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":192,"end_time":760.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":759.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"It.","index":193,"end_time":760.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I added that note here.","index":194,"end_time":802.179,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":801.14,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll swap that one out.","index":195,"end_time":803.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.179,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That folder.","index":196,"end_time":805.86,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":804.82,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":197,"end_time":813.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":813.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":198,"end_time":822.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, I think besides that, that was the only additional one.","index":199,"end_time":828.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":823.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Was just moving that.","index":200,"end_time":829.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":828.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So we''ll create those three versions.","index":201,"end_time":831.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.75,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Let me just make a note here for.","index":202,"end_time":834.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.47,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay, great.","index":203,"end_time":852.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.84,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we will make those adjustments, not send over those designs to you.","index":204,"end_time":856.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":852.24,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But yeah, and then we''ll just look for any additional things from your team.","index":205,"end_time":862.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":858.8,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And like I said, I''ll leave this one as is so you guys can review as it stands, and then we can just swap it out with whatever design you.","index":206,"end_time":869.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":862.16,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You approve is preferred.","index":207,"end_time":870.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":869.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":208,"end_time":871.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":870.69,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then as I mentioned, I should have the rest of my team''s comments in today, tomorrow, midday.","index":209,"end_time":877.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":872.33,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''ll drop you a note when they let me know they''re finished.","index":210,"end_time":881.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":878.41,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And that should be it on this.","index":211,"end_time":883.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":881.89,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That would be great.","index":212,"end_time":884.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.01,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s exciting.","index":213,"end_time":885.61,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":884.81,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Hopefully we can get it launched soon.","index":214,"end_time":887.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":885.61,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":215,"end_time":887.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":887.45,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And you said you did have some changes to that poster.","index":216,"end_time":892.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Did you want to review those quick?","index":217,"end_time":893.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":892.05,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Oh, yeah, we can take a look at it real quick.","index":218,"end_time":895.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":893.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"They were pretty straightforward.","index":219,"end_time":897.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":896.17,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So there.","index":220,"end_time":898.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":897.61,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Do you have it up or.","index":221,"end_time":900.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":899.59,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I can share.","index":222,"end_time":900.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":900.35,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Whatever''s easier.","index":223,"end_time":902.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":901.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I can pull it up.","index":224,"end_time":902.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902.15,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or if you have it there.","index":225,"end_time":903.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":902.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Do I have.","index":226,"end_time":905.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":904.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":227,"end_time":906.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":905.59,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Cool.","index":228,"end_time":909.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Can you see my screen?","index":229,"end_time":910.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":909.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yes.","index":230,"end_time":911.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":911.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"These.","index":231,"end_time":914.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"What?","index":232,"end_time":914.989,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"These white margin bubbles.","index":233,"end_time":917.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":914.989,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I don''t love the way they look here.","index":234,"end_time":920.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":918.47,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, so if we could just get rid of those white boxes around and.","index":235,"end_time":925.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":920.79,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Just have it be a gray box.","index":236,"end_time":926.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":925.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, just the gray box on the gray background.","index":237,"end_time":929.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":927.07,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Maybe if it was a, you know, if.","index":238,"end_time":932.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":930.43,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"If there was a reason to have this, if we tightened it up so it was almost kind of a white line around the gray box, then that could work.","index":239,"end_time":939.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":932.03,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"But I think this is just too thick of a margin.","index":240,"end_time":941.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":939.27,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, I see why we have it up here.","index":241,"end_time":945.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":941.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":242,"end_time":946.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":946.27,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But I don''t think we need it down here.","index":243,"end_time":949.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":947.23,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":244,"end_time":950.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":950.11,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Or if we do use it, let''s just tighten.","index":245,"end_time":953.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":950.99,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Let''s just tighten it up to a tighter band.","index":246,"end_time":955.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":953.07,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay.","index":247,"end_time":956.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":955.87,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":248,"end_time":956.95,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.51,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Reduce the thickness.","index":249,"end_time":957.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":956.95,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":250,"end_time":958.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.27,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then down here, I want to combine these.","index":251,"end_time":967.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":958.91,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"These two lines into a single line of copy, which I emailed over to you.","index":252,"end_time":973.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":967.47,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Oh, perfect.","index":253,"end_time":974.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":973.31,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Okay.","index":254,"end_time":974.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":974.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Same content, just.","index":255,"end_time":977.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":975.95,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That should let us tighten it up so it looks.","index":256,"end_time":979.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":977.35,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So it just matches the formatting of the rest.","index":257,"end_time":982.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":979.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Okay, perfect.","index":258,"end_time":985.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":983.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And now that I''m actually zoomed in close on it, can you check if this text is the same size and font as the rest?","index":259,"end_time":996.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":986.53,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we can double check that.","index":260,"end_time":998.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":997.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":261,"end_time":999.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.01,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Just specifically this down here looks like it''s.","index":262,"end_time":1003.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, it looks like it was compressed.","index":263,"end_time":1005.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1003.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"To fit in there.","index":264,"end_time":1006.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1005.01,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So it looks and this is a typo.","index":265,"end_time":1009.78,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1006.01,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"These are typos.","index":266,"end_time":1011.3,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1010.26,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Great.","index":267,"end_time":1013.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1013.38,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, we will replace it.","index":268,"end_time":1016.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1013.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Looks like.","index":269,"end_time":1016.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that text got compressed on this end too.","index":270,"end_time":1019.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1016.42,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, we can fix that.","index":271,"end_time":1020.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1019.26,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s quick.","index":272,"end_time":1020.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1020.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Cool.","index":273,"end_time":1021.38,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.9,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And actually, if you, if you wouldn''t mind, I just, I feel, I feel like I, I stared at this enough.","index":274,"end_time":1027.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1022.42,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I don''t see anything new.","index":275,"end_time":1028.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.5,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"If you could just do a pass through for like little typos like that.","index":276,"end_time":1032.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1029.06,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely.","index":277,"end_time":1034.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1033.41,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''m a little disconcerted that every time I look at it I see something different.","index":278,"end_time":1038.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1034.29,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"So I think a fresh pair of eyes would be great.","index":279,"end_time":1040.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1038.29,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yes, absolutely.","index":280,"end_time":1041.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.45,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Same thing here.","index":281,"end_time":1044.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1043.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"This, this just looks like it got the way it was for the way it was aligned or something.","index":282,"end_time":1051.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1044.69,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Got a little squished or something.","index":283,"end_time":1052.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1051.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah, I can just.","index":284,"end_time":1055.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1054.13,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I''ll let them know about the specific section but then I''m going to see if they can.","index":285,"end_time":1058.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1055.09,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Since we kind of built it back out because we didn''t have the permissions.","index":286,"end_time":1061.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1058.85,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, things might have gotten squished.","index":287,"end_time":1063.65,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1061.97,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So I''m just going to see if they can do like control check on the entire thing and make sure.","index":288,"end_time":1067.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1063.65,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That would be awesome.","index":289,"end_time":1069.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1067.87,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":290,"end_time":1069.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1069.31,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And thank you for that.","index":291,"end_time":1070.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1069.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''ve got, I''ve got a fat external hard drive with all the design things on it, but it''s bitlocker encrypted and I''m trying to work to get into it without having it fry itself for me.","index":292,"end_time":1081.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1070.71,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"No worries.","index":293,"end_time":1082.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.03,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Understandable.","index":294,"end_time":1083.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1082.67,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":295,"end_time":1083.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1083.39,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"They were able to get in and kind of replicate it here.","index":296,"end_time":1086.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1083.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So.","index":297,"end_time":1086.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1086.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s why there might be a couple of those like compressed sections so we can go through and make sure everything is aligned.","index":298,"end_time":1092.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1086.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":299,"end_time":1093.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1092.81,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":300,"end_time":1093.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.29,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And if it''s just part of that, just if you could check that the font and font sizing on everything kind of came through or updated and is consistent, that would be awesome for sure.","index":301,"end_time":1103.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.65,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yes.","index":302,"end_time":1104.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.33,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":303,"end_time":1107.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1106.89,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":304,"end_time":1111.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1110.97,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I think that''s all I''ve got right now.","index":305,"end_time":1113.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1111.49,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Emailed back on the blog.","index":306,"end_time":1116.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.05,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"That looks good and ready to go.","index":307,"end_time":1118.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1116.33,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Great.","index":308,"end_time":1119.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1118.8,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"We''ll get that on the site then so we can get some more content.","index":309,"end_time":1122.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1119.92,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":310,"end_time":1123.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1122.88,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And then we can get hopefully get this launched for next week and then look at dialing in on SEO and some other stuff kind of off of the launch site.","index":311,"end_time":1132.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1123.36,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":312,"end_time":1133.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1132.72,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"As soon as we get this up, we would definitely like to, to focus on that, shift our focus.","index":313,"end_time":1137.12,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1133.12,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I will say we are off Monday for the holiday, but we are back Tuesday.","index":314,"end_time":1141.36,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1137.76,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"So if we have all of the edits and everything complete by the end of this week, we can just plan on a Tuesday morning launch if that, if everything is complete.","index":315,"end_time":1149.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1141.44,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"By then.","index":316,"end_time":1149.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1149.43,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Great.","index":317,"end_time":1150.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.19,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Let''s.","index":318,"end_time":1151.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1150.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I mean, I''ll.","index":319,"end_time":1152.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1151.55,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"I''ll work on my end to get everything ready for that.","index":320,"end_time":1154.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1152.35,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Let''s aim for that.","index":321,"end_time":1155.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1154.51,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"And if it slips, we''ll pivot.","index":322,"end_time":1157.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1155.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":323,"end_time":1159.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1158.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":324,"end_time":1160.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1159.79,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":325,"end_time":1160.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.19,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"All these edits.","index":326,"end_time":1161.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1160.91,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And thank you for the feedback on the blog.","index":327,"end_time":1163.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1161.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"We''ll get that going too.","index":328,"end_time":1164.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1163.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"But, yeah, I''ll update you with all the changes that we make so your team can go through.","index":329,"end_time":1171.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1165.71,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I''ll send you the designs, too, as soon as we have those.","index":330,"end_time":1173.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1171.07,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":331,"end_time":1174.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1173.63,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":332,"end_time":1174.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1174.11,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"},{"text":"All right, thanks.","index":333,"end_time":1175.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1174.83,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Have a good rest of your day.","index":334,"end_time":1176.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.59,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"You too.","index":335,"end_time":1177.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.75,"speaker_name":"Dan Nelsen"}],"dateString":"2026-01-13T18:30:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/81421883896?pwd=9iHNOeWOt9gp3Uqm9ajWXxGhOvoFVO.1","participants":["taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,dnelsen@biosafeeng.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","dnelsen@biosafeeng.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEQBG5BC2T15DVQWAFZ9KWDD","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.92,"bullets":["Aligned on final website edits; Dan to send feedback by midday tomorrow at latest.","Taylor to deliver three header mockups to visualize layout options before implementation.","Agreed to swap lead homepage image; Dan identified preferred replacement from image library.","Poster refinements underway; team to address formatting, typos, and text consistency issues.","Targeted website launch set for Tuesday following Monday holiday, pending completion of edits."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I''m sure that they will have thoughts on how best to lay this out.","speaker":"Dan Nelsen"},{"quote":"We’ll create three versions and then I can send those over to you.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"Let’s aim for that, and if it slips, we’ll pivot.","speaker":"Dan Nelsen"}],"topics":["launch","delivery","design","review"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-16T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Website Launch and Design Adjustments**\n\nThe team is finalizing website edits aiming for a launch early next week.\n\n- **Dan Nelsen confirmed the last round of website feedback is expected by midday tomorrow, with the goal of launching on Tuesday following the holiday** (19:10)  \n    - Dan’s team is reviewing final edits today and tomorrow to avoid delays.  \n    - Taylor Doerbaum suggested launching on a Monday or Tuesday to monitor performance early in the week.  \n    - They agreed to pivot launch timing if feedback or changes delay readiness.  \n    - The launch timing aligns with internal holiday schedules to ensure full team availability.  \n\n- **Design improvements will include three mockups for header layout and photo presentation to enhance visual separation and impact** (05:28)  \n    - Taylor’s team will create versions with a blue banner behind header text and options to add dimension behind images.  \n    - Dan requested swapping the far-left hero image with a sharper, less-used photo from their folder to improve page appeal.  \n    - Taylor will note this swap for Brandon or Roland to act on during their review.  \n    - These design options will be sent to Dan for selection prior to final swap without disturbing ongoing site review.\n\n- **Dan emphasized the need for clearer space delineation on the homepage, suggesting visual separation between header, photos, and text areas** (02:31)  \n    - He proposed dropping the \"Safe engineering as a world leader\" text lower to create breathing room near the contact section.  \n    - Taylor agreed to explore banner backgrounds or text highlights to distinguish segments from the navigation bar.  \n    - Dan deferred final preference to the design team’s judgment, trusting their ability to find the best layout.  \n    - These layout changes aim to enhance user focus and brand message clarity.\n\n## **Poster Design Refinements**\n\nMinor but important formatting corrections will finalize the poster’s presentation quality.\n\n- **Dan requested removal of white margin bubbles around text boxes, replacing them with gray boxes and a tighter white border to reduce visual clutter** (15:14)  \n    - Taylor confirmed they will reduce box thickness and align it better with the gray background.  \n    - This adjustment targets a cleaner, more consistent poster look that matches overall design language.  \n    - Dan sees this as a straightforward fix to improve aesthetic balance.\n\n- **Text formatting issues including compressed text, inconsistent font sizes, and typos will be corrected across the poster** (16:37)  \n    - Taylor will have their team run a full control check for alignment and font consistency after recovering editing permissions.  \n    - Dan stressed the importance of a fresh review to catch subtle formatting errors missed by prior reviews.  \n    - This quality check ensures professional presentation and avoids distracting imperfections.  \n    - The team acknowledged that some squishing occurred during file permission constraints, explaining current issues.\n\n- **Copy tightening will merge two lines into one on the poster’s lower section to match formatting standards** (15:55)  \n    - Dan emailed the revised copy to Taylor for implementation.  \n    - This change supports a more compact and visually uniform layout.  \n    - The adjustment will help the poster’s readability and overall coherence.\n\n## **Content and SEO Strategy Post-Launch**\n\nContent updates and SEO focus are planned immediately following the website launch.\n\n- **Dan approved the blog content, marking it ready for site publication to enhance ongoing content marketing efforts** (18:30)  \n    - Taylor confirmed they will upload the blog to the website to increase fresh content availability.  \n    - This addition supports SEO and engagement objectives post-launch.  \n    - The timely blog publication will complement the new site’s launch momentum.\n\n- **SEO optimization will become the priority once the site is live, aiming to improve organic traffic and search ranking** (18:52)  \n    - Taylor noted the team’s availability resumes Tuesday post-holiday, aligning with the launch timeline.  \n    - They plan to shift from design edits to SEO tactics immediately after launch.  \n    - This phased approach maximizes resource focus and business impact.\n\n## **Team Coordination and Communication**\n\nClear communication protocols and documentation support smooth project progress.\n\n- **Taylor will keep Dan updated on all design changes and provide the three header mockups for review before final decisions** (19:18)  \n    - This ensures Dan’s team can review and approve changes without disrupting ongoing feedback cycles.  \n    - Transparency in updates helps maintain alignment and avoid surprises.  \n    - The approach balances iterative feedback with efficient workflows.\n\n- **Dan requested notes be left on design files to guide Brandon and Roland during their review, ensuring clarity on requested changes** (06:42)  \n    - Taylor confirmed she will add comments to relevant assets for easy reference.  \n    - This reduces confusion and accelerates review turnaround.  \n    - The note-taking practice supports accountability and smooth handoffs.\n\n- **Dan shared challenges with accessing encrypted design storage but confirmed Taylor’s team replicated necessary files to avoid delays** (18:02)  \n    - The workaround prevented bottlenecks in editing and review cycles.  \n    - Taylor acknowledged the technical issue and ensured continuity of work.  \n    - This contingency maintained project momentum despite file access hurdles.","outline":null,"keywords":["Website launch","homepage design","poster edits","image replacement","visual hierarchy","quality control"],"overview":"- **Website Launch:** Final edits expected by midday tomorrow, aimed for a launch on Tuesday post-holiday.  \n- **Design Mockups:** Three new header layout versions will enhance visual impact, including a sharper hero image.  \n- **Poster Adjustments:** White margin bubbles will be replaced with gray boxes for a cleaner presentation.  \n- **SEO Focus Post-Launch:** SEO optimization efforts will begin immediately after site launch for improved traffic and ranking.  \n- **Team Coordination:** Regular updates on design changes will ensure alignment and timely feedback throughout the process.  \n- **Access Issues:** Encrypted design storage challenges resolved by replicating files, maintaining project momentum.","action_items":"\n**Dan Nelsen**\nProvide final feedback from team on website edits by end of day or midday next day and notify Taylor when complete (00:47)\nConfirm if any other sharper lead photo options exist in folder to best replace far-left homepage image and share suggestions via chat/folder (05:28)\nReview and confirm poster copy consolidation and font size/format consistency and coordinate any further required corrections (15:50)\n\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nSend website developer three mockups of homepage top header variations with blue background banners and image dimension effects for selection (04:57)\nSwap the far-left homepage image with a sharper alternative as discussed and add a comment/note on backend for design team visibility (06:42)\nPerform a comprehensive quality control check on poster design for typos, font sizes, and formatting issues, particularly for compressed text areas (17:14)\nUpload approved blog content to website to increase fresh content post-launch (18:30)\nKeep Dan updated on all changes and send finalized design mockups for review (19:18)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"22534484-8479-4f65-9e10-72a042a4a17c","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
