  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: BioSAFE Weekly Meeting',
  '## **Website Launch and Design Adjustments**

The team is finalizing website edits aiming for a launch early next week.

- **Dan Nelsen confirmed the last round of website feedback is expected by midday tomorrow, with the goal of launching on Tuesday following the holiday** (19:10)  
    - Dan’s team is reviewing final edits today and tomorrow to avoid delays.  
    - Taylor Doerbaum suggested launching on a Monday or Tuesday to monitor performance early in the week.  
    - They agreed to pivot launch timing if feedback or changes delay readiness.  
    - The launch timing aligns with internal holiday schedules to ensure full team availability.  

- **Design improvements will include three mockups for header layout and photo presentation to enhance visual separation and impact** (05:28)  
    - Taylor’s team will create versions with a blue banner behind header text and options to add dimension behind images.  
    - Dan requested swapping the far-left hero image with a sharper, less-used photo from their folder to improve page appeal.  
    - Taylor will note this swap for Brandon or Roland to act on during their review.  
    - These design options will be sent to Dan for selection prior to final swap without disturbing ongoing site review.

- **Dan emphasized the need for clearer space delineation on the homepage, suggesting visual separation between header, photos, and text areas** (02:31)  
    - He proposed dropping the "Safe engineering as a world leader" text lower to create breathing room near the contact section.  
    - Taylor agreed to explore banner backgrounds or text highlights to distinguish segments from the navigation bar.  
    - Dan deferred final preference to the design team’s judgment, trusting their ability to find the best layout.  
    - These layout changes aim to enhance user focus and brand message clarity.

## **Poster Design Refinements**

Minor but important formatting corrections will finalize the poster’s presentation quality.

- **Dan requested removal of white margin bubbles around text boxes, replacing them with gray boxes and a tighter white border to reduce visual clutter** (15:14)  
    - Taylor confirmed they will reduce box thickness and align it better with the gray background.  
    - This adjustment targets a cleaner, more consistent poster look that matches overall design language.  
    - Dan sees this as a straightforward fix to improve aesthetic balance.

- **Text formatting issues including compressed text, inconsistent font sizes, and typos will be corrected across the poster** (16:37)  
    - Taylor will have their team run a full control check for alignment and font consistency after recovering editing permissions.  
    - Dan stressed the importance of a fresh review to catch subtle formatting errors missed by prior reviews.  
    - This quality check ensures professional presentation and avoids distracting imperfections.  
    - The team acknowledged that some squishing occurred during file permission constraints, explaining current issues.

- **Copy tightening will merge two lines into one on the poster’s lower section to match formatting standards** (15:55)  
    - Dan emailed the revised copy to Taylor for implementation.  
    - This change supports a more compact and visually uniform layout.  
    - The adjustment will help the poster’s readability and overall coherence.

## **Content and SEO Strategy Post-Launch**

Content updates and SEO focus are planned immediately following the website launch.

- **Dan approved the blog content, marking it ready for site publication to enhance ongoing content marketing efforts** (18:30)  
    - Taylor confirmed they will upload the blog to the website to increase fresh content availability.  
    - This addition supports SEO and engagement objectives post-launch.  
    - The timely blog publication will complement the new site’s launch momentum.

- **SEO optimization will become the priority once the site is live, aiming to improve organic traffic and search ranking** (18:52)  
    - Taylor noted the team’s availability resumes Tuesday post-holiday, aligning with the launch timeline.  
    - They plan to shift from design edits to SEO tactics immediately after launch.  
    - This phased approach maximizes resource focus and business impact.

## **Team Coordination and Communication**

Clear communication protocols and documentation support smooth project progress.

- **Taylor will keep Dan updated on all design changes and provide the three header mockups for review before final decisions** (19:18)  
    - This ensures Dan’s team can review and approve changes without disrupting ongoing feedback cycles.  
    - Transparency in updates helps maintain alignment and avoid surprises.  
    - The approach balances iterative feedback with efficient workflows.

- **Dan requested notes be left on design files to guide Brandon and Roland during their review, ensuring clarity on requested changes** (06:42)  
    - Taylor confirmed she will add comments to relevant assets for easy reference.  
    - This reduces confusion and accelerates review turnaround.  
    - The note-taking practice supports accountability and smooth handoffs.

- **Dan shared challenges with accessing encrypted design storage but confirmed Taylor’s team replicated necessary files to avoid delays** (18:02)  
    - The workaround prevented bottlenecks in editing and review cycles.  
    - Taylor acknowledged the technical issue and ensured continuity of work.  
    - This contingency maintained project momentum despite file access hurdles.',
  '2026-01-13 18:30:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Provide final feedback from team on website edits by end of day or midday next day and notify Taylor when complete (00:47)","completed":false},{"text":"Confirm if any other sharper lead photo options exist in folder to best replace far-left homepage image and share suggestions via chat/folder (05:28)","completed":false},{"text":"Review and confirm poster copy consolidation and font size/format consistency and coordinate any further required corrections (15:50)","completed":false},{"text":"Send website developer three mockups of homepage top header variations with blue background banners and image dimension effects for selection (04:57)","completed":false},{"text":"Swap the far-left homepage image with a sharper alternative as discussed and add a comment/note on backend for design team visibility (06:42)","completed":false},{"text":"Perform a comprehensive quality control check on poster design for typos, font sizes, and formatting issues, particularly for compressed text areas (17:14)","completed":false},{"text":"Upload approved blog content to website to increase fresh content post-launch (18:30)","completed":false},{"text":"Keep Dan updated on all changes and send finalized design mockups for review (19:18)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
