614,"end_time":2048.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2048.35,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Anything else you don''t understand?","index":615,"end_time":2050.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2049.07,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Because like I say, I.","index":616,"end_time":2051.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2050.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Lots of thoughts just went thrown on a.","index":617,"end_time":2054.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2052.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"On a plate.","index":618,"end_time":2055.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2054.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"See?","index":619,"end_time":2056.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2056.11,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And I was going, I''ll just throw that in and.","index":620,"end_time":2058.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2056.59,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Does that make any sense to me?","index":621,"end_time":2059.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2058.47,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Sometimes reading this guy, it doesn''t make any sense.","index":622,"end_time":2061.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2059.67,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"What the hell was I talking about?","index":623,"end_time":2062.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2061.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":624,"end_time":2063.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2063.63,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then just let me know and then hopefully you two bring.","index":625,"end_time":2068.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2063.99,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Bring.","index":626,"end_time":2069.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2068.91,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I throw.","index":627,"end_time":2069.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2069.23,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Throw thoughts into that document.","index":628,"end_time":2071.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2069.87,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":629,"end_time":2071.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2071.27,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s.","index":630,"end_time":2072.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2072.19,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"It''s there for that.","index":631,"end_time":2073.68,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2072.72,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"And then we''ll hopefully meet in the middle and then we''ve got at least, it''ll be lovely on the 28th, at least to say, okay, we both, we both understand what the other one wants, what''s real, what can, and I think more anything else is for that.","index":632,"end_time":2087.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2074.16,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"28 is to say, right, let''s agree what we can actually achieve.","index":633,"end_time":2091.76,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2087.04,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Excuse me.","index":634,"end_time":2092.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2092.32,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"This year.","index":635,"end_time":2093.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2092.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Let''s put some timelines against it, let''s put some real time thought behind it and let''s make it, make it happen.","index":636,"end_time":2101.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2093.84,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So.","index":637,"end_time":2101.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2101.05,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, absolutely, that sounds great.","index":638,"end_time":2103.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2101.69,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"I think my thoughts, I think we, I think my thinking is a little bit more realistic in terms of what we can do in how we would measure success, you know, because.","index":639,"end_time":2114.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2103.37,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Right.","index":640,"end_time":2115.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2114.73,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Defining.","index":641,"end_time":2115.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2115.21,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"That''s what we talked about before.","index":642,"end_time":2117.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2115.81,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"I think that makes more sense.","index":643,"end_time":2118.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2117.25,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"So that''s, that''s what I''m hoping.","index":644,"end_time":2119.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2118.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"We''ll see.","index":645,"end_time":2121.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2120.57,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"But like I said, I need your guys expertise on this.","index":646,"end_time":2123.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2121.65,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":647,"end_time":2125.1,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2124.62,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"No, agree with you there.","index":648,"end_time":2126.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2125.1,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"It''s good to define what we''re looking to do and have good deadlines or timelines.","index":649,"end_time":2130.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2126.02,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Absolutely.","index":650,"end_time":2131.58,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2130.86,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":651,"end_time":2132.58,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2132.06,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Well, listen, thanks for overrunning.","index":652,"end_time":2134.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2132.58,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Appreciate it as always and hope you feel better.","index":653,"end_time":2137.5,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2134.26,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Thank you.","index":654,"end_time":2138.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2137.74,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Have a good rest of your day.","index":655,"end_time":2139.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2138.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"And I''ll speak to you.","index":656,"end_time":2140.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2139.5,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Like I said, we''ll communicate.","index":657,"end_time":2142.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2140.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Certainly by Friday.","index":658,"end_time":2143.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2142.06,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes.","index":659,"end_time":2144.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2143.9,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Yeah, for sure.","index":660,"end_time":2144.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2144.3,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"On the content and then as soon as you''ve got some thoughts on the LinkedIn stuff.","index":661,"end_time":2148.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2145.1,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yeah, share it with me and we can go backwards and forwards on that.","index":662,"end_time":2151.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2148.74,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Yes, absolutely, will do.","index":663,"end_time":2152.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2151.34,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Thank you, Michael.","index":664,"end_time":2153.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2152.78,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"text":"Love it.","index":665,"end_time":2154.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2153.62,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"All right, take care.","index":666,"end_time":2155.34,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":2154.38,"speaker_name":"Michael Jones"},{"text":"Bye.","index":667,"end_time":2155.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":2155.5,"speaker_name":"Taylor Doerbaum"}],"dateString":"2026-01-14T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/87549285494?pwd=ibWG4xRLddaHqf8JzJ7T48gg886wbu.1","participants":["josh@hydrian.com,baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com,michael.jones@hydrian.com,taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com","josh@hydrian.com","baylee.gunnell@marketersindemand.com","michael.jones@hydrian.com"],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KESXWXMZZDAX55BWVJNQFM01","organizer_email":"taylor.doerbaum@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"positive","confidence":0.91,"bullets":["Agreed to wait until Friday to finalize survey reminder wording based on response rate.","Taylor confirmed SurveyMonkey reminders and custom links are easy to implement and schedule.","New domains are being warmed to avoid spam filters and improve email deliverability.","Michael emphasized producing data-driven content like carousels to boost engagement and shareability.","Booth visuals, one-pagers, and LinkedIn content formats are being refined for higher impact."],"highlights":[{"quote":"We need to produce some very, very clever thought leadership type material that will support all the different avenues.","speaker":"Michael Jones"},{"quote":"We can schedule that Monday for Tuesday so we can give it more time to kind of get some more results in.","speaker":"Taylor Doerbaum"},{"quote":"If this is a format that works, then whatever... If we get new subscribers to it, whatever it may be... great, it worked.","speaker":"Michael Jones"}],"topics":["survey","marketing","design","delivery"],"model":"openai/gpt-4-1106-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-16T22:38:12Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Survey Strategy and Engagement**\n\nThe team agreed to send a **custom reminder email** for the current SurveyMonkey survey on **Tuesday** to boost response rates without overwhelming recipients (05:15).  \n- **Taylor Doerbaum** proposed using SurveyMonkey’s native reminder feature to target unopened emails gently.  \n- **Michael Jones** suggested including initial response highlights in the reminder to encourage participation and show value.  \n- The reminder email’s wording will be drafted by Michael by **Friday morning** to ensure timely deployment.  \n- The approach aims to increase total responses beyond the current **4 within 24 hours**, improving data reliability for analysis and marketing use.  \n\nThe survey cadence will shift from monthly to **quarterly**, reflecting exhaustion of the initial question set and the need to integrate external data for richer insights (08:38).  \n- Michael explained that statistical questions require complex cross-industry data from **7 different companies**, complicating comparisons.  \n- Future surveys will slightly adjust questions but maintain core themes to build longitudinal benchmarking.  \n- Between survey cycles, the team will focus on producing marketing content from existing and newly gathered data.  \n\nTo increase survey accessibility, the team will add an **external survey link** in the upcoming newsletter, allowing recipients to click directly into the live survey (13:21).  \n- This external link feeds into the same SurveyMonkey database, ensuring data consolidation.  \n- Michael approved adding the link and emphasized the importance of monitoring subscriber engagement and response rates post-deployment.  \n\n## **Content and Newsletter Development**\n\nThe newsletter will launch **early next week**, featuring survey insights and a call to action linking to the current survey (15:13).  \n- Taylor will finalize the newsletter design incorporating Michael’s four posts and the external survey link.  \n- Michael prefers a **carousel-style post format** on LinkedIn for survey content, which increases engagement by breaking information into clickable slides (16:28).  \n- The carousel will cover individual survey questions like **growth and AI expectations**, highlighting key responses and trends per slide for easier consumption.  \n\nTaylor will create a **copy document and visual mockup** outlining slide headers and content flow, which Michael will review and refine to ensure clarity and impact (20:23).  \n- Michael aims to keep posts **non-salesy and insightful**, drawing from client work examples without revealing sensitive details.  \n- The strategy focuses on posting high-quality content **weekly** rather than daily, aiming to build sustained engagement and brand recall.  \n- Both agreed that shareable, forwardable content will help broaden the newsletter’s reach organically.  \n\n## **Booth Design and Marketing Collateral**\n\nMichael prefers **booth design option 4A** for its balanced branding and less aggressive tone compared to 4B (25:23).  \n- He highlighted the importance of placing the **Hydrion logo prominently at the top** for better brand recognition in busy environments.  \n- Michael requested resizing the **forklift icon** and aligning the “limited access” text on a single line for cleaner visuals (26:15).  \n- Taylor will adjust the icon size and layout and send an updated mockup for final approval.  \n\nRegarding the **one-pager brochure**, both agreed the current draft contains too much text and needs to be shortened into **three or four bullet points** for quick readability (29:05).  \n- The brochure should clearly explain the purpose of the QR codes and the free assessment while avoiding lengthy paragraphs.  \n- Michael emphasized the need for concise, actionable points that convey benefits like **improved fill rates** and **better profitability** at a glance.  \n- Taylor will coordinate with the design team to update the layout accordingly for use as a standalone handout.  \n\n## **Data and Analytics Preparation**\n\nMichael flagged potential gaps in the **most engaged firm spreadsheet**, noting the latest data appears to stop at **November** (32:15).  \n- Taylor will check with the developer to locate any updated traffic and engagement data, considering that exclusions may have moved some data to a new sheet (33:02).  \n- The team plans to pull detailed **web traffic insights**, including firm names and job titles, for the upcoming meeting on **February 28th** to inform marketing strategy.  \n- Michael stressed the importance of defining **clear success metrics and timelines** for campaign measurement during the February meeting (34:08).  \n\n## **Strategic Marketing Vision**\n\nMichael shared a developing marketing strategy focused on producing **thought leadership material** that provides clear, non-salesy insights to target audiences (10:57).  \n- He noted that inbound leads so far have mainly been **spam**, highlighting the need for valuable content to attract genuine interest.  \n- The strategy involves combining survey data with internal analytics to create **benchmark reports** and case studies that resonate with clients.  \n- Michael’s goal is to align expectations with realistic timelines and measurable outcomes, seeking input from Taylor and Josh to refine these plans (35:01).  \n\nTaylor and Michael agreed that defining **realistic goals and deadlines** is crucial for progress and accountability (35:14).  \n- The team will continue iterative content development and data analysis to support this vision.  \n- They plan ongoing collaboration on LinkedIn content and newsletter enhancements, with regular feedback loops to optimize engagement.","outline":null,"keywords":["SurveyMonkey","Newsletter","LinkedIn Carousel","Booth Design","Marketing Strategy","Web Traffic Data"],"overview":"- **Survey Strategy:** Reminder email for SurveyMonkey survey is set for Tuesday to boost response rates beyond current 4 returns.\n\n- **Quarterly Cadence:** Surveys shift to quarterly to integrate external data, maintaining core themes for longitudinal benchmarking.\n\n- **Newsletter Launch:** Newsletter launches next week with survey insights and a call to action linking to live survey.\n\n- **Booth Design:** Preferred booth design 4A emphasizes brand identity, with Hydrion logo prominently placed for recognition.\n\n- **One-Pager Revamp:** Brochure content must condense into 3-4 bullet points for quick readability; focus on benefits like improved fill rates.\n\n- **Data Gaps:** Potential data issues noted; request update on traffic and engagement data by February 28th for marketing strategy revisions.","action_items":"\n**Taylor Doerbaum**\nMonitor SurveyMonkey responses through Friday and prepare reminder email copy with initial survey insights for Michael to review by end of week (04:01)\nAdd external SurveyMonkey survey link to the closing section of upcoming Hydrian newsletter and finalize design for early next week distribution (13:21)\nCreate a LinkedIn carousel mockup using existing newsletter copy; prepare slide-by-slide copy outline and send it to Michael for review and additions (20:40)\nAdjust booth design per Michael’s feedback (reduce forklift icon size, reformat text to single line) and send updated mockup (24:55)\nCollaborate on revising one-pager brochure text to be more concise, bullet formatted, and explanatory of QR codes and assessments (28:55)\nCoordinate with developer to locate and retrieve the latest web traffic/exclusion data spreadsheet and share with Michael (31:20)\nShare final newsletter content draft and LinkedIn post ideas with Michael by Friday for feedback (35:32)\n\n**Michael Jones**\nReview survey data and provide initial impressions and wording guidance for reminder email by Friday (05:15)\nOffer feedback and finalize draft copy for LinkedIn carousel posts and newsletter content once Taylor sends mockups and drafts (20:40)\nDecide on booth design preference (favoring 4A) and provide icon size and layout feedback for the design team (24:55)\nAssess existing brochure versus one-pager designs to recommend text tightening and bullet list content (28:55)\nReview web traffic and engagement data once Taylor secures full dataset for preparation of March 28th meeting (31:20)\nPrepare strategic input and clarify realistic goals ahead of March 28th meeting (33:47)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"3ea06e37-b0b7-4adc-83fb-eb0bb3a06f47","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
