INSERT INTO compass_notes (contract_id, meeting_id, note_type, title, content_raw, note_date, status, action_items, is_auto_generated)
SELECT
  new_meeting.contract_id,
  new_meeting.meeting_id,
  'meeting',
  'Meeting Notes: Hydrian // New North: Weekly Meeting (new)',
  '## **Survey Strategy and Engagement**

The team agreed to send a **custom reminder email** for the current SurveyMonkey survey on **Tuesday** to boost response rates without overwhelming recipients (05:15).  
- **Taylor Doerbaum** proposed using SurveyMonkey’s native reminder feature to target unopened emails gently.  
- **Michael Jones** suggested including initial response highlights in the reminder to encourage participation and show value.  
- The reminder email’s wording will be drafted by Michael by **Friday morning** to ensure timely deployment.  
- The approach aims to increase total responses beyond the current **4 within 24 hours**, improving data reliability for analysis and marketing use.  

The survey cadence will shift from monthly to **quarterly**, reflecting exhaustion of the initial question set and the need to integrate external data for richer insights (08:38).  
- Michael explained that statistical questions require complex cross-industry data from **7 different companies**, complicating comparisons.  
- Future surveys will slightly adjust questions but maintain core themes to build longitudinal benchmarking.  
- Between survey cycles, the team will focus on producing marketing content from existing and newly gathered data.  

To increase survey accessibility, the team will add an **external survey link** in the upcoming newsletter, allowing recipients to click directly into the live survey (13:21).  
- This external link feeds into the same SurveyMonkey database, ensuring data consolidation.  
- Michael approved adding the link and emphasized the importance of monitoring subscriber engagement and response rates post-deployment.  

## **Content and Newsletter Development**

The newsletter will launch **early next week**, featuring survey insights and a call to action linking to the current survey (15:13).  
- Taylor will finalize the newsletter design incorporating Michael’s four posts and the external survey link.  
- Michael prefers a **carousel-style post format** on LinkedIn for survey content, which increases engagement by breaking information into clickable slides (16:28).  
- The carousel will cover individual survey questions like **growth and AI expectations**, highlighting key responses and trends per slide for easier consumption.  

Taylor will create a **copy document and visual mockup** outlining slide headers and content flow, which Michael will review and refine to ensure clarity and impact (20:23).  
- Michael aims to keep posts **non-salesy and insightful**, drawing from client work examples without revealing sensitive details.  
- The strategy focuses on posting high-quality content **weekly** rather than daily, aiming to build sustained engagement and brand recall.  
- Both agreed that shareable, forwardable content will help broaden the newsletter’s reach organically.  

## **Booth Design and Marketing Collateral**

Michael prefers **booth design option 4A** for its balanced branding and less aggressive tone compared to 4B (25:23).  
- He highlighted the importance of placing the **Hydrion logo prominently at the top** for better brand recognition in busy environments.  
- Michael requested resizing the **forklift icon** and aligning the “limited access” text on a single line for cleaner visuals (26:15).  
- Taylor will adjust the icon size and layout and send an updated mockup for final approval.  

Regarding the **one-pager brochure**, both agreed the current draft contains too much text and needs to be shortened into **three or four bullet points** for quick readability (29:05).  
- The brochure should clearly explain the purpose of the QR codes and the free assessment while avoiding lengthy paragraphs.  
- Michael emphasized the need for concise, actionable points that convey benefits like **improved fill rates** and **better profitability** at a glance.  
- Taylor will coordinate with the design team to update the layout accordingly for use as a standalone handout.  

## **Data and Analytics Preparation**

Michael flagged potential gaps in the **most engaged firm spreadsheet**, noting the latest data appears to stop at **November** (32:15).  
- Taylor will check with the developer to locate any updated traffic and engagement data, considering that exclusions may have moved some data to a new sheet (33:02).  
- The team plans to pull detailed **web traffic insights**, including firm names and job titles, for the upcoming meeting on **February 28th** to inform marketing strategy.  
- Michael stressed the importance of defining **clear success metrics and timelines** for campaign measurement during the February meeting (34:08).  

## **Strategic Marketing Vision**

Michael shared a developing marketing strategy focused on producing **thought leadership material** that provides clear, non-salesy insights to target audiences (10:57).  
- He noted that inbound leads so far have mainly been **spam**, highlighting the need for valuable content to attract genuine interest.  
- The strategy involves combining survey data with internal analytics to create **benchmark reports** and case studies that resonate with clients.  
- Michael’s goal is to align expectations with realistic timelines and measurable outcomes, seeking input from Taylor and Josh to refine these plans (35:01).  

Taylor and Michael agreed that defining **realistic goals and deadlines** is crucial for progress and accountability (35:14).  
- The team will continue iterative content development and data analysis to support this vision.  
- They plan ongoing collaboration on LinkedIn content and newsletter enhancements, with regular feedback loops to optimize engagement.',
  '2026-01-14 20:00:00+00',
  'published',
  '[{"text":"Monitor SurveyMonkey responses through Friday and prepare reminder email copy with initial survey insights for Michael to review by end of week (04:01)","completed":false},{"text":"Add external SurveyMonkey survey link to the closing section of upcoming Hydrian newsletter and finalize design for early next week distribution (13:21)","completed":false},{"text":"Create a LinkedIn carousel mockup using existing newsletter copy; prepare slide-by-slide copy outline and send it to Michael for review and additions (20:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Adjust booth design per Michael’s feedback (reduce forklift icon size, reformat text to single line) and send updated mockup (24:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Collaborate on revising one-pager brochure text to be more concise, bullet formatted, and explanatory of QR codes and assessments (28:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Coordinate with developer to locate and retrieve the latest web traffic/exclusion data spreadsheet and share with Michael (31:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Share final newsletter content draft and LinkedIn post ideas with Michael by Friday for feedback (35:32)","completed":false},{"text":"Review survey data and provide initial impressions and wording guidance for reminder email by Friday (05:15)","completed":false},{"text":"Offer feedback and finalize draft copy for LinkedIn carousel posts and newsletter content once Taylor sends mockups and drafts (20:40)","completed":false},{"text":"Decide on booth design preference (favoring 4A) and provide icon size and layout feedback for the design team (24:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Assess existing brochure versus one-pager designs to recommend text tightening and bullet list content (28:55)","completed":false},{"text":"Review web traffic and engagement data once Taylor secures full dataset for preparation of March 28th meeting (31:20)","completed":false},{"text":"Prepare strategic input and clarify realistic goals ahead of March 28th meeting (33:47)","completed":false}]'::jsonb,
