    '{"id":"01KEYQ6SXYW6FSB7BCXV07XGFF","title":"GSS Weekly meeting","summary":{"notes":"## **Content Development and Distribution**\n\nThe team is steadily producing targeted content focused on CFO turnover and cash flow management to support lead generation and engagement.\n\n- **One blog post on the cost of CFO turnover** is currently in progress, targeting keywords related to CFO talent challenges (03:12)  \n    - A second blog on regaining control of cash flow has been completed and will be shared for review after the meeting  \n    - The focus remains on topics that resonate with CFO concerns to attract relevant traffic and prospects  \n    - Content is designed to maintain steady output and relevance in the financial services space\n\n- **Podcast episode planning centers on mid-sized groups'' growth stories**, aiming for one episode this month featuring operators with 20-30 locations (05:23)  \n    - Initial outreach includes a contact who recently acquired a restaurant and another scaling a pop-up bagels brand  \n    - The goal is to share authentic business journeys and best practices to engage listeners and establish thought leadership  \n    - Short video clips from past podcasts are posted biweekly on YouTube and LinkedIn to maintain audience engagement  \n\n- **LinkedIn activity is consistent and strategic**, with posts 1-2 times weekly on the company page and personal profiles (08:40)  \n    - Content includes reposting blogs, podcast highlights, and industry commentary to keep the brand visible  \n    - Tagging relevant contacts in posts is used to increase reach and interaction, following successful tactics shown by recent posts  \n    - This approach supports ongoing brand awareness and positions the company as an active market participant\n\n## **Gated Content Strategy**\n\nThe team is finalizing an ebook designed to capture leads by requiring contact information for access, enhancing the lead generation funnel.\n\n- **The completed ebook on restaurant cash flow for 2026 will be published on a landing page with a lead capture form** (09:45)  \n    - Will and Nick are asked to provide quotes and contact details for inclusion to increase credibility and personalize the content  \n    - Social media posts will support ebook promotion, framed around addressing uncertainty in the restaurant industry this year  \n    - This gated content aims to convert website visitors into qualified leads by offering valuable insights in exchange for contact info  \n\n## **ABM Campaign Performance and Strategy**\n\nThe current Account-Based Marketing campaign has stalled due to list exhaustion and lack of engagement, prompting a strategic reassessment.\n\n- **Out of the original 201 leads, most have completed the workflow or were excluded due to prior outreach, halting new connections and replies** (11:55)  \n    - The team recognized that the initial offering of a free 30-day trial was perceived as too salesy and failed to drive expected responses  \n    - Will emphasized the need to explore more personalized approaches with smaller, well-filtered lists of about 20 prospects for better targeting  \n    - They plan to review campaign tactics with Bailey next week to explore different messaging and channels beyond LinkedIn connections and emails  \n\n- **There is skepticism around adding Google Ads spend without first proving campaign viability through organic and targeted outreach** (13:40)  \n    - Historical inbound leads primarily came from SEO and organic newsletter reach rather than paid ads, guiding current caution  \n    - The team expects to stimulate inbound interest through the campaign before tax day, April 15, aligning with client decision timelines  \n    - Will stressed the importance of finding the right formula to trigger demand rather than assuming the market lacks interest  \n\n- **The team accepts the need for an additional conversation to pivot strategy and improve lead generation outcomes** (16:50)  \n    - They acknowledge that even a few successful connections can justify ongoing efforts but require better targeting and messaging  \n    - Feedback loops with Tristan and Bailey will inform adjustments and new campaign ideas for the next meeting  \n    - The focus is on refining lists, enhancing personalization, and exploring alternative outreach methods to increase engagement  \n\n## **Marketing Goals and Pipeline Alignment**\n\nThe group underscored the importance of aligning marketing assumptions with pipeline targets for 2026 during the upcoming planning session.\n\n- **Marketing is expected to drive between 30% and 40% of the sales pipeline in 2026, making this alignment critical** (19:15)  \n    - The next meeting with Bailey will focus on goal setting and reviewing campaign plans to ensure realistic expectations  \n    - This alignment will guide resource allocation and campaign priorities for the year ahead  \n    - Clear pipeline contribution targets will help measure marketing’s impact and justify investments  \n\n## **Client Portal and Reporting Transparency**\n\nThe client portal provides real-time visibility into campaign activity, results, and financial balance to support informed decision-making.\n\n- **The portal shows upcoming activities, current campaign points, and balance status to keep stakeholders updated** (17:45)  \n    - This transparency supports accountability and quick identification of issues or opportunities  \n    - It enables better coordination among team members and faster response to campaign performance shifts  \n    - The portal serves as a centralized source of truth for progress tracking and strategic discussions","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast","Gated Content","ABM Campaign","CFO Turnover","LinkedIn Strategy","Lead Generation"],"overview":"- **Content Focus:** Team creates content on CFO turnover and cash flow to enhance lead generation and engagement.\n\n- **Blog and Podcast Production:** Ongoing blogs address CFO challenges; podcasts feature growth stories from mid-sized operators for audience engagement.\n\n- **Consistent LinkedIn Activity:** Posts 1-2 times weekly increase visibility, engaging audiences through strategic reposts and tagged contacts.\n\n- **Gated Ebook Launch:** Ebook on restaurant cash flow will capture leads via a landing page, supported by social media promotion.\n\n- **ABM Campaign Strategy Shift:** Current campaign stalled; exploring personalized approaches and refining targeting to improve lead generation.\n\n- **Marketing Pipeline Alignment:** Aim for 30-40% sales pipeline support from marketing in 2026, aligning goals with resource allocation.","action_items":"\n**Will Santana**\nProvide quotes and pictures for the restaurant Cash Playbook eBook to add credibility (10:32)\n\n**Nick**\nReview and provide feedback on the regaining control of cash flow blog shared post-meeting (03:45)\n\n**Will and Bailey**\nReview ABM campaigns next week, develop alternative strategies beyond LinkedIn outreach, and explore personalization and filtering options (17:45)\n\n**Bailey**\nCollaborate with Will to prepare ideas and modifications for ABM campaign effectiveness to present in next meeting (17:45)\n\n**MarketersInDemand Team**\nPublish gated eBook landing page with form, incorporate provided testimonials, and prepare social media posts promoting the eBook (09:30)\n\n**Meeting Host/Coordinator**\nFollow up on outreach for podcast guest confirmations and schedule recording (06:00)\n\n**Marketing Team**\nContinue posting biweekly short clips and engaging on LinkedIn with tagging strategy to maintain content presence and outreach (07:45)\n\n**Tristan**\nAdvise on campaign options including Google Ads and other tools to improve lead generation efforts (17:45)\n"},"duration":19.780000686645508,"speakers":[],"sentences":[{"text":"Hi, will.","index":0,"end_time":92.63,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":92.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Hi, how are you?","index":1,"end_time":94.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":92.63,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Good.","index":2,"end_time":95.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"How are you?","index":3,"end_time":96.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Good, thanks.","index":4,"end_time":97.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":96.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is Nick going to be joining us?","index":5,"end_time":156.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":154.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m not sure I can send him a message.","index":6,"end_time":159.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":157.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because Bailey won''t be joining us today.","index":7,"end_time":163.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":161.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She''s still on a desert vacation.","index":8,"end_time":166.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay, let me see.","index":9,"end_time":169.82,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":168.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, let''s get started.","index":10,"end_time":182.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":181.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Send him a message.","index":11,"end_time":184.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":183.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":12,"end_time":185.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":185.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, let''s get going.","index":13,"end_time":191.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":189.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She.","index":14,"end_time":193.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":192.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"He said he''s waiting to get in.","index":15,"end_time":195.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":193.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe he''s in the old link.","index":16,"end_time":197.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":196.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe he is.","index":17,"end_time":198.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll send him the.","index":18,"end_time":200.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Here, I, I''ll.","index":19,"end_time":202.11,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":201.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll send him a message.","index":20,"end_time":203.27,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":202.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I just said to go to the email.","index":21,"end_time":211.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":209.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There he is.","index":22,"end_time":240.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":239.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sorry about that.","index":23,"end_time":242.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":241.29,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I was on the old link.","index":24,"end_time":244.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":242.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s my fault.","index":25,"end_time":244.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No worries, no worries.","index":26,"end_time":248.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I was just telling Will that Bailey won''t be joining us today.","index":27,"end_time":253.93,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":250.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"She''s on vacation.","index":28,"end_time":256.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":254.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So that''s why we wanted also to write review the goals and targets next week so that she can be here to like, just go over that stuff with you.","index":29,"end_time":268.06,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":30,"end_time":269.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":268.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right, let''s get started then.","index":31,"end_time":272.86,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":270.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The agenda for today, as always, we''ll walk through some content updates, the gated content strategy and the stuff of the ABM campaign that we have.","index":32,"end_time":285.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":274.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Well, as for content updates, we have one blog post in progress.","index":33,"end_time":293.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":288.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We keep writing blogs on the keywords CFO turnover, like CFO talent crisis, stuff like that.","index":34,"end_time":305.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":294.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the one that we''re writing is the risk analysis, the cost of CFO turnover.","index":35,"end_time":309.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I also have a new one for your review today on regaining control of cash flow, which I will be sending out after this meeting.","index":36,"end_time":321.73,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":310.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Question I wanted to ask is when are you guys planning to record the next podcast episode?","index":37,"end_time":329.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because I know the last one we recorded mid December.","index":38,"end_time":334.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":329.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t have one scheduled, unfortunately.","index":39,"end_time":339.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.86,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yesterday I sent out a couple of emails.","index":40,"end_time":343.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":340.54,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I really don''t have even an idea of a concept of a podcast.","index":41,"end_time":349.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":345.26,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I guess what I''m trying to do on this next one, what I''m really interested in is seeing, trying to get a mid sized group, you know, 20, maybe 30 locations and just tell the story and how it started, how, how it came to be and how are you managing things and what are the best processes and infrastructure and, and then what do you see the future being like?","index":42,"end_time":379.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":349.1,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s all I want to do.","index":43,"end_time":383.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":381.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I want to, I want to have more of those.","index":44,"end_time":385.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":383.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Probably like every other one.","index":45,"end_time":387.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Just, you know, we did that with a different group and that one went really well and I want to.","index":46,"end_time":394.48,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s my, that''s my next focus.","index":47,"end_time":395.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":394.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ve got two or three emails out there, one already politely declined, and then hopefully I can get one of these guys on this month yet?","index":48,"end_time":405.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":396.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s not too much to ask.","index":49,"end_time":407.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":406.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And this one guy I have in particular I actually sold my, my restaurant to and he''s, he''s scaling quite well.","index":50,"end_time":418.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":407.68,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then the other one, for your information, Will, I reached out to Cal over at mpz and he''s, he''s grown like crazy with the pop up bagels brand.","index":51,"end_time":432.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":420.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then Dave''s hot and, and then he''s also got his pizza stuff.","index":52,"end_time":436.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":432.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But he''s always been really nice to answer my emails.","index":53,"end_time":440.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":436.77,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I know we moved on from each other, but I just want to hear his story.","index":54,"end_time":444.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":440.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, you know, how did he come to be.","index":55,"end_time":447.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":445.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So those are the two I''m kind of working on right now.","index":56,"end_time":450.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":447.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Got it.","index":57,"end_time":452.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":452.11,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Sounds like it will be like a good podcast episode if we get him like, and to start the year.","index":58,"end_time":458.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":453.07,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right, hopefully.","index":59,"end_time":461.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":460.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What I continue to do too is yesterday I just, I posted like a, you know, a minute and a half clip.","index":60,"end_time":471.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":464.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You guys, you know, you, you submit the shorts, the shorter clips.","index":61,"end_time":477.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":472.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I do that every other week just to keep content on YouTube.","index":62,"end_time":482.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":477.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I posted that, shared that on LinkedIn, so I continue to do that as well.","index":63,"end_time":488.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So it doesn''t look like we''re just sitting still.","index":64,"end_time":490.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":488.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s still content coming out.","index":65,"end_time":492.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.67,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, that''s a good idea.","index":66,"end_time":494.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":493.24,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And do you guys also like, keep the GSS LinkedIn updated, like the regular page with like, I don''t know, repurposing old content?","index":67,"end_time":504.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":494.52,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because that will be good as well.","index":68,"end_time":507.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":504.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yes, I do that.","index":69,"end_time":508.999,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":507.96,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Personally, I''m pretty active on there.","index":70,"end_time":512.36,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":508.999,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I post once to twice a week on there.","index":71,"end_time":514.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":512.36,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Usually what I''ve been doing is, you know, just keeping it.","index":72,"end_time":518.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":515.48,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ve been reposting your blogs, your content with a little comment.","index":73,"end_time":522.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":519.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll share the YouTube episodes on there, the podcast on there, and then my personal page.","index":74,"end_time":530.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":524.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I, I comment on some industry things that''s not too particular to gss, but once in a while I share the GSS content as well, but otherwise it''s just general content.","index":75,"end_time":541.74,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":531.18,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":76,"end_time":543.02,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":542.14,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":77,"end_time":543.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":543.5,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Alrighty.","index":78,"end_time":545.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":545.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s, that''s a great strategy.","index":79,"end_time":550.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":546.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Also, like tagging a lot of people seems to work on LinkedIn a lot.","index":80,"end_time":554.95,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":550.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So if you can tag your friends, people that react to your post as well, maybe in the comments.","index":81,"end_time":562.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":554.95,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I have seen that work for a lot of, like, clients.","index":82,"end_time":566.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":563.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":83,"end_time":568.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":567.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like yesterday I posted a clip of our audit podcast from Carrie over at gbq and I tagged, I tagged her in the GBQ firm.","index":84,"end_time":576.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":568.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we''ll see.","index":85,"end_time":580.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":579.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, we''ll continue to do that.","index":86,"end_time":582.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":580.35,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Got it.","index":87,"end_time":584.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":583.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then for the gated content strategy.","index":88,"end_time":587.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":584.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We finished writing the ebook, and the idea is that we publish the ebook on the website on a landing page.","index":89,"end_time":596.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":587.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We embed a form over there so that people have to leave their information to read it.","index":90,"end_time":601.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m gonna send it out for review.","index":91,"end_time":603.8,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":602.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think we will benefit if we could get, like, a couple of quotes from you, Will and Nick on the ebook just so that it seems that lattice that is coming from you guys.","index":92,"end_time":616.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":604.92,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe we can put your pictures, your contact information at the very end, and when we''re done writing, it will do, like, little posts for your social media.","index":93,"end_time":627.14,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":616.12,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, like, hey, we wrote this restaurant Cash Playbook for 2026.","index":94,"end_time":631.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":627.22,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You can write something like, I know, like, it''s uncertain times this.","index":95,"end_time":636.74,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":632.34,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"This year for, like, restaurants, but xyz.","index":96,"end_time":640.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":637.7,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So I''ll send that over for review.","index":97,"end_time":643.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":642.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Feel free to, like, leave your comments change, whatever.","index":98,"end_time":648.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":643.94,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You don''t think it''s, like, suiting or an app, like your source, so that we can make it more, like, attractive for people to download.","index":99,"end_time":660.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":648.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I will be sending this over today after we''re done meeting.","index":100,"end_time":665.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":661.47,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":101,"end_time":666.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":666.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And then for the AVA campaign, we identified, like, why the ABM appeared inactive and it wasn''t sending new connections, request, or replies and stuff like that.","index":102,"end_time":681.94,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":669.31,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s because everyone on the list completed the workflow.","index":103,"end_time":686.26,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":682.82,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So out of the 201, like, the 201 leads that we had, a large portion of them was excluded because we already reached them through other campaigns.","index":104,"end_time":698.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":686.58,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, like, the past campaign.","index":105,"end_time":699.54,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":698.46,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s, like, expected behavior to protect our deliverability.","index":106,"end_time":704.52,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":700.02,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But what we need to do now is to keep leads coming.","index":107,"end_time":708.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":705.16,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We need to add more to the list or enrich the new contact list that we have so that we keep getting connections.","index":108,"end_time":719.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":708.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Because right now, we''re not getting anything after we resume the campaign.","index":109,"end_time":725.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What I think we can do is just build a new one.","index":110,"end_time":730.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":728.37,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But I don''t know if you guys want to, like, have any comments on, like, do we keep reaching to the C suite or.","index":111,"end_time":739.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":730.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, I mean, I think that we.","index":112,"end_time":743.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":741.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''m not.","index":113,"end_time":743.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":743.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, so we started this campaign and I think before Thanksgiving.","index":114,"end_time":748.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":744.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We really haven''t gotten any traction.","index":115,"end_time":752.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":749.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think we need.","index":116,"end_time":754.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":753.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Whether it''s, you know, we discuss it now or have a series of discussions, we need to figure out how this campaign becomes more viable.","index":117,"end_time":765.39,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":754.13,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, it''s.","index":118,"end_time":767.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":765.55,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''d say now is.","index":119,"end_time":768.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":767.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is.","index":120,"end_time":769.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":768.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s the middle of the month from this point forward.","index":121,"end_time":773.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":769.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s.","index":122,"end_time":773.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The timing shouldn''t be an issue.","index":123,"end_time":775.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":773.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But, I mean, when we first spoke with Tristan, the goal was to.","index":124,"end_time":782.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":778.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Have something that was irresistible I think that we changed the offering a little bit because it, it seemed to me that, you know, just offering the free right out of the gate for 30 days was a bit, it cheapened the, the service.","index":125,"end_time":802.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":787.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or maybe people didn''t believe that, or they felt like it was a, a sales hook.","index":126,"end_time":807.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":802.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And, and it, it didn''t seem to work so well, so we''ve modified it and, But I, I think it''s, it''s.","index":127,"end_time":817.64,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":807.01,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"The, the, the.","index":128,"end_time":819.56,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":817.72,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t, it doesn''t feel like it''s, it''s produced what we thought it would at this point.","index":129,"end_time":825.44,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":821.32,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So the question is, why is it.","index":130,"end_time":827.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":825.44,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is it the lists?","index":131,"end_time":829.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":827.8,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Is it.","index":132,"end_time":830.28,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":829.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I know we''re trying to do a lot of people at the same time, so that doesn''t lend itself to a personalized approach.","index":133,"end_time":839.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":831.08,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Do we need to reconsider that and try to make it more personalized and have different filters?","index":134,"end_time":847.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":840.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, you know, maybe we have a smaller list of 20 based on some filters, and we have to really make sure that''s a good list.","index":135,"end_time":854.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":847.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it, and then, and then the.","index":136,"end_time":857.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":854.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Does the content need to be personalized for that, for that group?","index":137,"end_time":862.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":858.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, just when we started this discussion, Tristan was recommending Google Ad purchases in addition to this.","index":138,"end_time":872.75,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":864.03,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I, I wanted to see if this campaign would, would be viable because we haven''t had success in this approach in the past.","index":139,"end_time":882.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":873.39,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, I''m open to it and, and I, I''d like to think it can be, but I mean, the idea.","index":140,"end_time":888.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":882.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t think just buying some Google Ads changes the situation.","index":141,"end_time":893.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":888.81,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I could be wrong, but I don''t know if I want to spend more money without trying to figure out if this can be something that can drive leads, because if it doesn''t, I mean, because historically where we got inbound was just on basic SEO.","index":142,"end_time":909.69,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.61,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like people that didn''t know us or maybe they received the newsletter, somehow we got their email and they would, they would reach out to us when the timing was right.","index":143,"end_time":918.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":909.69,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"With this campaign, what we''re trying to do, I guess, is, is change that timing or reach it.","index":144,"end_time":925.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":918.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"People that we don''t know and try to try to stimulate a response from them based on our offering.","index":145,"end_time":935.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":925.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And it doesn''t seem like we''re doing that.","index":146,"end_time":937.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":935.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So is the market.","index":147,"end_time":941.09,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":939.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not is just the nature of the market, can we not change the timing?","index":148,"end_time":946.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":941.78,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t know if that''s the case.","index":149,"end_time":948.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":946.74,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, right now, from this point until tax, the tax day, April 15, we should have the ability to stimulate inbound if we''re doing it in a way that people feel that they should reach out, but, I mean, we have to.","index":150,"end_time":966.26,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":948.3,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I feel like we''re in a situation right now where we have to have an additional conversation.","index":151,"end_time":972.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":967.06,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe this goes in line with the discussion from.","index":152,"end_time":976.16,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":972.42,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"From Bailey, but, I mean, just Getting connections through LinkedIn I don''t think is enough.","index":153,"end_time":981.88,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":976.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Or at least that''s not what we were anticipating.","index":154,"end_time":984.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":981.88,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, right, Right.","index":155,"end_time":986.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":984.64,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So for next week, what I.","index":156,"end_time":989.12,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":987.04,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"What I''ll do with Bailey is we can review the campaigns and maybe bring a different approach.","index":157,"end_time":998,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":989.2,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Not just LinkedIn connections, LinkedIn messages and emails, and see if we can explore something different with what we have so that we don''t keep doing the same thing and getting the same results, which is like, really just no replies at all.","index":158,"end_time":1017.21,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":999.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Right.","index":159,"end_time":1017.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1017.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we tested it.","index":160,"end_time":1019.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1018.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It didn''t work.","index":161,"end_time":1020.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1019.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Let''s see what else we can do with what we have.","index":162,"end_time":1022.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1020.49,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It''s not the end of the world.","index":163,"end_time":1025.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1024.25,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We can do a lot of things.","index":164,"end_time":1026.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1025.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And I''ll check with Tristan as well on what we can do for these campaigns.","index":165,"end_time":1034.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1027.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But, yeah, and we recognize that, I mean, we''re.","index":166,"end_time":1040.49,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1035.45,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It doesn''t take.","index":167,"end_time":1042.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1041.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"It just takes one or two to justify, you know, an ongoing scenario.","index":168,"end_time":1047.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1042.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But.","index":169,"end_time":1048.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1047.97,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So, I mean, we recognize that, but there''s.","index":170,"end_time":1052.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1048.89,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"There''s somebody out.","index":171,"end_time":1054.73,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1053.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, we know for a fact, like, one of our customers had the demand for.","index":172,"end_time":1060.53,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1054.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"For this type of service.","index":173,"end_time":1061.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1060.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"They.","index":174,"end_time":1062.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.05,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We offered this to them and they decided they already had another scenario in place, so we weren''t able to.","index":175,"end_time":1070.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1062.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"To.","index":176,"end_time":1072.13,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1071.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"To get that in place.","index":177,"end_time":1074.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1072.53,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"But, I mean, it''s.","index":178,"end_time":1076.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1074.93,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t think it would be the correct statement to say that there''s no demand.","index":179,"end_time":1082.93,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1076.85,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Like, I think it''s more probable that there is demand.","index":180,"end_time":1087.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1083.57,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"We haven''t figured out the right formula to stimulate that demand to create a response.","index":181,"end_time":1093.33,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1088.21,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.","index":182,"end_time":1095.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1093.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And we have to, like, figure it out.","index":183,"end_time":1097.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1095.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Maybe it''s a different list, a different message, but we''ll look into.","index":184,"end_time":1103.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1097.73,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I''ll look into it with Bailey and.","index":185,"end_time":1105.04,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1103.41,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And come with, like, ideas for the next meeting.","index":186,"end_time":1109.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1105.27,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Okay.","index":187,"end_time":1110.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1109.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Yeah.","index":188,"end_time":1112.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1111.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"And that''s everything we had planned for today.","index":189,"end_time":1119.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1115.83,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Here''s your client portal.","index":190,"end_time":1123.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1121.51,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"You can see everything that''s coming up and the points that are working and the balance.","index":191,"end_time":1133.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1125.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I don''t know if you guys have any questions, something maybe that we didn''t touch.","index":192,"end_time":1140.81,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1134.65,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"No, I think the content is great.","index":193,"end_time":1144.01,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1142.09,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I think our primary focus is the discussion next week to really sort of make sure when we look at our plans that we have for 26, that we can make the assumption that, you know, marketing, for example, will drive 30 to 40% of our pipeline.","index":194,"end_time":1165.55,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1144.33,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"I mean, that''s.","index":195,"end_time":1166.99,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.19,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"That''s kind of, particularly at this time of year, we getting alignment on that I think, is our primary focus right now.","index":196,"end_time":1174.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1166.99,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"So we covered that.","index":197,"end_time":1176.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1175.23,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Got it.","index":198,"end_time":1177.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1176.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":199,"end_time":1179.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1178.75,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"All right.","index":200,"end_time":1180.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1179.87,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Well, thank you so much.","index":201,"end_time":1181.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1180.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Thank you, guys.","index":202,"end_time":1183.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1182.43,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"See you next time.","index":203,"end_time":1183.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1183.15,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bye.","index":204,"end_time":1184.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1184.59,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bye.","index":205,"end_time":1185.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1184.91,"speaker_name":null},{"text":"Bye.","index":206,"end_time":1186.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1185.63,"speaker_name":null}],"dateString":"2026-01-14T17:00:15.000Z","host_email":null,"meeting_link":null,"participants":[],"transcript_url":"https://app.fireflies.ai/view/01KEYQ6SXYW6FSB7BCXV07XGFF","organizer_email":"guille.santana@marketersindemand.com"}'::jsonb,
    '{"label":"neutral","confidence":0.83,"bullets":["Shared content pipeline includes new blog on CFO turnover risk and a cash flow guide.","Podcast planning stalled due to lack of concept; outreach continuing to potential guests.","ABM campaign underperforming; completed workflow and duplicate list cited as key issues.","Team discussed trial offer’s low traction; considering personalization and revised messaging.","Next week’s focus is aligning 2026 goals and reassessing campaign strategy with Bailey."],"highlights":[{"quote":"I think we need to figure out how this campaign becomes more viable.","speaker":"Unknown"},{"quote":"It doesn''t seem like we''re doing that.","speaker":"Unknown"},{"quote":"We tested it. It didn''t work. Let''s see what else we can do.","speaker":"Unknown"}],"topics":["content","ABM","podcast","strategy","delivery"],"model":"gpt-4-0125-preview","version":1,"generated_at":"2026-01-16T00:00:00Z"}'::jsonb,
    '{"fireflies_summary":{"notes":"## **Content Development and Distribution**\n\nThe team is steadily producing targeted content focused on CFO turnover and cash flow management to support lead generation and engagement.\n\n- **One blog post on the cost of CFO turnover** is currently in progress, targeting keywords related to CFO talent challenges (03:12)  \n    - A second blog on regaining control of cash flow has been completed and will be shared for review after the meeting  \n    - The focus remains on topics that resonate with CFO concerns to attract relevant traffic and prospects  \n    - Content is designed to maintain steady output and relevance in the financial services space\n\n- **Podcast episode planning centers on mid-sized groups'' growth stories**, aiming for one episode this month featuring operators with 20-30 locations (05:23)  \n    - Initial outreach includes a contact who recently acquired a restaurant and another scaling a pop-up bagels brand  \n    - The goal is to share authentic business journeys and best practices to engage listeners and establish thought leadership  \n    - Short video clips from past podcasts are posted biweekly on YouTube and LinkedIn to maintain audience engagement  \n\n- **LinkedIn activity is consistent and strategic**, with posts 1-2 times weekly on the company page and personal profiles (08:40)  \n    - Content includes reposting blogs, podcast highlights, and industry commentary to keep the brand visible  \n    - Tagging relevant contacts in posts is used to increase reach and interaction, following successful tactics shown by recent posts  \n    - This approach supports ongoing brand awareness and positions the company as an active market participant\n\n## **Gated Content Strategy**\n\nThe team is finalizing an ebook designed to capture leads by requiring contact information for access, enhancing the lead generation funnel.\n\n- **The completed ebook on restaurant cash flow for 2026 will be published on a landing page with a lead capture form** (09:45)  \n    - Will and Nick are asked to provide quotes and contact details for inclusion to increase credibility and personalize the content  \n    - Social media posts will support ebook promotion, framed around addressing uncertainty in the restaurant industry this year  \n    - This gated content aims to convert website visitors into qualified leads by offering valuable insights in exchange for contact info  \n\n## **ABM Campaign Performance and Strategy**\n\nThe current Account-Based Marketing campaign has stalled due to list exhaustion and lack of engagement, prompting a strategic reassessment.\n\n- **Out of the original 201 leads, most have completed the workflow or were excluded due to prior outreach, halting new connections and replies** (11:55)  \n    - The team recognized that the initial offering of a free 30-day trial was perceived as too salesy and failed to drive expected responses  \n    - Will emphasized the need to explore more personalized approaches with smaller, well-filtered lists of about 20 prospects for better targeting  \n    - They plan to review campaign tactics with Bailey next week to explore different messaging and channels beyond LinkedIn connections and emails  \n\n- **There is skepticism around adding Google Ads spend without first proving campaign viability through organic and targeted outreach** (13:40)  \n    - Historical inbound leads primarily came from SEO and organic newsletter reach rather than paid ads, guiding current caution  \n    - The team expects to stimulate inbound interest through the campaign before tax day, April 15, aligning with client decision timelines  \n    - Will stressed the importance of finding the right formula to trigger demand rather than assuming the market lacks interest  \n\n- **The team accepts the need for an additional conversation to pivot strategy and improve lead generation outcomes** (16:50)  \n    - They acknowledge that even a few successful connections can justify ongoing efforts but require better targeting and messaging  \n    - Feedback loops with Tristan and Bailey will inform adjustments and new campaign ideas for the next meeting  \n    - The focus is on refining lists, enhancing personalization, and exploring alternative outreach methods to increase engagement  \n\n## **Marketing Goals and Pipeline Alignment**\n\nThe group underscored the importance of aligning marketing assumptions with pipeline targets for 2026 during the upcoming planning session.\n\n- **Marketing is expected to drive between 30% and 40% of the sales pipeline in 2026, making this alignment critical** (19:15)  \n    - The next meeting with Bailey will focus on goal setting and reviewing campaign plans to ensure realistic expectations  \n    - This alignment will guide resource allocation and campaign priorities for the year ahead  \n    - Clear pipeline contribution targets will help measure marketing’s impact and justify investments  \n\n## **Client Portal and Reporting Transparency**\n\nThe client portal provides real-time visibility into campaign activity, results, and financial balance to support informed decision-making.\n\n- **The portal shows upcoming activities, current campaign points, and balance status to keep stakeholders updated** (17:45)  \n    - This transparency supports accountability and quick identification of issues or opportunities  \n    - It enables better coordination among team members and faster response to campaign performance shifts  \n    - The portal serves as a centralized source of truth for progress tracking and strategic discussions","outline":null,"keywords":["Podcast","Gated Content","ABM Campaign","CFO Turnover","LinkedIn Strategy","Lead Generation"],"overview":"- **Content Focus:** Team creates content on CFO turnover and cash flow to enhance lead generation and engagement.\n\n- **Blog and Podcast Production:** Ongoing blogs address CFO challenges; podcasts feature growth stories from mid-sized operators for audience engagement.\n\n- **Consistent LinkedIn Activity:** Posts 1-2 times weekly increase visibility, engaging audiences through strategic reposts and tagged contacts.\n\n- **Gated Ebook Launch:** Ebook on restaurant cash flow will capture leads via a landing page, supported by social media promotion.\n\n- **ABM Campaign Strategy Shift:** Current campaign stalled; exploring personalized approaches and refining targeting to improve lead generation.\n\n- **Marketing Pipeline Alignment:** Aim for 30-40% sales pipeline support from marketing in 2026, aligning goals with resource allocation.","action_items":"\n**Will Santana**\nProvide quotes and pictures for the restaurant Cash Playbook eBook to add credibility (10:32)\n\n**Nick**\nReview and provide feedback on the regaining control of cash flow blog shared post-meeting (03:45)\n\n**Will and Bailey**\nReview ABM campaigns next week, develop alternative strategies beyond LinkedIn outreach, and explore personalization and filtering options (17:45)\n\n**Bailey**\nCollaborate with Will to prepare ideas and modifications for ABM campaign effectiveness to present in next meeting (17:45)\n\n**MarketersInDemand Team**\nPublish gated eBook landing page with form, incorporate provided testimonials, and prepare social media posts promoting the eBook (09:30)\n\n**Meeting Host/Coordinator**\nFollow up on outreach for podcast guest confirmations and schedule recording (06:00)\n\n**Marketing Team**\nContinue posting biweekly short clips and engaging on LinkedIn with tagging strategy to maintain content presence and outreach (07:45)\n\n**Tristan**\nAdvise on campaign options including Google Ads and other tools to improve lead generation efforts (17:45)\n"},"migrated_from":"contract_meetings","original_id":"a2a0801f-bc46-4224-9e47-fa91d42f80fc","master_marketer":{"status":"migrated"}}'::jsonb,
