    '{"id":"01KEVVT7ATD2CW48FE5E896J0G","title":"AQI // MiD","summary":{"notes":"## **Salesforce and HubSpot Integration**\n\nThe team is finalizing Salesforce integration with lead lists and HubSpot data flow to streamline contact management and scoring.\n\n- **Kyle''s access issue to lead lists delayed review, but the lists impressed his team once accessible, prompting a shift to public visibility for all three lists** (04:01)  \n    - Kyle will immediately review the lists once access is granted.  \n    - Colin emphasized clarifying duplicated data fields like segments and product brands to ensure accurate record matching.  \n    - Barb acknowledged database inconsistencies but expects Kyle’s review to confirm usability.  \n    - The integration will proceed once Kyle approves the lists, ensuring clean data transfer.\n\n- **HubSpot contact properties now pull from specific dropdown sources to maintain data consistency across customer community and sales outreach segments** (06:25)  \n    - Barb confirmed the team agrees with this approach after seeing the setup.  \n    - Guille reported the landing page with two forms is live, but inconsistent sales rep name formatting needs alignment before Monday’s kickoff.  \n    - Colin committed to fixing formatting and removing a fully embedded input lead form immediately to prevent confusion.  \n    - These updates ensure contacts are accurately tied to accounts in HubSpot, supporting targeted outreach.\n\n- **A Zoom integration issue broke workflow due to a newly added required question, but the team quickly fixed it, preventing further data loss** (08:32)  \n    - Barb learned not to add required questions retroactively to avoid breaking flows.  \n    - The fix restored correct data reflection in dashboards, improving event tracking accuracy.\n\n- **Newsletter templates built in HubSpot are fully customizable and delegated to the new coordinator, enabling faster cloning and deployment across product lines** (09:22)  \n    - Barb confirmed the coordinator is familiar with HubSpot and ready to manage newsletter cloning and edits.  \n    - This delegation accelerates content distribution and reduces bottlenecks in marketing communications.\n\n## **Lead Scoring Development and Prioritization**\n\nLead scoring logic is under construction to enable better sales qualification, with a clear plan to address backlog and prioritize key segments.\n\n- **No leads have been scored yet, but uploaded contacts from recent webinars are ready for scoring to start manual outreach by BDRs next week** (10:55)  \n    - Barb explained that scoring over 100 points does not automatically push leads to Salesforce yet; manual calls are expected initially.  \n    - Colin detailed that HubSpot scoring rules now exclude internal companies from progressing beyond Prospect status, refining lead quality.  \n    - The ICP fit score and other criteria are being built out progressively to reflect the detailed logic Barb provided.  \n    - This phased scoring approach balances automation with manual sales effort while the system matures.\n\n- **Barb requested clarity on managing negative lead scores and emphasized the need to clear current backlog points owed to the agency** (12:46)  \n    - She confirmed a **$10,000/month Q1 budget** is approved but highlighted a small January refund issue that delayed payments.  \n    - Vivian supports increasing funding by an additional **$6,000** to clear backlog and accelerate priority projects like ABM for mining and Food & Beverage segments.  \n    - Barb wants to front-load spending for February and March to enable faster delivery and testing of these key initiatives.  \n    - This funding adjustment is seen as critical to maintaining momentum and meeting Q1 goals.\n\n- **Tristan outlined coordinating a simple addendum for increasing Q1 budget to avoid disrupting ongoing weekly work** (17:02)  \n    - Barb agreed to prioritize defining backlog costs and next steps before finalizing the addendum.  \n    - She confirmed availability for a short meeting next week to align on priorities and confirm payment details.  \n    - This approach keeps core work flowing while enabling increased resource allocation for critical tasks.\n\n## **Account Management and Client Relationship**\n\nStrong collaboration and trust between the agency and client are enabling steady progress despite challenges.\n\n- **Barb praised the agency for never dropping the ball and maintaining consistent delivery over the past three months** (20:44)  \n    - She contrasted this with other affiliates struggling with HubSpot adoption and integration.  \n    - Vivian’s pragmatic, no-perfectionist attitude helps keep projects moving without getting stuck on minor issues.  \n    - Tristan emphasized the strong team dynamic and client responsiveness as key to success.  \n    - Barb frequently recommends the agency to other affiliates, reinforcing long-term partnership value.\n\n- **Barb expressed concern about financial arrears and stressed the importance of timely payments to maintain trust** (13:58)  \n    - She highlighted issues with HubSpot shutting off accounts despite payments, praising the agency for avoiding such disruptions.  \n    - The client wants to avoid owing money and prefers upfront budgeting and clear funding plans.  \n    - This financial transparency supports a stable working relationship and prioritizes clearing backlog promptly.\n\n- **Plans were made to schedule a focused meeting Tuesday at 3:00 PM Eastern to finalize backlog clearance and prioritize Q1 deliverables** (23:08)  \n    - Barb will lead the conversation with support from Colin, Tristan, and possibly Kyle for clarifications.  \n    - This meeting aims to lock in budget, backlog scope, and project sequencing for the rest of Q1.  \n    - The goal is to ensure all parties are aligned and ready for the upcoming product launches and ABM testing.\n\n## **ABM and Product Priorities**\n\nThe team is focusing on Account-Based Marketing (ABM) and microsite development as critical for Q1, with clear resource allocation plans.\n\n- **Barb identified ABM for mining and Food & Beverage as the highest priority projects for February and March, targeting Q1 testing and rollout** (16:33)  \n    - Vivian supports dedicating increased funding and agency effort to these segments given their strategic value.  \n    - Barb noted some microsite landing pages for video hosting could be handled internally by James if agency points run low.  \n    - This prioritization reflects a focused approach to deliver high-impact campaigns within limited time and budget.  \n    - The team aims to start testing ABM by end of Q1 to gather early feedback and optimize.\n\n- **Tristan committed to managing workload boundaries and coordinating between weekly tasks and priority projects to avoid overloading Colin and Guille** (18:07)  \n    - He will handle communications with Barb and Vivian on budgeting and scope changes separately from daily project calls.  \n    - This division of responsibilities helps keep core work on track while enabling flexible scaling of resources for critical initiatives.  \n    - The approach minimizes context switching and supports focused execution.\n\n- **Hawk integration remains an affiliate-driven initiative with no direct agency involvement but close monitoring due to shared referrals and reputation** (18:50)  \n    - Barb reported positive endorsements for the agency from affiliates despite some not currently using the service.  \n    - The agency is positioned as a trusted resource and potential partner for Hawk-related CRM decisions expected in Q1 or Q2.  \n    - This relationship may open future collaboration opportunities and expands agency visibility in the affiliate network.\n\n## **Process Improvements and Workflow Stability**\n\nContinuous learning and quick fixes are improving workflows and reducing downtime risks.\n\n- **Zoom integration failure was traced to a required question added after the initial setup, underscoring the need for change management** (08:32)  \n    - Barb acknowledged the importance of finalizing form questions before workflow activation to prevent breakage.  \n    - The quick fix restored data correctness and dashboard accuracy, avoiding long-term tracking gaps.  \n    - This incident highlighted tighter controls on form adjustments moving forward.\n\n- **Lead form updates and newsletter template deployment demonstrate improved operational flexibility and user experience** (09:22)  \n    - Drag-and-drop newsletter modules allow non-technical coordinators to make edits and clone content easily.  \n    - Lead form adjustments on the landing page will remove unused forms and standardize fields for better data capture.  \n    - These updates reduce bottlenecks and empower internal teams to manage content dynamically.  \n    - The improvements contribute to smoother marketing execution and faster response cycles.\n\n- **Clear escalation and communication protocols ensure high transparency and responsiveness between client and agency** (12:46)  \n    - Barb and Colin maintain close contact to avoid arrears and resolve payment issues quickly.  \n    - Tristan’s role includes managing scope, prioritization, and resource allocation to keep projects aligned with client budgets.  \n    - This structure reduces risk of miscommunication and supports steady progress despite evolving demands.  \n    - The team’s responsiveness is a key factor in client satisfaction and project momentum.","outline":null,"keywords":["Lead Scoring","HubSpot Integration","Salesforce","ABM Tool","Budget Addendum","Affiliate Onboarding"],"overview":"- **Salesforce Integration:** Lead lists delayed review; once approved, transition to public visibility for accuracy in data management.\n\n- **HubSpot Consistency:** Contact properties now use dropdowns to maintain data accuracy; sales rep names need formatting fixes before kickoff.\n\n- **Budget Allocation:** Approved $10,000/month Q1 budget, seeking additional $6,000 to clear backlog and prioritize important projects.\n\n- **ABM Priorities:** Focus on mining and Food & Beverage projects for Q1; testing to start by end of March for effective rollout.\n\n- **Process Improvements:** Zoom integration failure highlighted change management needs; quick fixes are enhancing workflow stability and data accuracy.\n\n- **Communication Protocols:** Close contact between client and agency to resolve issues quickly; clear role divisions support project alignment and progress.","action_items":"\n**Colin Costigan**\nChange all three contact lists from private to public and notify Kyle for review (04:01)\nCorrect sales rep name formatting on Hawk and OTT web forms for consistency (08:27)\nMake changes on landing page forms as discussed (08:27)\nContinue building out lead scoring logic and integrate scoring rules based on Barb’s input (10:16)\nKeep lead scoring updated and prepare for integration when contact lists are approved (24:50)\n\n**Barb Willans**\nInform Kyle to review public contact lists and report any changes (04:06)\nCheck with Kyle on sales rep name formatting preference (07:26)\nMonitor and manage scoring process; coordinate manual outreach with BDRs until full automation (10:55)\nCoordinate discussion with Vivian regarding budget priorities and addendum for Q1 backlog and next quarter funding (14:38)\nConfirm availability for Tuesday 3:00 pm Eastern meeting to finalize backlog and priorities (23:18)\n\n**Tristan Pelligrino**\nSupport communication on budget addendum options and Q1 front-loading process with Barb and Vivian (18:07)\nSchedule and lead follow-up meeting with Barb to discuss backlog clearing and priorities (22:46)\nAssist with Hawk affiliate outreach as needed and coordinate internal team focus (18:07)\n\n**Guille Santana**\nRefresh and update landing page forms as requested and fix ''check your data health'' label on Hawk form (07:26)\n"},"duration":26.68000030517578,"speakers":[{"id":0,"name":"Colin Costigan"},{"id":1,"name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"id":2,"name":"bwillans"},{"id":3,"name":"Guille Santana"}],"sentences":[{"text":"How''s it going?","index":0,"end_time":36.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":35.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"What''s up, man?","index":1,"end_time":36.89,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":36.09,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I had a call with Ad Roll.","index":2,"end_time":42.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":40.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I''m gonna have another one next week to demo their ABM tool.","index":3,"end_time":46.97,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":43.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Roll Works, essentially, yeah.","index":4,"end_time":52.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":50.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What used to be rollworks is now Adrolevm.","index":5,"end_time":55.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":52.45,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Does it cost anymore?","index":6,"end_time":57.57,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":56.21,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That''s what they.","index":7,"end_time":59.09,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":57.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They didn''t answer pricing question.","index":8,"end_time":60.77,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":59.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"They wanted to show me features first, but it would probably be completely switching over from one to the other.","index":9,"end_time":67.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":60.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Really?","index":10,"end_time":68.77,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":68.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":11,"end_time":69.49,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, Barb''s here.","index":12,"end_time":70.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":69.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":13,"end_time":72.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":72.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Be interesting to check how.","index":14,"end_time":74.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":72.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What''s up?","index":15,"end_time":75.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":74.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Da.","index":16,"end_time":76.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":75.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What''s up?","index":17,"end_time":78.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":78.06,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"What''s up?","index":18,"end_time":80.06,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":79.26,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Hey, guys.","index":19,"end_time":94.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":94.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Barb.","index":20,"end_time":95.82,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":95.18,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Hey, folks.","index":21,"end_time":97.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":96.78,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"How are you doing?","index":22,"end_time":98.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":97.74,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good, how are you?","index":23,"end_time":99.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":99.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hey, stranger.","index":24,"end_time":100.7,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":99.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hey, Tracy.","index":25,"end_time":101.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":100.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hey, Barb.","index":26,"end_time":101.78,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How you doing?","index":27,"end_time":102.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":101.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I heard you.","index":28,"end_time":103.34,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":102.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You heard?","index":29,"end_time":103.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Wear the markers in Demand hat now during meetings.","index":30,"end_time":106.32,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":103.96,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Had to come and see for myself, but.","index":31,"end_time":108.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":106.32,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":32,"end_time":108.88,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hang on.","index":33,"end_time":109.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":108.88,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Because I''m freezing and it''s right there.","index":34,"end_time":111.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":109.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, hang on.","index":35,"end_time":111.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":111.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s like I live in Canada or something.","index":36,"end_time":126.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":125.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m frozen.","index":37,"end_time":127.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":126.96,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"There it is.","index":38,"end_time":128.2,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":127.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":39,"end_time":128.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.44,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"If anyone needed that hat, it was you.","index":40,"end_time":130.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":128.84,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We thought you, though.","index":41,"end_time":131.98,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":130.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s so northern.","index":42,"end_time":133.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":131.98,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, it is pretty warm.","index":43,"end_time":134.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":133.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll say that.","index":44,"end_time":135.74,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":134.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s a good brand.","index":45,"end_time":137.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":136.14,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It doesn''t itch.","index":46,"end_time":138.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":137.02,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, yeah.","index":47,"end_time":139.42,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":138.62,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Carhartt.","index":48,"end_time":140.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":139.42,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Good stuff.","index":49,"end_time":142.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":141.42,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s my first car heart, so I''ll get.","index":50,"end_time":144.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":142.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You''re decked out.","index":51,"end_time":147.22,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":146.38,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You got Carhartt, you got the North Face.","index":52,"end_time":148.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":147.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Looking great.","index":53,"end_time":149.7,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":149.1,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, it''s like.","index":54,"end_time":150.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":149.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s.","index":55,"end_time":151.42,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":150.94,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Yeah, it is cold.","index":56,"end_time":153.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":151.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Not.","index":57,"end_time":155.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":154.78,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Not terribly cold.","index":58,"end_time":156.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":155.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"My family, it''s -27 where they are right now, so.","index":59,"end_time":159.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":156.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Wow.","index":60,"end_time":160.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":159.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":61,"end_time":161.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":160.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Anyway, I''m going to wear it.","index":62,"end_time":162.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":161.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Do it.","index":63,"end_time":164.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":163.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, Barb, thanks for rescheduling.","index":64,"end_time":168.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":166.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know you guys have had a crazy week.","index":65,"end_time":169.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":168.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You had the event going on and everything, but.","index":66,"end_time":172.13,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":169.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":67,"end_time":172.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Wanted to just still take time so that we don''t slow down progress on any projects.","index":68,"end_time":176.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":172.41,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":69,"end_time":177.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":176.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, of course.","index":70,"end_time":178.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":177.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So we''ll talk about the Salesforce integration.","index":71,"end_time":180.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":178.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did get your email, by the way, and wouldn''t you know it, that everything you sent was in our agenda.","index":72,"end_time":186.25,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":181.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I felt that it was so late.","index":73,"end_time":188.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":186.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Usually I try and do it on Thursday and I just lost.","index":74,"end_time":190.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":188.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"No worries.","index":75,"end_time":191.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It was all in there.","index":76,"end_time":192.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":191.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Then we''ll go through Zoom in the.","index":77,"end_time":195.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":193.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The newsletter as well.","index":78,"end_time":196.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":195.23,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I know you wanted to talk points, so we''ll.","index":79,"end_time":198.59,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":196.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll save a few minutes for that as well.","index":80,"end_time":200.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":198.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I know you just had a meeting, you said, with Kyle and team, how they feel about the lists that were built.","index":81,"end_time":207.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":201.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Were there changes we need to make?","index":82,"end_time":208.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":207.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"No, he couldn''t access them.","index":83,"end_time":211.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":209.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So that was the thing.","index":84,"end_time":212.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":211.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"He just sent me a note and we went through everything you guys are doing.","index":85,"end_time":215.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":212.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Went through the form like they were so impressed.","index":86,"end_time":217.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":215.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Data box.","index":87,"end_time":218.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":217.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then I said, okay, I have three things to give you.","index":88,"end_time":221.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":218.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And he said he couldn''t access them.","index":89,"end_time":224.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":221.97,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Could you?","index":90,"end_time":225.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":224.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re private.","index":91,"end_time":225.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":225.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Oh, okay.","index":92,"end_time":227.45,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":226.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That would do it.","index":93,"end_time":228.41,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":227.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"He doesn''t think there''s going to be an issue, but he''s just going to eyeball it right away and then, you know, just to be transparent.","index":94,"end_time":236.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":229.53,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I think I move this into public.","index":95,"end_time":241.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":236.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, public.","index":96,"end_time":242.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":241.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Great.","index":97,"end_time":244.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll let him know right now and he''ll take a look.","index":98,"end_time":246.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":244.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Change all three of those.","index":99,"end_time":248.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":246.97,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The one was really small, the segments.","index":100,"end_time":252.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":248.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll take a look at that one as well.","index":101,"end_time":256.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":252.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just want to make sure that we''re utilizing the right fields to identify those because there are a few fields that seem almost duplicative.","index":102,"end_time":263.29,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":256.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So like for segments, for example, 91 records, if we go into edit to understand the logic there, the filters are just industry equals drinking water or wastewater.","index":103,"end_time":276.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":265.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because that was what you shared in your email.","index":104,"end_time":278.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":276.87,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Not equal to test account.","index":105,"end_time":280.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":279.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s a bunch of those in here and then created in the last two years.","index":106,"end_time":283.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":280.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, so is that different than.","index":107,"end_time":287.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":284.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Are there duplications on the segment?","index":108,"end_time":289.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":287.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"One that could be on Aquarius or wims maybe.","index":109,"end_time":293.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":289.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So when I mean duplicate, I''m like, there''s.","index":110,"end_time":295.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":293.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s several fields for production.","index":111,"end_time":297.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":295.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"There''s like inferred and then primary and then there''s also brand.","index":112,"end_time":302.16,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":298.88,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And this has.","index":113,"end_time":306.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":305.52,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Maybe it''s not pulling on this one.","index":114,"end_time":308.56,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":307.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"On one of the other.","index":115,"end_time":309.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":308.56,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Let''s see here.","index":116,"end_time":312.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":311.28,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know that we used brand.","index":117,"end_time":313.84,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":312.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, product brand.","index":118,"end_time":318.24,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":317.2,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this one for example is Aquarius.","index":119,"end_time":320.44,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":318.8,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then there was also inconsistent entries of whims.","index":120,"end_time":323.72,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":320.44,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Rio.","index":121,"end_time":324.08,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":323.72,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Some were Rio whimsical.","index":122,"end_time":325.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":324.16,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So just things like that.","index":123,"end_time":328.43,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":327.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That''s really why we wanted to be.","index":124,"end_time":330.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":328.59,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So double, triple check with the team to make sure that we''re picking all the right context to port over.","index":125,"end_time":335.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":330.15,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":126,"end_time":336.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"He''ll take a look and let us know.","index":127,"end_time":338.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":336.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, it''s kind of a mess of a database, so a bit awesome.","index":128,"end_time":343.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":338.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then real quick, on the HubSpot side, I didn''t add definitions per se because I think they kind of muddy things up.","index":129,"end_time":349.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":343.51,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I want to show what this is though.","index":130,"end_time":351.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":349.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So these are just pulling from specific property sources in HubSpot.","index":131,"end_time":355.47,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":351.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So for the customer community, for ex example, that was one of the fields that was in the spreadsheet that they wanted us to create over here.","index":132,"end_time":363.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":355.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And so there are dropdown options like customer referral, transplant and champion, et cetera.","index":133,"end_time":370.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":364.09,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So when we port over the contacts, they should have that information tied to their account, their contact record, and that''s when you''ll see those update.","index":134,"end_time":377.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":370.25,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So that''s the same for, like, sales outreach and partner and channel sources.","index":135,"end_time":380.89,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":377.77,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Those will populate once the contacts have those dropdown options filled in.","index":136,"end_time":384.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":380.89,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"That makes total sense.","index":137,"end_time":385.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":138,"end_time":386.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":385.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And they agreed.","index":139,"end_time":387.23,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":386.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I showed them this as well, and it''s like.","index":140,"end_time":388.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":387.23,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it makes sense.","index":141,"end_time":389.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":388.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":142,"end_time":390.51,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":389.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, so.","index":143,"end_time":393.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":391.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right, once Kyle takes a look at those, then we''ll be able to move forward with the integration.","index":144,"end_time":397.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":394.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then Guiller, I know you''ve been spearheading a lot of the form work, so I''ll let you chime in here, Barb.","index":145,"end_time":406.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":398.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So the landing page is ready.","index":146,"end_time":407.71,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":406.03,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Both forms are in there.","index":147,"end_time":410.07,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":408.27,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"If you want to refresh the lead input, input landing page, you can see the changes that you requested.","index":148,"end_time":415.52,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":410.07,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I just wanted to let you know that on the hack form, their sales rep field is first name, last name.","index":149,"end_time":425.36,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":416,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"And then on the OTT form, it''s last name, comma, first name.","index":150,"end_time":430.64,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":425.36,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"So I don''t know if you want me to format them, like, the same way to make them consistent or is there a reason that.","index":151,"end_time":440.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":430.64,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Or is there a reason why you guys had it like that before?","index":152,"end_time":444.93,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":441.33,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"I do not know the answer, so I''ll have to ask.","index":153,"end_time":449.17,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":446.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''ll ask Kyle.","index":154,"end_time":450.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":449.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think it''s in, I would say, good enough shape for the kickoff that starts Monday for our gm.","index":155,"end_time":456.129,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":450.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So thank you so much for that.","index":156,"end_time":457.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":456.129,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The only thing I would ask, when I refresh the landing page, it says hawk.","index":157,"end_time":463.65,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":457.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then the OTT form is correct, but it says check your data health.","index":158,"end_time":468.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":463.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Oh, I think our dev made a.","index":159,"end_time":470.56,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":468.4,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Mistake there, but he''s just looking, so.","index":160,"end_time":473.2,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":470.56,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":161,"end_time":474.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":474.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then to remove the input lead form that is fully embedded, just get rid of that.","index":162,"end_time":482.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":474.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then, you know, all the sales team, they''re going to be in that meeting next week.","index":163,"end_time":486.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":483.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Nobody is submitting this form, so guaranteed.","index":164,"end_time":490.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":486.96,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I will.","index":165,"end_time":491.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":490.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I will figure out from.","index":166,"end_time":493.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":492.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Call from Colin.","index":167,"end_time":496.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":493.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Kyle, you know, it has to be first, last, last, first.","index":168,"end_time":500.75,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":496.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I. I can fix that in.","index":169,"end_time":502.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":500.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"In HubSpot, no problem.","index":170,"end_time":504.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":502.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Got it.","index":171,"end_time":506.47,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":505.83,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":172,"end_time":507.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":507.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, we''ll make that change today on the web page then.","index":173,"end_time":510.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":507.67,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":174,"end_time":511.109,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":510.629,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":175,"end_time":513.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":512.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think that was everything there.","index":176,"end_time":514.15,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":513.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We did.","index":177,"end_time":515.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":514.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I know we sent you an email that we fixed the.","index":178,"end_time":516.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":515.11,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The zoom integration.","index":179,"end_time":517.83,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":516.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"The break was in a required question on the zoom side, so we just wanted to make sure.","index":180,"end_time":522.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":517.91,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Was that added, like, somewhat recently?","index":181,"end_time":525.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":522.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I think it was added after.","index":182,"end_time":527.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":526.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It was added afterwards.","index":183,"end_time":530.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":528.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay.","index":184,"end_time":530.61,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.21,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"After we set up the flow.","index":185,"end_time":531.65,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":530.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":186,"end_time":532.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So now I understand what the workflow is.","index":187,"end_time":535.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":532.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then, you know, we always knew yesterday was going to break and it did break very, very well.","index":188,"end_time":542.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":535.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All on my side.","index":189,"end_time":544.21,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":543.01,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But we fixed it.","index":190,"end_time":545.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":544.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we learned a lot from yesterday.","index":191,"end_time":547.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":545.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, that I''ll, I''ll know next time that I can''t go back and add the questions afterwards.","index":192,"end_time":553.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":547.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":193,"end_time":554.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":553.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, Cool.","index":194,"end_time":555.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":554.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, we got them reflecting correctly in the dashboard.","index":195,"end_time":558.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":555.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So very excited there.","index":196,"end_time":560.31,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":559.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":197,"end_time":561.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":560.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":198,"end_time":562.07,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":561.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Then we''ve also built out the newsletter inside of HubSpot.","index":199,"end_time":565.11,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":562.47,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So here''s a preview of that and I can even go back to the actual editor.","index":200,"end_time":570.79,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":565.19,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You know how we build these so it''s all drag and drop.","index":201,"end_time":573.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":570.95,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"You can remove, replace any section, all custom modules so you can edit text, replace images, everything like that.","index":202,"end_time":579.35,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":573.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"It''s perfect.","index":203,"end_time":580.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":580.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We, we now have our coordinator on, on board and she has it.","index":204,"end_time":584.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":580.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She has access to HubSpot and she''s just going to clone it for the product lines, et cetera.","index":205,"end_time":590.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":584.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So it''s, it''s, it''s great.","index":206,"end_time":591.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":590.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She, she knows HubSpot.","index":207,"end_time":593.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":591.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Perfect.","index":208,"end_time":593.75,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":593.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"She knows what to do.","index":209,"end_time":594.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":593.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So it''s all good.","index":210,"end_time":595.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":594.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thanks.","index":211,"end_time":595.549,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":595.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":212,"end_time":596.07,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":595.549,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"All right.","index":213,"end_time":596.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":596.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I have your email pulled up here just to make sure that we got through everything.","index":214,"end_time":600.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":596.79,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Today''s call, lead form, pulling in leads, scoring.","index":215,"end_time":608.87,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":603.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":216,"end_time":611.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":610.55,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, so this is.","index":217,"end_time":611.99,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.03,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"I just want to have a conversation around this.","index":218,"end_time":613.67,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":611.99,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay.","index":219,"end_time":616.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":616.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":220,"end_time":619.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":618.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So sent you a massive scoring updates, I guess.","index":221,"end_time":624.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":619.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"God, is it already Friday?","index":222,"end_time":626.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":625.11,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Last Friday, Monday, Tuesday, I have no idea.","index":223,"end_time":629.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":627.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that''s just something that we, you know, we have about a month to chip away at that.","index":224,"end_time":633.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":629.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, we know that things are going to be manual.","index":225,"end_time":635.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":633.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"A little bit manual.","index":226,"end_time":637.22,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":636.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, between now and then, we, we gave ourselves all of Q1 to get it right.","index":227,"end_time":642.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":637.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And so with the scoring, I guess there''s a couple of things.","index":228,"end_time":646.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":643.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t think anything is scored yet.","index":229,"end_time":649.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":647.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":230,"end_time":650.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":649.86,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So with the webinar yesterday, I can.","index":231,"end_time":653.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":650.9,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You can upload those contacts?","index":232,"end_time":657.46,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":655.3,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, the contacts are in there.","index":233,"end_time":659.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":658.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I just wanted to go in and give them a score.","index":234,"end_time":662.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":660.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And if I gave them a score over 100, would it push to Salesforce as is not currently okay.","index":235,"end_time":672.72,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":663.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I didn''t think so.","index":236,"end_time":673.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":672.72,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that''s okay.","index":237,"end_time":674.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":673.719,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I have the BDRs next and I told them, you know, don''t get too excited here.","index":238,"end_time":679.64,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":675.4,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, we''ve got a couple of weeks here, so they''re going to have to make a couple of calls just manually.","index":239,"end_time":684.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":679.64,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So nothing more to do there right now.","index":240,"end_time":686.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":684.92,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Except for the other question they had was, okay, let''s say we''re in HubSpot.","index":241,"end_time":692.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":687.24,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re already in Salesforce, let''s say at 100 points.","index":242,"end_time":696.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":692.28,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay, they''re already in MQL.","index":243,"end_time":698.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":697,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We never nurtured before.","index":244,"end_time":700.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":698.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And now in HubSpot, they gain another 20, 25, 30 points.","index":245,"end_time":704.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":700.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Those will be reflected in Salesforce.","index":246,"end_time":708.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":705.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They don''t reset to zero.","index":247,"end_time":710.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":708.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":248,"end_time":711,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":710.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Okay, cool.","index":249,"end_time":712.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":711.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yep.","index":250,"end_time":713.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":712.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":251,"end_time":713.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.05,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So this is where we''re starting to build out the scoring logic from everything that you had sent over.","index":252,"end_time":717.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":713.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can see, like, where we''re subtracting points.","index":253,"end_time":719.05,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":717.17,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I told you, we also added in.","index":254,"end_time":721.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":719.93,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Well, I''ll add it in here.","index":255,"end_time":725.01,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":723.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We added to your logic of making sure that any of the internal companies are scored only or only go to Prospect.","index":256,"end_time":731.53,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":725.01,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So even if we fill out forms when we''re testing, we''re just going to go back to Prospect as well.","index":257,"end_time":735.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":732.49,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":258,"end_time":736.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":736.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But, yeah, this is where we''re building it inside of HubSpot''s lead scoring mechanism.","index":259,"end_time":740.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":736.81,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So you can actually build several different scores, score flows in this now, which is cool.","index":260,"end_time":745.03,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":741.13,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"But, yeah, we have the ICP fit up here, and we''re just going to continue to add more logic to it based on everything you sent over.","index":261,"end_time":751.19,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":745.83,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds great.","index":262,"end_time":753.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":752.55,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":263,"end_time":753.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.11,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And.","index":264,"end_time":753.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.43,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And they''re fine.","index":265,"end_time":754.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":753.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re all on a plane tomorrow.","index":266,"end_time":755.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":754.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":267,"end_time":757.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":756.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re not making any calls today, so it''s all good.","index":268,"end_time":759.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":757.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":269,"end_time":761.27,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":760.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then I think that was everything.","index":270,"end_time":762.71,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":761.27,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then you wanted to chat through points.","index":271,"end_time":765.91,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":764.31,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":272,"end_time":767.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":766.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":273,"end_time":767.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":767.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I hope that made sense.","index":274,"end_time":768.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":767.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re in no rush, but we just.","index":275,"end_time":771.59,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":770.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Again, when you and I chatted last week and Tristan, you''re on the phone and we really appreciate, you know, that you guys don''t stop the work.","index":276,"end_time":780.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":771.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I guess there''s two things.","index":277,"end_time":782.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":780.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"One, we don''t like to be in arrears, and we have the budget for it.","index":278,"end_time":788.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":782.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We just want to make sure that it''s like, right now it''s just weighted the same, except for January, for a very funny reason.","index":279,"end_time":795.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":788.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But we just.","index":280,"end_time":796.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":795.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We had to take the money back that I was going to give you.","index":281,"end_time":798.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":796.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, if.","index":282,"end_time":800.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":799.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"If we need to take.","index":283,"end_time":801.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":800.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We haven''t talked about the rest of the quarters, 2, 3, and 4, but I''ve got, I don''t know, 10 or 12 grand a month for all of those.","index":284,"end_time":810.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":801.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But if I need to take something, let''s say from Q3 and back it up to February, March to get all of this stuff, because we''re asking you for a lot of things, and when I see the negative points, it kind of makes like, I don''t like that, so.","index":285,"end_time":823.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":810.82,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And other vendors like HubSpot, we.","index":286,"end_time":827.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":824.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It was paid.","index":287,"end_time":828.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":827.78,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They just didn''t.","index":288,"end_time":829.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":828.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They''re still trying to find the money, but we.","index":289,"end_time":832.14,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":830.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We paid it and they shut us off.","index":290,"end_time":834.54,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":832.22,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Hopefully they find it We.","index":291,"end_time":837.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":834.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, Tristan, I don''t even know if we told you that they just like Barbara sending proof of payment and they just weren''t letting us access the account.","index":292,"end_time":843.9,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":838.22,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah, I saw some of Barb''s.","index":293,"end_time":846.38,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":844.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I think I was copied on one of them or the.","index":294,"end_time":849.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":846.38,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"One of the partners.","index":295,"end_time":849.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, that''s, that''s pretty crazy.","index":296,"end_time":851.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":849.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"It''s funny, a company that big can.","index":297,"end_time":853.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":851.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Track that stuff and I know it''s only what, 20 grand, but it''s like we, we paid it, so.","index":298,"end_time":860.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":853.75,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, but if they can''t find it, they shut us off and you guys don''t do that.","index":299,"end_time":864.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":860.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Which is much appreciated.","index":300,"end_time":866.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":865.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So one, we don''t like to owe money and two, let''s find out how to level up and then what else do we need to front end load the first half of the year for you guys?","index":301,"end_time":877.53,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":866.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, so what?","index":302,"end_time":879.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":878.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And that''s why Colin made it pop in bar, because I know we worked on the, the one addendum and just wanted to see like what''s the best way because I think I asked that last time if you wanted like an addendum to what exists or we did a separate project.","index":303,"end_time":893.29,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":879.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Right.","index":304,"end_time":893.85,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.45,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"For the other one.","index":305,"end_time":894.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":893.85,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So how does that work on, on your side if we do want to increase front load or what''s the vehicle to do that?","index":306,"end_time":901.97,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":894.89,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, so we''ve already approved Q1 at $10,000 a month so that, that 30,000 is approved.","index":307,"end_time":909.97,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":902.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re going to have to bump it up to one, clear the backlog, like clear what we owe you and then add on additional funding to, you know, because we, we didn''t know what we didn''t know.","index":308,"end_time":924.45,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":910.69,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":309,"end_time":924.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":924.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And we knew that and Vivian is fine and she said, oh, even with the additional 6,000 like that, it''s not a lot of money, Viv, like for what we''re asking these people to do.","index":310,"end_time":938.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":925.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And, and she completely agreed and, and just said, okay, we''ll talk to, talk to them and see what it will take.","index":311,"end_time":945.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":938.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I think it, what it''ll take.","index":312,"end_time":947.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":945.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Let''s, let''s clear the backlog, but then set the priorities, which is the scoring, the testing, which maybe more than we thought it was going to be, you know, things I''m asking Gay to do that.","index":313,"end_time":962.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":947.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, I can go into WordPress and fix content, but I can''t or I don''t want to build out certain things, you know, because I''m going to break it.","index":314,"end_time":972.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":962.63,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So there''s certain things we can do and James, he can do certain things, but we want to make sure the ABM is really, really critically important to Us Mining and food and Bev, that we''re.","index":315,"end_time":983.91,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":972.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re building it out February, March, and just getting it, like, starting to test it at the end of Q1 and getting that out the door.","index":316,"end_time":993.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":984.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So those are the.","index":317,"end_time":994.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":993.25,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Those are the priorities.","index":318,"end_time":995.33,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":994.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, and then we have things like.","index":319,"end_time":997.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":995.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Which maybe James can do if we don''t have enough points, like the.","index":320,"end_time":1001.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":998.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Did you know the pillars of productivity, Like a couple of microsite landing pages that we want to put all our videos on now that we have Riverside.","index":321,"end_time":1009.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1001.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So that was a lot of, you know, me vomiting words, but those are the top things.","index":322,"end_time":1017.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1009.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So, again, we want to make sure you get paid, and then let''s prioritize the next stages.","index":323,"end_time":1022,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1017.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, now we can do that.","index":324,"end_time":1023.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1022.64,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And we''re not too far away because our job, too, is to stay within, you know, the boundaries that you have.","index":325,"end_time":1028.92,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1023.8,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I mean, for Q1, like the extra two per month, like you said, six in total.","index":326,"end_time":1035.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1028.92,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Is that something we could do through a simple addendum to what exists now?","index":327,"end_time":1040.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1036.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Or.","index":328,"end_time":1040.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What did Vivian say about that?","index":329,"end_time":1041.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1040.4,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Sorry, you said Q2.","index":330,"end_time":1044.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1043.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Sorry, Q for Q1.","index":331,"end_time":1046.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1044.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"The.","index":332,"end_time":1046.7,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1046.3,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, Q1.","index":333,"end_time":1048.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1047.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":334,"end_time":1049.5,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1048.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Again, it''s two things she wants me to prioritize to say, okay, what is it going to take to clear it?","index":335,"end_time":1054.46,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1049.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"How much money do we need?","index":336,"end_time":1055.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1054.7,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then.","index":337,"end_time":1057.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1056.54,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Because that is an addendum that we should put in, and we''ll.","index":338,"end_time":1064.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1057.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ll.","index":339,"end_time":1065.02,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1064.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Once we decide what that is, we''ll decide how to put it in.","index":340,"end_time":1067.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1065.18,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But then, you know, I''ve got the money for the rest of the year.","index":341,"end_time":1070.66,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1068.06,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I can spend it, you know, all on March 3rd if I want to, you know, but let''s not do that.","index":342,"end_time":1076.42,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1070.66,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we need to take a look at what the priorities are and say, what do you guys need to be able to do that for February and March?","index":343,"end_time":1082.38,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1076.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that''s an addendum onto what you have right now.","index":344,"end_time":1085.06,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1082.38,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Got it.","index":345,"end_time":1085.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1085.06,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And then we''ll take a look at Q2.","index":346,"end_time":1086.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1085.5,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":347,"end_time":1087.58,"speaker_id":3,"start_time":1087.22,"speaker_name":"Guille Santana"},{"text":"All right, Gotcha.","index":348,"end_time":1088.66,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1087.58,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How do you.","index":349,"end_time":1090.14,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1089.46,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because that''s probably separate from, like, your.","index":350,"end_time":1092.18,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1090.14,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Your weekly stuff.","index":351,"end_time":1093.22,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1092.18,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Like, I don''t want to pop in and.","index":352,"end_time":1094.9,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1093.22,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because work needs to keep moving.","index":353,"end_time":1096.54,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1094.9,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And that''s why columns like, why don''t you join?","index":354,"end_time":1098.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1096.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because I feel like some of this, you know, I don''t want it to take away from the conversation we need to have with Barb and the team to make sure stuff is working.","index":355,"end_time":1104.42,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1098.42,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I was like, I''ll pop in, I''ll see, like, where we are, and then I can talk with Barb and Vivian separate.","index":356,"end_time":1111.62,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1104.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Because I know there''s also the hawk piece and I know you''ve talked about other, like, CRM projects and, you know, I can work with you all on that stuff.","index":357,"end_time":1120.5,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1111.78,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Just so you know, Collins brain doesn''t get scrambled because that''s essentially, that should be my role.","index":358,"end_time":1127.3,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1120.5,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So, yeah, I just wanted to pop in and say that.","index":359,"end_time":1129.94,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1127.54,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Oh, sure.","index":360,"end_time":1131.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1130.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The Hawk stuff, we, it''s.","index":361,"end_time":1132.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1131.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re.","index":362,"end_time":1133.04,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1132.68,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re a referral.","index":363,"end_time":1134.12,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1133.04,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we, we referred you guys very highly.","index":364,"end_time":1137.24,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1134.44,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You know, we won''t.","index":365,"end_time":1139.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1138.12,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Other than being a reference, we, we are not a part of that integration.","index":366,"end_time":1144.52,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1139.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, we''re not a part of that.","index":367,"end_time":1145.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1144.52,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s something that they''re deciding soon.","index":368,"end_time":1149.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1146.36,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"They have to decide it in Q1, I would think Q2 latest, but we''ll pop in once in a while just to like, we''re huge fans, right?","index":369,"end_time":1160.57,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1149.76,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like, huge.","index":370,"end_time":1161.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1160.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think what''s going to happen next week at this massive kickoff is Vivian gets the stage and, and I created the slides and she''s like, look it, if you haven''t done this already, this is what you need to do.","index":371,"end_time":1173.289,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1161.65,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And here''s who you need to call.","index":372,"end_time":1174.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1173.289,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So she''s, she''s a big fan.","index":373,"end_time":1176.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1174.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So all the other affiliates are there as well.","index":374,"end_time":1181.29,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1176.37,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I told Colin, two of them are not using you, one isn''t using anybody, and they''re having a hard time.","index":375,"end_time":1187.62,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1181.29,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So I think just, just some proof points, you know, she''s got some great stuff to work with and she, she gave you guys a 10 out of 10 referral.","index":376,"end_time":1196.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1188.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So nothing to do.","index":377,"end_time":1198.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1196.34,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''ll keep you informed if they come back to us.","index":378,"end_time":1202.26,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1198.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But we really want, I think it''s dawn to, to reach out to you, Tristan.","index":379,"end_time":1206.9,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1202.26,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So that''s on Hawk now.","index":380,"end_time":1209.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1207.06,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I did have the call just before this call with you guys met Maria, Kyle, Justin, what I was really surprised about.","index":381,"end_time":1218.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1209.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The other affiliates didn''t even tell them that they were moving to HubSpot.","index":382,"end_time":1221.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1218.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Wow.","index":383,"end_time":1223.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1222.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yep.","index":384,"end_time":1224.35,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1223.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So they''re having a problem.","index":385,"end_time":1225.39,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1224.35,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But I said, look, these guys are sitting here just, yeah, we can do.","index":386,"end_time":1230.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1225.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The same process, lay out all the documentation.","index":387,"end_time":1232.39,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1230.43,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Everyone''s on the same page.","index":388,"end_time":1233.55,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1232.39,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":389,"end_time":1234.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1233.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":390,"end_time":1234.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1234.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And that''s why I wanted to show them the progress and the data box and HubSpot.","index":391,"end_time":1239.61,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1235.33,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m like, this is what they did.","index":392,"end_time":1240.85,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1239.61,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I think it''s three months today, actually since.","index":393,"end_time":1244.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1240.85,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And we''re right where we said we would be on the, on the map, a hundred percent.","index":394,"end_time":1248.17,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1244.37,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And I said, they didn''t drop the ball once.","index":395,"end_time":1250.09,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1248.17,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Except for now.","index":396,"end_time":1250.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1250.09,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We, we just don''t want to drop the ball.","index":397,"end_time":1252.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1250.81,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And, and you guys are carrying any deficit.","index":398,"end_time":1255.89,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1252.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We, we don''t want to do that.","index":399,"end_time":1257.49,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1256.13,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, Kind of weighs on us quite heavily, so.","index":400,"end_time":1260.93,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1257.73,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, not all the other affiliates have Barb on the inside either, so that''s, that''s the other thing we got to keep, keep in mind.","index":401,"end_time":1268.03,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1262.19,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We''ve become a good team, I think.","index":402,"end_time":1270.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1268.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean that''s all shows should be, not taken for granted.","index":403,"end_time":1274.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1270.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I love this team.","index":404,"end_time":1277.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1275.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I, I do.","index":405,"end_time":1278.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1277.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I, I recommend you guys all the time and I just don''t understand why people don''t do this.","index":406,"end_time":1284.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1278.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I don''t understand it.","index":407,"end_time":1285.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1284.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, well, good.","index":408,"end_time":1287.43,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1286.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well what, what can I do, Barb?","index":409,"end_time":1289.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1287.43,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know, you know, shifting priorities and such.","index":410,"end_time":1292.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1289.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I can work with you and Vivian to get the, the Q1 piece for the points backlog and then, you know, do you, do you want to have a separate conversation next week or what?","index":411,"end_time":1303.23,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1292.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"What''s your timeline there?","index":412,"end_time":1304.79,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1303.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I mean they''re all gone.","index":413,"end_time":1307.19,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1305.59,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I''m, I''m free next week.","index":414,"end_time":1308.95,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1307.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So, you know, if it''s, if you have time, we can bang it out probably in 15 minutes or so and say here are the priorities.","index":415,"end_time":1316.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1308.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Work with Colin and ga to say here''s what the back, the backlog looks like and you know, you guys owe us X amount of dollars for the backlog and is this something you can do?","index":416,"end_time":1327.78,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1316.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And I''ve been given the go ahead.","index":417,"end_time":1329.34,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1327.78,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like I, she just said, look, this is your money.","index":418,"end_time":1331.82,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1329.42,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s, it''s been approved.","index":419,"end_time":1333.1,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1331.82,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, it was just that tiny amount in January.","index":420,"end_time":1336.94,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1335.1,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I gave it to Colin and then I had to take it back hours later.","index":421,"end_time":1339.58,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1336.94,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"That''s not the case now.","index":422,"end_time":1341.18,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1339.98,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So.","index":423,"end_time":1341.98,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1341.58,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, don''t worry, I''ll do that.","index":424,"end_time":1344.02,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1342.62,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I''ll, I''ll set out, I''ll put a time on the board.","index":425,"end_time":1346.71,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1344.02,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I mean, well, what works at a high level for you?","index":426,"end_time":1348.59,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1346.71,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I just get it all now then that way.","index":427,"end_time":1350.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1348.59,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, I think just me is fine.","index":428,"end_time":1353.11,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1351.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Like she trusts me so.","index":429,"end_time":1354.63,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1353.19,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And also she''s in that meeting next week.","index":430,"end_time":1356.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1354.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So let me take a look at Monday 19th already.","index":431,"end_time":1360.55,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1356.87,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"My goodness.","index":432,"end_time":1361.43,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1360.71,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We''re actually any day but Monday.","index":433,"end_time":1364.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1361.75,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, any day.","index":434,"end_time":1365.79,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1364.31,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Okay.","index":435,"end_time":1366.31,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1365.79,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"The bank holiday here in the States.","index":436,"end_time":1368.23,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1366.63,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Oh yeah, I saw that.","index":437,"end_time":1370.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1368.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Actually, because of the meetings next week, I am suspiciously free all day.","index":438,"end_time":1378.16,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1371.2,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So let''s see.","index":439,"end_time":1381.6,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1378.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ve got to check in half an hour at 10:30 my time and that''s it, I''ve got nothing.","index":440,"end_time":1386.32,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1381.84,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Everything got canceled, so.","index":441,"end_time":1387.76,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1386.32,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right, we could do, let''s see, 3:00pm Eastern on Tuesday.","index":442,"end_time":1393.84,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1388,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"That would be what time for you new?","index":443,"end_time":1396.8,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1394.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, is that good?","index":444,"end_time":1398.04,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1397.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, just do a meeting calling if you want to come, of course.","index":445,"end_time":1401.96,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1398.6,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But yeah, if you could come and just say, look, this is what it''s going to take to clear it.","index":446,"end_time":1406.68,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1401.96,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And then let''s just talk about the priorities which I just outlined quickly.","index":447,"end_time":1412.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1407.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But that works.","index":448,"end_time":1412.999,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1412.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I''ll see how we call it.","index":449,"end_time":1414.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1412.999,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And yeah, I''ll just have it for, for you.","index":450,"end_time":1416.6,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1414.48,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"And I and Kyle, I might bring you in if there''s a question.","index":451,"end_time":1419.08,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1416.6,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"But I mean, we, we all have a pretty good idea what''s going on, so.","index":452,"end_time":1422.24,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1419.08,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, should be good.","index":453,"end_time":1423.4,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1422.24,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":454,"end_time":1424.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1423.95,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, we couldn''t be happier.","index":455,"end_time":1427.87,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1425.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Well, like I said, you know, we, we the teams working with you, Bar.","index":456,"end_time":1434.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1428.99,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We.","index":457,"end_time":1434.91,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1434.67,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We kind of know how.","index":458,"end_time":1436.35,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1434.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"How we work together.","index":459,"end_time":1438.19,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1437.23,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So I think, you know, it''s something to remember too.","index":460,"end_time":1440.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1438.27,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We, we appreciate working with you.","index":461,"end_time":1442.51,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1440.83,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"You know, things do move fast.","index":462,"end_time":1443.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1442.51,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"We don''t.","index":463,"end_time":1444.67,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1444.03,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I know Colin and Guille will.","index":464,"end_time":1446.83,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1445.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Will agree, but we don''t always have clients that give us things when we need them so that we can move forward.","index":465,"end_time":1451.87,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1446.91,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"So.","index":466,"end_time":1452.15,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1451.87,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"I appreciate that as well.","index":467,"end_time":1453.47,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1452.15,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah, no, I appreciate it.","index":468,"end_time":1456.07,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1454.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"And, and Vivian said one last thing.","index":469,"end_time":1458.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1456.07,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She said, you know, like, she is not a perfectionist.","index":470,"end_time":1460.83,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1458.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Not at all.","index":471,"end_time":1461.71,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1460.91,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She doesn''t get bogged down in things that are not going to matter.","index":472,"end_time":1465.15,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1461.95,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You got a typo.","index":473,"end_time":1466.27,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1465.15,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Deal with it.","index":474,"end_time":1466.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1466.27,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"We, you know, if it''s an hour late, I don''t care if it''s a week.","index":475,"end_time":1470.99,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1467.39,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But like, she''s so great to work with.","index":476,"end_time":1474.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1470.99,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She''s like, just like it''s reality.","index":477,"end_time":1477.47,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1474.83,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She doesn''t get mired in the details.","index":478,"end_time":1479.51,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1477.47,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Right.","index":479,"end_time":1479.67,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1479.51,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So she''s somebody who''s.","index":480,"end_time":1481.73,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1479.67,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"She is based in reality.","index":481,"end_time":1483.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1482.21,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s good.","index":482,"end_time":1486.13,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1485.49,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"All right.","index":483,"end_time":1487.41,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.01,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Awesome.","index":484,"end_time":1487.81,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.41,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Fantastic.","index":485,"end_time":1488.37,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1487.81,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Well, that''s all I had.","index":486,"end_time":1489.17,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1488.37,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Anything else?","index":487,"end_time":1490.05,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1489.17,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Now we went through everything, so we''ll.","index":488,"end_time":1492.37,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1490.61,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll keep chipping away.","index":489,"end_time":1493.57,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1492.53,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Barb on the lead score and everything.","index":490,"end_time":1494.85,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1493.57,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then as soon as you hear from Kyle on the contact lists, the reports that we built, let us know if there''s any changes we need to make.","index":491,"end_time":1501.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1494.85,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''ll make them.","index":492,"end_time":1501.69,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1501.33,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And then we''ll get this integration underway.","index":493,"end_time":1503.33,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1501.69,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Sounds good.","index":494,"end_time":1504.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1503.89,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"I think we''ve got some breathing room.","index":495,"end_time":1505.81,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1504.41,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, I don''t want to do it, honestly.","index":496,"end_time":1507.36,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1506.24,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Right.","index":497,"end_time":1507.6,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1507.36,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Because it''s 3:30 Eastern on a Friday and weekend is haywire possibility all over the place.","index":498,"end_time":1513.48,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1507.6,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"So I just, I want us to be like, all right, guys, we''re turning it on.","index":499,"end_time":1517.32,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1513.48,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We''re all on the same page here.","index":500,"end_time":1518.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1517.32,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"We are.","index":501,"end_time":1519.48,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1519.04,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":502,"end_time":1519.92,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1519.48,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah.","index":503,"end_time":1520.56,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1520.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"No, they''ve got that big meeting.","index":504,"end_time":1521.84,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1520.56,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"So we, we''ve got a week that we can work on it.","index":505,"end_time":1525.08,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1521.919,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"It''s totally cool.","index":506,"end_time":1525.8,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.08,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"But thank you guys so much.","index":507,"end_time":1527.28,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1525.8,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Yeah, thank you so much, Barb.","index":508,"end_time":1529.4,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1527.84,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"And have a awesome weekend.","index":509,"end_time":1530.96,"speaker_id":0,"start_time":1529.4,"speaker_name":"Colin Costigan"},{"text":"Will do.","index":510,"end_time":1532.25,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1531.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"You guys take care.","index":511,"end_time":1533.77,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1532.57,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Thanks, Barb.","index":512,"end_time":1534.45,"speaker_id":1,"start_time":1533.77,"speaker_name":"Tristan Pelligrino"},{"text":"All right, bye.","index":513,"end_time":1535.05,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1534.45,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"Guys.","index":514,"end_time":1535.37,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1535.05,"speaker_name":"bwillans"},{"text":"See ya.","index":515,"end_time":1536.41,"speaker_id":2,"start_time":1535.77,"speaker_name":"bwillans"}],"dateString":"2026-01-16T20:00:00.000Z","host_email":"colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com","meeting_link":"https://us02web.zoom.us/j/85331830874?pwd=C39FwMqUkzptIvUTmrIza1MBNuGN7K.1","participants":["guille.santana@marketersindemand.com,tristan.pelligrino@marketersindemand.com,colin.costigan@marketersindemand.com,bar